[{"Name":"Pouyan Dehno","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtwhkr-cJdKmoYQrxfRnXcXnvOyhOTcEYJpa6EHWO8tS2Gmx8o=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"While the onion soup was overly onion forward and the wings slightly dry, the fish and chips were exceptional crispy, perfectly cooked, and paired with an outstanding tartar sauce. The calamari was also expertly prepared and delicious. The setting was pleasant, though the service was notably slow, with long wait times detracting from the experience. Despite these drawbacks, the standout dishes make it worth a visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMC8DYJAitzaxT2gQXIL-xQa5_Co0TLozQ7Jmra&fid=0x0:0xbe0f7eec186d1db8"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Gigo Navarro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJjpSRfgiVd7FGLteYcEIxlAuYk62vFeD6G-4X0GbzYQ52EWQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been going to this place for a while now, and I always have a great time. And last time was not the exception as my family and I had an absolutely wonderful experience. The service was outstanding, Rueburn our server was attentive, friendly and went above and beyond to ensure everything was perfect. And the food? Incredible! The clam chowder in the bread bowl was hands down the best I’ve ever had—rich, flavorful, and perfectly seasoned. The bread was fresh and crusty, soaking up the chowder beautifully. Hope this menu stays permanently as I know this is just seasonal :). Highly recommended","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMGINX7NNBNzmk4Zn1AzZvo3gU8gg8nv4GfZQIv&fid=0x0:0xbe0f7eec186d1db8"],"When":"2024-12-14"},{"Name":"Robert Polickoski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnWPQJMTZcKDiSfRRRxF-aXnxD9B-5Q59aHdVs2QZKiYRpc_Br=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The fish and chips was wonderful
. The tuna stack was delicious.  The sticky toffee pudding was the best we've had, including my own. But the real treat was Donna and Dominik who really made us feel welcome and set us up for our whole stay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwomrdOOgoPZnwDLlrymozN0SmNxuLUDch3W-Z&fid=0x0:0xbe0f7eec186d1db8"],"When":"2024-6-4"},{"Name":"Corinne Love","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUokO6T7rGH_Fihx4Mzid3i1bIJFmoWLWh3lRFVoMwTcn5nHIOOIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our company held the Christmas lunch here. Fantastic food, exceptional service - Raeburn was a fabulous server!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMuy21RP2l7l7VtUn5q5MN7HAglO4rxbMQn2wl&fid=0x0:0xbe0f7eec186d1db8"],"When":"2024-12-13"},{"Name":"Jerry Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvvBpZoMjueQB2J1i0SQDP1pCBU-HRcyxN-CW8114Ou5CuSCkJYg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for lunch on a weekday at the Delta location. There were six of us and one couple was late due to traffic. Our server Donna was understanding and kept us refilled with our beverages until our friends arrived.
Donna took our orders promptly and was outgoing and friendly. The food arrived promptly and was hot so it did not sit in the kitchen waiting to be picked up.
The menu was varied and anyone should be able to find something they like. Food was delicious and at a good price point

We will return and hope to get Donna as our server again","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sanders Mah","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8oSgPkwwOZHTBvIh2Qeq7JA6BBw3zBFQdgzlc1Wr9ngbPQj0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My first visit. Friendly, hospitable (and happy!) staff. Our primary server, Raeburn, was attentive, but we were gladly served by others as well. We ordered two BBQ Pitmaster Platters (summer promo), serves 4 or more. We added the tender beef brisket to one platter. The setting was clean and contemporary. Comfortable ambiance.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8C5ltVBd51J4rJqbGES0I3flfF1JCTH2aqXFt&fid=0x0:0xbe0f7eec186d1db8"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"Stephanie Maitland","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIO5GUSOFaBEMmzFD5ZJ8-X2bm8bdYdL-N93bamQM60AAVA_g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food, excellent service! Our server Raeburn was awesome! Very knowledgeable of the menu and made a suggestion to try one of the feature cocktails… it was Awesome! The Holiday Brambler will not disappoint!!!! Cheers!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjUm8NOHS9AHggklD0J4LXXnCWMU_ReH_Dv6XW&fid=0x0:0xbe0f7eec186d1db8"],"When":"2024-10-16"},{"Name":"C D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUiCNr9lxlwWhKqCOXf2rmN6L2e7MZVP5-xL_d6Ty6v0A7OWHYo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had the pepperoni pizza which was quite good and a Stella which is always great, only downside, it was a bit overpriced. However, the best part of the experience by far was Natalie, our server. I have never had such a professional, well mannered and lovely server at a restaurant! She had a wonderful smile, was extremely pleasant and attentive. I honestly thought she was a manager based on how she carried herself. Turns out she's only been there for a few days! This restaurant should giver her a raise! I recommend this restaurant fully and the only reason it didn't get full stars on the food was the prices being tad too high.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Colton Pinchin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWXJRXGIEv6GjqAxR8TA3ey5GAVu3RoRUtE7jDGugVD6oqTQMa9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have yet to be able to find another Pho place that lives up to the flavor and consistent quality of Pho Haven. Their broth is top notch, very fast lunch service, and customer service is so friendly every single time I am there. If you haven't tried this spot, you are missing out on a gem.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"V Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIQdp-U-_3QXqqmBN3-J1fZBEPhASUhCcpw0NO1DdU-_Ima_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I love their rare beef pho - the soup, beef, green onion, bean sprouts and lime ... as well as the chilli oil and sauces on the table.

Service wise depends on who's serving you. Individual server is still green and may need time to grow. For example, when I mentioned the metal bumper of a truck parked right outside was reflecting strong sunlight towards me, the server didn't say a word or offer to change my table (several empty tables were available at that time).  Another example was when my neighbour customer left, the server came to clean that table with a table of chemical spray and sprayed in the direction towards my table while I was still enjoying my beef pho.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFyc8WffYqiBcrT6NNrL5sHh4oSoQee3XeWCvG&fid=0x0:0x7db1b08061274d50"],"When":"2024-7-9"},{"Name":"Lila Green","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUcHHgcMxxmBJJAquTzpgF9hnedr1FbuhitY47ItxQYDJOkdjZXSA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I’ve been here a few times for takeout. Came here with my husband to share a quick bowl of soup before running errands. They told us no sharing allowed and I would need to order my own dish. We walked out. To say you can only be here if you both order a dish is insane. I only wanted a few bites since I wasn’t hungry. To say I can’t be here to keep him company and share a few bites is crazy! Place is always empty and now I understand why. They lost our business for life.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kurt Krieger","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLMW2X-xFPFz-dLejI3VdzYIMAzRQMXEqRyVRrXhH6YbFVLwDo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We went for lunch after checking out the nearby thrift store and bakery in Ladner.
The atmosphere is typical and expected of Vietnamese restaurant in a strip mall.
Overall, I would suggest to stick with the soup as it was very good, but the other items we tried were not as good.
We ordered three items: Vietnamese chicken wings, Bahn mi sandwich, and bun bo hue soup.
The wings and Bahn mi were both lackluster, but the soup was good!
The chicken wings were overcooked and a bit dried out.  I suspect the wings are par fried or pre cooked and then finished and sauced when ordered.  The reason I suspect this is the wings came out very quickly and there is no way they could have been fried from raw in that time. Anyway the wings, while warm when we got them were a bit overcooked.
The Bahn mi sandwich had fresh veggies but the meat (grilled pork) was a bit too grilled for its thickness and was a bit like jerky.  There was very little sauce/mayo and no pate (a usual part of a Bahn mi) so it made for an overall dry sandwich.
Finally, the Bun Bo Hue was hot, spicy, full of flavour and had very generous amounts of meat and noodle! We were not disappointed with the soup and would recommend sticking with the soups if you go to Pho Haven!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP0CfO94zptqbk3YU5mX_6u28LB9EDDpc83DTJL&fid=0x0:0x7db1b08061274d50"],"When":"2023-9-17"},{"Name":"Pongo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXT-qQCE1uUwfmES1FGLIpAmkroUlDIcsJZMXejhRkO1uA9CxO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Beef stew was rich and flavourful. Portion size was decent (inflation is tough on everyone). Prices are typically
below $18 for a good meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPsTgEaL-10b2lgUaxFOYmWtuoNvTh5N8ekdsBq&fid=0x0:0x7db1b08061274d50"],"When":"2024-5-23"},{"Name":"YG SES","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW0Kis1cWBDyJfiZPisOMtoVhL9GFh-0-wLhKlJ39yjU1Ij27OgCg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered Spicy Pho - $15.95 + Tax/Tip (One size)
Taste - 8.5/10
Noodle - 9/10
Meat - 7/10
Size - 7/10
Customer service - 7/10

Check out my other Pho restaurant comparison in BC collection from my profile!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOC_ZhgY8HUmWyyO6HMDz9KXg-sHxO5kLRVUum4&fid=0x0:0x7db1b08061274d50"],"When":"2024-2-1"},{"Name":"jdr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWh1ftBExR9TqLWvqnX-kSvVe3V7vLseaq1UAmtDRkM2BOcmUFr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"the best pho place in lower mainland hands down 🙏 their spicy peanut pho is simply perfect. its creamy it’s spicy and savoury, i get it w veggies and chicken and the veggies are always so fresh and sweet, chicken pairs perfectly w spicy peanut so does their brisket. love this place everyone needs to try this place","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Anne D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcpvA-h-AyBmANCHdhhrDOmLepgyc7gk09U5rqfGXZ7NBfzhU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you like spicy peanuty Asian noodles with fresh basil, you MUST try their spicy peanut soup. Makes my mouth water just writing this; it’s just the thing for a chilly winter’s day! Service is astonishingly quick and consistently friendly.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoh3yJsuEOxw9ne6ryFpg7MWJk-fMpTxwvxMIp&fid=0x0:0x7db1b08061274d50"],"When":"2023-12-12"}]

[{"Name":"Chris Falskow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDHYLkOf5n-HER50vuP5HWZOsRYYB1jUj2MxNuUj4Os_snreqq=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a long overdue review. Back in the beginning of October, we wanted Italian food for dinner. We also wanted to go somewhere that we had never been to before. A search brought led me to Illuminaté Restorante. We are extremely glad it did! So, a reservation was made.

Upon entering, we immediately found Illuminaté Restorante to be a comfortable environment with a rustic Italian feel. Obviously, it is a popular place too. We can understand why.

Our meal started off with the Grilled Romaine and the Grilled Calamari to share. Both were outstanding! The Roasted Garlic dressing was wonderful on the perfectly grill romaine. The Calamari was a surprising delight. The hints of orange and pickled fennel took this squid to another level. In a world, awesome!

Our pasta mains were next level Italian cuisine. The Pappardelle al Ragu was by far on of the best pasta dishes I’ve ever had. The Braised Angus Short Ribs and Mushrooms were in a sauce that was out of this world. As for the Spaghetti and Meatballs, one would think “What a basic dish.” This was far beyond basic. Whatever is in their “Family Recipe” is extremely flavourful and delicious. Best meatballs ever.

Of course there was dessert. We shared the Citrus Crème Brule and the Mini Cannolis. The Lemongrass and Citrus was a great edition to this delicious custard. One cannot go to an Italian restaurant without having Cannolis. The Pistachio and Ricotta filling was superb. These mini cannolis rivals those of Mike’s Pastries of Boston.

And then there’s the service. Marie took extremely good care of us. She is very knowledgeable about the menu when we had questions. In chatting with Marie, she told us how much she loves her job and what she does. It shows. It’s always a pleasure to have service like Marie’s when dining out.

So, would I recommend Illuminaté Restorante? Absolute! This is a gem of a restaurant that you don’t have to travel downtown to. We can’t wait to dine there again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXDTu5sqwygeUAS-YGuWvWI20XRqTq1z238hnD&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"KAP Magnuson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuEWJRpclnUBzUp95TdnZT4hJ49cO3TDHBdnPq4gPy3qq4zyA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It was our first time at this restaurant. When we noticed such a high Google score we decided to check it out and we were not disappointed.  The food was amazing - we had the onion soup to start, the spaghetti and meatballs and the halibut.  Best halibut I’ve probably ever eaten and the other dishes were amazing too.  We finished with the ganache and needed to be rolled out to the car.  Our server Rebecca was amazing (hi Rebecca!), super friendly and knowledgeable about the menu.  Thanks for a fabulous experience.  We will be back - highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOaFafIa0C-nnTbbzsG3IIYHOIPTm8d7AMTJaZl&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Donna Ye","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJV1vavqz3zyaXi6Dvbre135doVls1OY1S5ukulsw_Q4Xvwxg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Was going for some cannoli, but surprised by its appetizer and penne sausage! The marinara sauce is greatly balanced and tasty. The mini cannoli’s are absolutely amazing. Love the light creamy texture of its pistachio and ricotta filling! The atmosphere and decor was great too.We sat at the patio with cute turkey lamp.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOti4icsQsVH9RjOMhRLdPAhj9IZPYcrtbXIO4S&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-9-9"},{"Name":"Gia Dhillon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXt-wWmrFf5v4ElmZfQdGGB4prkhbT7axsOdXsHSggrDA2TsNU7YQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A hidden gem! Wow we had the Gnocchi Gorgonzola and veal scaloppini. I have to say 10/10 it was delicious pure perfection. The feature dessert, chocolate espresso mousse with passion fruit glaze amazing! The service was great. The vibes of the restaurant are lovely. I’ll be back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMF4O0NMfWW4rdABxqEuYiYWesN88umxgWPHwkR&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-9-21"},{"Name":"Greg Leo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWm8ssH7mLognVswOCUTCA_m_WUoavv1VB46ZtNXUUngffyGHMZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I stopped in to treat myself to a nice dinner after hitting Windskill.
Had a non alcohol Caesar which was outstanding.
Ended up having the Wagu Ribeye.. It was excellent !
Cooked perfect and so delicious. Accompaniments were tasty too..
For dessert I had the off menu Chocolate Creme Brule which was the perfect finish..
Have not been here for to long I guess but I don't eat out to much anymore as I also love to cook..
I've been disappointed in some of the other local restaurants over time but its refreshing to know I can count on this fine establishment when in need..
Its not cheap, but nothing good is, especially food wise.
I never mind paying for good food and service..
My server was Marie and she was absolutely delightful.. She has a smile that could light up any room..
My compliments to the chef/owner..you regained my faith in quality restaurant food again.
Thank you !
Greg Leo","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTj-WmKSJzNDNALSoyDSd6C_mNM8Ie63Q2e6mP&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-8-16"},{"Name":"John Su","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUc9FQ5QoVibyoNeurZTd7sS4c7gYNxIpenj-uGAqD2nzBUX8GW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Old school traditional Italian.  Great quality that tasted like home cooking, so simple and  well done was the flavours.

This restaurant is better than most of the popular  Italian restaurants in Vancouver easily, Tswassen lucky to have such a local gem.

We had the lobster pasta special and baked Bocconcini wrapped in prosciutto.

Will definitely be back and tell ally Friends about you.

We had a bday there and the staff was attentive to those little things for service such as decorating the plates the birthday cale we brought to the restaurant and remembering the flowers. Felt like family, so nice touch on that.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN6mvfrEPvArZETUhl0WGFI7msHI-YC9BPN79Ew&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-8-29"},{"Name":"Munro Stuff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWj0Wcuk6ox5dfAeJ4fAaMbhX_F-nzzt3p5oc_f0hBd0NpbGSM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Enjoyed our dinner here. Great service and daily specials. Meals were excellent.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYoWUqi3fexYis0jeDoNjjoIaOwCcF3zx1lmGD&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-11-17"},{"Name":"Renu Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIZvuHBKRjp_jsMy08_ZVHVd4w9doVVOIC483AZihlQ8FS_-g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We've heard good things about Illuminate and finally visited, and we weren't disappointed! Great service from start to finish, from the host to our server Sarah. The food was delicious - grilled calamari with pickled fennel, lamb sirloin with risotto and t-bone steak with scalloped potatoes and vegetables. Citrus creme brulee was yummy! Sarah was friendly, knowledgeable and attentive, she went above and beyond. We will be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMl-RRLHreWeGBN1XgFU8PkRwlWCW3caUDuDRE7&fid=0x0:0x15d7115c41800af7"],"When":"2024-2-1"}]

[{"Name":"Kristy Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWEfZ2rjxNiODjhooQ3vu4wU52UFmMssx1nBEw-QrGtiP3D8nPb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Food quality was not very good for the amount that they are charging, I was not impressed. The waffles were undercooked and doughy, while the chicken dish was basically a bunch of stuff thrown together. We also ended up waiting forever for our server even though the restaurant was pretty empty, would not come back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMb3ZcpjsbN2mWPico-HrYxXhLPtLz-8VfNHBBZ&fid=0x0:0xc0f5845d941c9b55"],"When":"2024-1-2"},{"Name":"Swimming Lion","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIoNuKoBPU8hDsJrOBlEDRPQawlWHi3C9rUvrLYtz7paaZM0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"First time at Ricky and I m impressed
Cozy environment comfy sitting
Server very attentive and polite
I m allergy to potato and they substituted it with mushroom on the side at no cost
Big portion and taste is good and they serve with sour dough
Coffee is decent and unlimited refills
Plenty of free parking","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOpY7HxjUMtF3tPC3Gbg0rsGfwKJzAZsEIPkQyJ&fid=0x0:0xc0f5845d941c9b55"],"When":"2023-11-26"},{"Name":"Amanda B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLnKCRQ1GQfbejNMsZtjT5Ot66eqQ8UIw1UiCBfMoP3TbeGwA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We ordered take out delivery for breakfast and the quality was a 2/5. The breakfast sausages look nothing like the photo, and the eggs Benedict fell apart by the time it arrived.  The store forgot to pack any condiments, no butter or jam or pancake syrup. When we called the store to complain they suggested driving back ourselves to pick it up. This is such a small issue but really ruins your meal. It would have been nice if the store refunded a small amount or gave a discount for future purchase since this was such an inconvenience.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Emilia Muirragui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVbrBdWMJwAdDmTKF2rqn3OE2f7BKVf4ff7Eui90G41UPNKe7l=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Walking in this place reminded me of Dennis or something similar. It has a cozy atmosphere, simple, with options that range all the way from breakfast, to pizza, burgers and salads. The girl who was our server was very nice, but she didn't know too much about the menu and so couldn't answer our questions. We ordered a burger to share and a capresse salad. Unfortunately, I was disappointed. The burger was ok, nothing extraordinary, but I felt that it lacked flavour. The capresse salad was NOT a capresse salad (see photo). We were served a salad that consisted of mixed greens, principally lettuce, with a lemon on top and a single slice of tomato and 2 mini mozzarella balls at the very bottom. I was so confused by this that I assumed there must've been a mistake and asked our server to double check with the kitchen, she responded that that was their capresse salad and left. It is criminal to call this a capresse salad, and if they don't know how to make one then don't put it on the menu because it will lead to disappointed customers.
Maybe we'll give their pizzas another chance in the future, but let's just say that the first experience in this place wasn't a great one.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_gzWLwz0vCYM_15hbkQgsr02T5OplSW3-d1Nm&fid=0x0:0xc0f5845d941c9b55"],"When":"2023-9-14"},{"Name":"Raeburn MacDougall","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIoXHoCNiCsL0dOjQhl4dr7HXmy8LsAXROqZKdAcT-ThcE0fCn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was walking by and saw their happy hour sign...good price for an app and a beer instead of fast food joint...I ordered poutine and breaded shrimp...it was awesome and just enough...service was great. Jazz is a new server and really friendly. Varinder the GM chatted with me at the bar. Both were super nice.

Thank you I had a nice visit and will come back again..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTbIOTlHVU5GiIYSke-wUNF4q1y6lG6UOj-FN_&fid=0x0:0xc0f5845d941c9b55"],"When":"2022-5-4"},{"Name":"Michele Winter","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHr_t_YGaPncZI084MFLZ_EKMbKPZtJeyjOVKYIiEaSna7fFs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Always enjoy our weekly dinner out at Ricky’s Ladner.  Friendly staff, quick service and good food.  Great liver and onions!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dangerous The Dreamcatcher","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUx96eh6RRSm4PZMj4rCG9YeqjLZWiAMCM898qxN20MElrdVwKa=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food is solid with generous portions, good value and our son loves the kids menu. The service is warm, friendly, and Denver is great and always on point.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"William Plowman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLjsa7qYBlT3VDIdixUWsTndUeVzLP0IGJuChAHGq1toEV2Mw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Stopped for lunch, we all enjoyed our food.... atmosphere is like being in a Denny's.....Ricky's all have the same menu and the food is always tasty.
I love the liver, veggies and mashed potatoes. Something I rarely have at home.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Bronson VM","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLtc-bPdNjsYMvBcP2Txz2fw_jtG1usp53QQ5fldtfCo_CO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Dinner Buffet pre Thanksgiving. Salad is good but limited choices.
Turkey is good, rest of the limited choices are so so, fish and chicken wings are little dry.
Desserts are of limited choices and taste not good.
But coffee is good.
$73 for 2 persons all included. It could be a fair choice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_3E8Q091uWslCmZzIxqYtqcNCHFhBM5eKT64&fid=0x0:0x5a345b8bacadba47"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Angel Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJIsoMHf_oT1sexNTYsN95NzTMtQ-KbRSmn7F6LYbrMmOFQ-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Went there for the Saturday Roast Dinner buffet. Absolutely horrible roast. Wasted beef. There was no pink inside the meat at all. It was 100% cooked through, dry, and rock hard. Don’t be fooled by the poster outside. Very little food selection and all the proteins were over cooked. The pork was chewy and dry, more jerky like then roast.
The dessert table was always running out. Watermelon was the only fruit and almost always out.
They also have a staffing problem so the refilling of the buffet line was slow. Most tables were waiting to be cleaned when we were seated.
The only reason to even eat here is because of the BOGO coupon. Even then it might not be worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPv73hNCoM0xRfWO9KqYRjmOFtm9bx4D2tj8AH_&fid=0x0:0x5a345b8bacadba47"],"When":"2024-8-4"},{"Name":"LC In","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVAtXfAwjX-9e8sNNB0I0UgMHWur_XDqLCqKzchP_4vVFsEw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The variety is very small. There is no steak or ribs, and there is no bread. There are four kinds of desserts and one kind of fruit - watermelon. The charge is $30 + tip including tip. $37 per person. It will be a bit disappointing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0DhWJ8FIDETscKb967DvPQwks3tajj3KdyUs&fid=0x0:0x5a345b8bacadba47"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Mike T.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVee33ACkN-3b3k5FSLbk_ccPjyHZ-BIlWZB4iPklVrWHsEUomFKg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I came here just to try the dinner buffet but I don't think it'll come back because the food quality isn't great. There were a lot more things i did not like compared to the things i kind of liked.  I can’t recommend the dinner buffet at their full price of $30 per person. The food quality is not good enough to warrant such a price. Out of all the food I tried, the only thing i really liked the cheesecake at the dessert bar. The buffet is a decent choice for dinner if you happen to get your hands on a coupon like the $10 discount or the buy one get one free deal they give out from time to time.

As for the soups, the coconut curry soup was too watery and didn’t taste like anything. I couldn't finish it.

As for the salads, I took some coleslaw. It tasted alright. I only took it so my meal would be more balanced with veggies.

As for desserts, the cheesecake was very good. It wasn’t overly sweet which is good.  I noticed it was taken very quickly from other customers at the buffet but it was replenished quick by staff.
The chocolate cake bar slices were too sweet. It was sickly sweet. It had caramel drizzle on top of double chocolate breading and icing. Didn’t like it.
I was disappointed that some dessert menu items were not at the buffet table. Under feature desserts, on the menu displayed at the front of the register, it says jello was included but there were none. There were no cookies either. I’m not sure why was it listed when it wasn’t included.

As for the mains, the pot roast with gravy didn’t have enough gravy. It was too dry for my liking. I couldn’t eat a lot of it because there was too much fat. The meat portions that I tasted was just OK.
the cheese mashed potatoes were very plain. they were bits of melted cheddar cheese with bits of potato skin inside. Worst part was that there was no gravy included. Who eats mashed potatoes without gravy?
I kinda liked the spring rolls. They were on the salty side but they still tasted alright.
The fish with garlic butter sauce was alright. The garlic butter sauce barely added any flavor though. It really needs to be seasoned for it taste very good.
The ravioli pasta was alright. It could use a little more sauce though. You really need to season it first for it to taste any good.
The rest of the food, such as the chicken wings and the veggie stir fry, didn’t interest me.

Drink selections were plentiful. The soda machine was a coca cola freestyle with many types of pop to choose from. My root beer soda tasted great. They also have coffee, hot chocolate, and juice. The apple juice and hot chocolate drinks were good quality.

The staff were friendly and fast. At opening time, there was a line at the register and the attendant was quick at taking payments to get the line moving. The servers were quick in taking any used plates at the table. When food was getting low at the buffet, the cooks were fast at replacing them. Tables were clean quickly by the staff after each use.

The place was only maybe 30-40% full at most during my visit. It was pretty quiet and you could get your food at the buffet table with barely any wait.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNP9xdfe6lIaHXFbIQqnIVAMTRH5ciiMGWo-ocz&fid=0x0:0x5a345b8bacadba47"],"When":"2024-5-13"},{"Name":"Willy Lien","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjtYKchlA79TYXKTZwGGIIf_Z56Q8GUi7XQwp6JJc1BOg8sP9a=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We came around 7pm for the Saturday Prime Rib special and were seated within 10 minutes. My first impressions was tamed and not of particular excitement; the buffet was small and did not have many options. However, it was to be expected if you read the menu ahead of time.

To be concise, the food quality is what you might expect. Tasty but not spectacular. However, as I walked through the buffet, I saw the prime rib sitting beautifully under the warming light. Upon first bite into the prime rib, I knew we made the right choice to have our dinner here tonight. Delicious.

To conclude, the staff were very polite and helpful, the dining space was clean and well kept, soda pop machine was fantastic, and the food was not as bad as many have reviewed.

If you are considering whether you will come to The Buffet at Cascade Casino for your dinner, I welcome the idea and suggest coming for the Prime Rib night!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNKZW7-fs3AMq1vbiDUodEHOU2BNNDL3vRuTdgH&fid=0x0:0x5a345b8bacadba47"],"When":"2023-8-20"},{"Name":"T Sandrin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHKHwdADXLwFjrDslSpUTuO1ElllzR7CqiY288yvq2u5ulpX1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The brunch buffet here is awful. Selection is very poor. Quality is disgusting.
Was quite good until they changed chefs. It appears as if they are trying to make it so unpopular that they can justify closing the buffet.
Matches has a nice brunch menu. Matches food is good. Price for 2 worked out to be less expensive than the buffet. The food at the buffet is now mostly inedible.
Go to matches or the buffet brunch at Starlight Casino","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPW8DdhEzs-LmmELir_Lfw37moUL1_QrNSQcshK&fid=0x0:0x5a345b8bacadba47"],"When":"2023-9-26"},{"Name":"Felice Rafael","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLLtOx4FpDFSCrfZoGEbh_4bd-CIQ7_QJx5hYkC5JFS9juoFg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I've eaten at the Buffet twice so far.

First time was for Friday Night Mexican  buffet. I would not recommend it at the more expensive $29.99 (similar to the prime rib. other nights are $26.99). For the cost the value is not worth it with stale chips and just different combinations of the same things.

However the breakfast is pretty good and probably a much better value than the brunch buffet. For $13.50 (or 9.95 with encore) you can get decently sized plate of food. Between the two of us we ordered 3 plates only costing $30 vs 21.99 pp. We got two regular breakfasts and then waffles. Freshly made","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkY8MVMpXfwB6Dt8ixiciiOM6itb1vyQCsJL5Y&fid=0x0:0x5a345b8bacadba47"],"When":"2023-12-23"},{"Name":"gg k","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJkHwA4wiIce898eurhvZLkYr1qBkswcDI3byajNa4Yc6ciLg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We went there for Monday buffet dinner. Hot food selection is limited and there was no roast beef but pork loin. Dessert selection was better than expected with well presented cheesecakes/cream cakes. Given that I got a 2 for 1 coupon (from the Encore Rewards email), it was alright. Even without the coupon, if you like unlimited potstckers/noodles/dessert,  $27.99 weekday is still better than eating at a food court.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMn2cvGUPdXvrearqw5oAibNVpO_AkwA2nDsNXI&fid=0x0:0x5a345b8bacadba47"],"When":"2022-11-21"}]

[{"Name":"Steven Chaisson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIiJVoFVDaXnk_rSuDItByweWXDsLEaHLy4CULO-sUxoPyMSg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very happy to see a good Korean restaurant in Ladner. Had the medium sized sweet & spicy fried chicken and filled me right up. Next time I’ll be giving the spicy stir-fried pork a go.
What would be appreciated however are some cuts/vents in the takeout container to let the steam out and not cause the chicken to lose its crispiness.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMr8u43xxoArjrqk0TaUdCatRpKedQRVHI8GjYL&fid=0x0:0x7d3e2a056af9f0fd"],"When":"2024-8-20"},{"Name":"Graeme Burns","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWrgbPK60pqIB_A-EEZqYRC6GJXG5ZJ3IgTY5qEQ7yRpniYaKxSPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great little spot for amazing Korean fried chicken. The Sweet and spicy and volcano are my favorite flavours. Also really nice that they are open later than many of the other places to eat in Ladner.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"dook duck","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKTnm1BBJbpGuwZhZVEGSKICUvKAn43Q-s5w-PPuVSkusKZIw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went to CM Chicken for the first time with my family. the lady who took our order was very sweet. We ordered the rice cake skewers, the burger meal, and one of the variety fried chicken combo. The chicken was soo juicy, warm and super crispy! Everything tasted amazing. This was my first time having korean food. I’ll be coming back a lot now for sure!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzxqN_YEEguHhzIKLqfPezb4Qg20VwNit02azu&fid=0x0:0x7d3e2a056af9f0fd"],"When":"2023-7-18"},{"Name":"Bionic JS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJGm3sKRl22i3V5BABQPkSuxCeoEuF4PS9rUO0aHqDFYGVuEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ordered the classic fried chicken, the curry fried chicken and the lemon garlic fried chicken - all bone in and all the smaller size.  Very tasty and our favourite was the curry fried chicken which I don’t often see. It seemed to be curry powder mixed into the actual breading of the chicken with honey drizzled on top after it’s been fried - insanely addictive.  The classic was great in texture and a little plain in flavouring for me but maybe it should be that way since it’s their original. Pieces were of decent size - you can choose between two sizes and we opted for the smaller size which is about $15.  You only get a handful of pieces but Rib & Chicken charges $25 for their half orders so I guess it makes sense that 5 or 6 pieces is $15.  I hope this place does well so Ladner has some variety in eating options.  Also had ttboekki on skewers which is less spicy compared to the rice cake swimming in its’ sauce.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMSmCSRQRwzsRGH3fG4_TKvrzWyc9_KO3mDR0zE&fid=0x0:0x7d3e2a056af9f0fd"],"When":"2023-8-15"},{"Name":"Cyn & Ken","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIK3fmvuP-4gKXzPKHgvFVsQ7wNy2-77pYaYJrP200j2GtdWQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I've eaten here many times and I love the taste of the chicken. Soy garlic green onion is my recommendation. The seating doesn't seem to be designed for long sittings and not as comfortable, so I usually opt for take-out. They are always quick and courteous.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sophia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIn7v4PQkkb5NktyLAF3n9qZRlVaRXQw2P58nQshbLJE02iKA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I haven't been here since they called it CM chicken I believe. But I didn't realize till after I order that I got boneless . 8 just assumed based on all the background images that's there was an option . To my surprise when I picked up my order it was a small box (like a happy meal) . Kimbap was smaller than your average sushi rolls.
Was not expecting a korean mini meal for 20$ . Might be better to drive out and get it cause this was not it !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOP17H_P4LuNVllamIR3p3MrXBsNF4aRi9B6l7a&fid=0x0:0x7d3e2a056af9f0fd"],"When":"2024-6-14"},{"Name":"Leanella Wadhams","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWoQkmHNg9RoygmizJEcq5xR7f7wWUHYcSNOC1Fnv-BhFmbQF4X=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The chicken tasted like fish. They were incredibly rude. They got my order wrong, got mad at me for getting my order wrong, and charged me extra. Because they messed up my order, they rush cooked my correct order. It was slimy and raw. I'll never return, or recommend this place to nobody.

Update: your reply is 100% false. I ordered combo A, which was chicken, fries and a drink. I let you know that I was in the back seat of a vehicle, so I couldn't see what I was eating because it was night time and dark. I let you know I took a bite of one piece and realized it was sea food, which I don't eat, so i spit it out and threw the remainder of the piece out of the window. I returned to let you know that my order was wrong, and the lady at the till and the gentlemen who was cooking got mad at me for getting my order wrong. I don't eat sea food, so i wouldn't ever order it. That also means I wouldn't eat another piece. I appreciate you correcting my order, but I didn't appreciate being blamed for my order being wrong, and treated so poorly. I also didn't appreciate how fast my food was cooked after that. It was clearly half cooked and slimy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Stephanie Maber","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8DGahQWQUa0E7cP6I5VrKcm-LE2NJiKP7PuCPCO_GcV8y7op3Ng=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went for Dine In today for the first time, and will definitely be back.

We couldn't decide which flavor to get so we decided to get the Variety tray and get a taste of 5 different flavors, ranging from original to spicy.

For those who have a sensitive tongue, the batter does have a but of a kick to it but it does make it very flavourful.

The chicken was very tender and cooked perfectly. The presentation was well done and the staff was friendly.

We enjoyed a nice green tea with our meal which was perfect for the cold wet  day.

We will be back again and will most likely do the tray again as it was a great mixture of flavors and more than enough for the two of us.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZY-ezmZ_4AeDZ7PcaUQCJcCty-7_WxlEA9USR&fid=0x0:0x7d3e2a056af9f0fd"],"When":"2022-11-7"}]

[{"Name":"Bradley Dougherty","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJqgGwHhnGDE0p20s1bs7ju-N01GgzCaA_vBAarBf3FDMzl3w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"We used to order boneless wings from them ALL the time.
This particular order, the chicken is a different quality chicken, and a different breading, and clearly a different oil.

They went from fantastic, crunchy, good sized, and now I have baseball sized wings as well as teeny tiny half the sized of a McDonald’s nugget.
Check the picture, (it is 2 wings, only 2)
I would now not order these wings again.
Sad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfsJykTkmmH8vRK4yEc2dpap1Bi2ns3DPNJ1Kq&fid=0x0:0x2fa5a70bd7a8b973"],"When":"2024-6-9"},{"Name":"Brandi Gonsalves","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVITR2s0-e9HBSr-NeM-uRnTuWRik3g235739WXyPzipx2vBNg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Go elsewhere! The cashier seemed annoyed and couldn't answer basic questions about the menu. We asked if the sauce was on the chicken or on the side... her reply "ummm two sauces that must be the same. "... it was on the side. But you must get the SAME sauces?!?
The drink machine was dirty, and 3/4 drinks we tried tasted horrible.
Chicken strips were overcooked, and fries were under cooked. Garnish veg were limp.
For the price, it was a terrible experience.
Definitely won't be back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Richard J Bergeron","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZExnbUKFKvplHQ_0M_2nTN2L_GFTHbWz1_5aOGcpxIqn_GckSKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had a king burger with everything and fries . Good size patty hand made and very good . Good bun . Fries were ok . Not bad price considering burger prices these days . Will go back . 👍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnK2Rl-EN1GIAkIb3Sj6sesqa9lUtbN4N6hCOn&fid=0x0:0x2fa5a70bd7a8b973"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"BSM","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLYlwGzbjoyODXhD6pFnHAoToKfrBY7rEUloCV_QSP0NrskNb0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I have ordered the veggie burger from here twice now. First time the mushroom melt veggie burger, and today I ordered the regular veggie burger. Both times on DoorDash, and both times it was absolutely terrible. Both times the burger was so salty that it was difficult to eat. I have no idea if the patty just comes salty, or if Fat Burger adds the salt. but if so, please stop adding so much salt to the burger. It tasted terrible and I had eaten in, I would have sent it back and asked for a refund. I’ve had the veggie burger at other locations, but it was never this terrible tasting. Onion rings are overpriced and over cooked, chewy, salty and hard.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Simon Campbell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMT0QbaHdpbejHj2jzI-pv1MaucbWXRj-6YEiM0IFv52TmnD2nAQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Lady is rude and why are they stapling the bag closed when you order take out.  Not feeling the cheese and soggy burger but fries are ok and pop ok.  The lady makes the food taste bad from her attitude, like lady why you have to cut me off and not listen and make me repeat myself. Last time I go there for a 20$ combo and not eat the soggy burger with a side of attitude Sheesh","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andrew Nicholls","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWo_NWS1o0s2ZxtS6yNRH30SDYBwAEU0vrljur60hJgYMMJ1FWE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Little known fact: they have a very good breakfast here. I was skeptical at first but it was great.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Connor Ganuelas","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIMynlYweBjW9PKF3XXd1L7R7k1li8naMsh93me5hHV2c658OU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food is good, place could use some love, upholstery could be fixed, music could be on in the background because all I can hear is the hum of a fridge","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"CC Sampson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIF0Z6eIgNcIZnLtiIjNhBtnKKbGQyc5Wthn7IujapNreIls_s=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was so excited to try Fatburger for the first time. Unfortunately, it was a disappointment. When I walked in and went to the counter, the employee who worked the counter looked so unimpressed when she saw me. Like how dare I disrupt her conversation in the kitchen. Eventually she decided to take my order, however, she had the dirtiest look on her face while doing so and very rudely replied to my request and even gave me my change and drink cup with so little effort I had to catch them while she rudely almost dropped them. Apparently I need to reach my arm over so far towards her end of the counter. While she didn’t even look my way while doing so. My gut said to just leave at this point but I really wanted to try the burgers. I wish I could say it was delicious but it wasn’t at all. Very dry and salty, I was disappointed. I might try a different location though, just to give it another chance. Maybe the next restaurant will have a front of house employee who actually wants to represent the business with a positive attitude. Fingers crossed.

I’ve got to add to this because about 45min to and hour after having a few bites of the burger I’ve been so sick. I’m so glad I didn’t eat very much however this is not ok at all. Was it expired, raw, contaminated, I don’t know. But I hope they do a thorough clean and get all new products. I hope this doesn’t happen to anyone else. What a disgusting and disappointing experience","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Patrick Leclerc","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV67FRA9owWfaFoOVrnLSzSrftJ-VgE4r2F69jHm_pFpiDZYVYYlw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had the honor of eating at this restaurant during my short stay in Ladner. I loved it so much that I went back a second time.  We were well received, the person who served us, probably the owner, was beautiful, kind, funny and attentive. I literally fell in love with the restaurant's charm and atmosphere so much that I hope to keep in touch to open a franchise in Quebec!!! Thank you for the welcome, the exceptional service and the high quality of your food. I can't thank you enough that I'm almost considering moving to the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKGTQMOu1HT3EUUQSLwHPt0_GckPWElci-5HwE&fid=0x0:0xc9b1307cf0c842b3"],"When":"2024-9-14"},{"Name":"Steven Legatto","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV8L2nKw1EPV1ph0AIhYhg-v_kV3CGDAO6pDONWluuSVXOOO3oo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best sushi in Delta! We recently travelled to Japan and have sub par sushi since we came back since our expectations were so high. Maguro Sushi blew away our expectations and was the closest thing we have had since being in Japan. Very unique and cozy atmosphere makes you feel right at home. Fast service and very friendly staff. They even brought ice for our son’s miso soup to make sure it was the right temperature. 10/10 recommend and it will be the only sushi we eat in area from now on!!
**make sure to get the snowy roll it is the best!!**","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOK_7tYiSFhIMyO08AyG7iTTWzLruIcwAr8zSLB&fid=0x0:0xc9b1307cf0c842b3"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Stephanie Chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXik3B7vaPnWcHZjcG3q2jFmLJS8fHQDOOaY6O_oShuu5kT_OfjIQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My dad introduced this place to us. The moment when we walked in, the waitress greeted us right away with a lovely smile. The atmosphere was cozy and welcoming. The portion of the food was great and decently price as well.

Will definitely come back and try their rolls next time!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Karina Gaivoronska","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVF_JRYB5dW1JASFBW0a-ojYQoyG-RJLpt6o6e9xboVN7OvVywnCw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really enjoyed our visit. In this very uneasy time of pandemic it’s our first time eating out since March. The place is very welcoming, and all the precautions they are taking , makes you feel safe. The tables are cleaned with antiseptic after each customer. Very nice and cozy little place and delicious food!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOG0jywj7oKgwOinsMxjTOLWZwSKSe42a3M0S6M&fid=0x0:0xc9b1307cf0c842b3"],"When":"2020-6-20"},{"Name":"Annie Lowrey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWTh5tuQTs3AJq4T-pK_pjS2zyX1bQSZnosJS6WV81_9c_2VrM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First of all, the servers are amazing. They are so attentive and friendly. I got helped choosing some food since i’m a picky eater. If you come to the restaurant, try every single Special Rolls that they have, they all are outstanding and creative. The food was served quick with their cute decorations. I love this place so much, they treat me like family. From sushi chefs alway greet us to the freshness and good food quality, I’m so impressed. I hope everyone could support our great local business like Maguro - Love","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"M LAURELES","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIFfVETzmVsm_Q5GDYnUSEmGJ6xMVXa7B1C4-LlASZJbFdna41=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time visiting Maguro Sushi. We were pleasantly surprised by the beautiful atmosphere, extremely quick food service and friendly staff.

The food was DELICIOUS!! We were surprised by the large portions! The menu offered many Korean/Japanese favourites. We ordered LA Galbi ribs, beef teriyaki, prawn tempura, agadashi tofu, salmon sashimi, tuna maki, spicy salmon roll and a sushi sashimi lunch box (& chicken teriyaki meal to go). EVERYTHING WAS AMAZING!

We will definitely return for more family gatherings. Thank you for making our impromptu mother's day lunch amazing! and surprising the mothers with a gift!
💜💜💜💜💜💜💜","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPh4mM1zeSCMJRY2RCQY4DBDCmDa7Yvx9IGr2a&fid=0x0:0xc9b1307cf0c842b3"],"When":"2023-5-15"},{"Name":"rakesh reddy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXdUXx4RXtHOhM58VZHfAijrgUk_05dS1Iabx46tjfqSVeoAFWK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"An ok experience! Was skeptical about ordering from here looking at the prices, but was satisfied with the quantity. The beef teriyaki box was neatly packed. The taste wasn’t the best compared to other sushi places in Ladner. The rolls had too much rice. Miso soup lacked flavour to it. The spicy salmon roll was the best tasting out of all I’ve tried.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_yPQ7tSN9YVuYf05K4XGTPmMOubEB62lElPmm&fid=0x0:0xc9b1307cf0c842b3"],"When":"2021-12-17"},{"Name":"Cortland “cort” McKenzie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXtdl7p6sK-kUdE22Um4v5bF_BtzKIDutj6z9qUiSiWz7GWgTY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"An intimate but bustling atmosphere and delicious food. Definitely a hotspot in Ladner, so plan accordingly! Peak dinner rush can leave you waiting a while, but it's worth it!","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Olha Diachek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKapYGpIaHHL_bYwAq1JBs_HDSsE2Hp1SZ1O_3KZuVv9Zypvs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was surprised by how spacious this place is. On a Saturday afternoon, it was quite busy and noisy, but that’s exactly what gives it its unique vibe. I was particularly impressed that your order is brought to you by waitstaff. The team is very friendly. There’s a huge selection of desserts, which seemed to sell out quickly. I ordered the waffles platter, but the portion was so generous that I couldn’t finish it all. I ended up taking two waffles home with me.

The interior deserves special mention. The abundance of fairy lights brightens up the mood, even on the gloomiest, rainiest day.

This place is definitely worth a visit. I’ll be coming back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO5-SdGkXj3GbWivZzbkY_2IlQXOp-GBo11NQ83&fid=0x0:0xee497c0e629fc581"],"When":"2024-12-1"},{"Name":"Alysa Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJcgTm0ud5IEy5AFweNCtfAx_NW6IUKANq244urxoakJ5YPzw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This cake shop has a beautiful interior design that makes you feel comfortable as soon as you walk in. The atmosphere is cozy and welcoming, and the overall vibe of the shop is relaxing. The staff are incredibly friendly, always greeting customers with a smile and making you feel at home. Their warm and attentive service really adds to the experience, making it even more enjoyable. The cleanliness of the shop is also worth mentioning, as everything is spotless and well-maintained, which makes the place even more inviting.

Of course, the highlight is the food itself. The cakes and other treats are absolutely delicious, made with fresh ingredients and a lot of care. Whether you're there for a simple snack or a special occasion, everything on the menu is prepared to perfection. It's clear that a lot of attention goes into both the presentation and taste of their offerings. Overall, this cake shop is a fantastic place to relax, enjoy great food, and be treated with excellent service. Highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQlkV62UIFpdE8hs2hwu1ckZA2mGJag-ImqovN&fid=0x0:0xee497c0e629fc581"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Lucy Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVuwCjTEBDQem6hcfmmxSA0I0nNlJPkS88N0KyjwlMUZAjI_Jdm8w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Finally tried this place out and it did not disappoint! We went on a Sunday around 2pm and it was packed, but there were a couple tables available so we didn’t have to wait. Recommend reserving to avoid the wait during peak hours. I got the bulgolgi sandwich with squid ink buns, and it was so yummy. The food also comes with salad as well. The interior of the place is also super aesthetic and there are a lot of seats, and it’s a great place to study! The pastries are also really delicious and we tried the red velvet Oreo cake :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNip0Qa07f4r-TlKrE6qKhz5mGJwAH1aOqBPNgV&fid=0x0:0xee497c0e629fc581"],"When":"2024-12-3"},{"Name":"Minsu Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVeQw_YhBoAI2Nw8r0LMwW0nIB7-k0xmL7wVLR2dXlH04ac3BEx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Coffee was great, they make it with lots of love.
I had a cookie which was very good, many people in seats around me were having heavier meals and they all looked good as well.
The tables are wide, good for studying or working, but after sunset it’s a bit too dark for reading.
Highly recommend a visit!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBXBYe_LYyLjs7bhCJqvipCXDux8aJl7sDFKZC&fid=0x0:0xee497c0e629fc581"],"When":"2024-11-9"},{"Name":"Angeline Rafael","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLNIjGFt3AwM_dbBlrzN87xEqd8MR6IorQ07Mu1L2X8Ih11nQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is always busy and packed but their service is fast. Once you placed your order, one of their staff will help you get a table. We got their chicken platter but not a fan of their soy&garlic chicken. But their desserts and drinks are really good. We liked the tiramisu roll and their matcha latte. 😍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtkwPk3bDK3tLOAy1n3F8pNttR_FbsDjRBJjoc&fid=0x0:0xee497c0e629fc581"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Elaheh Mahraban","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUM7Oi6ZA5Fr6MkruIzoopb-zB6aVtEKxKffUhhlHzjMxNIqDrL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a really nice and relaxing time at this bakery. The mango waffle was delicious, and the high ceilings along with the well-thought-out interior design created such a chill atmosphere. Perfect spot to unwind and enjoy a sweet treat!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmj1dEDAV0h4hXUMfuaOLxsuAcGqL2mpHbS5Nw&fid=0x0:0xee497c0e629fc581"],"When":"2024-9-27"},{"Name":"Cap Holz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPyOU4gu8e0VDkbUMnKwJdDhYwFFnSKwX2msPVNIE1ol0wz4i8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food is really great looking,  but when it comes to taste, it's just but there.  Waffle is very bland, only toppings are tasty.

Coffee is good! Drip coffee is really strong :)

Service is fast but theyre always very full.

Also, 90 dollars breakfast for 2","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO201plN8k843wl1PqhX3BWdkrO8cjU8MAEvZI&fid=0x0:0xee497c0e629fc581"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"AIZY A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW63HuUeCCv9sgK_rgm18cZfVwLP0r1WfmUCdIu1jqRWz_XpAFKzg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful ambience, everything look appetizing. We truly had a great time. The croissant is great for sharing. We ordered cakes for take out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPziO2zFmOZnE5wNv3vMu6Yt--6MCks-ZqU8qnx&fid=0x0:0xee497c0e629fc581"],"When":"2024-11-8"}]

[{"Name":"DLH","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKNxoVJChN19TlxEyh2PqXcySZWcsWGp-pw0aGewSStRgeU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Edit Oct. 27/23:

Return trip on a sunny morning, saw 5-6 planes coming and going.
We ordered 2 items to share for “breakfast” …Denver Omelet $19.95 and The Flying Club $18.95. The club was so huge with generous fillings that we took 1/2 home. Comes with fries or salad.

Happy to see Tina and Chris again, she’s a riot!

Oct. 21/2023:
Have heard good things about this restaurant for quite awhile.

Stopped in for brunch on our way back from Ladner and so glad we did!

Service from Tina and Chris was excellent and quick on a busy Saturday.
We ordered Eggs Benedict ($17.95), Crispy Chicken Burger ($18.50). Corned Beef on Rye ($17.50) and a coffee ($4.50).

Prices are a little high but the value was in the meals, coffee is still free refills.

There is a patio area on the airport taxi side where you can watch small aircraft’s and sometimes helicopters taxi in so seat facing that area. Kids would love it especially on a sunny day!

The restaurant is located inside the airport, we asked someone in the free parking area as first-timers we were unfamiliar.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNdzcEcSAUfhZVMqbTYg7F26xlOxWI3hlCm6YE&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2023-10-24"},{"Name":"Nikolas Patentalakis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkK6kpPZmsqugkZHHHUTudWmaHcTBZOTH5jIJfhMtjzp1O_Vk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice and relaxed place for food and talk. The taste was great, the service was friendly, good selection if you're in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJP40qEUUsJs-DqxJejJLNzNrZX5czXYRW6QWr&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2024-5-15"},{"Name":"Micaela Robinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2QksgdiepfAQ10tl72lYcRqkt6l1FugMIhmMIfzOnP4rJ1IYySg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice average restaurant, food is ok, pub style.  Service was great 👍.
The best part about the restaurant was the patio where you can eat and watch the planes come and go, and it's quiet frequent !

Not the best bang for your buck when it comes to the food.  However....the fries are amazing !
(Beer seemed flat and my son's chicken strips were way over done)
We will go back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYRyIUETYRss89MdHg001CXwD9ChidMTVBI0aP&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2021-7-8"},{"Name":"Karen W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIZZPfpr3QNA42Rvf5GRma8e9wVZe75RxS8Wiz-RehL8Z3PSw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was yummy.  Waitress was super nice.  Clean spacious and great view of the planes

Update:  went again for mother's Day. It was busy but the service was excellent.  Food is yummy and good portions","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNl3V8jEm1Cm3oGJ3AJ3X83MjQle3bV1dUbxZYs&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2024-5-15"},{"Name":"J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWDTN1lhnYS5iEP8rL2hX6NJWGP7creXX64ESId7jrGtvi6HN4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Friendly service, delicious hot food, decent prices. I've been there multiple times and always enjoy the experience!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJUUm8E0pJaPEFyir8aWMwdTk0hmE9aJw9Stux9y1rNRtE68A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This place was really well staffed. Good food, not too pricy and it seems like a popular breakfast spot but I can't comment on the lunch or dinner fare.

Sounds like they have a decent wing Wednesday deal w pints at $5.

If you don't live in S.Delta however I'm not sure you'd find the destination to be worth the trip unless you come here for more than the food.

Its worth checking-out if you are in the area but very much feels like a restaurant tacked onto the end of a quiet terminal at an airport.

It should be noted that the service here was far friendly, fast and attentive compared to what I have received at restaurants in well located venues.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNOwshIYECAEATB6k8tB-4er1CKJu5z6I2RBmPO&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2018-5-1"},{"Name":"Roberta Jansen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXKH87Hd_iQysIPycT0E4kbf-VLo-hJsPyz-0iW67QQxFQNCRFq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Always a good place to come to. Has a bit of a diner feel to it in terms of the food. It's good for the whole family. Reservations on the weekend are probably a good idea especially with current covid in-person dinning limitations.

It is located right inside Boundary Bay airport so you can sit inside or outside and watch planes and helicopters come and go.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbhAw4o9HcG23xdgU-iToq7vrOlE8lBPD2XxH2&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2021-6-20"},{"Name":"Westbank Harvest Pure Fruit Juice","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUW1ZWYhDij58pE8I9cJAuHO53WkHTFafQwt-rH-1xgkBgAHi8n=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is my second attempt at the Skyhawk. I am firmly of the opinion that for the great cost that it takes to travel out to venues for meals overall (time, travel, fuel, meal, taxes, etc.). So here’s my rating.

* Cost and Value
Cost seems slightly higher than necessary. When I was young it was a quarter for a coffee and that wasn’t that long ago! $4.25 plus tax for a single, no-refill coffee is outrageous. French toast (on this visit) was a decent size and tasty. But still feels about $3 overpriced.

* Customer Service
The service here knocks two stars off. Both of my visits the servers were snippy, abrupt and had so little patience that they wouldn’t stand for ten seconds to wait for change or an order to be made. Entirely uncooperative, very surface polite…but eye rolling etc = management needs to immediately give a customer service lesson to most of the staff. The server was totally unwilling to discuss dietary requirements, minor modifications or to check on food allergy concerns. If I was the manager of this place I would have fired the server on the spot. They were all old enough to know better and regardless of the difficulty of the customers they may deal with, in an almost empty place I expected MUCH better decorum.

* Enjoyment and Presentation
The food was good, and presented decently. I would say there is a strong disconnect on what Canadian culture currently is, as vegetarian options were few and both the “veggie” soups when I went had meat bases! How disconnected from the food industry trends is the cook? Other than the rude server and a lack of options or cooperation, this rating is below average. Still passable if you need to have a filling meal while nearby.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNglz6VQRc8uX1Ev_WYLtrshL2SZ-GXuvnIuydR&fid=0x0:0xbe1267c3150ee48b"],"When":"2022-6-16"}]

It's clear that the team takes pride in delivering a top-notch dining experience. The location within the golf course added an extra layer of relaxation and enjoyment, making it an ideal spot to unwind after a round of golf.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMh1yJ2CKTMo3Ec0P2h-OMm5hWax5Qt8R0X9PUj&fid=0x0:0x43e3d449c10dc3d7"],"When":"2023-8-28"},{"Name":"Kieran Purewal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLpsPXqRQa5lSQQbUcJ-pLRyGzdXE2MzyreRO2yhH26kI4Ucg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a fantastic experience at the restaurant located within Delta Golf Course. It's a wonderful locally owned establishment that offers a delightful selection of drinks. The staff was attentive and friendly, creating a welcoming atmosphere. Whether you're a golf enthusiast or simply looking for a cozy place to unwind, this restaurant is definitely worth a visit!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmsr7r7gwWdslZFp0Ml69dLhpjPztzxkyswill&fid=0x0:0x43e3d449c10dc3d7"],"When":"2023-8-15"},{"Name":"Taylor Bedwell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXZWLJ3RcudeRgXIVBblH3jVecf-tsQTZwINuAN24YjEHWWjEz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great atmosphere, customer service is top notch always making sure the customers are looked after. Great spot to have a burger and beer on the patio during a round. The happy hour appetizers are arguably the best in town at a great price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNPN-WqVt0xCf2DxjqzjVC-5zAfrXMmrNbXX46c&fid=0x0:0x43e3d449c10dc3d7"],"When":"2023-9-7"},{"Name":"Steven Kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-x7cQwEtj11Axf55kjZunlEnP5kAzpOHZ1osDVDUecbGF-xg2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had the pleasure of dining at the Delta Golf Course Restaurant and was truly impressed by the overall experience. The atmosphere was incredibly relaxing, creating the perfect setting for a memorable meal. The serene surroundings of the golf course added to the ambiance, making it an ideal spot for a leisurely meal.

The standout feature of my visit was undoubtedly the food. The menu boasted a diverse selection of dishes, each prepared to perfection. The flavors were exquisite, showcasing the culinary expertise of the chefs. From the appetizers to the desserts, every bite was a delightful journey of taste and texture.

Equally remarkable was the service I received during my time at the restaurant. The staff was attentive, friendly, and knowledgeable. They went above and beyond to ensure that every need was met and that the dining experience was nothing short of exceptional. Their genuine warmth and professionalism truly enhanced the overall enjoyment of the meal.

In summary, the Delta Golf Course Restaurant is a hidden gem that excels in creating a relaxing atmosphere, serving mouthwatering food, and providing top-notch service. It's the kind of place where you can unwind, savor delectable dishes, and feel truly taken care of. If you're seeking a culinary haven that combines tranquility and culinary excellence, this restaurant is a must-visit.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jordan C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJjM9Rrddd4BGlei5U4rYSx9cI_mVXDYx5cDGL7il0O1EvDrA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delta Palms Bar & Grill is the go-to spot for awesome pub grub. Their burger is great– super juicy and packed with flavor. It's the perfect place to kick back before or after hitting the golf course, and the staff is super friendly. Plus, their beer and cocktails are on point. So, whether you're teeing off or just craving some top-notch pub food, it’s a great spot.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tristan D'Cunha","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpHaH20-kKiUCiDkLg1FgbTbBAskciaolD0CPhXnwoWIhieFY2uA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Awesome post golf experience! Hannah was great with attending to our order following our round of golf. The burger was excellent and the masala fries were a hit!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Romeo Balicaco","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLfjBOPXAvFUxN4q7ocjmN5iMLbqn3L8WfucIjuEgLomiD6qA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great restaurant not only after a round of golf but any occasion.
The staff are very efficient and very nice to their clients like me and my group of golfers.
I would recommend this restaurant to family and friends.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dale Cadeau","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPzMToz-IZYTaQpOAH5GjhcO03MVs-CamC4QgHe3uhoYsYPJ5bEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Surrey/Delta’s hidden gem.
Well rounded menu with unbelievable prices. All day happy hour and great service to boot! Breakfast burrito is massive, tastes great and healthy with the added beans. Quesadilla is also great. Took leftovers home both times so great value. Another time I did take out dinner: Lobster cakes, pasta and some Indian pakora- all great too. Make the trip down highway 10 to check this place out.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Devon Phelan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXorWAedHbb59VsAXuR_js0R_xERF5lT44CmILYrHhE3b98PaXr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great classic pub dining and drinks. Happy Hour was a great value, and the chips + dip with a pitcher of beer wasn't crazy expensive.

Excuse the half-eaten food and drink. Absolutely delightful and refreshing coming straight out of the kitchen.

The room ended up getting completely filled shortly after Happy Hour, so be sure to go in and grab a seat before the storm arrives.

The staff are very polite, kind, and make you feel welcome even if you are sweaty from biking!

I was able to bike here from Tsawwassen and was pleased to hear that they had a bike rack available AND visible from inside of the pub.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP88uDKJH14Zit44mY8BnWMTKMIcF2ZC_lnuriI&fid=0x0:0xac558cb712c2f718"],"When":"2024-11-6"},{"Name":"Lister Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWbNvO55wOzkDRxCcJ-fMoCcdWyut5hlx-H_zUreRnwso9_V0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoyed shared beef dip sandwich and grilled chicken avocado salad with wife. Attentive server Kaya filled our water without asking. Nice view of river","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP_BF3u_oFkquzClJQ5jUVASFlhl5RLakL4T1OM&fid=0x0:0xac558cb712c2f718"],"When":"2024-8-27"},{"Name":"R B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvwlyjB4u92gNs2XkVMCtEEv1bbhznwa-XyALuorQtBg64Yw0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great place, warmer months you can sit outside with a great view and peaceful view.
Food was very good, I had the pulled pork sandwich. Very good, we tried the pub area but want to come back to the dining room area. Great bar area also !
Plenty of room, good seating areas. Comfy chairs, those little things make a difference 👍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOtHpbeuPf9EcOsFnLVXnEfiKZVkRBkdaYtp59a&fid=0x0:0xac558cb712c2f718"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Kanako Sakurada","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKYybgPjG_d3LYq66Ui47Ocd_2PMrfkKaju5V_L0IyVTR19lQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Fantastic location by the river! We enjoyed the patio seating with nice view! Good service and food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMzMvLeDxFMBh5o4qzVIOwOIC69SYGi1nbdHbhR&fid=0x0:0xac558cb712c2f718"],"When":"2024-7-1"},{"Name":"Leona Zheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmB6XMzxTi6G9GEmyD0MJjB6nkqYOP7GVBTMUakDrRUolumXkH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We thought we booked a dine-out Vancouver lunch here but quickly realised that River House only joined Dine Out for the dinner. But, with this view and a very nice brunch menu there's no regrets!
The server and the host were very friendly and accommodating, and knowledgeable!
The food: We ordered Pork Skillet Benedict and crab shrimp bacon Benedict. Both were tasty, full of flavours. I particularly want to recommend the Pork Skillet Benedict, crispy, rich, soft, gooey, the right textures of everything. Hands down. Will come back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPubVkEn1dnJ6_wrSs3eq02ZayEU18zlM3xFIv0&fid=0x0:0xac558cb712c2f718"],"When":"2024-1-20"},{"Name":"Megan Lennstrom","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUCSf5LnFVz8T-B1pDG3eAlTscSGC5k2LLxD6Fh9oGTIKiBWAaRqQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice patio, good view. Fast service. The spiked strawberry lemonade was refreshing, I didn't find it too sweet, but someone who is more sensitive to sweet drinks probably will think it's very sweet. The Cajun burger was juicy, and I loved the crunch of the pickle and lettuce.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnjXsRK4m5U711hEf68WbIkpLEt917zmq592LI&fid=0x0:0xac558cb712c2f718"],"When":"2023-8-22"},{"Name":"Scott Gue","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJWeS1I23-ZSSrp-hQHJIqnUKAZH-wxHH03ODf79qlSTiO14Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My girlfriend has a gluten allergy so I had to inquire about the menu. Danielle was super accommodating and an excellent example of what customer service should be.

I've eaten there three times and the service and food has always been awesome.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Debbie H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ7pWLCBcdrOZz-aP0miN89E6nSOdYsj46m0wJ4iC_PJpkqgA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First visit to the RiverHouse and I was impressed.  We sat on the pub side outside which was gorgeous and not too hot.  Our server she was excellent. 3 guests had brunch eggs Benny, omelette,and eggs and bacon
Everyone said it was very good. I chose the fish & chips which were one one best I have had and chose the curly fries. We live in Vancouver and it was definitely worth the drive.
Highly recommend.","Images":null,"When":""}]
