user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Cindy Ly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIzge4iM_AthUe2Y8lEMYg2Y2ExA0fMxlIza7QeGpuo6ooWkw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I came for their Happy Hour menu which I thought was the most affordable. I tried almost all their items. Their chicken wings are a showstopper...definitely a must have. I liked their chicken burger but not the side salad. Ambience was comfortable and staff were attentive.  Will definitely go back again if I'm ever in the area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPH91GTRSzk1oTMM9p1IO53xs2WIKdEM3AxtjvG&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"Stephanie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBV5KRG75WlxmWo1wuDhWSQhlZCOao4V2_9kFkOn0OqRNe45TP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We came on a Saturday during happy hour. The restaurant was pretty empty. I love how it's laid out and the number of tables they have.

Our server was knowledgeable and friendly. Happy hour wildlight drinks get $2 off

Inverted dude - was a coffee based drink. I didn't really like it. I wouldn't get it again

Negroni - strong and delicious

Mussels and fries (16) - plentiful and well seasoned. Loved the sauce. The French fries were crispy and addictive. Would recommend

Chicken wings 10 pieces (12) - pretty standard. Crispy on the outside. On the sweeter side.

Overall would come back to try their other items. Prices during happy hour are a steal","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDxXa1iPMIaDUb3dYUzqDVP3M8rux0dOeqzQqE&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-11-29"},{"Name":"Crabby Ermine","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7ghzWacgyIAQrG2Lk7qt0s7V3r_adVAnu6EbLXS1Ck1zLBRgjvA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"10/10 experience. Great service. Great atmosphere. Great food.  Parking is free underground and register with check in. Loved all the dishes we had today.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMaJa3xW-fN0TaVwqmoUrrmVKfqPIH5GB-Ezcgu&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Ray Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3wj8Ne3ngI4eg9ouEU6zPmvERlQuudbckz4ma4Vg6pfYrsWM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful service in a nicely appointed dining room with a fun and trendy atmosphere. The location is particularly convenient for parents who are looking for more upscale dining options while visiting their kids studying at the nearby university.  The seafood chowder, seafood linguine, and duck breast were particularly good. We went on “Wine Wed” where select bottles were 50% off offering good value. Portions were just adequate but not what you would consider large, but that just means you get to leave room to try their yummy desserts (I particularly liked the Stawberry Fraisier, and the Basque Cheesecake with red wine reduction).","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4tLmOOTAsLJvn5WtbD1OyzUmHRy-gI1MFkAD8&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-9-19"},{"Name":"Riley Taylor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ-9EcAoNHnhEH_CEFhkVuk3VNbTy11CmDBZ6MWN5FAekK6Cw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"TOP TIER. Premium EVERYTHING.

Quite literally one of the best dining experiences that we have ever had. From the second we walked in, we were approached by GM Margot who made us feel the warmth and excitement to host us for supper. Victor, our bartender didn’t miss a beat with suggestions and promptness of beverage top ups! Food…. Don’t get me started!!! I’m salivating a day later writing this review thinking about how beautifully curated each dish was designed. Chef Chow is a total artist and a master of his craft. A few musts include the Tuna Tartar, Oyster Motoyaki, Beet and Burrata salad, duck, the scallops OMG, sable fish… DOUBLE OMG and an array of desserts that the pastry team had skillfully curated to reflect British Columbia’s nature and environment.

From the bottom of our hearts- HUGE thanks to the entire team for the special hospitality and delicacies. You all truly outdid yourselves.

Thank you!!
Riley and Anna","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM8Z8XjNkHyhAvJM342-p_KpqBWYsIkY1rwLmYe&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWuLCrwKa9NLpGvoI7KXeamb10EWAoAmRoPxgdu96hyYHG6mtPkhg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came the other day as a solo diner for lunch. Had the smoked sable fish chowder and the harvest green salad. The chowder was the best I've ever had. Very nice atmosphere. My server Mel was also welcoming, attentive, and came across as a genuinely very lovely person.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfJygC171kXxCcNsSJo3-wLP0SQ2Uyt1Mnw7Sc&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-9-26"},{"Name":"Alex Smith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIuPG0P_xvSAHjLq3lehdcGbMVx_kB14iyd4zXzj-7VOUEMAw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First and foremost, a huge thank you to our server Naomi for making our evening at Wildlight truly special. She was an absolute joy, incredibly sweet, and very attentive and informative throughout our meal.

We split the pescatarian board and mushroom gnocchi, had the strawberry frasier for dessert, and finished with the complimentary shortbread.

Everything was absolutely wonderful.

The pescatarian board showcased a fantastic mix of seafood and pickled vegetables and was a true pleasure to explore.

The mushroom gnocchi was the epitome of comfort food with some great textures.

The strawberry frasier was incredibly refreshing and had the best ripe strawberry flavor in several forms.

The shortbread was a lovely surprise and sweet treat to end the meal before we left!

My partner and I each had two cocktails (Awesome Blossom and Pacific Vesper in the picture) and were thoroughly tempted to try more! Each cocktail was delicious, well balanced, and complimentary to the food.

Wildlight was a lovely experience from start to finish. Both my partner and I would strongly recommend an evening here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipORrSSDOzpPYS1WvgEYc9nnBneuVG28DZxfzgy3&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Mary Proulx","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEhEtou551etajvQPOzB4dygQrXePqTCHvPLlyMk3uMrquxnRA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love gnocchi - the mixed mushroom stroganoff gnocchi here is the most fresh and flavourful ever. Half price bottle of wine Wednesday a wonderful surprise. Dessert is beautiful and enough to share. A fabulous lunch with friends; food, location and space and great service - thanks to Brandon","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTKSTnTBH98HWxtMSpyf0Dq2J26QKkVW-G2ebL&fid=0x0:0x2990e8c80679c2f1"],"When":"2024-10-23"}]

This location needs some help and I hope they get it because Triple O burgers are exceptional!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Don Barthel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2v4b2MiOKOBPPZGdy2Fh2fxQ-AEZnGAAgycxkJMWig5pi-BDy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Somehow the food isn't as precisely prepared at the Marine and Main location which I go to a lot. Will not support this business anymore.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pardeep kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIhPMDjRpJN2YOv4UMCNO-f_3ILIH596c2Kim5JmSFODv0kwg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I would give 0 stars if I could. Will never visit this restaurant again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPVhg_HaJx9BRECvI0ktvFMn38FJwfgl0XGgF1S\u0026fid=0x0:0xb139d078fb7f473"],"When":"2022-1-23"},{"Name":"Orit BC","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKPRXuuE3pPEEo6Du7mgOM4Iz0LnG-vEXqfrhT9HbrMuvsYug=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Nasty place. This is not how white spot burgers should taste and we were quite disappointed 🙁","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Chris Helgren","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMAlSlQnmQbIkMlcbNUhzxzkQe_i_pBwvNmCrJ1Wm7NdB_9U0R=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I hope this doesn't turn out to be a eulogy in the end, but I walked in for brunch and was told that this was the final day in this location at Jericho Beach. Apparently the landlord didn't want to extend the lease. I hope they find a new space in Vancouver. That said, the service was fantastic and deserving of a good tip. I loved the eggs Benedict with hashbrowns and pork belly, I forget what they called it but the food was memorable. And it's in a perfect location near the marina at Jericho so a great place for a walk to burn off the calories","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO44BS-QhzVwExBGdBt60sVJ7rQI5WrhEEj06X1&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-12-15"},{"Name":"Laurel Windover","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWnEhLdsjZ16qCFrqZXUCMvuEzXtbI46OBVg6YSX7imdPsfZHYlwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I love the casual patio and the menu is priced right. I asked for the salmon burger as a salad instead of a burger and it was delicious!
The service was a bit slow the day I was there though. It didn’t appear to be too busy but we waited 40 minutes for our food and nobody came to do a quality check after we were served. In fact we didn’t see the server again until quite awhile after we were finished eating. That said, it’s a cute, casual spot in a great location and I would definitely go back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOg4RgddnYKK-Gjr0FDLECUohwzN85d-LhzmZqd&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-7-8"},{"Name":"Tina Fischer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_PBoE3UhL3iJ077dZx_qOA7mXIKHJuwtODDKop9ishOSiUuMS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Classic breakfast was awesome! Wonderful servers! Very fast and yummy! Even gave me a green onion when I asked for it!! Thanks for making my travel experience a good one. 😃👏✈️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoOAvh2tRDsfrjuEP1ANoDHO4Ncr2jLxqAl9Ga&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Y. Cherski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK-7SLlKKRW0Rqcp9wRXFlvt6gbh0rtI7PMIroLgxETtGiPwQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stumbling upon this establishment was like uncovering Vancouver's best-kept secret. Critics of its operations might miss the bigger picture: this place is not just a restaurant but a cornerstone of the DICED Culinary School, which champions affordable and sponsored culinary training programs. With very reasonable prices, especially for its locale, the ever-changing menu keeps the dining experience fresh and exciting. The patio and the events hosted there add another layer of charm. More than just a meal, dining here supports a noble cause, making it all the more worthwhile to explore and endorse.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNY6bN7P2eB7zct_4A0kOI6o7FgWoR-H3d3oeSf&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-2-25"},{"Name":"Ben Jefferson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXBEOMkGOoEkxaChUtJDYIbi9DXvbFJ44f1Vjs7ERmTv1vlDzvJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Super friendly staff. We had the salmon burger and vegan burger. Both were delicious - the salmon in particular. A low key local vibe. When we visited there were young kids, students, and old timers like us all enjoying the food. Good amount of seating outdoors and inside.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Daniel Silver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJawI80c4qwvuA-pWmht_nhIypwFKNS8vUDHnZIepoqs0gJvft7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I really wanted to like this place but unfortunately we didn't. Affordable prices but the food just let us down. I'm fine with basic but found the DICED burger lacking and the nachos were ruined by the corn chips. The fries, which were pretty good, and the biscuit were the only items I liked.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM2IuCEopmqKeJmI6RJiYC1Jx0nJYLnmSgbhl5z&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2024-3-16"},{"Name":"Tina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAKiC5J1ql1LsLTTfBwgvAj6sVGUusHXghumDKVG9ZTQ8QjcD_1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We went for brunch on a rainy Saturday. Service was great and food came out fast. A lot of the customers were guests from the hostel/inn located above the restaurant.

We got classic breakfast and breakfast sandwich with side of bacon , plus two coffees. Total came to around $40.

The interior decor isn’t the best. On a sunny day I bet the outside seating is nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOahCT_-keSla43Jnn3SmbBXF2WST1Ki2TU9TY8&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2023-6-14"},{"Name":"Adam Myhre","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLlloGTdin2BEFn5bg_e4KC9zJLJE3T-tVTT7t76H3j3mWQRw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"DICED Discovery Cafe, tucked away near Jericho Beach, surpasses its seaside competitors remarkably. This establishment prides itself on prompt service and observant staff, showcasing an unwavering dedication to guest contentment. In fact, there were staff hovering near the entrance the entire time looking for tables to clear or anyone needing anything.  As a dog lover, the inclusive pet-friendly policy significantly enhanced our dining experience, contributing to the overall laid-back vibe of the place.

The outdoor seating area presented a slight hiccup, as only half the tables benefit from the shade, either natural or via umbrellas. However, after a short wait, we managed to nab a shaded spot for our meal.

A point worth noting is the slightly elusive location of the restrooms, hidden within the upstairs hostel. This required a minor search, but the overall experience outweighed this minor inconvenience.

The charm of DICED lies within its simple but well done menu. The irresistible Cuddle burger has managed to capture the hearts of many, including mine. The unbeatable combination of delectable flavor and affordable pricing make it a standout choice!

A crucial aspect not to be forgotten is the cafe's commendable work within the community. Functioning as a social enterprise, DICED invests in shaping the future of young adults in the culinary field. Every delicious meal served is a testament to their commitment towards empowerment and opportunity.

To top it off, we found free street parking just one block away, saving us the usual parking hassle. DICED Discovery Cafe is a great combination of delicious, wallet-friendly food, comfortable ambience, and admirable community engagement.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSPfi0AwhrYBYvn8ORU8C3XN4mxY8m-1H40jSJ&fid=0x0:0x8724e7521984580"],"When":"2023-7-26"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Marienus de Jong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI9nIIIwXEkvpUKs0busLKrDpWfPoGmtgZ_KCpM-1DHdLIrMA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Just wanted a evening snack. Ordered six peach pies, checked to make sure we got what we ordered, they were just thrown into bag and some boxes were open and we left a little disappointed. Got home, took them out and they were all burnt on the bottom and around the edges. Some had a burnt taste too. We live in the area and seldom go to this McDonald's due to issues like this.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMfmQIEARsLSBS4I_EqAfgjP_yeKELhz-LUkPbL&fid=0x0:0xe8f22c6700651276"],"When":"2024-10-31"},{"Name":"Lina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUkH5c_dtaDXSimtB1Q_ah5H1c4hIAdN4G2XOA54HXJSaaHI_0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Fries were half empty but the fries that they bothered to throw in were cold, soggy, uncooked, limp and gross, had green and brown bits

Orange juice underfilled.

Nuggets cooked in burnt oil.

Requested “no toy”. Included toy.

First and last time ordering at this location.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8hUtcjcLUdQh9JIo_TQ7qEE1RMrnVgNrKLt_j&fid=0x0:0xe8f22c6700651276"],"When":"2024-8-21"},{"Name":"Brad Haywood","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLU9qqgnoMHo6FG4jONaVsw4p4SZeCAyU-NVcNYRuKL2dj2qw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I rarely do this, but here we are...
This location has transitioned its workforce like ALL the rest in the past few months.
Service, Food Quality, and Cleanliness has ALL suffered accordingly.
The food takes forever, it's rarely accurate, and frequently cold.
When you're paying top dollar for McDonalds these days, it's unacceptable.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Peter Storie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKG2pc64V87Hgmf4FdXtbGaCMCmgGVEDEQO6Xc9r6nPxnK8Ng=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Staff got multiple items wrong in order. Front staff was awesome, in rectifying ones that were apparent while still in restaurant. Extra, extra pickle requests, probably means that the customer wants more than 3 pickles on their burgers.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tara Palmer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVzwWcAthijC8hOLe5QOCWaMWs4Z124P8FjpCTzT1Z3tm7wqh4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Unfortunately this place has gone far down hill and across the field. The food used to be hot and fresh, the fries full and the service almost always wonderful. Over the past several months it’s gotten worse and worse and shockingly even worse. The fries are never full and are usually soggy and  lukewarm. Custom orders are often not customized properly. Recently I ordered a Big Mac with triple pickles and for some bizarre reason there were absolutely no pickles on the burger. Another example was a few weeks ago I ordered a sundae and it only had half the amount of ice cream and fudge as previous. Curbside orders take CRAZY long to be delivered. My most recent visit I watched 14 cars go through the drive thru and be served before my large fries were brought out, lukewarm and soggy and definitely not full. This used to be such a great place to grab a quick bite or take the kids for the occasional treat.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQzCBT4gySw8Km6ybAPz_EaecnDptQMOck2S5E&fid=0x0:0xe8f22c6700651276"],"When":"2023-12-10"},{"Name":"ramandeep","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK4I_pX-9eVspxGu-yPDAppa-obRCrnJJsb3RV_A38NOyHWUrRh=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"So, this morning, I used to come here all the time for my favorite meal, but not anymore. I ordered a spicy egg wrap and hot chocolate from the self-serve section. I was waiting my turn when the "now serving" sign disappeared, and my food wasn't ready. The lady with glasses didn't respond when I asked her, so I tried another worker, but they had no idea either. Finally, she found my order and asked if it was mine, but I was missing my hot chocolate. I asked for a warm drink similar to hot chocolate, but she offered something with ice. I insisted on a regular coffee because it was raining. She seemed lost, holding my coffee and asking other customers. When she offered me the coffee, I asked for a refund instead, but she said the manager wouldn't allow it. It was chaotic, and I even saw the manager yelling at the employees in the back. I'm so disappointed; I don't think I'll be going back there anytime soon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shawn Wright","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJGXlIRrPmj0OfCRywfNnfadhYjLL2Pl5ywTiDMkYMCLYbPjg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Was never great under the previous owner but it was at least passable as a McDonald’s.  Under new ownership the quality of service has gone downhill, and all the new employees who replaced long time, former employees need a lesson on reading comprehension and general customer service.  They can’t get a order right to save their lives.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tim Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV78mpuQFXhuGoAVJ2r0U1bxumPNQ7fzV53EvXnyeS9xFdb00XE9w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I visit this McDonalds frequently - both drive thru and in-restaurant - and the service level and long waits are nearing catastrophe. I am a patient person but today was the straw that broke my camel's back. I waited nearly 30 min inside the restaurant for 2 cups of decaf coffee. I anticipate decaf will take longer as they don't always have it ready. Today, it was ready but a tad too quick and sure enough the coffee they gave me was practically cold. I requested a fresh brew to get a proper cup of HOT coffee. Was told it would take 4-5 minutes. Reasonable. Except it ended up taking nearly 20 min. And it's near impossible to flag a worker down. They all seem so busy. Please McDonalds...do a review of your procedures and training!!!","Images":null,"When":""}]

Easy to get to. Big room. Nothing fancy but nice and clean.  You get a text when you can check in with your keyless code to access hotel and room.   Pool and spa could have been cleaner and maybe some chairs around it if you did want to use it.  Nice balcony in main street but no real outdoor chairs. Some random chairs.  No pictures of room but pics from balcony","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_J5l08TAD3aH075HnMrtQEt87FrPh0_sfzaUv&fid=0x0:0x688266101374d1ec"],"When":"2024-8-16"},{"Name":"John Robinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKjHtJgGvBEBWtYL4Ta9uVIbM4KXzzoMRP03a8B_OXwjduHRw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"On line shows they open at 9 am. We showed up at 9:45. The girl that "greeted" us said they were not open yet. We asked what time they open and she had to search in her phone to find out. ?. Zero personality and NO interest in having customers at all. Will never go back there again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tricia Dresel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLZv5OmgD3xAl1YEmq1hEQxrY9OWkopDap_kcDfS2V7dm5Zaw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Not a fan. Not to mention the bed was like sleeping on a granite slab.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Antonio Gutierrez (Dad)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJsssb4ZAR-e_QeG6ZzyTigxYj3IE1APp7viJbmz3cjMJB8NA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Service was good workers were awesome. Rice Bowl was amazing!  Loved it. I usually add Salt n Pepper to all my food and in this case I didn't have to. Rich in flavor and perfect portion of everything. I would definitely return again and definitely suggest to add this place to your bucket list.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJwVDYq1ObYpsQgUpFJ6rTQlKI5NlgTsq1br2DNgtTRUBpB5bk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I stayed at the lodge for a wedding so I didn't have time to check out the restaurant or bar.

[Also, the phone number listed here and on the website is for the Restaurant/Bar. If you need to contact the Lodge, you can do it on Airbnb.]

The room was very spacious and clean. I really enjoyed staying here. The host was very sweet and accommodating. I asked if it was okay to check in around 12 pm and she made it possible. In the future, I will definitely pick this place again.

Unrelated to the Lodge:
I do wish that I had more time to explore the stores nearby. I have read that there's a lot of history here and also there's some bars in the area :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Christopher Geul","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKTKH882MDWVFMJDXxV9qs1du_4Dt224g-MR-WxNiwuHWwv4w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We made reservations for this place about a month ago for a wedding of one of my best friends. Upon arrival, we did not find anywhere to check in. We eventually made contact with the receptionist at the bar downstairs who gave us the number for the manager. The first two calls went unanswered. Eventually after 20 minutes waiting, we made contact with the manager who apparently sent a confirmation text to a wrong number so we never received instructions on how to enter the property and get to our room. She was also very rude to my fiancé after she pronounced her name incorrectly. After waiting another 20 minutes for the code to get in the room we decided to go to another hotel that we could actually get access to. Would not recommend staying here if you have an event to go to seeing as this circus almost resulted in us being late to the wedding. There are much better hotels in Elk Grove for about the same price. Hopefully, the manager will do the right thing and refund us the money that we are owed for a room we did not use.

Follow up with the manager, they will not be dropping the charge. They failed to confirm that we received instruction to get in and did not send us the entry code in a timely manner. Do not recommend this place to your friends.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"George Aragon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUzYyIepi4jObnII0GfThosn_QRT-uPounNqnovsoOew1Zmg7k=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice old timey place to have a drink. Bartender was really nice and made a great drink. The price was right on the money 💰 I will be stopping by here every time I'm paying through.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPEMskNgTevKvQm158mcL12xSo01S7xp4YzpAD5&fid=0x0:0x688266101374d1ec"],"When":"2024-6-20"},{"Name":"Lucas Stefani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKa1SoyrmDZjlKKyyaKjReLbfv9TMgZzpXpdqCJgE-BZSeYi4boQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A very nice experience for lunch or dinner. Menu reflects local flavors and the roots of the town culture. Steaks, scampi, chix & waffles, to deep fried battered pickles. Also Asian selections. Large portions for the price. Friendly Service. Tipped the kitchen $10 for an excellent meal from a talented kitchen. Clean and welcoming atmosphere.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Ang B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX7POUiAXSpRIAJEYEy09CE0QoEm6u4CDMMysXW9ORO_FCB9ooY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Definitely go for the ambience. The menu is small and doesn’t have a lot of choices so if you’re looking for a large variety, this isn’t the place. Dining on the boat however is a nice experience and would be terrific for a date night. We sat outside at the water and the view is so worth the trip. It’s a bit on the pricey side though so be prepared. We had a bottle of wine and some appetizers, just a nice evening sitting and talking. Service was great and very attentive. You walk through old town Sacramento to get to the boat and it’s nice because it’s situated right by the parking garage.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNL0QL8Na5YkID-1TUpWTBxzbCVFCW_qbZz-Vjf&fid=0x0:0xc379835b2103c263"],"When":"2024-12-10"},{"Name":"Amanda Parks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrQtKULqWGuVmLPmiOzubyUi31xprUyro1Nuz7JgbtSLQ2skod=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We went for the murder mystery dinner and had a great time. Albeit, we did not guess the killer and I was a little bummed that the boat didn't actually move. I would absolutely recommend this if you've never had this kind of experience.

My mushroom chicken was delicious but I think the best part of my meal was the salad with Champagne vinegarette.🤤

Go with people who will get up and interact with the show.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3HD3GEUoWdV0jU89tRahngErWklOr0bQZEAYi&fid=0x0:0xc379835b2103c263"],"When":"2024-7-16"},{"Name":"Alison M C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWMD_iUWr1OtN05YTSQJoHQ6qM2CJiqqLdc8LyeQAHqkUinpT4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful setting. Who doesn't love drinks on a boat? $11 for a French 75 with a fresh lemon twist is pretty fantastic. $9 beer. Friendly bartender.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2LcqC57jVJbWtEBNS0tC_RVkxw5J49JIAYqM&fid=0x0:0xc379835b2103c263"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Breighton Zorn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKTDPXcUECl246lf2zNF_0LV49Y5QNRYh1nI6Y37fK1Y67oUA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had some friends in from out of town. I knew Old Town would be a good time, and the Pilothouse was high on my list of spots, but I didn't know they'd have outdoor seating! Such a beautiful place to sit and have a drink or two. Amazing!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfQJvAD3o4R6w58BdOu3eUS5PR9MMue2h0AuFi&fid=0x0:0xc379835b2103c263"],"When":"2024-9-3"},{"Name":"Laurie Poe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLixdsnTtgMge2G8OJpVearJ6rTa0P0yzZJ4jMDLM7n0oz5cQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Thank you to the whole staff. Julian it was awesome meeting you. Wonderful food. Best calamari i ever had.
Had a very, very great time.Thank you so much","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPLI287U1b2BWUsTWL4WUVEMKN9OjBl8xesj4WJ&fid=0x0:0xc379835b2103c263"],"When":"2024-10-18"},{"Name":"AnM Racing","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXC3txcJY1_bZ7H2dC2K1N1k4nQgTpZklcFVkJO1NSypSnebPxx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Stopped in for a couple of cocktails. Very friendly staff, and attentive. Sat outside on the second deck. Wonderful view.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPSoWcJrvvNfkuA8EBavIuGFlubeaDgB06LHCHO&fid=0x0:0xc379835b2103c263"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"Donald Peck","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJYHQJ-vHejF4EpoXGbMhUKGd_8j71YGT6Hd86JoX1xOzpLDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We didn't have reservations,  but they said they would work us in.  However, working us in didn't appear to be an issue since there were few people and a lot of empty tables.  Ambiance was powerful and very impressive.  Service was very slow, and the food was good,  but not overly impressive.  I don't believe that they have a dress code,  but everyone that I saw was dressed better than average street clothes. I have to say that despite my lack of enthusiasm in this review,  I would be willing to chalk this visit as an off night and give it another chance, should I be in the area.  I have to believe that there is potential for a night of fine dining as a whole.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMK2cs2pNv2wM_Lj6uzvAElOs_higjDoMofceKa&fid=0x0:0xc379835b2103c263"],"When":"2024-2-17"},{"Name":"Chad Chapman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_xxADBcr-xOPERyi-TAv4cn6_3-AtlRrG-Qg1H2i5dG4F8dnX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were staying at the Delta King hotel so we decided to check out the restaurant before we went out for the night. They had live music which made for an amazing time and a great atmosphere. It is a little on the smaller side, but it didn't feel crowded at all on a Saturday night. The bartender and staff were incredibly friendly and fast. It was such a cozy and delightful bar, we will absolutely be coming back here in the future!","Images":null,"When":""}]

The girls  their name was Gurleen and Pawan, they should be trained properly, if not, they should be fired.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bonny MacRae","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ9qdEduKopzghI6DBSgseV8_8ZJj7OK9Cbj56pyPnNV6brJQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"5 staff behind the counter. All working the drive through, ignoring 6 people in line at till
I was 3rd in line and left standing while all staff dealt with drive through.
I ended up not ordering a sandwich, as I had been in line so long, the kitchen staff was struggling.
Also 3 or 4 people waiting that had already paid, waiting on food.
Terrible service
Milk spilled all over counters, overflowing garbage behind the counter.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hannah Bay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXaNJ7MRCSPWWwBfs1ctzMsrjwOAjH99l-vaRVEmrWiuwdk9tc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I visit this tim hortons VERY often and my order has never been wrong once and sometimes i recieve my order almost immediately. I have to eat out often so tims is my first choice. Staff are always very kind and working VERY hard. I really appreciate you guys for the coffee and warm breakfast when i really need it. Never have had a problem here, keep up the good work you guys are amazing. I wish for people to be kinder to food service workers, it’s a privilege to be able to eat out.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mike Bul","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKFHr8OS9yCArTD_AyaGQBPpxrxS5krFsS6frrxgHiWPxUXqw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The staff can be good in some ways, but they just don't interact with people the way us local Canadians expect. Don't greet you when you enter and no one at the til is common. I overheard one gentleman ask if anyone was home, they still don't greet him. Took three times or so. Another customer asked for a box of a dozen and mixed and the staff repeats she wants all the same flavour. No, she wants mixed. And the staff was not picking up things she was saying. It's on Tim Hortons itself and gov't to allow a 100% staff from one particular foreign country. Of course there will be differences in customer service, language, culture, conversation flow. Food is also bad quality at all Tim Hortons.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Robin Cook","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ7tDVcDYwBh0vpbpT747MPMqIuFrNCQ93cSa1-xiDoYaV9x3e-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is a gem. My server, Avery, was absolutely amazing. She was so attentive  and friendly. I had the fish and chips, the fish was of good quality and cooked perfectly.
They had  a live band while I was there, and they were really good. There was a nice view of the river with a really enjoyable atmosphere.  I definitely will be back when in town again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKZzHO864uw-6-E7-7H_cBvLxcoeiz57cmMp0t&fid=0x0:0x734ea059a7f98481"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"Rod Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL6ucRDnAxgRP6lAWFk8FSnklh0WugApZw2efIUiVO-ggHc5A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful outside dining area, right on the river.  Food was outstanding. I had the Jambalaya and it was really good.  Wish it had more shrimp in it for $28 but the flavors were spot on.  Service was excellent as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKySZ2On4WNDjFlLGayWEXghKZWsanLoP2DbwN&fid=0x0:0x734ea059a7f98481"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"Ruben Pasion","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIVV54grAcfiF285CEStd4punH5cnGogRuQPNPzsn3w9k4ONw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice place to enjoy dinner. There are lots of items to choose from on the menu.  I have cod you got the cod sandwich with fries, very tasty.  A bit messy, but that's good.  Washed it down with a cold  IPA.  One of my coworkers had the jambalaya they say it's very good. The other had a burger with fries which he said is also very good. We're definitely going back next time we are in town.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMvR9ZaCt9HSbo8x-59Vh6CcqciCzIdqEIAf6ba&fid=0x0:0x734ea059a7f98481"],"When":"2024-5-21"},{"Name":"Michael Stokes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQ00IhxntMbUXNz7ZJhbEw0tZyoH9zrvOzBmFC18fXxCZbvSA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My partner and I got in our boat and went to Crawdads on the Sacramento River. Nice view and nice place to eat. The cocktails are strong and the food delicious. My clams and chorizo was just a bit salty, which is why I didn’t give a full five stars. The food was hot, delicious and it wasn’t our first time there. You don’t have to own a boat to eat at this very cozy restaurant. The live music is perfect for this place.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"patti brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUBZKDiR0RJvWwypofAn6sWKKEmFEzk60scWgEPj5Dj9pJXj3KzhQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Was a great place to eat with people visiting from out of town. Has heaters, fans and shades. Right on water with parking for boat. All great seats and bar options. Depending on time of year could be hot but can't best the atmosphere. Food is very good. Had fish sandwhich, burger and chicken sandwhich and 2 sodas was 59 dollars. Highly recommended when weather and time of day is right.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN-c_s3NWi8v3-RxwN7RP1--CrlF_NDcsyEZwuQ&fid=0x0:0x734ea059a7f98481"],"When":"2024-6-4"},{"Name":"Amy Craggs","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX82YXY_eByO7iP7XwgrZfN-np6HKKZ8D1h0WeAqzafMlioYEX2CQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went there on a whim with friends from Tennessee... I loved the river view. There were a lot of big parties  kinda loud but it was cool.Sat in the bar area. I ordered the chicken sandwich. It was delicious, I wanted some crawdads but they only served them in a big bucket with corn and other stuff. I only wanted a dozen regular crawfish. But they didn't do that so I was bummed... We'll be back, super good food...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-TmQ5t5taXb9T9x2c0Tua_kXTWRCz57oExJ7C&fid=0x0:0x734ea059a7f98481"],"When":"2024-5-20"},{"Name":"Jarrard Payne","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWjWqAAZYyqRb69T4YzY_XSB_lOS_8NIE5sgOZPpI0NFL6-GRbW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoyed the outdoor seating with an amazing view of the river. The atmosphere was great with a good music selection. Service was amazing as well. You can not go wrong with any drink you choose.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNsMqUP7S8zTU2t0k49-fw6I8jkuF3JpbTzM0rS&fid=0x0:0x734ea059a7f98481"],"When":"2024-8-3"},{"Name":"Janae Gautier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4FUnsSLTxs-7vddLmiPUFapoJh1KcQM2HwE-hXS-RSQFsxUbX7A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a great place to come and relax during the day, catch up with friends and enjoy some really delicious food. Sitting and eating by the river feels so peaceful and luxurious.

I highly recommend the nachos as an appetizer, the pickled onions on top really made them extra delicious! Also the Cubano sandwich and BLTA were extremely satisfying for my friend and me, the homemade potato chips are a nice change up from fries and add great texture to the sandwiches.

We went on a Sunday around 230-3pm and there was plenty of seating available outside but by 4-5 it started to get crowded.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPX3K9-Ey-qRrNYLt9d0fHdL_r3w9c0SbDy0Ej8&fid=0x0:0x734ea059a7f98481"],"When":"2024-4-8"}]

Excellent customer service..I couldn't decide between chicken or beef for the rice platter so he offered to do did half and half for me! That was awesome..thank you. The platter was very filling! I loved the chicken, the beef was good too if you like the donair style beef. Excellent long grain rice, flavorful sauces and the chicken was nicely well done which I love. My son got the beef donair and LOVED it..said hed have to come for lunch during school as its so close and the prices are very good.
We both had a piece of baklava as well..it was very good, not too sweet like some but just sweet enough! We will definitely be coming back as regular customers, esp since the whole family loved it..as we brought them some home. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Nikki Judge","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUvNYhWH6PpAkYC7rLa4L9_Ax66oFT2x767cqhNjW8Mv1yARUU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We always have a fantastic experience when we dine at Brewmasters. Also we most always show up right before the doors open and drop 20-25 riders on them the moment the doors open. Never once has this been an issue. Our food comes out in a timely manner and it’s always absolutely delicious. Not gonna lie probably one of the best sandwiches I’ve ever had.
The restaurant is always clean and homey and typical for what you would think of a “mountain” restaurant but even nicer oh and the outdoor seating is so nice to eat under the pine trees. When in the area do yourself a favor and stop here for a drink and a delicious bite to eat..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNaxBwzlNZRe0ie63lkFJWSkbTg_BZM79c8ReXX&fid=0x0:0xc83151e25f1e62e4"],"When":"2024-8-10"},{"Name":"Lou ggle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKR3DExnhPOq2WW-wLDr4IVqqQrPR1PIX0XU0JJ3lowm9kPHg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pretzel bites with stuffed cheese is an experience to try. Homemade ranch was delicious. Love the hot sauce they provided. Very difficult to find great tasting habanero 🌶 sauce, found it! Great selection of beers 🍻 on tap!
Worth the trip to visit. Great feel to the place. Love how small the town is n all.
Would sure come back to this small town n make time to visit. Great decor and service was on point.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNpLiBNkNr-nRs79GUghq7G7goghbluyYYIeTf2&fid=0x0:0xc83151e25f1e62e4"],"When":"2023-10-24"},{"Name":"Mitchell Ryan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUau1nHrzLSypGxmefp2hU4VAD8mszyEZigv8P40uMvGXFJTFdR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Passing through on a Sunday.  Appears to be the only place open.  Beer was good.  The Bavarian Pretzel good, the soup good.  The blue cheese roast beef sandwich, the mini corn dogs and the buffalo wings with the buffalo sauce not good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steve Bidondo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLJr9YOw_LF3Cdc78W0bliSVQ4kq0ClE_P2CmRmZFLROGcnOA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Complete hidden gem.  The pretzel with the beer cheese and the smoked wings are staples.  The daily specials were fantastic.  Beer selection is top notch.  Staff was very helpful and willing to please.  Great spot up in the hills after a day of riding in Foresthill OHV.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"William Diggs","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUd8nxVqSzuxi824wtU4dzr2bwn_i_U62x28jsWyCnBytPuyv4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A comfortable hometown feel in this local eatery.
A large selection of domestic and imported beer a dozen or so on tap.
Rotating selection of delicious sandwiches, pretzels, chicken wings,salads.
All the employees are friendly and helpful. Dog friendly outdoor covered seating area.
They also host car shows, bake sales, and some musical events. Go already!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMOo_aIA24VIf96N1YnJzZcdwSfYJXYv4OPWci8&fid=0x0:0xc83151e25f1e62e4"],"When":"2023-5-27"},{"Name":"K B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLXjOn071FPexIFZvBxtOfteYOoqKEJL8l9s7aniNyw6mL4SrQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Definitely worth the stop, delicious food, great service & Atmosphere!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM-M7Ium9teQ-ll-N1-aTr7bxrcooOZ82zC6-Tp&fid=0x0:0xc83151e25f1e62e4"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Mark Simpson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJxT2X4PIBi0YxY-65gMUoDK_CIBD-ikPI1evF5zn24bPdqXw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The service from the staff was excellent.  The pretzel (huge) and beer cheese was delicious. Also had the Philly sandwich (their version of a cheesesteak) was good; however, I would leave off their special sauce. A good sauce, just didn't need to be on this particular sandwich in my personal taste. I took some of the beer cheese from the pretzel and it made the sandwich crazy good..they have a lot of brews on tap and the bartender seemed very knowledgeable about them. Dont be affraid to ask questions or tell them what you normally drink and they'll find a good one for your taste buds...I'll be back!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQdXYzCkQ3om5t7xLrLuD0OQYi1IyBuqT6yyII&fid=0x0:0xc83151e25f1e62e4"],"When":"2020-9-7"},{"Name":"Tyler Lopez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLYgJMnIQ9-2lcqQM2ER-k2ZzZUzmbjeI9YLvwHBlxC8lFfNw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food here is top knotch! Service is amazing with a very friendly and inviting staff. They are always making something new on the board, never anything short of delicious here! What are you waiting for? Go eat there.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIIcwABPK8NZI68gj69dKyL2bROczc6Msn9vDS&fid=0x0:0xc83151e25f1e62e4"],"When":"2022-8-19"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Tom McDougall","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0J48kC1hZM1V1aRsvHOZVDophlDmEISwqhKMFe94oVeHk06c2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We recently had dinner at Taverna Gorgona in Ladner with my wife and son, and it was a truly memorable experience. From the moment we walked in, the warm and inviting ambiance set the tone for the evening. The decor, with its Mediterranean charm, created an atmosphere that felt authentic and cozy.

The service was impeccable. Our server was attentive without being overbearing, knowledgeable about the menu, and eager to ensure our dining experience was perfect. We appreciated their recommendations, which proved to be spot-on.

The food was the star of the evening. We started with the calamari, which was perfectly crispy and paired with a delightful tzatziki sauce. For mains, my wife had the lamb souvlaki, my son opted for the chicken souvlaki, and I went for the seafood platter. Each dish was cooked to perfection, bursting with fresh flavors and generous portions. The accompanying Greek salad and rice pilaf were delicious and well-balanced.

We couldn’t resist finishing the meal with baklava, and it was easily one of the best we’ve ever had—crispy, sweet, and not overly heavy.

What stood out most was the genuine hospitality and the restaurant’s ability to make you feel at home while enjoying a fine dining experience. Taverna Gorgona is truly a gem in Ladner, and we’ll definitely be back soon. Highly recommended for anyone craving authentic Greek cuisine in a welcoming setting!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXYUpZJAvbuqXGAsrCEKP0lKgYnHzse8JtSiBc&fid=0x0:0x903b595afd3f3553"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"V M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJucmQqtBf1kft8datC4d6xRc1U6LHj0kk67hUDpJTqeEoU6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing restaurant feels like you’re on a Greek island with Greek music setting the mood. Aesthetically the restaurant is super clean with crisp white walls. The bar draws you in with its blue led lights. We were with a group of friends, sat outside on the very nice patio.  We love the awnings blocking out the sun, made it very comfortable, looks very chic. The service was excellent, they went above and beyond. We started with drinks, refreshing Sangria’s, Mythos Greek beer, perfect on a hot day. My friend wanted a specific drink that wasn’t in stock,  they went to the store and bought it for her. That was mind blowing, unbelievable service. Franco the owner pays attention to every detail, great guy, he’s so kind, genuine, and generous.
Excellent mouth watering food,  Appetizers:  we had the succulent garlic prawns, Saganaki they light on fire at your table, and homemade dolmades, best I’ve ever had, all yummy. Main dish I had juicy fall off the bone Greek ribs. My husband had roasted lamb, both tender and delicious, we were licking the plates, wanting more. Finished off with a beautiful hot  bougatsa dessert. We were very pleased, happy and super satisfied. Good ambiance, excellent service, delicious food, and the best company. Thank you Franco you have a very fine establishment, it made for a very memorable experience.
Don’t walk, RUN to Taverna Gorgona!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUVqwRSxryggr_IcP-7a7j1l5SXjLlnPWVQV4G&fid=0x0:0x903b595afd3f3553"],"When":"2024-7-14"},{"Name":"DLH","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKNxoVJChN19TlxEyh2PqXcySZWcsWGp-pw0aGewSStRgeU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our first time on this very busy Saturday night but not for the friends who invited us along to celebrate a birthday.

Even at 5:15pm & onward I would say recommendations are a must on weekends. We were surprised how many staff they had, our server Anna offered the appropriate amount of attention.

There are several sections inside in addition to a fairly large outside patio area.

Our entrees were delicious and prepared perfectly:
Greek Ribs $31.95
Spanakopita $23.95
Beef Tenderloin Souvlaki $30.95
Calamari $26.95
Double Martini and glass Rosé $13 each

Street parking except on Ladner Market day (Sunday)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMpEepy2Q643ScEfBI4GwIt2YrnbwckseE-cj8&fid=0x0:0x903b595afd3f3553"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Pamela Pamula","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUzY3sSX6mSOQ-zdR20X5Mihb_6kUPL0HILeQBqRT1d8-WlJ0xs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our favourite Greek restaurant! Great atmosphere! So helpful for birthdays! The food is always delicious! Cocktails and wine very nice!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQKjL6PqHb-jT96uXkT5p3dNWmcKODRe4hJrXe&fid=0x0:0x903b595afd3f3553"],"When":"2024-7-12"},{"Name":"Patrick Soon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVv4YGSxRhxSqazv4BlRw4vWA7zBtdDCe5jBYYunXYPza58m48qcw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Good food. Awesome service. We had a reservation for Father's Day. They seated us immediately after we arrived. Kelly, our server, was extremely hospitable and quick with making sure our needs were met. Really appreciated her attentiveness. Calmari, lamb chops, and garlic shrimp were the standouts for us. Will definitely try other dishes (like Mousaka!) next time. Highly recommend this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2rdwB_ibCXTGI30eJCsAN22T6R7QYjpbG3rC6&fid=0x0:0x903b595afd3f3553"],"When":"2021-6-21"},{"Name":"Amir Alimohammadifar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVrMzehyYKL2N5MygYIJn0Qq0Mw_ICezrph5kn4Lgaj3XeaBUPp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's a great restaurant with a great environment, clean, cozy, seuper delicious food and amazing staff.
The staff are super friendly and very nice and polite and the service is fast.
The food was amazing specially the lamb chops and the roast lamb. The ingredients are fresh and OMG the pan fried cheese is the best! So delicious that I was about to order the second one. And don't miss the Ekmek! It's one of the best desserts I've ever had.
Overall I'm pretty satisfied with this restaurant and I'll be back here soon 🤩😃","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDRkEjogVbEzDKO57gxLeIOeTneh3JF-1ZHYSW&fid=0x0:0x903b595afd3f3553"],"When":"2022-8-7"},{"Name":"Antonio Gil","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWLbAmEKmBvE2fZn3e5W8ukiDk-BINWaeC1MJJBzLlD36PDjvA2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We were visiting Lander on a Sunday,  and we found this beautiful place for dinner.

Everything was excellent, super friendly and attentive staff .

Beautiful decorations.

Tasty food ( just keep on mind to clean the prawns properly)

We will definitely come back","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMIx3DAQzVpQ4w1FysMmhAeFv7dnLsUWwdxFU12&fid=0x0:0x903b595afd3f3553"],"When":"2023-6-5"},{"Name":"Emilia Muirragui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVbrBdWMJwAdDmTKF2rqn3OE2f7BKVf4ff7Eui90G41UPNKe7l=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Visited this restaurant for the first time a few weeks ago and we were gladly surprised. The staff was very friendly and happy to provide suggestions. The pita bread and dips were fantastic, I would go again and again only for that. The main plates are very large, enough for at least 2-3 people to share. Don't be scared by the price tag because like I said, you're getting a lot of tasty food for what you're paying.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNsoX_-1lfvFWDbiJnKry_r_p3OmANohNuvEwSL&fid=0x0:0x903b595afd3f3553"],"When":"2023-9-14"}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Stepheney Shannon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI7Wef4dHDN5CmEEuHgPJp1YZGVBShXBVj-NJE3VKjtL9L-nw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The decor was interesting and unique. The staff was friendly but seemed shorthanded. I ordered the salmon with mashed potatoes and vegetables. My salmon was flaky and perfectly cooked. The lemon drop I ordered was strong and tasted like it was made with plain well vodka instead of a citrus-flavored one. My fiance ordered a Beast Burger with fries and a draft beer. The beer was a little on the warmer. The burger was well-seasoned and perfectly cooked and the fries were hot and crispy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCnEq_aDQqlJei0Z-s6SzkC4uK6em6Om63_Lq8\u0026fid=0x0:0x1b34a507f9d36ec6"],"When":"2024-4-22"},{"Name":"Ton T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXTeqqp-cNmK4ds8H5fo_mb6tavSKL1rUyeJSuy53z-auApiBAS_w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It’s not often you get to walk in a unique and interesting place. Fosters Bighorn is the culmination of Bill Fosters bootlegging and big game hunting adventures in Africa and Northern America in the early years of the last century. Unfortunately my schedule did not allow me to a sit down dining experience but I did get to chat with the wonderful staff who had some less-common knowledge of Bill. I’m told that the burgers and fish n chips are very popular here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyvV8MFVcbg7R2xBhuE2ZBrarI6apmj969Dl6V\u0026fid=0x0:0x1b34a507f9d36ec6"],"When":"2024-5-20"},{"Name":"Larry McCart","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLTXpWWctOKcYQ-eU7Axq-6xsjY6ENKr9dRAZ_NeUM20xKnig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have eaten here, but did not eat on this visit. Just had a drink at the bar. Quick and friendly service and a very good dirty vodka martini.  The stuffed animals are amazing and are a statement to a different era. The food on previous visits was really good and nicely priced","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPX4zh3opu0rldOe8JSUT_zVefcHSQwxBNchOIn\u0026fid=0x0:0x1b34a507f9d36ec6"],"When":"2024-6-18"},{"Name":"Sonny Sparks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUipVF414NMhgz7pK1akHxZRoO47bmCuakH7SUYAMBOpF-G7xdr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Foster's Big Horn in Rio Vista, CA is the real deal! The atmosphere here is laid-back and welcoming, with that classic blue-collar vibe that makes you feel right at home. The menu is packed with hearty, no-nonsense dishes that hit the spot every time. Plus, the amazing trophies adorning the walls add a cool touch to the place. Located right in the heart of Rio Vista, it's easy to find and perfect for grabbing a bite with friends or family. And the service? A+. The staff here are friendly, attentive, and always make you feel like part of the family. If you're looking for good eats and good times, Foster's Big Horn is where it's at!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZYPxyxxq-48WIl5ZKS7hDbF50J79Hm7slvgoa\u0026fid=0x0:0x1b34a507f9d36ec6"],"When":"2024-3-7"},{"Name":"Mark Wittekind Sr","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWWNWhCbsXfjxwzCgsRghm_rxm0ockrl6m9viq_DoAzWeGsOo_X0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow! What a cool place and amazing story of thier history. Not very big but packed full of incredible animal mounts. Not only that, the service was quick, accurate and the food amazing. I love the fact they serve more than the same old stuff. Though I'm not a hunter I can appreciate the beauty of all the animals. Prices were very reasonable too. We will definitely go back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"merton preston","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTmVhroe4sq8MieuZDTVBPQIPKmwRrw3ktHL4TpNAlM79_ZFPI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Definitely a fan favorite! Unique atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPiNG0rfP84k0WECyrcX5IZyvSJzhgt8CcEk-a9\u0026fid=0x0:0x1b34a507f9d36ec6"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"scott wittke","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUGuqUSl8T1VUM4rAE4vfv-DqzOMvjKMAFFAj-OGPsOaBzQbL6d=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Didn't have eats but Bar was great. Definitely worth a visit and I'll be back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNDVk0k0b1gHaXjp78mrwyYGBe331mfF5P7q9YJ&fid=0x0:0x36673326a66854e7"],"When":"2024-6-12"},{"Name":"JS WP","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3ieifuGNwdoddzk3aAh9OzspcRwyjucsDzIUXZIbfufct3fWg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We have been frequenting Doon for a number of years. Their buffet has been my family favorite and has always satisfied us. Thank you and keep up the great work!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Yvonne C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiht0ZFoJ6DOgr6bSZnnGy8rPYprmRtmKG0EWCYdy5NpcfLUEr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Kids craving Indian and this place was 1.5km from the rink we were at.

Surprisingly really good good with good portions.  Ordered:

Garlic naan x2
Lamb biryani - huge portion
Lamb vindaloo
Butter chicken - not a ton of meat
Yellow daal - very tasty

Server checked on us constantly!

Used a groupon
White rice","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwGDx9UcZGoW1nmKMpu1BIGBNfPCnjb631cTUi&fid=0x0:0x36673326a66854e7"],"When":"2023-10-23"},{"Name":"Mohit Kumar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLHazSQow9QCvNSX4-9qFXiQDocgoLACI1ZpsSK5ugC9IPhVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I got chicken biryani today from them , absolutely disappointed in taste , too much food colouring, got exactly 4 pieces of chicken in it . My partner and I frequent this restaurant as our go-to Indian food in Ladner!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPiQvMMlvjp6H9tlGfGbA_R6Nnlnjba2SjBjX8&fid=0x0:0x36673326a66854e7"],"When":"2023-12-30"},{"Name":"Joan K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKNuIXag8VkuMHRnuPyQy-scVfVGitSXDypn0KaODMdfyPKmg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love this place, try to go once a week or bi-weekly, tasty, quick service, amazing naan, everything is made to order. I haven't tried the all you can eat buffet (reg $16, on Thursdays 1st person $16, 2nd person 1/2 price. No matter what you order, it is worth it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"glynn gates","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWRLDFBx3wWalMgZBYsrJwtpNeAD8RVns-Sx-kcJiMTBGl3yyz0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Been wanting to try this place for a while now and just had their dinner buffet.   Really excellent and at $16 quite the bargain.

Butter Chicken was excellent as was the beef curry and chili fish.  I was happily surprised with the variety of dishes on offer, which was 3 proteins, a paneer and 3 vegetarian dishes plus basmatti and fried rice.  And a variety of salads and Gulab Jamun (indian donut balls)  The naan and garlic naan were fresh and hot and also excellent

The Mango Lassis we ordered ala carte were again, very good.   I'd highly recommend and will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiMNFDvHDo5cZuNfW4ywoAjA6wpDaW4F70z_xJ&fid=0x0:0x36673326a66854e7"],"When":"2021-9-20"},{"Name":"Tj Lamba","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWmOAhgYB7P764wij9df4_24Pk7sYzp3Pl5vCb2bpAFV3lgO5e2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing food. Decent price and great service. Special shoot out to Raj for making all our parties complete with great food. Their dal makhni and butter chicken are really amazing. Keep it up Doon Express.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPkQQUST6omFcVzs7uo6MuXOGATEzak7UvrS7F9&fid=0x0:0x36673326a66854e7"],"When":"2023-11-2"}]

Beautiful views of the water while eating .","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPeDlOiKsNloC5FZyW33VrEemjxC97A8jfNOeM4\u0026fid=0x0:0x4a9b4cc9f6c67532"],"When":"2017-7-3"},{"Name":"Elke Mulgrew","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV1xmN1-WyXRR6r1lFy-RZooJSZKE0qXbt8e8x7VAJ1xGugE7Zy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"My friend and I had lunch there last weekend and sat outside. My Crab Benedict had a very off flavor to it, the English muffin was soggy and the tomato was old. I ate half of it and then just couldn’t eat anymore and complained. The server did take half off my bill  The next day I see three charges on my credit card. My friend and I had split the bill so there should’ve been one charge. They were all pending so I waited till today. I noe see that all three charges went through. This is just absolutely fraudulent. I will never go there again after this. They charged me $100 which was the full bill for both of us and then they charged me two times $50 for half the bill, so three charges totaling over $200 when the bill should’ve been $50 for my half. And my friend also got charged for her half. Disputed all three charges and will definitely take the tip off.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Nayana Upadhyay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXDhRiR_BFddc4IotYzsTZXqH0caJUaky-rswd5LUX3xYv9806J=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"To dine next to the bay was great experience! I’m in no hurry to return, so disappointed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"cassidy carew","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKguQzjWGBBnBh8h6u57L3g3yRabAoZjABSt_57maE0hRYr9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Horrible costumer service. I ordered via skip the dishes for pick up and sadly chose the wrong store. When picking up from the wrong location we stated my name and order and the two employers shrugged and handed a bag. When opening the bag when at my destination I realized it was the wrong order. Called the store and realized it wasn’t mine and they continued to argue that it was my order after I repeated the name and order number. Which at the time they could have listened and realized that wasn’t the order name. A few minutes later the location I ordered at said my meal is waiting. The owner was extremely disrespectful and blamed the whole mishap on my mistake rather than her employees who just handed any random order off to someone without clarifying. Will not be back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dave Murray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYjlPIsQIrixnPTA-jPVZQ51YxJv8Q0xX-SuSDvcyC7ed1-uX5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Just started going here with my salad lovin' sister and I like it. Feel good eating here. I'm satisfied and get my greens without being bored. The chicken that I get is really good.
I feel like I'm getting a healthy meal. It may cost a couple bucks more than a burger/ fry combo but you have to be making a healthier choice.
There are a couple of Mediterranean themed items that I like and the southwest with chicken is tasty and satisfying.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Laurie B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVohn_SvtM5RtWVr1TWDg_gHPIRnYL7kbkiaTPjU4Kak1S-wdMp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Customer service is lacking as much as the food was.  We ordered a group order ( About 10 orders)  They totally missed one order as well as the side salad for another order.  Person on phone argued and was not helpful. We went back to pick up... and it was pathetic. A quesada should have visible cheese, this had maybe a pinch...and maybe 2 nuggets of chicken.  Definitely NOT up to par with other locations.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Oshrat Zemel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXtnJ7EN06WHLhNMIyZZ6LxgRu5ISHT2cQ54JmAV88vRolDgl19=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Order online 4 times and each time something was missing.
Paid extra $3 for chicken but no chicken
Paid extra $ 2 for avocado but no avocado.
I ordered the sunshine salad with chopped mix, cucumbers, mozzarella, avocado & apples with goddess dressing. When I opened it there was no avocado and  no cucumbers.
I called to complain and offered $2 off next time I buy, took my name and number , when I come in next time they couldn’t find the $ 2 discount written anywhere.

Do not order online or double check before leaving.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tyler Treftlin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUIxrtwC0yCLBEg7O-2MAqOTzD0XcxkyQ-CYC4W4UWl0FD-y89Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A breathe of fresh air, and healthy fresh food, that separates itself from the competition easily. In a day and age when fatty fast food is around every corner, and readily available, it's incredible to have an extremely healthy option like chopped leaf. I drive right by all the burger and fry joints to get to this place, and leave feeling full, healthy, and extremely happy with my decision. Communities need options like this to maintain our health. Thank you to all chopped leaf owners for bringing this great tasting, and healthy, food into all of our lives. Please keep it going strong!","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"A Plus Alex","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtWOn-TmFgm-QgPGWEldghqwwb3rVVjkMKOlSHQW8Q265Ux3h5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pleasantly surprised!  Stayed at the University Plaza while on a work trip and my group decided we’d eat in as the weather was so terrible.   I got the chopped steak that was smothered in mushroom gravy with a side of mashed potatoes and broccoli.   This was $19 and it was absolutely delicious!   Even came with a salad!   Other people in the group got the shrimp and scallops and the fettuccine Alfredo.   Everything was really good and fairly priced.   The wait staff was very nice and professional.   I would definitely come back here!    The venue is really pretty too.  Large windows overlooking a green outdoor area right next to the water, upscale feel.  I heard they were having staffing issues and the restaurant was even closed on Monday 3/27 because of it.   If you’re in the area, consider trying them out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMcEFeve31e56ykDHd2d4XLS-qrbh9QaLZLMgYC\u0026fid=0x0:0xd17899d0871a4371"],"When":"2023-3-29"},{"Name":"Christiane Highfill","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkL2Y25q_WX-YUSDngQ1N-bLeSeHEamVkM22TWe0By1iSIm40d=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This was my first sit-down meal experience at this restaurant. We were seated right away and quickly given water, however, it took a while before our server came to get our drink orders. After receiving our drinks, it took a while before we got our order taken. The restaurant was not busy, so I didn't understand the long wait periods.\n\nIt was a Friday during Lent, so I ordered the grilled salmon with the sweet chili sauce on the side, along with the clam chowder.  As an appetizer, we ordered the grilled artichoke to start. The artichoke was a good size and prepared well.  It was tender and you could taste the smokiness of the grill. Absolutley delicious!  The clam chowder was like wallpaper paste. It was thick and gloppy; not very good. The salmon was nothing spectacular. It was a tail portion, grilled all the way through (I prefer mine just slightly underdone), served over a bed of rice pilaf with broccolini.  Overall, the meal was good, but a bit overpriced for what we got. If they ever do the prime rib buffet again, I would give them another try.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO-o08iYkUee25Ud7Z8vAxT0Ypi1R5hAYdU8m7n\u0026fid=0x0:0xd17899d0871a4371"],"When":"2019-4-8"},{"Name":"Goldie Locks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLRQ-0ubpz498cNLstU3ZcQjwt5EWawg_R4zl6LUKzOZM_6zw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Food is OK. Improve customer service. Updat the atmosphere and this place will be great again. Currently the vibe is just screaming boring people eat and drink here. Don't you guys want to make money? Don't you want to give your employees more hours? Increase their pay? Need to improve your drink and food menu. Menu should wake taste buds up for folks not dribble a bed time story to put them to sleep if that is what most of your guests want. But this place used to be hopping! Now its just a sopping boring mess.  Tell your managers to wake up!!!! Bring the life back to Stockton!!! Throw grad night specials! Love you guys but stop being boring 😴","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Fabian De La Torre","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUBYSzK4SSyAWT4dFCJxhP6zMkdvsT1DJtqrLTkeBtAt36QWK3U=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great place to come have a good drink and food. bartender kris, he sure knows how to make his drinks and keep customers entertained, best bar tender in town!. Food is always delicious! It's never a disappointment. If your in town want to get a good drink and some delicious food stop by you won't be disappointed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBWsK9uDmNMN1RaGhJToIx08lILQN8P2HnzPUf\u0026fid=0x0:0xd17899d0871a4371"],"When":"2022-4-13"},{"Name":"Jessica Talamantes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVTbp4sytiQEkEypIZkoTdj40ToWh-EywWqYEYEq3_3a6K0dVNBIw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tried this place for the first time and I was very impressed. Probably the best clam chowder I've ever had. Very clean and nice restaurant and wonderful. friendly service. Will be back!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"avancuren","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLEluG0dNlnmHK-Krp9Uc4fq7shxjF4G3S87ZG6W0GhiN-P1g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Delta Bistro is the reason to stay at the Waterfront Plaza. The menu is varied and the food is well prepared, particularly the prime rib on Thursdays. The service from Kris and Ray at the bar is great.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVfeauSxliaWEb9j5aSRhAMbQCgn7ookh_IAoYl2wGxeb6ldE7C=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Had breakfast. Only option was a buffet. Ants were all over the table. Staff did not seem to care. Was still asked to pay. I do not recommend.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brian Stone","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIhU3e3DK4eC2nogpI3O-S6k7PT0GekDHTCSDUHWKqFnPOyPw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Was not staffed properly for events that were occurring. There was a cheer competition and a concert of some sort going on. Took 30 minutes to get our order taken and server never came back to ask us about refills. Servers were not assigned to any sections and were taking orders at random throughout. Management needs to know events that are occurring and properly staff the restaurant. Food was decent. The supervisor on staff didn’t seem to care and even snapped and talked rudely to another guest that was complaining of the situation.","Images":null,"When":""}]
