user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Maddy Clair","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDu77UjJrIO-kqRLZ8NPwO32ypV2d9CpNkIjtlP5VM-3foXIae=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First of all… No matter what you order here the backyard is ridiculously gorgeous.
And the inside windows that face the backyard or Florida ceiling.
There’s beautiful original art throughout the café.
It is a very fun place to go.

This morning, I ordered a very specific meal… Egg white veggie scramble.
Attached photo.
I’m not saying anybody else besides me who is such a boring meal… But they did amazing job with my specifications.
It was absolutely delicious and abundant vegetables.
I’ve had other things here and everything has tasted wonderful and they are very accommodating to your particular food needs.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPZ8Ajlp6DOJV13J5N64l1IqmsfcCmmYEM2q5IT&fid=0x0:0x76af91edcfa9b6c7"],"When":"2024-9-25"},{"Name":"Loc Nguyen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKzEoqvjJ2cetXE3sr9u8EfZTYb87XRg990VWXop6cfAw2-=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Nice outdoor/indoor cafe. Very dog friendly !  Looks like all the people who brought their dogs know their dogs are well behaved before bringing them. The food is exceptional in creativity, taste and value. Any place that serves lamb dishes has to be alright. Bathroom is ok.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOOmsWvEm9D1aI5ZMRg48s5KSsapNxf-D7DV0Q&fid=0x0:0x76af91edcfa9b6c7"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"Cinde Salazar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXkhAhSamOdJLIOfEapc98id2V6TJg_M040G8M64KXiC1s6wxld=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time here with a GF and had a great experience! I pulled into their parking lot at noon on a Wednesday, and it was full, however, the owner was so nice. He was sitting in his van and said to park right in front of his van. What a great start!

While standing in line waiting for our order to be taken, we were looking at menu along with the bountiful amount of teas and drinks! I was overwhelmed with giddiness. I ordered the veggie scramble with a side of turkey bacon, the peach smoothie, and the lavender lemonade! As we walked through the interior dining room, the outside tables were calling us! There were plenty of available tables with some in the shade and sun. However, it quickly filled up just after we ordered. The space has a very casual, laid-back atmosphere, where you get your own water and utensils before finding your table, and you feel like you're eating in someone's backyard. The overall vibe was just great, and the food & drinks were truly delicious! What a wonderful find and gem. I'll definitely be back!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMAoAa6h-zqQiEQ9PE4wu4sqOw820B38Id6MdWf&fid=0x0:0x76af91edcfa9b6c7"],"When":"2024-7-19"},{"Name":"Mike Nolan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0Iwn0UqrgQ9Vvgj6Svb9Y96n-Wkih7AIF5UVhFdZ8WgY02A3M=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Cafe Leila is a hidden treasure in plain sight. Food and drinks are all very good and they are very accomdating to make sure you get what you like. Double yummy,","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNxm1XwPzZ2UallW0-6evqEDdsFITs2c98GPMhn&fid=0x0:0x76af91edcfa9b6c7"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"Hayley Sawyers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU3idA2-t5AMV95qi7BBVYeHVNUOMbeImnuCXegi8gII3Z6tAhk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our smoothies tasted so fresh and delicious. The omelettes were spectacular. The garden area was gorgeous and little birds were flying around and getting very close to check out our food. So cute. The waitresses were also very nice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHVlEOUl_W_gSwGnkLOqs0R0WPKa799a5s8t1u&fid=0x0:0x76af91edcfa9b6c7"],"When":"2024-7-25"},{"Name":"Ben Emmert-Aronson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtOE5qbJBxl0z-6_L8ftVAM2SVoCxeD8tfvE18368rlMLB-gFD4g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very cute brunch spot with a huge outdoor space. It was so nice to get a great brunch in the middle of the weekend brunch hour without having to wait 45 minutes for a table. Food was great, the ambiance is cute, I'm a fan.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPb-PF9YffeQbZJKHXwhWd10BrOxwtn-6-OH0T-&fid=0x0:0x76af91edcfa9b6c7"],"When":"2024-9-25"},{"Name":"Phillip Sablo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUX1nZKRxo1ilha3ApriguJqEWTNg9Y-08r4cKWHAWVAAHGPCs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I see Reuben sandwich available for breakfast, I buy Reuben for breakfast.

They were nice enough to swap the side salad for home fires - because what kind of maniac eats salad for breakfast.

Great food all around. 5 stars for having full menu available during breakfast!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP224KgxR541V_QzUZ0jy-mXfbMUbKNcRe5TJty&fid=0x0:0x76af91edcfa9b6c7"],"When":"2024-8-4"},{"Name":"Talia Karasinski","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAm2iymgb8Utf_3B3vSjG3wsk81C4eSzkyaBX2EoXZJ9RUFlp2=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely love this place! Came here for brunch on a Sunday morning. It was easy to get a table and there was no line at 1030am. There was also a guy playing guitar on the patio! I tried the tofu scramble and it was so good. They have a ton of chai and tea options I didn’t get to try - next time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyZafErzN6N8RvbJBe8kCX30GcFMBhX4Ymto6d&fid=0x0:0x76af91edcfa9b6c7"],"When":"2024-6-30"}]

This place has back east Montreal style Pizza! Saputo mozzarella Cheese!
Ask for Pepperoni green peppers mushrooms with extra tomato sauce!! Amazing!  Just missing the classic Dough ball in the middle!!    Add the dough ball guys!!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Christie Bocking","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUaGRRIAKrQt6npi4YkQXsFAJIhWKtSd4WfzX1kgx0TqEcM_-6BEQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My sister (who is visiting from Ontario) and I had dinner here last night. Our server, Layton, was fabulous: ⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ specifically for him. He was so engaging, and funny. He took a photoshoot of us that made us laugh so much we will remember it always. Thank you Layton 🤩","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dawn Mist","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyR-na2sQcGqnSW-JxTn27RMX1oocQ3hojpV86Eb8qwbPHRL0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Decent pizza always but prices have gone up huge and toppings have gotten light. This time round my pizza was burnt to a crisp on the bottom and you served it up. Shocked that you would still serve that up to a customer. Asked double shrimp and paid for it but got less than what I would have gotten if I never asked for more.. You need to step up quality control folks. Grumpy service and tip hungry waitresses who do very little.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kathryn Grant","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK8ya9jJ3H3DnY-HNDIGFZJZUZ1BN76ICQpfB3OKX8zJb7L680=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I have been a guest at Niagara many times, but tonight's visit was the worst.  I want to be clear, the food was very good, hot and fresh, so none of the rest of this review concerns the food quality.
As stated I have been a guest at Niagara a number of times over the past 20 years, tonight myself and my friend were treat as an after thought.  It started upon our arrival, we had made a reservation only to be made to feel like we were imposing.  The table we were taken to had been set for 4 but "the people had not arrived so we could have the table."  We knew what we were having and ordered immediately (we were sharing a medium pizza and a baked lasagna). Neither of us want anything other than water, I guess that was our first mistake not ordering alcohol. Our pizza arrived in the appropriate amount of time but no lasagna, we ended up having to ask and then we had to wait for the garlic bread.  At no time did someone come by to ask how our meals were, but we noted that the large parties were being fawned over by 3 or 4 service staff, not professional at all.
I was not happy.  We were not offered desert or coffee, instead we were brought take away containers and 2 candies were DROPPED on the table and were asked "one cheque or 2?". As the fellow walked away my friend commented that a cup of coffee would be nice.  When the fellow came back with the cheques my friend asked politely for a cup of coffee, he never apologized that we had not been asked.....just walked away.  And to note all our dirty dishes were still on the table!  He came back with coffee and the cheques.  After 10 minutes another fellow walked by and said " oh you want to pay?" Another 10 minutes and we had to request to pay, at that time I commented that I was having the worst experience and was not happy.  The waitress, nor anyone else asked why.....finally we paid.  My tip reflected my disappointment.

In this day and age when restaurants have an expectation of a minimum of 18% Gratuities the management  better be ensuring that the 18% is deserved.  I refuse to pay for poor guest services. I work and have worked in customer facing businesses for years, sometimes for minimum wage and I do not receive tips other than how to do my job better.  I pick and choose carefully the restaurants I want to spend my money at, tonight's experience has given me reason to take a restaurant off my list.  Always remember, word of mouth travels far and wide.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Pongo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXT-qQCE1uUwfmES1FGLIpAmkroUlDIcsJZMXejhRkO1uA9CxO=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Pretty good pizza; definitely a notch above the greasy chains. There's quite a bit of overlap in terms of toppings/combinations on the menu. Gluten free crusts are offered without additional charge. Prices are not cheap, and portions are not the biggest","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sherri Brown","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUQkSuN1OiR4qFZ8MdDhJnuphoN7FGI6toKXWC2U07ZsWrwbT4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"This place has deteriorated in both quality and service. Very little gratitude from servers for your hard earned money spent there, and the pizza has declined in quality and amount of toppings, while getting more expensive. Hard pass here for the next pizza night.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Cerra Gelz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0QfnFtHR8obSs6YVsgCeB_gvJJ9sW_t0QEhbsdpTjlpnR4HX7MQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"For how weird the location is, inside and food is pleasantly surprising! Ordered a pizza, the calamari, and the roast lamb dinner. Food was awesome! 👌","Images":null,"When":""}]

Staffs were excellent in their service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsPXr1yDted2KGkihvr4ET6lXoS-W6BtSXBv-l&fid=0x0:0xaa13cdbe8ee84038"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"D G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6NgtNHsMX4LS948o8YDNySJH2Eq6HMDstP5SClrE9B2QR8YuM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A very enjoyable experience. They opened up 3 bedrooms for us to explore. They were very nice! Food was good. A bit pricey, but I think it's worth it to go to a mansion to eat brunch. You don't pay for parking, and the drive to the mansion is very scenic.

It is a buffet, and the menu doesn't change except for Thanksgiving and Xmas. I will definitely go again. The experience is enhanced if you go with friends and dress up really nice.

My cousin was pounding down the mimosas. I love pasta, and this pasta was one of the best I ever had. The pear salad dressing was very good! I didn't care for the dessert though, and I wish they could do better. Their cakes were dry, especially the white one.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM84xTJkOWcd-CR3Et7Q_ehGxVicQl6V9Avk9A&fid=0x0:0xaa13cdbe8ee84038"],"When":"2023-11-3"},{"Name":"Whitney and Matsaya Photography","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhLpb1-BPMFduoZ5Uin3SI1tQhft69yRP__2iZCKGTAQslCv5V=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We've photographed weddings here and are excited to be back again this year! It's a stunning venue with vintage vibes and you never have to leave site for portraits (everything can happen right on location). Our brides are stylish who like a timeless classy look and this venue fits right into their aesthetic. Can't wait to be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgiss1i2Dh_ikBLImB-WF8vI9ynbB7aN-mLu2O&fid=0x0:0xaa13cdbe8ee84038"],"When":"2024-5-7"},{"Name":"Cecilia and Jordan Headley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKtuK3Kow9AIvuckxMbfxUJYvvW7ecxmIJAr9l9W3HwwxZ2MQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This review is long overdue. We got married at GIM back in July, and we had the most amazing experience. The mansion itself is beautiful. I fell in love with it the first time I laid eyes on it. The lawn is manicured to perfection. My favorite thing about the venue is all of the beautiful artwork. The food was also phenomenal! The hospitality and service provided by the GIM staff far surpassed our expectations. Every staff member we encountered was kind and helpful. Our day of coordinator was Tara, and she was amazing. She kept things running smoothly and was so supportive throughout the entire day. We also booked overnight rooms and had such a fun time at our after party. It was truly my dream wedding come true, and I wish I could go back and do it one more time! I loved everything about GIM. Thank you to all of GIM staff! You all are amazing.✨","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5J8a1L-ORV9B99vXxLwM-06aZDi7_7v9aKvlZ&fid=0x0:0xaa13cdbe8ee84038"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Inka 6Toes","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocINqBWZYOYxfCNezQIXRmqHL3R3Cv-kCzjUjhXv54sYDbcriQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We went for Sunday Brunch!  The food was amazing, best buffet we have ever been too.  Staff were very attentive making sure we had plenty of coffee and Mimosas.  Grounds were absolutely beautiful.  Would highly recommend!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9p9ohVi_mimohzukRHiLQJPjHVTstWkQJvZEW&fid=0x0:0xaa13cdbe8ee84038"],"When":"2024-4-15"},{"Name":"Joel Marsh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUICvQ-fqrDnbyyuthHn9YNo80q4Hc7laDLmFXjj23mDvMOOEXPTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came for Thanksgiving brunch and as always great service. Matt and Debbie were our attendants and always made sure we were taken care of. The food was cooked amazing and everything was so fresh. I do always think they are missing an opportunity by not having the espresso machine up and running in the basement or even the bowling alley while people are on the premises.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMls0Aw7sfMh-vn3drOtP0usroUFSRYQfFf2frD&fid=0x0:0xaa13cdbe8ee84038"],"When":"2023-11-25"},{"Name":"Jim Van Velzer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXMr5W8KeCpdMHbopHZgUwxumLob1kiZfAdF9jA-bZMCB6bUVpI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Grand Island was a lovely place for Father's Day Brunch. Roast Beef was superb.  Excellent desserts.  A couple of minor details seem to have been overlooked.  The dinner rolls were cold.  Although they were very tasty,  they could have been so much better, if they had but been warm.  For a place working toward elegance, serving butter in foil wrapped bits seem a little off.   Ambiance was wonderful.  Service was faultless.  Mimosas were terrific.  The champagne was excellent.  All at a quite affordable price.  What's not to like?  Well worth the trip to the country.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOPmuv-kbSV2aq1958eLo2EC5n2IDfw2IRcuOHk&fid=0x0:0xaa13cdbe8ee84038"],"When":"2023-6-19"}]

The food came in around 10 minutes which I felt was fair because the place was fairly busy. I ordered there $5 meal deal. At first I was disappointed because there chicken wrap was one chicken strip wrapped around a tortilla. The fries were good and right out of the fryer. My only complaint was some of the fries tasted under cookek. I was disappointed that there was no free wifi. Props to this location. [{"Name":"CP","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5JIi6fgkahNqxTdjvaeJmOnTfjZRidJGrQjtJl3lyCblB2Ng=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The worst thing about Bobs is their prices. The food is pretty good nothing too special. The onion rings are garbage. The location and environment are cool but beware it can get busy on the weekends especially in nicer weather.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvc1VNMl3OJWQc1a9TbvMiC7hK4q9YMf62oI_0&fid=0x0:0x76273a9e2237cc88"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Richard Andrade","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGqLNjWx_YFM0Jz1dBcsnnjPq3ekzXSjJNNR3wutJqjjoL3S58=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I don't know why people are giving this place anything other than a 5 star. We crave these burgers a couple times a month and they never let us down. Honestly I want to try something else but everytime we go We end up with burgers and garlic fries!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNk5sdlol00ShLySVpb3UjHAA-NBXiLIgTOuVIu&fid=0x0:0x76273a9e2237cc88"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"B P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXQg0Z3sKNB0PuJKgBtkyBIoqvJ9OMmpuGm9XZqYSgFnMZ81QVA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"It was a 103F day and we were traveling with our dogs. No one brought out water so we had to get our own dog bowls. But that aside, the main reason for the low review is the food. Cheap and low grade. The mozzarella sticks "squeaked", the boiled eggs on the chicken salad had grey yolks and the chicken was rubbery. The outdoor section looked like something out of Miss Havisham's house (Great Expectations) - big cobwebs under each table and over each umbrella. We couldn't get out of there fast enough.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOL4pxh9_tVb_y3RbvMST2C_wtbRN4ORqv-0M5Q&fid=0x0:0x76273a9e2237cc88"],"When":"2024-7-22"},{"Name":"Juneve Kimble","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXPvoMjqAuZsRWLZ9ye2jy3l5DNfzt81dpVilAqN-WnMqd9znY0sw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I wanted to try their French Toast, but they ran out of bread, so they offered Chocolate Chip Pancakes, so I was willing to give them a try. The wait took a while for the food. They were busy. It was a giant stack, for sure. I was able to only eat half of it. It was ok. They brought it out to me without the butter & syrup. Had to ask for it and wait some more. 🤦🏻‍♀️ My husband usually enjoys their burger, but he tried the Chicken Fried Steak this time. We always enjoy being near the ocean or river.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4wXnmjt4L5IOEyefoRPnkkiSTNF0AC4pSimKa&fid=0x0:0x76273a9e2237cc88"],"When":"2023-6-11"},{"Name":"Javier Nunez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpZIWkG8UncSMkY0vKivyZX60Yr353pVKK2Zay6hwT02ybevw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The hamburgers are good here. I do recommend it. I came on a Sunday afternoon not too bad.
The football game was on . There was really no distractions. Great servers. Parking is pretty OK at that time.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"patsy cady","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW3BuFVd7eeC2wEj9IuNNTc4Lvqe36Qdup9BIsSyPp6qqTfXtfz=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Away from home and looked for a restaurant I could take my dog to have lunch.  Found bobs at the marina .  Great location with great atmosphere.  Food was good.  My dog even enjoyed there hamburger patty.  They even asked if the could bring my dog a water bowl.  Very pleased with this location would go back next time I'm in Stockton.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcPefIMIz1YTts7yMgsRl5vPrfXSudm8itKM5F&fid=0x0:0x76273a9e2237cc88"],"When":"2024-4-28"},{"Name":"Michael Wilson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKxzTBzfgH38VaeTYSfB7WXuF5H6XX0xS_TlyO9U3-14X6TCQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We spent a Sunday afternoon on the deck here last Sunday. To start with I got a double burger done medium, my mom got a single cooked to Bobs specs... They were juicy and delicious and absolutely wonderful. We got garlic fries and onion rings to go with it ..but that's when the real star showed up!! THE RANCH...as in scratch made with buttermilk and mayo.. like Hidden Valley in the 80s .. omg so delicious and flavorful.

The breeze was amazing and the view was great.. the people watching was fun too ... The aromas are special though.. between the cooking meat of two restaurants and grills and the river water smells... It's just good for the soul. So I guess I'm saying I highly recommend this restaurant 😁👍","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ava Koster","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUVlEuN0qO7GkqB-JxQwFbI1yK8o5CRD4S647s2WOFdKTjt-xmOoA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been going to Bob's for a long time, since I was in elementary school. And I've seen this place grow. There are a few bad reviews here but that's hard to believe considering the fact that the workers, food, and atmosphere were way above the minimum. I love this place personally. The Patty melt and French toast are to die for. and the French fries beat the average fast food place. Don't miss it. The only thing to complain about is the closing time. But that only makes for a healthier working environment that the majority of the middle aged average workers like to bash on. Bob's is one of my favorite places to eat. Don't miss out for breakfast and Lunch. It's also very dog friendly and has boat access. Its often brimming with a whole bunch of people, animals included. Birds, dogs, sometimes even the stray cat will survey the area. And an earlier complaint about "spiderwebs" comes normal when you're sitting outside. so if you hate bugs, you always have the inside option. I highly recommend Bob's, and if you give it a try; I'm sure you will too.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"V T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIHUsnxA__SaJIzFMnt9WPKgaJ0P7SYW4tyY9G21uonLnNYjVe=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited this stunning restaurant and quickly realized I had been missing out on such beautiful scenery! It was my first time here, and after enjoying an incredible lunch, I loved it so much that I came back for dinner. The views are absolutely breathtaking—some of the best I've seen when visiting. The food was just as impressive, with the fried ice cream and garlic fries being my absolute favorites. Just wow","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMH4A5lJFrPDcoZeO9YJ3ulCpQqSXMg19JKRyB7\u0026fid=0x0:0x7918e7d0d662d251"],"When":"2024-8-24"},{"Name":"Nise R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUPYCHm7fICKFkhl-iN0AMUXtO1Oh5TTH74sZ5_sxcbrxAphBRd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here on a Monday night and was surprised that any entree and any pizza is only $16 or maybe $17! What a deal in today's times. We tried Seafood Pasta and it did not disappoint. Loaded with seafood and a tasty tomato based sauce. The other entree was the Salmon and it was cooked perfectly. Got it with Polenta and also their house pasta and asked for Pesto sauce. Nice portions and gorgeous view. I've been coming here for so long (decades) but somehow didn't know about the Monday special. Our server was outstanding. Very patient and very attentive. Try coming before sunset and enjoy the views and dine outside on their large patio overlooking the delta if you can...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMm2R-oTAeGUTH3cLcQvCWVpOthwZuziqsIZRo\u0026fid=0x0:0x7918e7d0d662d251"],"When":"2024-8-7"},{"Name":"Jackie Vincent","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvt27mKmoybuMBXWCM_V5ZM8U8gqRcK-xysrvaZAW8Z1ZszuDvjg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"They didn’t have it on the menu, but the chef made me some butter garlic noodles with tri-tip strips in it, It was awesome. My daughter had the gumbo over steamed rice, she said it was great. We drank the fishbowl slurrr for two. It was the best, and biggest drink in an actual fish bowl. My daughter loved the oysters. She tried the fried ice cream, and said it was ok, but I didn’t like the fried ice cream at all. The service was awesome, and the outside vibe and view was amazing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMQQUs-yZ5vH8GwTOWzBaAEyLG22xzqguXnTc09\u0026fid=0x0:0x7918e7d0d662d251"],"When":"2024-10-28"},{"Name":"Cris Bee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyIOoHyofAcaA2-q_61YUZ_F6H2jIlZcxzMwBdEf1GCUMLQZt0Mg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We went on a Thursday night around 5, and it was a little busy. Our server took a bit coming to our table but from that point forward our drinks and food came out at a reasonable time. I got the green death and it was rich and flavor, my friend got the salmon and highly recommended it. Also, everything is reasonably priced, and I like how they have  different happy hours for almost everyday.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTFj2lfFbj4SJ07F0XgiWeJ2X3-s4zbBSS7i7h\u0026fid=0x0:0x7918e7d0d662d251"],"When":"2024-7-30"},{"Name":"Work_emout Medina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZnZ9MLMgkFf4QHfOBjVR72vvH7-jdsqJtZ_0cKKbIfnN7NT9J=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"LOVE, LOVE AND LOVE Garlic Brothers. I have been coming here since I was a little girl and I’m in my late 30’s now. It’s hidden in a marina all the way down Benjamin Holt and such a flaming view and atmosphere. If you love tri tip, pesto pastas, calzones, pizzas and more then you will have to try Garlic brothers. Look up the menu….mind blowing. It’s a must try restaurant and an even better place to visit for happy hour with the girls or guys on Friday’s and Saturdays. Also during the summer, you can rent kayaks and boats near by…it’s beautiful.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMVlN72zrcJH7ddrtF0K58Q60qc8jmFaSU5RMpA\u0026fid=0x0:0x7918e7d0d662d251"],"When":"2024-12-24"},{"Name":"Malik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-t64phD0vG0CulYu3nuQf3KLos_XpeLTw_DT5fXfxPVTXR77vjg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went here on my first day in California and the food was great. I had the hamburger and fries, and it tasted even better than I expected. Some of the other people at my table weren't as delighted, but I'm writing this review based on my own experience. The service was very friendly and the atmosphere is great, the outside seating area has a nice view. Would definitely recommend","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNbtl_t5hGuu6KM6Gf-zue8Woq2W67y3mvOG92w\u0026fid=0x0:0x7918e7d0d662d251"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Amber H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUFxL5Bv_LlyViBKh43n550buc-ImUiVMAoT5ldto4vPglMtYFOg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Loved the festive vibe, service, and the delta view. The watermelon margarita reminded me of jolly rancher candy and was light and refreshing. Pizza was decent but I have had way better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPleFR_RuCDKtC4jXtu_s5kywEhVt8YDVUOI27D\u0026fid=0x0:0x7918e7d0d662d251"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"ichibangai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI7p9XAdOurAGcBHlsztBnwRfnrVcwR-K7SBrRc23MPeRBbGw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Garlic Brothers: A Stockton Surprise\nStepping into Garlic Brothers feels like a world away from Stockton. I was lucky enough to witness a breathtaking sunset there. It was like being immersed in a vibrant canvas of color. The friendly and welcoming atmosphere made the experience even more special. It's a hidden gem that shouldn't be missed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMURh1igoF-I05uu36i9SXGuAG3Ixv2-f-I3B1m\u0026fid=0x0:0x7918e7d0d662d251"],"When":"2024-8-13"}]

[{"Name":"لجين علي عبدالله","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJknstfVQBYVOicM756T8lGplERKL0_UBI-91D2Lx8i3wQBxzk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It was nice spot to have breakfast after a long walk. Order the spinach and eggs benny and tomatoes and chives omelette.
Didn’t try the coffee (which I regret) but my friend had English tea and it was great!
I liked the food but didn’t love it, need more spices from myside to hit that sweet spot.

Loved the view and it has great atmosphere, very relaxing place and would visit it again.

Also, use the front door entrance of the club, it also leads to the restaurant, don’t need to go around for the stairs entrance.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMETZkxZHuffXBSBsYx-EvpU3vpLe7F4XwpUHnt&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2024-9-30"},{"Name":"Ben M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLY7-DFsqx-InW5CnlXpJd6DWvP1u6nfShJnLWMiHPMX_9EZw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great place for lunch in a sunny day. The view is beautiful. The shepherd's pie, mashed potato on the pie, and the sandwich are all very good. The French fries are so so.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOeS23iArM7RRGT9MMGW-BLlqdTh458oebRv1Dp&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2024-6-8"},{"Name":"P G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0fCU2Qc0a_c6EyAnrC9oWHMXOLKbAIpYaZPyN9xTdV9lbUoGm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice spot on a sunny afternoon/evening and food is quite ok (used to be better but maybe recent visit was a blip), just service is lacking and that’s a constant","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0IdqGqVO6XZ26pKrpEN0UmMy9Yc_gm_xQbLJh&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"Jasmeher Kathuria","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRPxourZkFGqspJqITB0BgxzAESvenlWO0L3A_jSAljqDI09n1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The short rib rigatoni and the apple pie are my go to dishes. Always order them whenever I go and am greeted by welcoming staff members.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOm84TuBZ6_Hanftej6Q9Qh1oBHQJWYDM1JM6Vk&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2024-6-9"},{"Name":"Lil Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDgF8p2j50UmJKzkx4VadmKu8Ao0Nvxlfi-pi40gh9UM4OrRn61w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice place. Pricey but not excessive for a nice patio golf course. Great view overlooking a garden with a bridge and stream. My husband had a decent burger, I had a turkey BLT sandwich with wholegrain (nice touch), our friend who invited us had an avocado salad. Second time this year dining here. Only complaint is their lunch menu does not start until 2pm by then most people had left!?! There were several young ladies serving us but sometimes have to flag them down but once you got them, they were really friendly and even recommended dating apps for our friend. LoL 😂","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzxDJvkBMo7yIDx75UBzMcOykNPDaOoc2-cWEz&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2023-8-2"},{"Name":"No MSG No Garlic Foodie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-PVOn6GcWxsKb-qqVJDTqvJ5rfua5QVuFocwcMF-ZRwuEIPLm=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The points for this review is purely for the pleasure of sitting outside on a 2nd floor patio overlooking expansive area of green lawn, gardens and forest. I am also grateful for the non-metal chairs!
It was 27°. We've just been cooling in the forests of the beautiful UBC Botanical Garden and not quite ready to drive back to the city. Westward Ho at the UBC Golf Course came up on my Google search for brunch. Their patio picture was the deciding factor. Since it was nearly Happy Hour, the pub wasn't crowded and we were able to get a table in the impressively big patio. Not sure if it would be equally impressive had it been a really sunny day. We'd have to check that out another time. On this cloud day, the patio was very bright – almost to the point where I have to put on my sun glasses.
As for the food, we had a hard time choosing: fresh fish and chips, fish sandwich, Beyond Beef burger, all day breakfast, etc. I ordered a Club House with multigrain yam fries, my companion ordered fresh Cod and Chips. The bread in my Club House was dried out, the sandwich did not look as scrumptious as the one with sour dough presented to the table next to us. My sandwich was too 'orderly', the chicken did not spill out of the sandwich like the one I saw earlier. I enjoyed the cod fish though – very fresh and not over battered. So, I guess I ordered the wrong thing! I liked the choice of using vinegar on coleslaw instead of mayo. A decent size coleslaw for a more balanced meal. MSG? For a few hours afterwards, I was very thirsty, but did not get the usual sickly feeling from eating MSG. So, not sure what was in the food that caused my tongue to feel so dry.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNjr8zNCvHQWWPDvIvCsF-m8vfK6OTg8xyORYzH&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2021-8-2"},{"Name":"Azi Jahan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVoCqSGFWxXVxJxNnyUrYmJjWJKEtREeG-G0RXpmBRv8kbELxEL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"For gulf lovers for sure, it's a well-known place.

Beautiful location and view🤌🏻
Delicious brunch
So kind and supportive staff

It's a peaceful weekend brunch location if you are looking for a calm weekend's brunch🤩","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4NKPC_4N4_VYCzznfOGLy34Q4VWIecJtPF0BY&fid=0x0:0xb49fce853972ff8d"],"When":"2022-7-29"},{"Name":"Paul Rogers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-2DEuMMhV7vJRExrjz5OPFG99Ya8EpWqhlLnkXnZqRJpDqw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"My family went here with a few other people for dinner.  Nice staff (hence the 2 stars) but the food was very disappointing.  Out of the 3 in my family, none of us enjoyed our meals.  I had the fish tacos which were bland and mushy.  I would not recommend this restaurant.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"JD Garcia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXxoVUWMH44dNkDs-3Sti2iPd9ZlUJzrn_3dzpfF5JBpPyVmXnvHA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The steak sandwich was dry. The steak was overly cooked, rendering it hard to chew and enjoy. The waitress was kind but never came back to take our order. A gentleman walking by took our order. I was never offered a refill or checked on to see if my meal was good.  The pancakes were delicious, though. The atmosphere was chill, and the location is absolutely beautiful, but the quality of goods served...
Maybe if they didn't overcook the try tip and put the aoli sauce on the bread, it would have been a great experience. Oh yeah, have the servers actually check on the clients.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP7Uvw3zNmSuwh4Kya9dMCYqFaxRi0Nxq5zQPX8&fid=0x0:0xdafdf3b3a4c84078"],"When":"2024-10-14"},{"Name":"Jannine Renee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_1SqcgMNDz5UWswF5VLvN0uueroAqaWA0v2e98D_mLirexx0OKw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Wanted to love the food, however I found a hair inside my Chile Relleno.  That grossed me out.  Chicken fried steak was over-fried with too much batter.  Service was friendly enough.  Beautiful view but overpriced.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP6SO5l63ICo8fZ2PO5AQQalTmMkGh9dW1kZPvR&fid=0x0:0xdafdf3b3a4c84078"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Norlando Saavedra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJkzU6ta4b7xho8CKNrDe7V1PhZ9v_CArUCqooLT6y1uZ-uIP7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great place for lunch or early dinner. Watch the water while you wait. The service could have been a lil better. But like the live music","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNagcR7ofZ1MpZVswJWMIL7Au-wMlxw5LVD-IuC&fid=0x0:0xdafdf3b3a4c84078"],"When":"2024-9-23"},{"Name":"Kimberly Olvera","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUMrjJ_u-__ovcnex9xjpthAshTz5zVxUl65C0jft2NdmAa_qlH=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"To begin with as soon as I enter I noticed that the host was helping another customer very friendly. As she set her down in her table. She approached us and said how many?  in a very rude way. She had NO customer service skills whatsoever. It almost seemed that she did it on purpose since she was white just like her and Im a person of color. We sat down and order our food. The food was delicious The only thing I didn’t like was that the ham was a little bit too dry But other than that, the food was great. The portions are humongous. I would rate of this restaurant a 8/10.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPNft1TpmCBen_YBs1jak8MLSmscvGApEBTRSc9&fid=0x0:0xdafdf3b3a4c84078"],"When":"2024-8-11"},{"Name":"Mandey Alexander","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW7xfVKbfDvhx_uaYkTVQW1FRZSjNjTvOJKPD_3haU13Yyiu32ivw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The location is great the service impeccable, we came here for a company event and had large trays of
food that left a lot to be desired.  I know it's hard cooking in large quantities and keeping the food warm, but the Alfredo lacked flavor and the potatoes had a soapy taste.  The bruschetta was amazing though.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rocio Perez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwCtDFpaYSgOC_8-EK_nQGAx_SS3MV_-6_-2sggf04aakmmCvk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love the vibes, views, and food here! When it’s very busy however, the service quality goes down unfortunately. But when it’s not busy, service is great! I recommend going during non-busy times.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUxPh9C8XgzxVebR1vRS-X1qKqfe2N0XS7ZR7p&fid=0x0:0xdafdf3b3a4c84078"],"When":"2024-8-26"},{"Name":"Cris BA","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWRqwOF5mEgogytXeH9C-OT67zm_v3A7ZejmHa9iZvdg9e4Y06HKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a beautiful restaurant within the downtown Antioch area (that portion is rustic). Service has been quick to greet, eat, and follow up with us. The food hasn't been delivered to the table any less than hot! The flavor area quaint for some dishes,  fresh for others, but nothing was "drowned" is sugars or dressing.  The portion size is large, and it matches the cost for the items. The view was beautiful of the delta and Mt. Diablo. I have been here twice and I will make it my regular stop, over many other breakfast and lunch places. They are military proud and gave a discount for service!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"mansa shaka","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU4T7BV9MB0cBX0hDYkT5KM4SgNLiDUrpmmezGizo5Vtj0WXcuS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"5 stars because of the Bakery and the Delta view provided at this venue.

Frankly most of Antioch is a place where one must often look over their shoulder — at least at Monica’s one can be at ease. The food is delicious, the staff while often a bit stretched is friendly & courteous, it has a diverse arrangement of places to dine and drink. The fire pits can be enjoyable on a chilly night or day especially with a drink in hand! While you may full indulgent don't let that hinder the good time to be had.

They have live music which draws a crowd but that is great if your trying to enjoy an evening or socializing. Sundays are very busy after 10 a.m. onward.

The bakery while not open Monday’s offers throughout the rest of the week a fine array of decadent treats that would make your trainer blush. It handily puts the competition in its place.

A fine place indeed, that provides an escape which in my estimation is worth every penny!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNSKoIGETSB_S542POj5Bcl414tBvYKavJnPQvS&fid=0x0:0xdafdf3b3a4c84078"],"When":"2022-10-24"}]

title: Delta King Hotel

descriptions: Docked 1927 riverboat offering polished quarters & refined dining, plus an informal bar & grill.

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Chad Chapman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_xxADBcr-xOPERyi-TAv4cn6_3-AtlRrG-Qg1H2i5dG4F8dnX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had decided to stay here because of its proximity to the Golden One center for a concert we were going to. We were not disappointed! The valet parking was quick and easy, checking in was painless, and the rooms were great! It has such a fun and unique feel to it. We loved every part of staying here. The staff was incredibly friendly and helpful. We had a lovely view of the river. And the price was very reasonable. We are definitely going to stay here again in the future!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Morgan Cavinder","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJs_8zTSL68mO-83ncQO1BYfhBAyS7Q-nCaVP0iN71a0-PacQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best experience we could have imagined! We booked out a private room to host our rehearsal dinner, and working with Rachel was a DREAM. As soon as we started working with Rachel, we knew we were in good hands. She helped us organize and decorate the room for rehearsal dinner, offering great suggestions and tips. The food was delicious and the service day of was better than I could have imagined. Our friends and family were blown away by how cool the experience of the delta king was, how amazing the food and service was and enjoyed the personal bartenders and boat balcony to hang out on! Highly recommend Delta King for any private event you may have coming up! We will be back!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shann McC","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW8brPFIcTxW7kJK07tilmoeNUq-F8GykTMDOPOjBpYR4OUUhyb=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The Delta King itself was a beautifully renovated historic boat, and well kept. The staff were all very kind, helpful and professional. The bar and restaurant were very good. Morning coffee on the deck for sunrise was very nice. The room is small but charming with antique hardware and had everything I needed. I enjoyed my stay on the boat. Valet could use an extra person. I did not really care for Old Town Sacramento as it was a very busy tourist area and has a grungy vibe which reminded me of bourbon street in New Orleans.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQm_feIFZ2BXgRIL9mfaGDFZK4N3LLIDVxzdcr&fid=0x0:0x774e2a64c16aa382"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"LoveourHolidays_10","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdVsxDWqDDLG62Q3M3dmLlHORJs5jz0NWRJO3cP21KtRNPfosO7RpofjnbUgpyNjOTDew=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"We last stayed at the Delta King 13 years ago, and it was lovely to get the chance to return.|Nothing has changed the staff are all lovely. We were offered help with luggage on arrival, and used the valet parking.|As on our last stay we had a river view room, and knew to expect some noise from the river - but that’s part of the fun! |We ate dinner  on the deck as the sun was setting, having just flown in from the UK it was the perfect start to our holiday. Food was really good, at dinner and breakfast, and nice to receive a voucher for a complementary drink in the bar.|Old Sacramento is lovely, and staying in the river is just unique.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Danielle Guillette","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIw1rYpLAu9TgmAdHR-uov7yNeWwAbG9vq08_onzu31a9QrWg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A Delicious Dinner on the Delta King

The Delta King in Sacramento delivered a truly memorable dining experience. The restaurant's historic setting on a docked paddlewheel steamer provided a unique and charming atmosphere. But it wasn't just the ambiance that impressed; the food and service were exceptional.

Our waiter James Fitzgerald was incredibly attentive and accommodating, making sure my friend in a wheelchair felt comfortable and welcomed. His thoughtful service added a personal touch to our meal.

As for the food, the prime rib was absolutely divine. The meat was cooked to perfection, juicy and flavorful. It was a truly satisfying dish that I'll be dreaming about for a long time.

If you're looking for a special dining experience in Sacramento, I highly recommend the Delta King. The combination of delicious food, excellent service, and a historic setting makes it a must-visit.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"kate e","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QdGDJ6WBs5CBoNVcQAwShh25kntoFa0rN3szxhkmmJHnXagNPuSfO1BRpzbnKc5wyCe_g=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"Front front desk staff to Aaron the bartender I felt welcomed and looked after. The front desk gal was great and caring I had the best ceaser salad of my career. Too bad I have to head back east. Recommend highly!!|This is a unique property and I loved the sea lions barking!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"AnM Racing","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXC3txcJY1_bZ7H2dC2K1N1k4nQgTpZklcFVkJO1NSypSnebPxx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The room was a bit small but still fun to stay on an old paddle boat. I think it's haunted too. Yes, the noise on the weekends is a bit loud. Lots of partiers and seals howling. I would still highly recommend staying here. The staff is super friendly and always ready to help. Beautiful sunset and river.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLE4U-kSo47nXZRu-0TOMPKN_vrhy5SevgEq3s&fid=0x0:0x774e2a64c16aa382"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"demi tzanis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLB2rRF9kR90KZCZxtE1cUSAya0oExsA_4fkA-jcjyurwpo4A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Rooms are small, which is fine, and mostly clean but could definitely use a vacuum throughout the whole boat. The walls are paper thin so you hear everyone walking by and talking and the seals howling. We only stayed one night and for one night it was fine but wouldn’t have wanted to stay for longer. Great location though! Very walkable.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Alex Zhang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhM8_i0FgjcMWn1pe2iCTPCulYiJ6ZdM-BxEPPrbNCZswmBhAC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We got the 12.99 specials that come with the free strawberry tea. Food was good but portion sizes were amazing - way more than what we would expect for the price point. Would come back again, please don't come when I'm here though because I don't want to wait in like to get in.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwGUffMCid9mYoOZnoUamdNb5OEGSphWqcE3J4&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Grace","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpyR6lW9JHiyXGuG73lo5A19PTb1WXFzVLCnrO84Gv3hfeDE5c=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A new restaurant on campus serving Japanese and Chinese cuisine! I got the corn croquette set for $12.99, with a small bowl of udon added on for $3.50. The set came with a melon smoothie. The corn croquette was delicious, crispy on the outside and creamy on the inside. It came with curry sauce and katsu sauce. It also came with a big portion of rice (the rice was well-made, which was a relief since I’ve had mushy rice at other restaurants before). The miso soup was salty, but paired perfectly with the rice.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP24-dj3EKzX1h2q3vosOg1MLmiGK8BW9sRxAVJ&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-10-11"},{"Name":"Madeline Kam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVpk6Vux-KZ276SHSgtsoa9YbbByLpXdFWBO-biQ8KXP9MZVJYZxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The staff and atmosphere were great, but the food was a bit bland. I ordered the combo which included miso soup and drink of the day and I believe it was 10.99 which is a pretty good price. However, the food did not have much flavor and included scarce amounts of protein (in this case chicken). The drink was a winter melon slushy which was a bit icy and crunchy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO0eJ6zfyWxK9NGBkvDlyPP7AyjsetQVWVPollW&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Anouk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX030nN0Ds_sauo0gxWlayfH_7n_wMK-lQfODkscyR8xTr0EynOFg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Place is bright and clean. We both ordered the Shanghai thick noodles and the dishes took 25 min to arrive. Taste was unbelievably mediocre and the soup was too sour - neither of us finished. The opening deals on the menu are affordable though, especially for UBC, and maybe they taste better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWiirhGWCywKk_4pWuAI7dmTssCBUA1V0fb4Cd&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-7-9"},{"Name":"Isabelle lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKeqOC4yQmaYwP6NpsFegJJEZXL9yVwbsvUjxB7-j-CAgqz2g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great service - all the servers were super attentive and even the store manager was helping with clearing, wiping down tables and serving food.

Food is decent, generous portions and very reasonable price. You won’t find anything cheaper than this these days.

I got the 3 fried prawns, 2 fried scallops,  2 pieces of fried yam + bowl of rice and miso soup for $14 only.

Highly recommend this place. Give it a try (:","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNz-ZmsmRszrSY1eFYJM1K72lNbvdcZnF6Ubyzo&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-6-17"},{"Name":"Sophia H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJj7J89gHLVylfj7eNtEAHc3P50FouTDBLmVYxgTpUzNqmzNA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came here today for lunch with one of my friends and were pleasantly surprised by Beyond BBQ!! We both got the pork loin katsu ($17) and they had a special on where if you get any katsu you also get a free drink, so I got a supreme mango tea and my friend got the passion fruit tea. Everything was so delicious, and they gave us a TON of food for the price!!! The pork had an amazingly crispy breading and was flavourful without being dry, the miso soup came out hot (which I was very impressed by), and there was the perfect amount of rice. The sauces were good also and added a delicious pop of flavour!! Not to mention that the fruit tea was so flavourful and fresh!! The staff and servers were also lovely and did an incredible job, especially with giving recommendations. I would definitely come back!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4_goCkK_8lX1VMTr-7haXCj-Lb_pjZnBWZzOc&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-7-29"},{"Name":"Justina He","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJX5XpjJlDr-QcyrWD78qxzdGiJ3dWfMQkYELeI3EDDwTRmpES=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is an affordable new restaurant on campus that people should NOT go to. They serve horrible versions of Asian cuisine that not only are insults to the original recipes but are disgusting. Ordered a class mung bean noodle dish that took half an hour to be served despite being a COLD dish but what is supposed to be salty and spicy noodles in a sesame paste was grossly sweet and soggy with random vegetables. Friends got the croquette and udon dishes that had undercooked rice and just a pile of raw cabbage as a "salad", stale kimchi and noodles with no flavour.
TLDR: DO NOT be fooled by the cheap deals because they are too good to be true and you can get much better food for a similar price. Service was mid at best, with food taking too long to be served but the food itself was disgusting.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPzVrAc1rEc5JYNxc7W5m9l-YXkA8S25-YuqHcQ&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-10-21"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Big portion size, pretty tasty and great customer service! The food came pretty fast given that this is deep fried food. I liked the unlimited salad and rice servings! I wish the sauce was bigger in portion size too to dip the katsu in. Overall, the price seems reasonable for the portion size and taste that you receive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOz5ZRWgqek5cZ591Gbo4WglK7khxYCB4szBSK&fid=0x0:0xbd8c32877b79d527"],"When":"2024-5-22"}]

[{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best places at UBC to hang out! Lovely staff and wonderful vibe. Tried the grilled chicken ramen and it was generously filled, almost couldn’t finish the whole meal. Other friends of mine ordered burgers and they said they were fantastic. Prices aren’t cheap, so it’s a place to go for a celebration once in a while.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCAcUJj4YsDoBohcTlkfqkVoKoS5nD30m0xhBk&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-12-22"},{"Name":"M J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKuOygw8Aep3D50DIY1TUyT5-BADbHqefvUMdU3qf0JomdEvw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great selection of food and craft beer, good place to hang out for a few drinks. The small nachos was enough for us to share between 4-5 people, loved the roast beef sandwich too. Deep fried Mac and cheese was nicely cooked and the tomato sauce helps with the heaviness of the Mac and cheese. Ordered the IPA and loved it - crisp and had a nice aroma. The service was fast and attentive although it was busy at the time of visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXcjzjGRoyy6vduMIRbCuk6WLqez6jCJo-pmrv&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-7-4"},{"Name":"Dylan Magierek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV0kVFJpnKEbseG6UEIeqqL4lraFc9x941pplBP3I-C35nxYYtP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This was a nice sojourn from a long day of driving and walking around the UBC campus moving my son into the dorms.  The food was very good: especially the fries, chicken sandwich, side salad and burgers.  The French Dip was just pretty good.  I wouldn’t recommend it.  It didn’t have enough meat to balance out the kinda hard roll it came on.  Lots of beer choices and I enjoyed the Pilsner.  Expensive for a brewery/sorta pub!  But good service and atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9A45j3pzrU9X5vPV34VvyOZ59GJCSIADcF_aQ&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Anthony Le","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIC22IEsZIbsu-lUm5EyMjgm7JYJbJkRjU13-W8XkZYXAuixkB6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Nice place for a sit-down, fancy-ish meal. The drinks were pretty good, and the food is delicious; definitely a nice place for a formal meal.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOE7MmrhhKXG2H5sjxLe8eW9H0WqnR-Tuz2xtla&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Vanessa Becker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjP-M2atXZC7s46eJ4wd5XC-RHr2pn3fRoPwoLQqghdxSrQBA9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Browns is a nice pub type spot. We got seated quickly for lunch and our server was friendly and attentive. Drinks and food came out at decent times.
My sister has celiacs disease and had heard Browns has gluten free options. They were able to make modifications on a meal and she enjoyed it, Blackened chicken Caesar with no croutons.
I got a cheeseburger with Caesar salad.
There’s a ramp and accessible entrance and chairs can be moved to fit wheelchairs.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgyStbHqW6IqBgmoutJLEDmIuxPuu1FMQBsNe6&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-5-19"},{"Name":"Maria N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvvSp5rMnSOuZlWMjCChnc3kIAvhaXhf7fzSVxvOmtGCdirlnS=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Tasty food and quick service. There were barely any customers when we came in on Saturday afternoon.
We got a chicken burger with a side of fries and a salad with a chicken breast (came a bit late.) Both tasted good.
Very decent place to grab a bite around UBC.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMh6lhWfsmLChgTOHHA4RM65-xzqYFv7EYhpgf5&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-6-23"},{"Name":"Biggie Sandhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJJXTSWG9GRBzr7s-0VIl70S37U8PyPayiekKKBiKbK7ygPFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Had our work Christmas Dinner here. Great workers great food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMIthBnLk1en1HwdUUDWZ3GIt9z3pNtalz6zAt&fid=0x0:0xefc97cb7df41fcd0"],"When":"2024-12-18"},{"Name":"Zibiah Sandhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIV7J0QaWpaOWLAzK9jqKBW9H-FOCY6ViMt-aqG3Okqi6IgVQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am following up from my previous review that I had left a few weeks ago. Despite having a negative experience, the staff at Browns Crafthouse went above and beyond to make sure that my friends and I had a good experience to make up for what had initially happened. The manager Matt reached out and was very kind and generous, and offered to make the experience better for us. They accommodated drinks and many appetizers for our large group, and were super sweet the entire time. I cannot remember our servers name, but she was a tall caucasian woman. She provided excellent service and took my friend's gluten allergy very seriously. It was some of the best customer experiences I had. Matt himself had come out and greeted us, apologized for the previous experience, and made sure we had a great time. They went above and beyond to make sure that we had a good experience, and it was really appreciated!","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Carlson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfSH3Mvx6Gquzf2h2Yz13MuXUcH81ASX8ObjzRJu92XMv3J9M3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really enjoy the decor and atmosphere of the place! The prices are not bad for a place in UBC and they have great specials on different days of the week. You can even get a can of hard iced tea for $3 on Wednesdays! The food was pretty good as well and service was quick. Definitely a cool hangout spots for students","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPyTwuCZccSL-7X42Ctxdh6oCHq4iBc2RWWDEgi&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-9-17"},{"Name":"Anson Leung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLpRG7sV65M0Vk9fJln2fqg-G8cTgdbnIHe6i_26HAHg5rk2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This was the second time coming here for the all you can eat pasta.  Unfortunately, the policies have changed and a beverage and gratuity is added, very fair, since I was told that some didn't tip, so the policy changed from this week. From this visit, the sauce amount has decreased, and the pasta has gone from al dente to harder, basically raw pasta.

The first plate of pasta was almost perfectly al dente but still slightly under what I preferred, and was still a treat to enjoy.  After the first plate, I had asked if the pasta could be made softer for the next.  They said that it would not be possible since the pasta is par-cooked.  However, for the next 2 plates, the pasta got harder and harder until I tasted flour and I decided to cut into one.  Well, it was raw inside (photo included).  At this point after 2.5 plates of hard pasta, I didn't feel like asking for it to be remade since they told me before that it wasn't possible.

Overall, the food experience was marginally unacceptable after the first plate. The service was good and the sports bar atmosphere was excellent.   I recommend the rigatoni alla vodka sauce for the all access pasta since it tastes the best, pesto the second.

After the complaint, I was told there had been a miscommunication that the pasta couldn't be cooked longer, and the drink cost was taken off as a result.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMb5h3FMgcqIKIxfIJ4PYZyyEEGjALlZXy1MfK1&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Simon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWq3mMD7x0QRiQPROCB5BEqtJbykKAfvm5IFcPhyVt8QiitDIxq=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I got introduced to this place by a foodie influencer  (Howie) and got to enjoy a lot of their food. This visit, however, was solo and only just on a Monday evening so it wasn't very busy inside. There is  outdoor patio seating which is was my preference.

I ordered the Steak Sandwich which came with EXCELLENTLY crisp fries and a small dipping sauce. If you ask for any kind of hot sauce, they will charge you $1.50 - SO BE CAREFUL! The Steak  Sandwich was *absolutely* delicious! The taste from the AAA medium-rare flat iron Steak with the  goat cheese and bbq sauce had such a really nice, umami flavour and mouth feel. It was just so delicious!

I also ordered a Nashville Chicken Sando. No pictures taken as the first bite literally made me devour it on the spot! Will definitely come back again to take a photo.

Overall, I had a great experience at Sports  Ilustrated Clubhouse. Nothing to say about their  interior or service.

Definitely recommend although I will say most items in the menu is quite expensive for the value. About 10-20% more expensive than what I consider reasonable price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZ_l_-O0YA_6zwiOUN1AOIRb233AEnDOfUPpUz&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Elaine S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXw0NZVlw-DYhg6yu3CwCqawu2sEc8yv_yDRJNRZHiHpXsjuXCx=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A couple of days ago I met with my BFF for a much-needed catch up. We started off at the UBC Botanical Gardens and then she suggested Sports Illustrated Clubhouse for lunch.

It was a quiet afternoon which made the atmosphere perfect for us for a wonderful visit, and the food was great. The best part was the incredible service by Emi! She was such a lovely person, so friendly, and she took such great care of us!

My friend and I shared the truffle fries (they were sooo good!) and house salad. And Emi recommended the perfect beer - my new favourite - Main Street Brewing Hula Hula Tropical Sour!

Thank you Emi - you made the visit with my bestie so special!! We will be back! XX","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMkqcVOmUrER6YSL3yQW180GcblcqGtJukGWVDB&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-6-10"},{"Name":"Nai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIReum1hobq8yy8xS95oLeLTMWqUAVsUqS3FQjvLQXW9PrM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I’ve been here twice during the day-time and the service was great both times, I came with two friends during the evening yesterday as it was their first time and we thought it would be a fun place to come to in our own neighbourhood; however, the service last night was not it! We left feeling uncomfortable. The server made it seem like we were a bother, she gave two of us the wrong bills granted we should have double checked but we couldn’t because we felt rushed… the Attempt of a pleasant interaction was only when we were paying our bills and we left feeling really bad at that service! Mind you, we left at around 8pm and the restaurant was not busy. She wasn’t welcoming at all from the start. We were still all smiles though. For my friends that came there for the first time, I don’t think they appreciated last nights service. It kinda sucks cause I was happy that they could finally come there. It takes one little experience like that to throw you off! I appreciate the server the times I’ve been there during the day though, she was great! Food is good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lou CB","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiUtEy3y60GPfgpVV5JSZrfFEBJi2Q16v4jzANAcFWH_TE0GBffw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We had the BLT sandwich which came with fries and a salad, and the sizzling brownie. The BLT was well seasoned with quality bacon, generous amounts of tomato and shredded lettuce and the fries were tasty and crispy. The brownie was served with a scoop of vanilla ice cream. Good solid food in a bright clean space — ambience very different from when it was a pub, and some will miss the vibe! Still, will be back to try other items on the menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNh087caXrJbS0HKIa3aQ2-peVfgUHsyIosCQ2v&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2023-12-9"},{"Name":"Mahsa Haghjoo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXRSnT0Wip7Pbg6Z8m0cglGHkWd61YfkTkUIlG6b0IkPWIUcJi2=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"If you are in the village you might wanna check out this place. Food was delicious, plenty of seats and you can even sit outside. Food was good","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5VsJRScu6NCdsyshKWhhH-ZIiDoIN1Y9DqH8-&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-9-26"},{"Name":"Eugene Ho","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvb9M5oHuuuLu9F3QxDe3Xu-5rsVsCB6BayNIPfvQOtlwnoIIv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is a great place to watch a game. They have a massive screen above the bar flanked by smaller ones next to it, then more around the corner. There are also several TVs throughout other areas so there are almost no bad tables

The food was pretty good for the most part. Other than the guacamole being a bit bland and not as creamy as I’d expect (maybe they did a chunky style on purpose?), we enjoyed everything else. My Nashville Chicken Sando was awesome (normally I don’t think much of coleslaw in a sandwich but it really worked with this one). The brussel sprouts with bacon was awesome as well. My friends enjoyed their burgers and Caesar salads while their regular fries were extra crispy and tasty (it’s got some seasoning on it and isn’t just plain salted).

The drinks menu was pretty big and there are a lot of beer options.

The server was friendly and attentive despite a packed house for the Canucks/Kings game.

We’ll definitely be back for more games and meals.

Sorry for the sad food photo; we were focusing on the game too much. 😃","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPmEGUSnxAI5BuksllsLzdLs3sDJ4ayGy7dA9vP&fid=0x0:0xfbcd82c95f6df084"],"When":"2024-3-1"}]

[{"Name":"Edward Morgan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWlCdKVa5JRpIwPRgKv6NNGwpeGpzREQZR8ZT02GyKWsnAcP6g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"One of the worst food experiences of my life.  Bought a hot dog, hamburger and fries to share. The buns on both the dog and burger were stale to the point where you could chip a tooth on them. The meat in the burger was rubbery and obviously warmed up. The fries tasted of old oil. If I could give this place zero stars I would.  On the bright side- great location and views.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcMUOMo7TrK7_-QUVgd2YACx1ndTq9p8kPhAxW&fid=0x0:0xc6fc08f9b003f1bc"],"When":"2023-9-6"},{"Name":"Wan Ming Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKwNlRFQz1VdbZPr8e_ll_ehCUEStZLojP_qGYBHGN6qBI3UA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I always like this occasional breaking of restrictions of diet

Fish and chips are Soo tempting. Freshly made. It a "must" to enjoy.

Then a big cookie, + ice cream cone, or ice cream sandwich.

Fresh air, blue sky, mountains, sea, yachts, kids..,

HEAVENLY God's creation. FREE..

Who needs to go to Switzerland.
(I had been there!!)
NO CONCESSION STAND BY swiss LAKES.

We had Europe, Hawaii  right here in our back yard..+ Fish & chips/hot dogs","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMh0iI6z9T3XP9qBejCw583rhjzRSLWqfR6ixKc&fid=0x0:0xc6fc08f9b003f1bc"],"When":"2018-6-22"},{"Name":"Affan A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJLrM1LQYBsViBSZx78fpcohHxqSb34Funvp0-nxL1Ij2zSzg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I regularly visit this place and bought a scoop of ice cream (vanilla) which gave me stomach pain. Would not recommend their ice cream. As I  eat ice cream on regular basis from other shop(s) and never have such stomach pain.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVzWpxN7dQOjyf925QLIP6KlWKBxzoQDIDMXvP1EyvoqxWwlrRd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"First the good news: This cafe is located at Locarno Beach Park, which includes a beautiful sandy beach and grassy area in Vancouver BC. The views are magnificent, with the giant cargo ships in the bay and the North Vancouver mountains. Unbelievable these days, parking is free, but the number of spaces  is limited and tend to fill up early in the day.
Second, the bad news: A number of typical fast foods are available, but I made the bad decision to try the fish and chips. While the serving was large, the fish tasted like old, burnt, cooking oil. While some like crispy batter, this one was well beyond crispy. You had to battle through it with firm stabs of the provided wooden fork. If the word ‘fish’ had not been on the menu I would not have known what that white stuff inside the batter was. Zero taste. A bland, underwhelming taste of nothing. The fries were just passable, by which I mean only arguably edible. Thank goodness there was an unlimited supply of ketchup, vinegar, mustard etc. Having attempted to eat the food, I can see the need for unlimited access to condiments!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Phil Davies","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUfLb1D8MDBOtzug8AzffJQIiix-nC5Bs7PigxNbqp4KdqwfuLj=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Fries were cold and expensive.  Burger mediocre.  $22 wasted.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ceesandmarta van de Mond","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxvBVCdLnGQ5HMJJQgHLAcc6vBglpsEgPD3miHSUHcfmJiae0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lovely walk with my daughter; drinking kambucha on tap with the cardboard straw!👍","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO6V1NLI1rYZ_yfZCmLNEpW-L-AZrl4HQ4AX0Qx&fid=0x0:0xc6fc08f9b003f1bc"],"When":"2018-7-4"},{"Name":"Anthony Young","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJjLBVGvYMuQ_7irAafqyFenF84IHbDebi7uNt8G5dE291E5g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Just got fries and they were made to order. Tasted good and crispy. $8 dollars for a pretty big portion.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeff Hawkins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVAov8WLNavn33_4xhnBVu7w-e_3RFW9j5OAYzTVU_hvO3ZRAdY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Decent food for a beach stand, though a bit pricey.
