[{"Name":"Noah Budz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX0Ewk2p4lJMjX0ya6ZuSed77GhQR6jmylO5a7E4Iur3n7agfRd=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food is very good especially the build your own bowl. It used to be very reasonably priced for the portions but they have suddenly raised their prices by a fair amount, raising the prices of all the bowls by about $5 making the small build your own bowl the same price as the previous large build your own bowl. This is now in the range of overpriced food and can no longer recommend eating at this place anymore","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Don K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUeMe3Z2Dwdjz2ebe9Hu9zPz3XZzwiZvAUP2ovxUEYWB0bHcVvHYw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":""Unique" Japanese Dining Experience: Bones and Bad Attitudes

Just had the most "memorable" visit to a supposedly authentic Japanese restaurant in town, and let me tell you, it was quite an experience! 🍣🙄

If you're a fan of eel, I suggest you bring your own toolkit for removing bones because this place apparently believes in quantity over quality. 🐟😣 I've never encountered so many bone spurs in a single dish before, talk about a challenge!

The icing on the cake was the lovely attitude of the staff, especially the charming individual I suspect to be the owner. 🙄👎 If you're looking for that authentic Japanese politeness and hospitality, well, you won't find it here. They seemed more interested in asserting their authority than making guests feel welcome.

So, if you're in the mood for a unique dining experience that defies traditional Japanese standards, this is the spot for you! Otherwise, I'd suggest looking elsewhere if you want genuine quality and respectful service. Save yourself the disappointment and bone-picking frustration. 🚫🍽️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNk3gNOOJ4m47LMTvIRz_vf85Wr33som8XgJzch&fid=0x0:0x21697c2ced69071"],"When":"2023-10-8"},{"Name":"Lizzie Hammond","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLl0YNeVEnImfaQfmG0d1UhPs7gS14GBRTsKOd1-_XmOq8j_Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I work in the area and this is my go to place! Always get great service, always super quick. Sometimes proportions can be small but very rarely. Everything is SUPER flavorful, and easy to customize to your liking. Vegan and meat eater approved 👍","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"w","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVECjtzjKwGGU2yagM5sH2sMNpUPFv0VdGQBZqvehtzvpFlyVDi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Unmatched taste. I don’t like seafood so I recommend the chicken bowls here. The regular size is a giant portion, enough for lunch and dinner.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPdup22gIaVmhS5EXBwEDlAJEkvGPk4Iq8VYCI5&fid=0x0:0x21697c2ced69071"],"When":"2022-12-6"},{"Name":"Melisa Cecilia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsOywiiZ3W02HXLLCk9cIHylVJNujFJOz6-eB_DU63tYHWSz6A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good size poke bowl with reasonable price. Fishes are fresh and toppings portions are generous. The spicy sauce can be a bit too overwhelming though so I would reccomend to ask for less spicy sauce if you’re not used to spicy stuffs.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOwd37WpxeNHYjSTg-QCcXYLk7BN0oUTUUsah3Y&fid=0x0:0x21697c2ced69071"],"When":"2022-5-7"},{"Name":"Karen Ethier","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXYFnUkD1a6nSefmBlBQ2ebi64_BA51EwgSszgjUvaZtmIMNauJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband & I had a short period of time to eat lunch and decided to eat @ Poke - very glad we did. Both small-size Ocean/multi-grain rice and Ocean/spring mix salad bowls were very tasty. Service was efficient & courteous. Would eat here again the next time we're on the UBC campus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2U0MEEECKpFSI6GmRGyOYdghYg2uo_m9VlKPm&fid=0x0:0x21697c2ced69071"],"When":"2023-6-21"},{"Name":"Kenny Mutesa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKirpv0oIjW8vZxtJcijjgcdREfh2xbpxQcsC6m81Ac063JcQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Current small sized bowls are more expensive than what used to be regular sized bowls in the last three weeks. Not a place I can recommend price wise anymore.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Igor Gasparic","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXrvB3WmGo3cbb-dFDdSII30Ljg-ztBJ-gorZD3VLeq_lgm1Os=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very delicious and big portion - build your own bowl 3+3: multi-grain rice, edamame, corn, kimchi, spicy tuna, spicy salmon, unagi, house poke sauce, house spicy mayo, japanese style mayo, sesame seeds, nori, fried onion, tempura bits.","Images":null,"When":""}]

I think they are under new management. Had the bibimbap, a fried chicken combo, and cheese balls. Bibimbap is a staple, and was good. The cheese balls are wrapped in mochi and deep fried. Just a hint of sweetness and very satisfying. The chicken is less crunchy than some other places, which I appreciate (sometimes the crunchy stuff ends up taking a layer of skin off the roof of my mouth), and it did not feel greasy. The ordering system is a bit glitchy, but it didn't affect us because we went when it wasn't busy, so they were able to clarify what we wanted.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Forrester","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKclUfheJ5Bxu-Y63dr7FmLPgRgWHLqFZJYBG3AoUFZJiW0tA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We went in for family dinner.  The restaurant is under new management since the beginning of September.   Tteokbokki and corn cheese were a match made in heaven.  Regular chicken was delicious and crispy, and yangnyeom chicken was just right for us. (not too spicy)  Each table were equipped with ordering tablet which were self explanatory.  Definitely will visit again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Maggie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdRAltSXABaU9WZtDiDFGAwgNoF-T5Zl3pbuS7IiXA5Fsl5bFw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Only leaving 5 stars beacuse 10 stars isn't an option. We were pleasantly surprised when several side dished were served with our meals. Prices are fair considering how much food you get. Everything on the menu looked amazing and we are so excited to go back and try more!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPRJ_Squw7YgeJoXdgOp-5lGtNC1QcYeieuJw0&fid=0x0:0x4f0ca7813ea9fd69"],"When":"2023-8-30"},{"Name":"Jay Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXSUVkLvYII57O53AFz5DNj0b1kwpOH4F5g62j_GIqPi4-TXYaz=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"BEST Korean chicken spot in UBC!!

I highly recommend here for any casual lunch or family dinner spot near UBC!
(Their Cheeseballs&French fries are a MUST to try)","Images":null,"When":""}]

So many memories with my family! 🩷","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steve Dahle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJFPev8ihygs0WckPR92s1u0MzQFYPkaysEy8kNp2PbyRjPpA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We stayed at the Turner Cut RV Park in our Class A motorhome for 4 months. Dan, the owner, was always very accommodating and attentive to our needs. Samantha, his managing front  desk assistant, was always there for us and helping us in any way we needed with a very friendly attitude. All of the staff were attentive and helpful and kind and were constantly busy keeping up with the grounds and trying to update the facility. The location worked out well for us as a temporary home while we searched for our forever home. We are thankful that Dan made room for us.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"George Homan Jr.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK6kDcGsGqy_VIDn9SEGKaS-xFtfa9b0YmiPCmXM43sRU9Kpw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dan, Sam, Al, Miguel, and the rest of the crew at Turner Cut were great. My wife and I spent 3 months there while on assignment for work. It had everything we needed, a place for our rig, extra parking for vehicles, and even places to play fetch with our dogs! The park is getting a face lift with privacy fences between sites as well as updated infrastructure (electric, water, and sewer). To my understanding, Dan took ownership fairly recently so I wouldn’t bother reading reviews from 3 years ago and beyond as they aren’t accurate. I would highly recommend this park to anyone in the area long term, short term, or extended stay.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"malcolm stacey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLZDhfBuuTDFZavgs1gDCIkk80bAOEOcfYxckFClk7CP-A2HA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"went to subway at 7 pm...saw they had one half a bun left...asked the server is it fresh or hard,and old? she lies says it was soft/fresh,go home, hard  as a rock,will never set foot is Ladner subway again..last time turkey sub.zero taste, gross eats.👎","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gmail Account","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXgOSW0GVAvIimmkvU2TtDxqu3AFV5bKX9oU2BhnasC6ow8tJo7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This Subway in my opinion is the best subway in B.C . I think i have eaten at 90% of the locations. Every time I come here the owner helps me and is always so nice and gives a very good quantity of meat and never charges for extras like
other places . I always order the Rotisserie chicken wrap in other subways they charge me 15 dollars here she only charges me 8 . As well the quality of the produce is always the best . I love this place ! If you're ever in the area I would recommend checking it out :) Thanks Nabina!!!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jags randhawa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLX-AHldw9zQLFjnZLL4JqBOK3MF5qf1P_boH399EO05g9-Dg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Selling half filled bowls, worst subway store.
The size of bowl is just make customers fool, one-two scoops of rice and countable veggies.

Avoid at any cost, if you value your money.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-9l6jweLNNa52Ip3ZrBee_EetHahwJrXt3PeW&fid=0x0:0x179dd4aa64cdf30e"],"When":"2024-4-4"},{"Name":"Micaela Robinson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV2QksgdiepfAQ10tl72lYcRqkt6l1FugMIhmMIfzOnP4rJ1IYySg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I find the subs well stacked and taste fresh!  To order a subway sandwich, it is usually pretty quick, except during lunch hours, they are always extreamly understaffed and the wait is far too long.   If it is not busy staff is never really in a rush to come up from thw back to help take your order.   I would say all in all its a great place to have a healthy, or unhealthy sandwich!! The prices seem pretty fair still in this day where everything is going up in price!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOoe76rIzjm5Vjbj_hGYpmUq_Kp6TDFUreLW_LN&fid=0x0:0x179dd4aa64cdf30e"],"When":"2018-5-5"},{"Name":"Mike Nakhleh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVc8KRZ0mQCfbliEyvy7dNkOfwJ1IRPU4g0yJEYP_8FfcXeKII=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Last week, I went to go buy a quick early dinner for the family.  I ordered all 3 subs for the 3 for 24.99 offer on the app.  However, when I went to go pay the person at the counter didnt know how to use the app and refused to honour the deal.  I agreed that I would just pay full price. Then he asked if I wanted a bag and charged me for it. I agreed...when my food came, he literally THREW the bag at me and made me pack my own food.

Service is very embarrassing, Why would he not put the food in the bag for me if I pay for it.

PS- They were out of MUSTARD!..what sandwhich place runs out of mustard...why not just go to the Freshco and buy some. Very poorly run.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jyoti Kaur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9Ce61xFkQ00TYXaqBikYf4vNVzq_TgoHq7JVN2qdIBTtQbXov=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's a great experience. The ambiance is very welcoming and charming. Had a great experience with Tanya, a staff member. She is extremely knowledgeable and makes great food recommendations. She is quite good at her job.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mandeep Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJHEsUVyKkxUzBaT5GEoU-jL739o1ZWTbDoEXroIJf0cY7GZw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"never posted any bad review for any store before . but really felt like today . the bread was not fresh. maybe day old. service was so slow . waited there for atleast 10 min even though no one was infront of me and sandwich makers were free. the guy made sandwich so slow . just didnt liked it . need to change a lot of things.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Arsalan Butt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_2-HNSghyy0yY5NOkgWP34erO6HC4Xgf4b_2Bt6xNufEK_QkU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I understand that every small business owner has to save money where ever they can. If you are going to hire minimum pay employees, can you at least spend some time training them in basic courtesy and more importantly teach them the Food Safe basics. You are in the food industry. Handling cash, cash register, printed paper and then going right back to making sandwiches without washing hands or putting on gloves!!! Have we not learned anything over the last 4 years about infection prevention? Will never ever return to this establishment. Anyone reading this review, next time you are at any Subway, please spend a couple of minutes observiing the person making the sandwiches before you place an order to ensure they are being careful with hand hygiene. I have started thanking them if they are doing it the right way.","Images":null,"When":""}]

Only thing I tried was the chocolate milkshake. Was disappointed with the size, price, and texture and the time it took to make it. Why does it take 15 minutes to make a milkshake when I am the only one there? If you are going to get one make sure to ask for it well blended or get a spoon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Esmed P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWPaVfVvhS7UlShhw7n3W_Eju3p15-TBYDAUGYnwKIb2zgwxN8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Went during my lunch hour & ordered. I wait, & after 25 minutes pass watching the person who took my order have a conversation with another staff in the kitchen, I get up & start to hover at the counter. I guess they noticed, because I saw only then, did they start cooking my order. There's no ketchup available, so I asked for some. The lady seemed confused, then insited they keep it behind the counter. Finally after waiting another 20 minutes, I'm given my burger with smallest amount of ketchup possible, after this lady had sassed me about literally, 3 drips of water which fell from my fountain drink after pouring myself water. I didn't bother to try to ask for more kerchup I wanted. Bottom line, do not go here, unless you want horrendously slow & rude service.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brian Taylor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVS9FnL1Xm2VSimjexdVbc5QM_VHkzVtM3eQen6wRNt-IyDFLYSYA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I'm not sure how this place stays in business. I used the Vera's app to order a burger and got confirmation of my order at 6:12 pm, but the burger wouldn't be ready until 6:45 pm (not that the restaurant was the slightest bit busy). I showed up at the restaurant at 6:35 and the staff weren't aware of my order and asked what app I used. Really? Once the order was located they proceeded to make the burger and it was ready by 6:50. I had ordered a Vera burger ($10.50) with a few free toppings, cheese ($2 extra) and bacon ($2.50 extra). When I sat down to eat the burger I thought they'd forgotten the bacon so I brought it up to the counter. It was pointed out to me that there was a piece of bacon on the burger, but at most it was one square inch! For $2.50? The burger tasted fine and I've enjoyed Vera burgers for a long time, but if there were a Five Guys anywhere on the West Side I would never go back to Veras.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tano Pham","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLZTH6gNWlc-cb4ja-Rt0oeskyJW7A4uEUVtm6QYAF2hoCk8A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolutely terrible service on a non-school day at the UBC campus location by this employee. Had ordered my burger 35 minutes ahead on the app and she did not accept the order until I physically got there.
What is the point of skip the line function of the app if takes your money and not process your order","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOuESOGkrJ4ca-F7MGAy2wyT8MDyLvBk6Wdks6G&fid=0x0:0xfba7b2899b4f414c"],"When":"2019-2-23"}]

I love getting their rice burgers ($7)! They’re so filling and delicious! The dumplings ($7-8)are quite big and decent too. Highly recommend. And the service is very fast too. The lady (I’m guessing owner) is super sweet and nice! This has become my to go food place :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJtnYd6yS-h-3XGUnWH15MFjWbtolyyiBi0gUG\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"Yesong Park","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZ91KZByxRVp7hNBb-aKt5xKC5uCcHWJErPks1BHnBM5NsPqdN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Easy to order, super quick pickup, and the Vegetarian Kimchi hotdog was good (I am from South Korea 🤣👍). The staff were kind💚 Looking forward to coming back. Thank you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNRlR3UB5562u53xdhKrOsGJiz4rkZrE-p0ZaKU\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2024-10-2"},{"Name":"Monique Williams","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV5hu9g1OY7Ix0dBixz7zsHrRgMIwTKO5A1wsJR8uSbYtgX4VMh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the best and unique hot dogs I’ve ever had! Got the vegetarian kimchi with marble cheese… and the Seoul chicken dog… SO DELICIOUS!! And the service was great, she was really nice and helped me choose the best options :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxGps2TpWl4ZaIo9igfjKn_o84hHy6SiiGWHBt\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2024-8-14"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Lots of cool choices for hotdogs and very vegetarian-friendly since you can get a veggie sausage with any of the dogs on the menu (not as vegan-friendly since most options include mayo and/or cheese). The guy who works there is super nice. There are also Korean subs and other snacks, and bingsu. They use a good veggie sausage and the toppings are always fresh. The hot dogs and snack foods are very reasonably priced, the bingsu are more splurge-y, but they are pretty big. The shop is very small, but the buzzer system they have works well, so you can wait for your order outside and get a buzz to pick it up.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQM6Ga7Xs7_kR11FSzwpQzsjueEtvJo9hL6iqh\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2023-8-12"},{"Name":"J Psk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJysbWTRrHYTp8s-srkk4zt31Bl_q_WrtM2a-GsVp2w2ODMSw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Don't order the chi-bap (fried chicken rice) whatsoever. What I got was comletely different from the photo on the menu. The chicken is not fried chicken at all, they use oven baked chicken nuggets. The corn salad had like 3 grains of corn. NOT worth 15$ at all...","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO7aidT799VL6AA3Zdo-Tt2GjLqBpKF4IutJdaK\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"NixOil","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWa0-gf5561LR0YaDvsEO2rH9HzBIiXnz8EIWyrMmynW44HE3yV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best hotdog I have ever had in my entire life. This place was super fast and the hotdog was just amazing. I got the pizza dog which sounds weird but was so good that I had to review this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPV_LPo5uQklvQIOPMQmDjk9t5JYYTmqDNQoyQC\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2023-12-30"},{"Name":"K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK8Kffru-eJ-MFdAxDjN_kWwnt7cEHBHmGbUwwPuMFBkRwEcGM5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best hot dog place we’ve ever been to! The hotdogs were juicy, tasted fresh, and all of the toppings went so well together. We ordered 2 kimchi hotdogs ($9 each) and 2 seoul hotdogs ($10 each). Not going into lie, we had some difficulty finding this place but we would definitely come here again.  there’s not really a place you can sit and eat because it’s just a bench right outside the place, and you’re likely going to be harassed by birds so be cautious when you’re eating lol. The food took a bit of time (15 to 20 minutes maybe?) to make but we weren’t in a rush and there was only 1 guy making all the hotdogs fresh in front of us. Highly recommend this place if you’re at UBC!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOyyvUswrdO-Ws48fgWp7Nkh-O9hEzBay1CETlT\u0026fid=0x0:0xe4456a08a1c33572"],"When":"2023-11-13"},{"Name":"Marvin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIOUB9fqPRyAnJAGsLqhyOV_Bp81x_bJC8wIyyATYNP2vGJzmc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Small little shop with amazing customer service. Guy at the front was very welcoming and nice. Hot dog was pretty good, a little expensive for what it was but still great. Definitely will be back to try some other stuff.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Reliable for simple and satisfying homestyle Korean food. Nothing blows me away but everything is good and flavourful. The meals all include lots of vegetables which I appreciate, and things aren't overly oily.
There's no atmosphere to speak of and I think they probably have more takeout than dine-in customers, but having done both, dine-in is the way to go, because the food comes out super fresh. The people who work there are nice and hardworking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNXR2zL3EAW7SvQOTWGiznVuK83Eyw_nBeqY_6G&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2024-2-25"},{"Name":"Yuchang Zhan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJCu1wqeMUBpitsBVSAyQ29MPKUdyLQ__YQ2QBJ3AHY3DJY3g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went several times and recommended to all my friends. The owners are truly caring about the customers and always have THE BEST service ever. Once I mentioned I was cold, and later the owner offered me warm miso soup for free. This really made my entire evening.

Soups are always served warm with large portion. The pork bone is absolutely my to-go dish. So flavourful with so so much meat!

Never disappointed with their inari, I have tried beef, spicy salmon, shrimp, spam, tuna, kimchi, seaweed, some were even gifted by the owner. All the toppings are so delicious and flavourful, it’s hard for me to pick one favourite to be honest! The seasoning of rice makes everything even another level.

Foods are so authentic. My Korean friends said the dishes really brought them back to Korea. If you love Korean foods like me, you should definitely try it out!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNM3_rcDUbPQB4N10byn-i2gBKLWgdvTB41RrFy&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2022-3-10"},{"Name":"Sasha Sadiora","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqMB9CioB05yUeMJrchJN57cOo1BuZF_w3T8u4DS8Px3X91XTp=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The lady was very nice but the fact I paid a EXTRA $3.50 for cheese and got a KRAFT SINGLES slice is CRAZY","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLwLofol73ghxQyaPInWLd2gYRGqz6pWOzjLKe&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2024-9-12"},{"Name":"Niloufar Sharif","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3A88lqgzyr_DZVby4DylCumivfYhcpesHqnFk78Ei2iZVsggWWg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As a student, this place is so comforting and the food tastes authentic and homemade. The owners here are AMAZING, so caring, and kindhearted! They gifted us three free inaris to try as well as miso soup! Now the food. The portions are so generous and they will not cheap out on quality or amount of protein despite the affordable prices.
We got the gamja-tang and galbitang. The galbitang has a very clean broth and you can taste the fresh ingredients. Gamja-tang was packed with flavors and spices and soooo much pork!

Cant wait to go back and try all of their other dishes 😋","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMNkVy2Nj_O8RT1_bytgunpwMTz22R8HjUrX_Hu&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2022-3-6"},{"Name":"Ahnaf Muqset Haque","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9JdQZtXBMvD618JDWqRmaMkXk-I2NhqdPuW2NLQFP33Qn87KikQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The only reason for my four star is their  customer service is heart warming. Really welcoming and good service. However, if you are actually looking for really really good Korean food then this probably isn't the place. It's okay as I would describe it but definitely not the best. Also, quantity is not adequate. However, trying to improve quantity first would be resonable step towards improvement!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPATOMJVNA_QXKyqiMpX11OXghmAXYiZDhRB6OR&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2019-4-19"},{"Name":"Anne W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVq8l7IxqCBT6CUTt6a8ydNheNQQYDJZKBxOYNsNiNzdtSpTCtW=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The quality of the food here is excellent! I got the Jjajang Beef Udon today and it's now one of my favourite meals on campus. The sauce is delicious, as is the side of pickled daikon. The sauce is generous, so I might be able to get a side of rice and stretch it to two lunches (helpful with the high cost of living these days!).

Staff are lovely and helpful people. The outdoor seats on a good weather day are in the sun, so it's a great spot to enjoy your lunch. So glad this place is here!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP2GSZ-Y2SmizoNXA-E9OpCto2VOEvGfTSaozkJ&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2023-3-21"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I ordered Inari, it’s ok. The meat or topping to rice proportion was a bit off. There’s more rice than topping. I ordered 3 but it’s not enough, and it came out to be around 14$ so I’ll say just order a regular meal instead of this as it’s not that filling. The service was pretty good tho and the atmosphere was nice and cozy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOanBKptQ-R_H5eiyx4s67HHQU7ukggwSAkZ7tv&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2023-10-2"},{"Name":"cbl Google","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKseLK4QE-uFmbW8_hEmTOkS9RGzjwTJs3q9tyPwtQSc-dy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great Korean foods and such an awesome owner! Definitely a gem in the village area. Tried a few of their new inaris and was not disappointed. The spicy salmon and bulgigi are highly recommended!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMixXDyBd0gN0Cf58omWSw-4LIfMRQAXe33CFI&fid=0x0:0x4ab7ff7074636253"],"When":"2021-10-11"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"James","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXqV7s1ERcFGfwshWd43fVj2drCe4Q_9Q7yrW7t1yUcOV4l1RPe-Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Classic American-style family-run diner serving hearty portions. I cannot stress how delicious their home-style potatoes are. They are thin slices similar to hash browns and cooked well.

While their menu doesn't have any food items that are exceptionally unique, you cannot go wrong with any of the choices.

The servers are nice and more than accommodating. Since there is no jam on the table for the toast, they'll happily provide that upon request.

On weekend brunch time, there is usually a wait, but they have plenty of indoor and outdoor dining seating in a rustic, open-air environment","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMyIqzVx3IpllwN0NYjD2vUnR7CIcaS_Rr9pzJQ&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Sunaina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhxDKiFQe8a5C5Tb2aKE23SI0Kdk4IWaJpX4r1npsWHQupcLu6Fw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cute little brunch spot with both indoor and outdoor seating. Prompt service & friendly servers. We started with lattes, and got the smoked chicken chorizo scrambled eggs which came with potatoes and cornbread & the pancake combo with chicken apple sausage. My favorite was the pancake dish, I loved it! I’m a bit picky about how eggs are cooked in general so it’s hard for me to find the perfect egg dishes and they usually end up feeling mediocre. I’d love to try a different dish next time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMoaz6Rnm3N-dY6FYKx-rnbHA_6iaS4gM8J5Dmp&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2024-3-22"},{"Name":"Cedrik Laplante","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX1fiDdQR57hkQayUOrLLKYe8hRwMHRj-f-yp8FEv14uvHM2DY_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food was divine especially the cinnamon butter for those fluffy pancakes! Eggs Benedict was good too. The stuffed French toast though! You really can’t go wrong but it is a little pricey","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMff6FXvb3YAW-_H7khRSdB1hlvVuL9LSUYiLp&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2023-9-20"},{"Name":"Arthur Glauberman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUF_clVoSZmScPHXT5Ms-BUb8Jmo72X-xWBoI2U0vBLB_o86Ax6=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We just  discovered the Doyle Street Cafe which has a very exotic breakfast & lunch menu! While they are only open til 2pm, I’m told that on the weekends, there are lines outside, waiting for a table!  We had the most delicious breakfast., their DELMAR CREPE: crab cakes, caramelized onions, mushrooms, jack cheese inside a large crepe, served with best best home fries i’ve ever tasted!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNIuvHeXFBk2pELCG999j6ocLAx-qJgjFeUYGS9&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2024-2-20"},{"Name":"Elijah H.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUhuMCL5qE_XwEF9xoarhFX8pVzbLM9hf5AbaEeTk94dnpjTm1bkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been going here for years now, and it never gets old. This is one of those true 5/5 restaurants for me. The brunch here is PHENOMENAL, I've never had a complaint about the food here, and it always comes out quick, hot, and full of flavor. I highly recommend the Egg Benedicts (pulled pork and salmon), French Toast, and my recent favorite, the buttermilk pancakes (so fluffy and perfectly made). The potatos are always crispy and well seasoned, and my gf absolutely loves the bacon (with 0 regard to my bank account). The inside seating is nice but we usually sit outside when the sun is out. I love introducing people to this location it's one of my absolute favorites. Stop reading this review and just GO! (Food is a tinnyyy bit pricy but it's so worth it for the flavor/portion/service/ etc.)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOolZVK2EJo6AXEdOQSEScqlyZr2ASboK6fy7mb&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2023-6-24"},{"Name":"BG M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ8ECc16Mqcli5HD65XbZIbBjpKfCFjUv72aQZNNL0AmxPyYw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this place. The food looked and tasted delicious. Server was friendly and the food came pretty quickly. Had the stuffed French toast, breakfast potatoes, scrambled eggs, bacon, but we got there too late and they were out of the cornbread. Must be delicious too. Relaxing ambiance, perfect brunch spot. Five stars.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOcxDrDM-lC8bRSqgiZLRlbCN0xr_l0sz5EnAPI&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2021-6-26"},{"Name":"Mal Pinlac","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL4GxsuuBPotT1R6zutCydr7dJUoU9VskrlylQ9SY1q7Oc7QQe4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my fave brunch place in Emeryville. The food always comes out  fresh and hot, coffee tastes great, the vibe is perfect and they have free parking. You'll want to get in before 11:30am otherwise the lunch crowd starts pouring in. Regardless of how busy the place gets, it seems they are able to keep up with the pace and get you seated, get your order and turn it around in under 10 minutes. There does not seem to be a bad choice on the menu and you usually have a choice between inside or patio seating 👍👍.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMct-elkow2r1AGaEdXHNJIOr9EQvlzaMIdz1GK&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2023-11-30"},{"Name":"Travis Hull","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUKxQxZ2Fw0iXg479yIzmfs1rvM-h6CiHCTG8-FuzNmS2uW6kb0NA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow, great American diner experience! Never ending cups of black coffee, giant portions, friendly service. The Homefries Heaven was more food than I could possibly eat, and of course I ate most of it. My girlfriend got the combo breakfast with French toast, bacon and eggs over easy. Super delicious as well, the cinnamon butter spread is really good. The atmosphere is busy but relaxed with the chatter of busy brunch goers in the background. 10/10 would recommend if you’re in the neighborhood. Thanks!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPgbDzpEacfxQrryeeFvQPKRZn95SEiDcJwj6Oz&fid=0x0:0x4cb6776373016f4d"],"When":"2023-10-14"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ayla Panini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLiwtVIpBtKGTSIlPRlXWoQjHmNImwpsGr8ajO3tXx2uHueUqE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"W deal, W service, W food. I came to use my $5 off birthday voucher and I got a mini byob for just under $10! Service was excellent and very fast, and the portion was perfect and filling. The poke scoop recommended by the guy serving me, spicy tuna, was as delicious as he said! Would definitely go again :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN5edVch4DjYxWTXzuzRzQtc_Tmid0kZNIxkrLH&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Selina Zhou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdh_K07G_35WE1XQolPePKtbRPCS7etPd4GO37eQJrOR8PInDd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The place is packed during lunches, but everyone is still quite attentive if you ordered pick-up. The portions are quite generous, and even the mini bowl is enough to make sure you’re not hungry.

The salmon is my go-to pick, the shoyu is a must hahaha.

There is not much seating near the place itself, so definitely just sit on some bench if it’s not raining.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOUL3NqhZUds1uCJFHjqiEfzEWo0vnCvKMwPjhe&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-10-20"},{"Name":"Nicole Villalon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvX-NXEAvIz9hfeDmCLJbpqDwAUM7ozgrgH4vZTSomKf59ULGv=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"STEVE’S POKE DOES IT AGAIN!!!
I’ve eaten here 4 times so far and every single time the service has been phenomenal. Today’s experience, however, absolutely takes the cake.

I ordered a mini BYOB with one scoop of poke online, coming up to ~$15 after tax and tips. The people at checkout were very attentive and made sure to check in and let me know my order was being prepared, and would be ready in a couple minutes. And then, the girl preparing my poke misread my order… and accidentally made me a large instead of a mini BYOB!!! She apologized multiple times, but how could I complain? More poke! And when I let it slip my birthday had been a week ago, the staff offered to throw in an iced tea, free of charge!

The poke was delicious, the service was stellar, and staff’s kindness absolutely made my day. I’ll be happy to visit Steve’s Poke again very soon!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOmSF-4CMT-TmWd3-H-5XYvs2169hWwMLVwRpNj&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-11-22"},{"Name":"Tresa Horney","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlCxWd5ESmqb9bOtTVn1nxYHpHQadHnSQ3MsNKRjtwrjVvD0jPDQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Easy to order, friendly service, and a great meal. Pleased to have a vegetarian option. I’ll return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPy2Vjy3vWoV_UVTxuZk8COaNosX0DfibJOIhOD&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Ben K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkChymkBEqoHC-DSLY-BlpEm3X8tgGaeAvEy7G17xjM-zfjw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"$20 for this poke bowl, comes with 4 different choices of fish/poke, and any number of free “toppings”. The rice is “regular” white rice, not really flavored with mirin or anything. The fish come with sauce, but I should have asked for extra sauce on it because it had either dried up a bit or soaked into the rice. Considering the other choices around UBC, this is probably pretty good value for money.

I ordered takeout, but they have a few seats inside and outside if you prefer. The street currently has a bunch of (summer) construction, though.

They frequently have promo discounts on their site, but if you order on their online platform, there’s a mandatory $0.25 bag fee.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMG5oLw7BBFbNinAOxoTystwMC33r4z7vTCasRg&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-7-30"},{"Name":"Hari haran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIiG04_8rXv0XFEGQSVtxLwFR51JdEUoQ099gTHIIYGUB0FAw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Edit: just picked up a poke bowl and it seems the folks at the store have overdone it with soy sauce (???) this is not good. See picture attached

People are less responsive for pickup orders. Not sure why.

But mostly, Some of the best poke you can eat in Vancouver.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5Fa39-wPyW-gxFrFm-dQJx5a5nADo4V_MO6ES&fid=0x0:0x408ff42ba8c24b07"],"When":"2024-9-20"},{"Name":"Vitalie Veclici","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVn8kycEuyvgu8wcx5Mpwijp97INeeCs7xxytZNIaEQ_HzZHS2yeg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Steve’s Poke Bar delivers delicious, fresh poke bowls with a variety of high-quality ingredients and customizable options. The staff is friendly and attentive, ensuring a pleasant experience from start to finish. While the food is top-notch, the interior could benefit from some updates to enhance the overall dining atmosphere. With a bit more attention to the ambiance, Steve’s has the potential to become one of the top poke spots in Vancouver. Still, a fantastic choice for poke enthusiasts looking for great service and tasty bowls.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Erika W","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXk-zmliLlm5bIplSxpmOCgffchZEiqu1WLJ9rhI9Bc-N96TAwesQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food quality is fantastic and the portions are extremely satisfying. The staff were super friendly and patient as I chose my ingredients for my bowl. Not from Vancouver but when I do come back, I’m going to be sure to revisit this place because it is a stand out even among the fancy dine in places I went to. Thank you so much and until next time all the best.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Bruno Rodrigues","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXhILuyIb0LIP6MudwbcSE2BAlE-f9U9SKRT2p9lsRwJ4hM0FgDLg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved my experience at the Gallery. Ordered burgers with salads and my friends also ordered some chicken wraps and fries. Everything was pretty tasty and well seasoned. Beers were fantastic. Prices a little bit on the high side, especially for a restaurant inside campus, but it’s definitely worth trying.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOs1KGPNL5W9iWl4zIgcxQSrnJ2fRONlu24N4UE&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2024-12-20"},{"Name":"Anthony Le","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWIC22IEsZIbsu-lUm5EyMjgm7JYJbJkRjU13-W8XkZYXAuixkB6Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pretty good place for a nice meal for ubc students. There wasn’t necessarily any service, but nonetheless the food was pretty good. Definitely would go here for a drink it I was a ubc student","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9K99fN-Zftq2MUemombIFm2bz26P8kglKa8XA&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2024-10-22"},{"Name":"Randal Chin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-rLwNvZI_YNkKUeSaM-3PNFSDfyyf9aevvVnQDsEtEwj3jDdP=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The dining room is spacious and has lots of natural light making it a good spot for lunch. During lunchtime there was no loud music playing so I could have a conversation with a friend. You order food and drinks at the bar, but I got both pretty quickly. I had a red sangria which seemed reasonably good. I had a citrus and beet salad which was also good but not very filling if you're expecting it to be a meal. The service from the staff serving the food and clearing the table seemed reasonably good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I like this place. I wouldn't go here as a night out, but at the right times, it's a chill hang. The atmosphere varies wildly depending on the day. On some nights it's louder and is in line with what you'd expect a university bar to be like, and sometimes it's very relaxed, and you can even find some people using it as a study spot (not something I would consider or really recommend, but you do you as long as it's not busy and no one needs the table). Sometimes it's somewhere in between or a weird mix of both. It's not always predictable, but I've found that to hit the quieter days that I prefer, early evening during exam season at school is best, and summer in general are chiller than the main academic year.
The food is good, often surprisingly good. The menu items are well thought-out and tasty, and nicely presented. It's not a veg-centric establishment but there's lots of choice for vegans! Off the current menu, I've had the Power Punch Salad, the Vegan Pulled Jackfruit, the Vegan Burger, Vegan Chick'n Caesar Wrap, and the Tempeh Teriyaki. I wasn't particularly impressed by the Caesar wrap - it wasn't awful, I just didn't feel like it was worth $19.5, but everything else was a delight. I'm glad their vegan burger is a (seemingly) housemade, minimally processed black bean patty instead of beyond meat or similar! I usually won't order a salad as my meal, but the Power Punch is substantial! The side salad that comes with the sandwich orders is actually pretty nice too.
They make good cocktails and have a long list of local draft beers on tap which I haven't really had a chance to dip into, but I got the "Green Bird" for fun on St. Patrick's Day, which is just a version of their house "T-Bird" lager that's been coloured green (maybe naturally, judging by the grassy notes I got from it, but I don't know for sure). It was actually a good lager though!
Sometimes the staff is nice enough, sometimes I get the vibe that they're too cool to be serving me or something, but because the only interactions you have with them are when you order and pay at the bar and when they bring your food out, an unenthusiastic bartender doesn't ruin the whole experience. Because of this service style, you can expect to be in and out of here faster than you would at a full table service restaurant, but it's not fast food, so dishes still take as much time to prep as they would at a "regular" sit-down place. It's also pricier than typical counter service food, but very reasonably priced compared to off-campus restaurants that serve food of this quality, and there's no obligation to tip 20%. To me, the service model, fair prices, and high quality are a combination of the best elements of counter service and full service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOQwEdJ88aXsSlarpRs-9jcRwBTBo0B-hIa3KfE&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2021-4-19"},{"Name":"Steve Morgan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXmgrmzSyB3CC_qWamR3pXmaZna6-RxfqDluiFzTGNrypDReGc=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very large service area. Games. Foosball table. Big patio. Not the least bit crowded for lunch in summertime. They have a limited menu but it has decent variety. Quality of the food is good for a university joint. Beer list contains a good number of local, craft beers. Kids can dine here but no kids menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPovaBoxIJBbbrqqo0D1-7ZOWCRu2vS1WYswiw&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2019-7-10"},{"Name":"N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIY4v8Faubu_Z2iYv4KPw3dI0PsoX4C2vKMs2dyC6KeQw7f0Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Almost no service (walk up to bar to order) and any service you do get is most often unfriendly. Like the type of attitude you would think takes more effort than being nice. They are not making a case for autogratuities in general because I think this is one of the reasons this place gets away with such unpleasant staff. The other reasons include that there just isn't that much choice on campus and the food is basic but decent here. The view is nice if you're out on the patio. And there's a lot of space. It's very sad that the sit-down nice restaurant didn't make it because that's exactly what the area needs. They just didn't promote it and since this is the top floor, no one discovers this space by walking by. The service at the Gallery when it was in the old sub was never this sad. Have pride in whatever you do. Just making people happy and not disappointed is a reward in itself. Or fake it. Whatever. Just don't make people more down than when they came in.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jade","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyJzoLeWrDhvC2NhSPJXZCJklxu-S39z3hI0-Hrrv9m9AA5ZkKQQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This is my first review below 5 stars.
They automatically charge a tip without telling their customers (I didn't notice any signage). This makes their prices misleading. Also, since I wasn't with a group and I ordered at the register auto-grat does not seem reasonable. I will happily change my review and return as a customer when they are more forthcoming about their prices.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Haleh Magnus","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUZGl2rvHWlqbzuuFKZ9pHQfQXwlTmRHH4ep4A1K4mjlsDM4dQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went there for a light food, beer and to listen to good #jazzmusic from amazing musician of UBC Jazz Club. The space was bright , spacious. I found it busy and big line up. The Jazz performance are on Wednesday 6pm to 9pm by UBC Jazz Club.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPIUZZN56p20ZRBTeW6npihhigzi31LzbVDTis&fid=0x0:0x7b84d3debc8f1cec"],"When":"2022-9-22"}]

[{"Name":"Jake Reed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3nqN-yftZBcYGBAQP-DgvnBcslLOeqJKxxvR9cAwQoa_pcA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Live music, outdoor seating, great food. Especially enjoyed their patty melt. Also a good selection of beer and wine. Prices won't break the bank either.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOnJCu5trrHkd59fZBD-eV4_TXqBQ5Zywh3Rp9D&fid=0x0:0x2f4e5d641305b588"],"When":"2019-9-16"},{"Name":"Wez So_N_So","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVF_eoubty8_D2JF47qVDrhSP0XGP4vXQRskvA7VFG2AO_k92KC-A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We stopped in for some dinner and it was $3 burger 🍔 night and $1 sides. It was very basic but at the price point I was pretty happy.

The rest of the menu is hit or miss. One major hit is the garlic wings so make sure to try them.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPL3ryya9tM0hRFCFmNBp52QGKK4dW9Z1md4zX-&fid=0x0:0x2f4e5d641305b588"],"When":"2017-6-18"},{"Name":"freshroasted coffee (Ron Pargett)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVwHk2-bFIoKzpXGBRb6W46626ETiJ9wvrFwokLAO5pUSKNSfs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely love the setting there, the spot in the delta where they are located is heavenly. The structure is a little distressed on the outside, so the curb appeal may be less than you expect. The service and the food were surprisingly rich. Thank you staff for the wonderful visit!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOqFS7BKDlTW-ZzW4hhGIt3uxEQDkOM5uxqOLRr&fid=0x0:0x2f4e5d641305b588"],"When":"2021-8-17"}]

The well drinks were $5 which for me, was a steal! It gets very busy here. I think the had 30 singers this past week. The sound is good, the food is good, the view, outstanding!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8ZvvCSSaqUFY2mptmfrASOpY6BiD6Z4VanI8j\u0026fid=0x0:0x7f6966c89b5e618b"],"When":"2021-5-26"},{"Name":"Colleen B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8hPfPoHrS4kiowyQLO-rHlLrLe71Q_xgCOd26Rko7tDTBTIGX9A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"What a great way to spend one of the last dines out of the year. Fun ambiance, on the water and Beatles memorabilia everywhere. All of the food was AMAZING! We shared the fried pickle spears, which were a blazing hot temperature with salty-greasy decadence. I had the veggie wrap and it was fresh and hearty--completely satisfying. The drinks were very well priced too. But the best deal of all was the no charge 2-person table top video games! Worth the drive if you are looking for a nice day trip away from the Bay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBw3CZQ7UKTGWz-PS4yitpJzxq5pRGLhzA6BjW\u0026fid=0x0:0x7f6966c89b5e618b"],"When":"2018-1-28"},{"Name":"Genesis Nambo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKizUaJvSQvAhvvIk3Sr1EZYE6fRIrnl2q_-qFL4SYsG1mmMfo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My boyfriend decided to take me here for a fancy date. Honestly, we liked the food here the first time we came so much that we had to come again. I had the salmon dish which was delicious and my boyfriend had steak. It is expensive so if you don’t mind paying over $200 for a meal and drinks check this place out.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sue Chambers","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJAii8P24Tfx08cUXMApiiIn7G4aG8bZEMX-401eUtXZutWKA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fun place to watch the boats. Family style dining with an Italian heritage, includes a flavorful cabernet at lunch, minestrone, crusty bread, & salad with entrees.  Rustic, old, historic fisherman & hunters find that's still fun to unwind in.  Cabin style comfort, good food, great staff.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsPWT9Jo6ZSlA-ApTDpBggw6ultwkElpK9KhOR&fid=0x0:0x26a11bd7a5410b8b"],"When":"2021-4-22"},{"Name":"bartellj","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS12R4HB4dbbMLfkKugvyUv4bKdD_kFbVV88JmrY8b_kWBMMM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A gem on the Sacramento delta. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Jeffrey Cheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuvw0DoMq0pOe2JGvzQ4U1FjBGerEQ4O70pk3YVGChUNSu7g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Update: I sent an email 2 months ago after the owner's review and have NOT received a reply at all. They have not done anything nor kept their promise. Totally soured by the customer service and have adjusted that to 1 star. Absolutely frustrated to see that happening and will never go back to the restaurant again.

The pasta was okay, nothing special and the pizza was awful, so watery","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAiQ5ZLOeaIrS5F737cTKWhpPO1WHu_H6eZ73O&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2024-8-9"},{"Name":"Wii Games","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1LF1yLZYvfPxybsCpHOF5AtzGVIeAoFgQLne7csT7MMJt7gY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Considering their pizzas are priced at a premium (average of 25 dollars,) you would expect their pizzas to be of higher quality. The toppings taste fresh, but the pizzas are extremely runny and the dough is very chewy even for Neapolitan style pizza. The crust lacks the air and lightness of other places. I also noticed that they don't use any wood in their oven, which just doesn't achieve the same flavor profile.

In terms of the service, i have come to this place a few times and seen the waiters talking and not noticing myself or other guests that come in at times.

The atmosphere overall is not bad, but personally i feel as though the place has an industrial feeling and is not the most welcoming .","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Brad Snelling","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVEo3ECglbJcC95bDjcm377gDXh3jMd9KEP9ANqJRBVc9D4SrM=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Thank you Maddie for the great service and the birthday cake…and thanks to chefs Shaq and Yuriko for the tasty food (the Il Bastardo and Salami e Funghi pizzas and the pasta cream pasta were amazing!).  I will be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNB5_ERDFOPMNUkHdMilCQ_UHzkC088WqZp8ggb&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2024-8-13"},{"Name":"Eve C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3TRd28YHMD0xZgG9Qff6WuaVQUBD8KHHFSJUDtDhJtE0o6w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was really excited to hear that Nicli has reopened in Wesbrook. I used to go to the gastown location all the time and was sad when they closed. I heard they are under new ownership, so we were weren’t sure what to expect. Luckily, it was still just as delicious as I remember 😋

We came for lunch and ordered four pizzas to share amongst 6 people. It was the perfect amount of food and we left very satisfied. They also have a lunch menu with slightly smaller pizzas and pasta options. The pizzas were full of quality ingredients and incredibly delicious. Our server was so friendly and made sure we were well taken care of. Will be coming back more often 🩷","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alysia Duemler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVOP2WaoVuXuPDA2rQrEDkqLAVmEa-LLcH53nj472C_ni_q4VtISQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Such a charming neighbourhood Italian restaurant with many gluten-free and vegetarian options, thankfully. It was the best pizza I’ve had in Vancouver, the cocktails were refreshing, the server was friendly, funny and attentive, and the atmosphere was pleasant. Had a nice little date there and would recommend. It’s nice to be able to sit outside, too. The prices are also fair.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcjHM66qrYK1NntlYCYUZ5aePNW-D9gzlCt-Gq&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2023-8-25"},{"Name":"Michael Moriarity","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNhkYaB9zjlkkl74OBPcplO2QslT6bqh419yvto-fc4bLKxsqAKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This local pizza location in UBC Westbrook Mall invites the pizza and Italian food scene customer for a fine tasting menu..we chose the Salimi & Fungi pizza and the Bolognese pasta…there was a warm welcome and we appreciated the many items on the menu…there was plenty of parking in the area..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNx9nIE0qOANzuFm6Ak0SYk8JNr2vubnJicmWxq&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2024-2-27"},{"Name":"Ray Jang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX3wj8Ne3ngI4eg9ouEU6zPmvERlQuudbckz4ma4Vg6pfYrsWM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The service was excellent. There was only one server and one chef but the two were very efficient. We really enjoyed the Napoli style pizza, and the fresh pasta had an interesting fusion sauce with a mixture of miso and carbonara. The guanciale in the carbonara sauce was rich and and full of flavour. The pasta was perfectly al dente and picked up the sauce nicely.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_SKvNF7awsi_PmQuHT87A8CDKGDP9aZlr2pKR&fid=0x0:0x5db6b9c97d14c25f"],"When":"2024-4-28"},{"Name":"Ishita Malik","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWV5NuG1NBDfsD_WLq2-zLuV8LgB51UWdsUfOaqy47D5rsrTXb5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I went there 3-4 times for some authentic Italian food.

The curries are tasty and pretty good quality for fast food. The portion is very filling, especially if you add naan. The veggie panini is really good with fresh ingredients. I also really like all of their desserts. Some of the items are more snack-size but most of their cookies/bars are huge.\nIt gets super busy at lunch time, and because there's so many counters and not a ton of space, it can be difficult to figure out where to stand, but the staff is helpful in directing you if you're confused. The service is generally friendly and efficient.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNfu8xFtp31SbafS8exo8vtV3PxU4WDHonOiRtz\u0026fid=0x0:0x8f55d57f925022a2"],"When":"2021-10-18"},{"Name":"J P","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJPNOwczxQeYq8Qup51h2PTCgzkWZZqiOeXeOFsoHWK1IWAROM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The line ups are very long during lunch hour. The food quality is average.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMKmfPg0wMwMMlY1z0OpBGl6AV2fLqkXWwWiZcO\u0026fid=0x0:0x8f55d57f925022a2"],"When":"2017-9-27"},{"Name":"TK","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUtNfsvt9Jqnmezc2PWV1KYVJeBq279Eo-JfhGEmrsy_0aCUzOt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I've been coming to the delly for years, as it's a cheap option with an assortment of options from salads, curries, sandwiches, and more. Basically, they are still making $5 sandwiches but charging $10 and with less sandwich...","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Akbar Shakenov","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX9WrUR0ZbYb0_kT2kk93PgA35IDV6kz8G9jFG29yrL4NkVBN8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"So sad, your curry was my favorite food on campus, but last two times were bad. So disappointed.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bradley Guislain","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLh0F_SXPBcpfBlKWAZ6_wXX7FaGctRt2U9-fybYt8v7MSNOA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Great if you like spending 15 dollars to get skimped on a curry bowl filled with rice so hard it could break your teeth.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paul Dante","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXjLXYa-Gi41DR82MW72_OBOxUKdygmYUf0O2nH158d2eOhgB0p=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"One of my favourite places to eat lunch on campus. user_reviews: [{"Name":"M B","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXIxiCIy7Ch29LlP7VXHtco7aO8YNkp89Hd11g67GLT8n9AIrZy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"They used to serve lettuce and tomato, in fact I think the menu still lists it with the burgers. Last time (August) I ordered the Pork (pictured), this time the Farm (October) and both came with meat and rice, and a tiny bit of slaw. No salad. I didn't realize how much the lettuce and tomato balanced the meat and rice combo. Now it is too dry yet also sort of greasy (not sauce) to eat. No freshness. Not for me anymore. I always get take out, as inside feels grubby, the floor is sticky when you walk. That kind of things always makes me wonder what the cleanliness behind the scenes where your food is made is like... Without the salad it is a spoon of meat and two spoons of rice with a sprinkle of slaw so very overpriced at $13. It is the size of the palm of your hand for reference. I also eat with my eyes and was disappointed with how the burger looked, and sadly tasted. I used to crave this place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYJ5S0DbHsJ0w9h1XuMRlCQCM8C4m_WwGggX4b\u0026fid=0x0:0x25762a4aae318566"],"When":"2024-10-10"},{"Name":"Dennis Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJgBHuKaxB6_AGRs3DyAn5DYWAJVYL8OdZQBLbOlZjEJJMR8F5KA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This restaurant is participating in TooGoodToGo app, this photo shows the surprise bag order, half the price of mini beef bowl, not bad but a little small","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM0PIYdSvzNdUvylTulTbOJ5JGQdxLKWUlz6DNc\u0026fid=0x0:0x25762a4aae318566"],"When":"2024-11-10"},{"Name":"leesa tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUWsWaHyhzcw7kKPh9V3HkvTK5TTa81TdmCDp9IylYllx4puXIy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Ordered the beef burger combo and it was really good. [{"Name":"Cc Ww","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJP0q9EHP94EL2cwLaPuRzE2AdbyVVCVuiEsNIB2kBAGc4ZZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was AMAZING! We started with the trio de mezze appetizer and it was such a treat. The bread it came with was a great texture and even had a little hint of spice. Definitely the biggest surprise of the night. The lamb shank was tender and came with a ton of delicious sides. we also really enjoyed the seafood skillet. The atmosphere was so lovely here and I will definitely be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNiJHdLuTbprlD8c6BxSDXT1aGnAK05UBhTekN0&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-12-12"},{"Name":"Hessam Dehqani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ9_xTs6k7X3RgR-GYtpDaVcRhHZYvAkCWBCnak0FYwr9rofA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The food was a symphony of delight and pleasure dancing on my taste buds. Extravagant amounts of seafood in the seafood fettuccine. Sauce was perfect. The Chocolate Lava Cake was the perfect amount of fluffiness and chewy-ness all at once. The cake was the slightest bit warm and the giant scoop of ice cream served on the side was not too cold, making it the perfect combo. The friendly staff will make you feel at home.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNJ5stowouGaXpUeYE6xdnYk5tTw2UAhlZkDP0B&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-11-23"},{"Name":"Sarah H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW92qwsfx_pIiwt2DlNeJL21vsXcUQcWFFO0CrTDqGo7aSuEtvR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We loved this Greek spot in Kits! We chose to share a range of appetizers- all were delicious, including the four olives with focaccia, the mezzo trio with the best pita, calamari, and spanakopita. We also had the yam fries- so perfectly hot and crispy. Everything came out quite quickly and fresh. The service was friendly and delicious. Definitely recommend!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOboR7reOpDZb_p0TsC_cSRvUDH0o3Bk4IppOyh&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-12-16"},{"Name":"Lister Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWbNvO55wOzkDRxCcJ-fMoCcdWyut5hlx-H_zUreRnwso9_V0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoyed lunch special with beet argula salad, lamb souvlaki, and ice cream. Everything made carefully and plated beautifully. Yummy salad and tender flavourful lamb. Lovely server and ample seating","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOvil2aWBw9xvb1WEocpbSTu5qJKwNogPEJmVBG&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-12-7"},{"Name":"Isaac Trenton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWcuG3EvRc-AAeKCn9g2ZfMQnNodo8xx3TwArbSevKXywtb2BIA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A wonderful experience with family. Would recommend for both friendly outings and special occasions. Great food, personal service, clean ambiance. Thank you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMO--eXeeKqPcjAD_zKFBygtnPBJ296t7XWlMGx&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"andy a","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ7Y7rwHyjfulEA1YHdfgv-xt7-eGezTRedst5phEBEmPsbXg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful experience, tried the four olives with the deep fried olives. If you enjoy olives I highly recommend them, you won't be disappointed.

The lamb shoulder was fork tender, and the Navajo bread was crispy fluffy and soft all at once.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPL8yvDzQrWpheoXTb2m_LsnPGF3AcaCpmykrT&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-4-20"},{"Name":"Yourstruly T","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUdAW_3mT95dnmWSH1jV5DzTjAp8VnRyKu5igqgCkvt_l-2XR77=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently had the pleasure of dining at this delightful Mediterranean gem, and the experience was nothing short of extraordinary. The ambiance exuded jazzy vibes, creating a perfect backdrop for a cozy and homely atmosphere.

The moment I stepped in, the inviting warmth enveloped me, making it feel like I was enjoying a meal in the comfort of someone elses' home. The restaurant's decor and lighting contributed to the overall cozy vibes, setting the stage for a memorable dining experience.

The main course portions were generously sized. Each bite was a burst of deliciousness. Appies were so flavourful. For the dine-out menu, I really liked the Mushroom Arancini and the Garlic Prawns. Ugh!! So warm/flavourful..

A special shoutout to the owner or manager, Amar, whose friendly and attentive demeanor added a personal touch to the entire evening. His passion for the cuisine and commitment to customer satisfaction were evident in every aspect of the dining experience.

The potatoes, a standout side dish, were a delightful surprise with their sourly delicious taste. I couldn't get enough of them. The chicken skewers were another highlight – juicy, flavorful, and a true testament to the culinary expertise of the kitchen.

In conclusion, this Mediterranean restaurant is a must-visit for anyone seeking a jazzy, cozy, and homey dining experience. With mouthwatering dishes and a warm welcome from Amar, it's a culinary haven that I can't wait to revisit during patio season as well!!

xoxo,
@yourstrulyfoodie","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP8hxYl3J7Guv437YZS_Uj8FCdYhvd9RqmOTMS1&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-1-16"},{"Name":"Daniel Silver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJawI80c4qwvuA-pWmht_nhIypwFKNS8vUDHnZIepoqs0gJvft7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I enjoyed everything we ordered. Portions were decent but not overly so. Definitely worth trying if you like Mediterranean food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODYFoK7X1vlNRzms1wWtQdlB7xQK729D7csvia&fid=0x0:0xdb1692f513539870"],"When":"2024-1-3"}]

[{"Name":"Rowan Tetrault","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfO97gMjqDhcxLto7LhpXIwpHTc_aV_Za2PD-ik6ShIa9lAwtk0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is one of the three conventional first year dining halls on UBC campus, and it is solidly alright.

They always offer a very wide selection of food at their various different stations including different types of pizza, burgers, pasta, and spins on traditional Mexican, homestyle, and Asian cuisine. They have all of this along with quite the yogurt/salad bar assortment + desserts and drinks.

Unlimited food with so many options is definitely a benefit, but some choices can be subpar at best and I noticed readily accessible protein options (primarily meat) are not always available.

My go to "clean" options (download nutrislice to be sure, but don't expect to see nutritional facts posted publicly ANYWHERE) that also taste pretty good include the sesame chicken salad with a hard boiled egg, any of their salmon meals, or a simple yogurt bowl.

It may be difficult to eat here everyday, but sometimes there are hidden gems and the staff never disappoint. This is why they deserve an absolute minimum of 4 stars :)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOp1PYN4xQ9rgNxumgQsKC0nK56EXU44ehjOiVv&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Robin Zhuo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX4YJfTGesCXz1xbhn6UpYAqxjtSHa4hbLPPN34KDkRy9WuDw0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Best 1st yr dorm dining hall for sure, but the quality are not stable :’( , staffs are absolutely helpful and amazing. If u r not in meal plan pay this dining hall for 12-20$ are insane.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOg61NRqlYqOY2-UH5B9vI8ZVC7VD4Ykn4YspXU&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2024-11-12"},{"Name":"Alexander Hunt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKntg94WsHup3cVgJBk3yO0jaRf4K-ndL2T0xGy94s_gBQtie8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The Feast is Totem Park Residence's dinning hall. With 4-5 separate kitchens serving unique styles of food, students and guests eating here will enjoy the food.

The atmosphere here is wonderful. There are celling-to-floor windows, allowing much natural sunlight into the dinning hall. The seating can sit 200-250 people. Sitting varies from cafe tables, to Howarts style long tables or high-chair tables found in coffee shops. The food-serving area of the dinning hall is immediately at the place where you pay so you can line up to get your food. To avoid the line at the main entrance of the dinning hall, you can go to the back to pay as well.

The food here is okay. This is not a high-end restaurant. The food may not be for everyone. Also, there's a self serve ice cream machine, yogurt and salad bar. There are coffee machines and juice dispensers. There are plently of fruits, snacks and bread. At night, the pizza kitchen opens. Food is served in small to medium portion which is perfect for those who do not eat as much or want to try multple things. Chefs are polite and kind and will be willing to give you a bit of extra food if you ask.

There is no washroom in the dinning hall. You will have to leave the dinning hall and lose your ability to come back to use the washroom.

If you come here during regular meal times, expect there to be lots of students. If you come during 8:30am, 9:30 am or any time when class is in session, there are not as many people. Menu of the dinning hall can be found at both front and rear entrance. Menu can be found online as well through Nutrislice app.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPWzm1_3n7h1l2H9rwoh2H89TZ0Fq1NXU3odOco&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2023-9-15"},{"Name":"Jarod Walsh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVvAxeA4y5ekP9kJ4EmyOw8TsE05_KmQ9ASGN1BZSNnDc39dHRw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This buffet-style restaurant is amazing. You pay $16 and can enjoy unlimited servings of various foods, drinks, and desserts. While the food itself is just okay, it’s truly incredible considering the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4uPJeAZ6lVIORSxF5yULsp8ZpenwbVQF3Fcqh&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2023-12-7"},{"Name":"Brendan Mitchell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3Qlg33iKZu8wkzLBmt9R9RBp_9-J_M_xbmFoyCBbc0eyazMCC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is awesome!  Very reasonable price and if you like to eat alot the variety is awesome.   I can't believe a place like this exists for the price.   It is not fine dining but it is deffinatly a few steps above what you would expect for eating lunch anywhere at a university campus.  Came here with my 9 year old daughter who is a healthy eater and we both had 3 breakfasts.  She loved being able to get up and go get whatever she wanted.   Good selection of different drinks avalible Aswell.   Highly recommend. For the price, nothing beats it!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMN7yTSIDM_65m4bBL6QwgHr2tRxv3ruxm0pDbJ&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2024-2-3"},{"Name":"Munchica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbQ6ACs51IPQJlRLrmnunOErED8bimOf5-y1uov4EWpuZvjQQjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba8-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This place is quite amazing and the food is very healthy, you can taste the health! For only a flat rate of $15.00 for lunch, it's an all you can eat buffet which includes roasted veggies, curry, rice, Bahn Mi, tacos, fries, burgers, smoothies, juices, milk, soft drinks, coffee, tea, salads, fruits, and desserts, including frozen yogurt! Where else are you gonna find a lunch buffet for $15.00 these days and such quality healthy ingredients!!! Highly recommend it! The only reason it lost a star is that the taste of the food is just average but for the price, it's awesome.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMefaQLhCYBXkPvbE6zYnfa2QtOKPoJTciFo0p1&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2022-10-5"},{"Name":"Ahnaf Muqset Haque","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU9JdQZtXBMvD618JDWqRmaMkXk-I2NhqdPuW2NLQFP33Qn87KikQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Feast is one of the first year resident dining places at the University of British Columbia. They have a bunch of variety of cuisines and have all sorts of options(vegan, vegetarian, halal, etc.) to meet your needs. The food is not so great in terms of taste and is quite expensive. Ambience is great though!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNYAuVTb8ktuztAQgPbE2inlqJ4Yo-UDnubXkp8&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2019-3-28"},{"Name":"Ethem Can","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGyCt7ndLGEeKEaL2-gks_s7s8Q37Wov3ouVX3P4o--96Axg9t=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Foods are delicious and perfectly designed. Only downside is there is always crowded and you need to wait some time to get your food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYUnLzVImnmGR01tQ3elsZg4CjFNKf14pGd5Sm&fid=0x0:0xec0f3de356e04cd1"],"When":"2023-9-5"}]
