[{"Name":"Rina Tedja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVCUXpJzYjJvgoEpkOVkc0pbrgG_5eFoaZqgY-XQUp-9x6VbVQf=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Made a reservation to celebrate my friends graduation, glad that they have a big table to accommodate all of us. Food were good, and we didn't have to wait too long. Price was students friendly, not too expensive. And the waitress was willing to separate the bills. Thank you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOECwl2kQckPquUlCvPef_3x4Heu87O09BQYUEo&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2024-7-7"},{"Name":"Olive Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVWaNKzMiC0kwUfahhPHKJzI23aKwHnkWquzcNkJSLJCjhuJoC_=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Restaurant's price with food court level of food and presentation.
$20 bento with only a little bit of rice, the avocado in California roll went half black, the egg tasted disgusting, the miso soup was served in a plastic bowl and the green tea from the water bottle was cold. The fried chicken was the only good thing....but definitely not come back again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kit Kat","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW3dZjoko9sqyxGJIpo6Vuc0LAP-G_ufVv3gqG1OzG8hLIiI4o=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dined in for the first time two months ago and the food was absolutely delicious! I've tried all of the bento boxes as they are my favourite to get a little bit of everything and they never disappoint. I've since returned many more times to enjoy the food here, and the staff are all so friendly. I would absolutely recommend coming here for a bite to eat 10/10","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Luke Y","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU-nw_Hipvgt6UpenAw0abcDlQMvwpFIko8ke_8Sy_24ohAlwTK=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"New food location here at UBC and of course I had to try it out. The restaurant was very clean and had very good COVID 19 precautions set up with electronic little hand sanitizing bottles set up at the entrance and payment counter. The server was nice and very direct. The overall environment while in the environment was very comfortable.

They had quite the variety of food on their menu and at affordable prices considering campus food prices. The menu was large, not overcrowded with menu items, and easy to follow. I ordered Bento Box A with beef (roughly $14) to go. I went at around 3pm on a Sunday, there were a few tables inside and I waited for just over 10 minutes for my food, which was a little longer than I had expected.  The packaging for takeout was pretty meticulous with everything being packed nicely in a large brown paper bag. The food was the typical bento box style food but everything was quite tasty. The beef to rice ratio was a bit lacking but the beef had adequate flavor and the added tamago (sweet eg) was a nice bonus. The California rolls were pretty good and the assorted tempura was light and did not leave an oily taste layer in my mouth.

Overall, a pretty good first experience here at this new establishment on campus. I will be back to try one of their curries.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzR7fkKpZwe8yvCpZLjeSxdz3pIlm7XjwH-llL&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2020-9-15"},{"Name":"Daniel Slick","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_rZhDYtX3p8Slyn1b3td54gJ7P5nOU91uTlm-nX3vMAWbK9f5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Food was very fresh and nicely prepared. Service was very warm and friendly but a little slow.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMV_MEbs8rViQqFqmGdJS2OXO_u5BMXbXZn7vqj&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2024-7-24"},{"Name":"Tina","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAKiC5J1ql1LsLTTfBwgvAj6sVGUusHXghumDKVG9ZTQ8QjcD_1w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Quick food and good price! I love their Bento box A (for around $14) with a good variety of thing: tempura, sushi, salad, tamago. It’s just enough to sample all and the chicken rice is very filling.
Also the service is great and they got my order ready really fast. Recommend for students!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNeaPUY7Q--PH_Rutk0VgFbhkRyMSLT8gkqANqC&fid=0x0:0x33085fd771659417"],"When":"2023-6-15"},{"Name":"Sepehr Mirzaei","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVZMkP1FM4xSnxxmsChX6t7nGX4XBELdM4VoX6LyFTiA8owPtU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Relatively good food at good prices for UBC. Love the gyu don, the beef Curry, and the fried bento boxes are quite nice too! I wish the tea was a little bit hotter though, but it's free so I can't complain. My wife and daughter had the beef stew and butter chicken and it was average. Service was friendly and attentive.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMxCe4rokS2lf9BBaZE7_T91FcRuvw6tC1IlYDA&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2024-12-6"},{"Name":"Allana Berger","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWKWM8axIi4jm1P_J7hVKEEINnOaULvzQtvyXxpQ3RFKEW2ytXRaQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've eaten here 5 times now. Every time I'm in BC I go back! The menu changes weekly and my meals have always been delicious. My favorite was a lamb stew. They also have delicious mocktails.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNhuGXRYPmzVYMJztbkxH__z7JHRuEWRdXiMbIT&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2024-4-16"},{"Name":"C.A. Walker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV6TWw2B1gYniTx9Jv9I-sjHY7yvLKIKSb2UNOXsFxJKyeXfY8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good vegan friendly healthy conscious menu. Recommend Butter Chicken and French Onion soup .. also the Brie fondue was great- if they’re on the menu when you go. We were in Vancouver for a weekend getaway. Only 1 star for service because our reservation was for 7:45p we got drinks immediately..but no food until around 9:15.. yes you’re reading that correctly. They were very apologetic and gave us a discount on the amount owed but it was still quite expensive","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOhHICAkL_sKB-ZBZ-EjwSeWQ4NZ9z0ntDCNs8&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2024-4-21"},{"Name":"Andrea J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK65HUpzpqY6517xF0fzpt6E222LL02oqw5uRrqd-JC0F_U3w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A family lunch today. What amazing service. So friendly, helpful and attentive. I would go back just for the service. As for food I had the French onion soup. It is very impressive looking, however the taste of the broth was bland. I'd like to try the Mac and cheese next time I go back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMn6uYKQ5t4T6IGLJ25lRXeUHAo393hZ2YcA8dH&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2024-2-19"},{"Name":"Rhys G","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKhDN_RhBJBaKomIPKrjzczztaQgfWjWmKvGOPFus9xAhXjrA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dined in and got served by Jan, so kind + welcoming + accommodating to my preferences! I ordered the lamb special and cherry cheesecake for dessert — 10/10 need to go again!! Definitely give this place a try when you’re in the area, this location specifically","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Blue Angel","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU7f51VtKBeHUyxFkPNC56JU91zCBjw1D7P5VQUMNOkHX1HFd_n=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Managed to locate a place nearby for dinner. Was quite a nice rusty restaurant with some special priced meals and drinks. Ordered the stew beef and lager beer for dinner. Beef was really great with rich flavour beef chunk. Hope to come again next time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM57iEqsxZjXMgh47M_yP-vqPJrVMC7AbcfxNdv&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2023-9-5"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Cute comfort food eatery. Very warm atmosphere, from the design of the inside to the friendly service. Because the place is relatively small, it’s probably not a good idea to bring a large group, but it’s a nice place for a smaller hang or even to chill by yourself. I have been curious for a while and just tried it with some friends. I probably will be back.
They have a great drink menu with lots of specialty cocktails and nonalcoholic drinks. I got a nonalcoholic pineapple guava soda. I don’t like drinks that are too sweet and this was good for me, but some people might find it weak compared to commercial fruit sodas.
I got a soup and sandwich combo as my entree with the Eggplant Caprese sandwich and the Crab Bisque. I really liked this take on a caprese sandwich, and the baguette was very fresh and soft. The bisque was very good too. Rather than being a super creamy bisque, this was more tomato-based and a little tangy. Good flavour with a fair amount of crab meat. I also liked the little side of coleslaw that was included in the combo.
Wasn’t really planning on getting dessert but then I saw they had a Chocolate Banana Bread Pudding, and I will rarely pass up on bread pudding. It was delicious but, as you might expect from bread pudding made of banana bread, with ice cream, with caramel sauce, VERY rich and heavy, and I had to get some help to finish it. I think this would be ideal for splitting between two people.
For this meal, with tip, I paid $48, which surprised me. I thought it was a good meal, but not $50 good - I’d associate that kind of price with a more upscale experience than this. I can understand the soup and sandwich pricing, the dessert was a little expensive, but what really strikes me as obviously overpriced would be the $8 soda. I understand it’s made in house, but it was just a fruity soda - no fruit bits or anything fancy, and no alcohol. It was a nice refreshing drink, but for $8 I wouldn’t say it was worth it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMA-33yhxlhuJWzrEmE3NBivENZ-qwhvFcoFjxN&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2023-5-20"},{"Name":"Keith Ver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXVdqxLCf1LEt0AU82myo-eUqDcb2LcbdnfhupJTEW0sPAQ-qQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Good food and good service! Loved the ambiance of the whole place. It gives me this vibe that you know you'll be ordering comfort food. Not only will it fill your tummy, but also your soul.

I ordered beef bourguignon and it reminded me of Filipino dish called Caldereta 🧡 - minus the mashed potatoes that is.

The whole place is accessible as they're located along Main street. Will definitely be back!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOT835yv9VmYFeqt5AwiAEPtu_4O-xMZON9EBlg&fid=0x0:0x57c0ba4874667b57"],"When":"2023-6-5"}]

[{"Name":"Jeff Downer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXl3HQ-1C4N-_a7ykvhIi5aM883AB-cDQVYb1xeenCY7zekayvZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wow! This is good. One of the LARGEST wraps I’ve ever had, must have weighed several pounds. The quality and balance of meat and vegetables is perfect. I will eat these all the time. I ordered a mix wrap, chicken, beef and lamb and all three are cooked perfect and not dry.
The counter service was so nice and accommodating. Upstairs was clean and a generally great place for lunch!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPm2KQDyO2c1CL0fzUMucqmbPUMgqg47YuRE_9v&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-9-10"},{"Name":"FARZAM ameri","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUC2df7lOXeiqMsnPi2htms2568VuOUkmExj9MZ8kkh6j2hvhus=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered Loghmeh kebab, and I have to say optimistically under 40% of that kebab contains actual Meat. The food was tasteless and It was just waste of money. I STRONGLY suggest you not to go there.
Staff was really polite and friendly though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPoCVXxYvNnPrU6RCsUdI-VTH87WanqMj-btLQ2&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Coline","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbX_QKuaEf6ecbnocWzjer3WudYneLMe_JJVgbs8i0ijFAVg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Extremely delicious and huge portion size (tho the size might vary some days, I have put the two pics for comparison). First time I went, the portion size was quite small for the price but the second time I went, they gave me a huge portion which lasted for 2 meals in total. I love the Vaziri meal that they have!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPih8L_Q2wK2QfkznE7CiefGaptLdidvJ3Bpds5&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-4-16"},{"Name":"Mariena Bui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6Nw1jeBXne8haJacgZytBHrMEqU2gmOMAF3l5QWK0CwO3rXPJ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ordered the saffron chicken with zeresht rice and I was satisfied with how the food taste and how filling it was, that I even had leftovers. My husband ordered khoreshte ghayme and he said that this place made this dish very well. For dessert we got sholeh shard and I love how it this place didn’t make this dessert to sweet! Next time I’m in UBC I will probably go to this place again ☺️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPCCrILJyF2kem_vb-iTitmN7-tSH1WfxWLBmab&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-2-29"},{"Name":"Negin Rahimi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4DUUoCWRf2VeIHKqwIhVGBDp6aPH06WL8KyLGIL_eC6FWBXb5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I recently visited the UBC branch of this restaurant near closing time. Unfortunately, the two jooje kabab (chicken) dishes we ordered were not warm. When I asked for a replacement and for them to be warmed up, they simply reheated the same plate, which did not resolve the issue and took a long time. The taste of the food was also disappointing, and the chicken was not cooked well. We ended up requesting a refund, but since it was late at night (around 11 pm), we couldn't find another place to eat. I have had a great experience at their other branch, but I cannot recommend this particular branch due to the poor service and quality that fell short of my expectations for Sahel Restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7yKfp8eM4dYI6zdmfXa1F0jAkoq40k9-j-8vc&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-5-23"},{"Name":"Miyuki Food","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIefbmBJIFd8vluRG1CtvO_cHUxsRdwtm3bVobO6E-icLpG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"So good!! I got the lamb and beef donair and the meat and everything was tasty, and the service was great. There is also a nice upstairs area with seating and a tv","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOFpW22RVhCzjq0t8O64yMaiiDBQ5d2EBHb_Nw&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-4-9"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"New branch of Sahel at UBC featuring donair and Persian food. The ordering counter is downstairs with a seating area upstairs. It wasn't particularly clean: some tables had crumbs and there was trash on the floor under some tables, which weirdly is carpeted. The furniture, however, is in good condition and comfortable.
FIRST VISIT: I had a felafel plate and a rice pudding. The food was average quality. The sauces they use are a little different than the typical sauces: the white sauce was thicker and tangier and the red sauce had a hint of heat but mostly tasted like a zestier and thinner version of ketchup (this is maybe not the most appealing way of describing it - it was good, like a cross between hot sauce and ketchup). I liked the different flavours and the rice was actually pretty good, but I was indifferent about the felafel and hummus. The felafels were like the puck-shaped ones you can buy at the grocery store. The rice pudding had a nice flavour but was almost gelatinous in consistency, which I can't decide how I feel about.
Second visit: I wanted to see if the more distinctly Persian dishes would be better, so I tried the eggplant stew, the one veg stew on the menu. The “broth” that the eggplant and tomato were stewed in was straight oil, which I did not like. Again the rice was great, but they give so much with the stew that I didn’t know what to do with it all.
The prices ($17 for the plate and stew w/ rice, $5 for the rice pudding) are fair for the amount of food you get, which is pretty generous. I finished the whole felafel plate but was very hungry, so if you have a smaller appetite you will have leftovers. Two people could easily split a rice pudding.
The staff seems very nice, but I just can’t see myself coming back for the food. I’d get the felafel again if it was the ONLY place to get felafel in town, but it is very much not.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNY72ngJ2ZaAwXFb3jb_xOhzFGMNLItp0KiPLjO&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2024-1-12"},{"Name":"Abdullah K","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVaOLs3U1NGAh-EH96OS0WG3dhkXXnjYtovUMs7UYINOdg16mA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This is my go-to place to eat on and around campus! With the limited halal options at UBC, this is a lifesaver. Good food, phenomenal portions, and fresh! If I had to suggest one thing on the menu, it would be the soltani meal. The steak is really well cooked and tender. I’m so happy Sahel opened at UBC.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP9Y519rm1k_jiyVqRKLtV2JmvAIaOwnipoGyUb&fid=0x0:0x615e3b717137617d"],"When":"2023-12-8"}]

[{"Name":"Lisa Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU2hRhOWIQf2ren7p1R3F9BVnb3q6vzlyk-JCc_U7cm7KJ7rH11fg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"i came to this restaurant starving after my afternoon classes. the service was pretty quick, we got our order around 10 mins of ordering. however the beef noodle was very disappointing, the beef tasted stiff and flavourless, the soup just tasted like soy sauce. The vegetables seemed undercooked. The texture of the noodles was fine. Overall, 3/10, was expecting better for the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOerFh-ScT0Avl732B3GQc_JRRKBuTvCqZjOmnU&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2024-9-13"},{"Name":"Henry Hu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOiklZbH_t_aRkBtZKTm3pDAeGGVqs_fJp0WPZNs_8inyrTWQy9Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came here with my aunt and her two young kids (we are Chinese).  Having seen poor reviews, we weren't expecting much, but the dinner was surprisingly very good!

The service was slow at the beginning even though there were few people there -- even after 10 minutes or so we still hadn't been served water or tea.  It was a cold night and the restaurant was also chilly.  The server was very friendly and spoke both Chinese and English.

The appetizers were fairly good (spicy beef tendon and beef slices).  I had the beef rolls (very good) and spicy beef noodles (very good).  The dumplings were ok.  The scallion pancakes were not very good.

At the end, it was close to closing time and she gave us some free mango shaved ice which tasted amazing!  Very fluffy with a subtle sweetness.  We will return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPnk7CIbwaPs_5-VtCw29sqwvLTOj_7hFEQDruC&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2024-1-15"},{"Name":"Katie Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVIjMysay4-FQVEPUnU2iivCs6D7x1kzSWlLVk1hwpWr3ttr5es=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Went at a time when there were almost no others at the restaurant. Pretty quiet meal aside from a few shouts by the staff (to each other?), which I think were instructions. Atmosphere was fine, normal restaurant vibes. Decent decor. Nice ceiling lights.

Service was fine, although I can see why some might see it as curt. She came by and refilled my tea without being asked, which is more than I can say for many asian restaurants nearby.

I ordered A3, and found the portions quite reasonable. The noodles are expensive but I think it's partially "ubc campus tax". They did put quite a bit of beef so I don't feel like the prices are all that unreasonable given the serving size and the location.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPOCR7J2-cBxj_MhFTA2O0HRjFvAoVseKHkoYN8&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2023-10-23"},{"Name":"Sartaj Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1doLfhIpPIdYO53EoD_63mHYE3jrQc1kxM-CAvFcju93a6Z1xPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Got takeaway, the brisket was really good! Really simple but satisfying meal- was slightly pricy though (menu with prices posted in the photos). Service was fine but I can see how some people may comprehend it as a bit too curt.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOm_WNO5NXyIgHBbu7z5LTIAqt8lrxTtLO88Ta3&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2021-2-10"},{"Name":"Sunny Hsieh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKn7JfczJPilvGMT4s7fYXLEV9lFRbn9veIkFCwiRyDnuZfxw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We order classic Taiwanese dishes here. The food taste average, but the dining environment is quite noisy since the stuffs talk so loud and don’t care what customers think.
If you’re looking for quiet dining, I suggest you order to take out.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXHF2vu1lLnJY4nrIl9jXR3Nco4mSagrnqGZF6&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2021-7-25"},{"Name":"Ryan Kim","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJg51dkTiELfwGSC3YeGg0Cqc2FbwTcp56uR5oMbjvMxs9-kgt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Came here with high hopes after being a happy customer of their West Van location that closed down, but was extremely disappointed with the terrible service and mediocre food.
Upon arriving, the restaurant was silent except for the yelling coming from the kitchen. The lady who brought us to our table didn't say a word to us, and left immediately after pointing to our table. The way she spoke, in both Chinese and English, seemed like she was upset that we were eating there and we were doing her an inconvenience.
Despite being only one out of two tables there, it took around 15 minutes for our order to be taken. Again, the lady sounded annoyed.
The soup was disappointingly bland - I had to add lots of chili oil and soy to make the broth taste of something at all. The noodles were overcooked and mushy, and the beef shank was tough and overly salty.
It's such a shame to see what Chef Hung has become, as it was once my favourite restaurant in Vancouver.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"nataku04","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU_SbO1MAS8FGX9Q1u4rgyMAxUXyAbqpEXgjPOqBTAPYYTV2-Ed=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I have no experience of the restuarant itself since I go it delivered. I'd say its not that great, apologies for the semi eaten meal before taking photos. I was just starving, first meal of the day after a 20hour fast. The noodles are a decent texture yet being so thin. The tiny beef brisket chunks were tender enough but so salty. The broth would have been good its light but tasted watered down.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM5ilPwOOcgkxQZCf75Ib1kTLwfreuMBYb5gUC2&fid=0x0:0x2669a59b57d60d56"],"When":"2022-8-30"},{"Name":"Eric","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWiQoGWet_oXsOFHl9IApfn5oX44S-A0_Tz_vgzgQxRW9yw_IDK=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Horrendous experience. I've always despised this place for its terrible service, inconsistent quality, and mandatory tipping on takeout.
But today crossed the line—raw chicken. To make matters worse, the server literally shoved the chicken into the box with her hands because it didn’t fit.
Absolutely unacceptable.
I'd rather starve / eat Neptune than eat here.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"SoCo Bass","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLvBnVIIUBTAO9i-PP1Cfy5ElZia22pH_cUnPsR4GRLCLdgGg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"this marina gives access to great fishing.  White Slough.  as a Kayak fisher person, I need to launch near the area I want to fish.  I can't go traipsing around for miles and miles like a bass boat.  the kayak fee is $7.50 which made me grin.  I never carry coins so I just left $8.00.  (you've been warned).  the bathroom is fairly clean, so the coffee inspired bathroom visit after my 2-hour drive was welcomed.   the ramp?  it is kinda janky.  it is steep and your entry will be skewed.  boats can only use one side of the ramp, leaving us the steep side if it gets crowded.  and there is no level earth anywhere nearby to set up (or take down)the kayak.  I had to Bogart a parking space to make sure didn't block the armada of boats launching.  overall, I will visit again.  maybe not during duck season and the fall striper run.  haha..","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kiera Tierney Giles","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWWVvpp7sYrCCL_JKTcPLAKB8mmpKJz0PeAaFpcDUdHVELl4cXfeg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We launched our kayaks here. We only paid for parking. Which you get the permit in the store. The launch isn't that great. A little awkward and with lots of slippery plants. After we got back we did eat at the restaurant. Very good food and service","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"D Dyson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJPHn815sG4H8YZaExaktgkUoGo5dD47Gw1yf9mqfp2TVT1KA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Not a bad place at all. As a night shift traveling nurse, I stayed here for about 4 months, roughly 4 nights a week. Travelers talk! I recommend this place. Chuck and Anne are honest and promptly corrected billing errors and found a spot for me for storage last minute. It’s no luxurious RV resort but it’s quiet, clean and I felt safe. There are a lot of mosquitoes that attract a lot of spiders, but management can’t control nature so it’s not a mark against them, the water smells like sulfur. I bought a filter that helped a little bit, just be prepared. Also, a lot of cats. No bother though, not 1 rodent! I would stay there again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Steve Polillo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVXR6AdBw1mFERCorYAmW56zPI5yn-E0UhcnvTwU7gaLx4K6WI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love this place .. thay treat you like family","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOZD9dX_LkjWmtSQXOgcGgZc5YKD6jBJJSD-Pp1\u0026fid=0x0:0x637f99266e6e6af0"],"When":"2019-3-31"},{"Name":"Dianna Henderson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWShZthNgQFBt6TN3_f-mEutGVqJaHPx4q44bbfNNG3YE89TDc1=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I was looking for a nice rv overnight spot. They are not set up for this gave us an empty spot all dirt lots of trash. If you require a regular plug for electric. It does not have it. The gal in the restaurant was very pleasant. She was waitress, cook and bottle washer. Breakfast was very good. I recommend elsewhere if you are just wanting overnight. Not a resort like the website says.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Michael McAlpin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJMkHSp4s5UnZ1ERK1M209-d62F05qUHxMJ3ntds2551NuQgA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I was kicked out for saying the manager was too uptight. I had a place to stay here but because I said the manager was too uptight, I ended up sleeping in my truck since I couldn't drive. I had to sleep on the floor of the truck so they wouldnt see me and kick me out. I wasnt attacking, I saw that the manager was aggressive to the other employees while the employee was already stressing and just said what I said. I didnt mean to berate or attack, I was saying what I thought","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ken Hicks","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLwV3WUioR-4zpNottAZV_68WbdJde4JS3lg1jKfoPYPE2e9A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great food, excellent staff, had a most enjoyable dinner and will definitely return soon. A little difficult to find but if you call they will guide you in. I HIGHLY RECOMMEND!!!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Phillip Freeman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKiD4IxTxkp1z8mSlRbb8mF7FE30mVAYf5tmR8_wMh-TUDnig=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Nice place ,good people , but if you want to stay there long term ,there's a waiting list and it's a long list. ( lots of bullsh*t goes on here.......Now four months down the road and if this place had an opening they have not told us anything about it.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews: [{"Name":"Na","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbWRUtiYRRPvrKwMe6vdozzm8j4VVPvwRIWUtuWvW0eKAOr20j=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love this place and it’s really surprising that the food is so good in this sad-looking hidden away food court.  They were open even when classes were not in session.  I love the Dan Dan noodle with 2 lamb skewers combo (comes with a canned drink).  Both were not too spicy for me, super tasty and generous portions.  I also had a breakfast crepe for the first time (ever. I’m just more familiar with Cantonese food) and it was so good and very large and filling.  I like their noodles which have a bit of a chew (look hand pulled rather than the skinny noodles you might expect normally in Dan Dan).  They were the same type of noodles in the meat sauce noodle dish (no soup).  The fried chicken is super crunchy so worth a try if you like fried chicken but I’m not looking for such an oily lunch/dinner.  Everything is fresh because it’s made to order.  They are open at night too. Looks like several of the other food court stalls did not open much.  Best thing to eat on the whole campus in my opinion.  Fair prices but if cost is an issue get their stamp card.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8ICOnqvJ0g5JPS6M6p7-6Q0WHwEXrNY8NPAUg\u0026fid=0x0:0x97af90bfdba20390"],"When":"2021-8-8"},{"Name":"Sartaj Singh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1doLfhIpPIdYO53EoD_63mHYE3jrQc1kxM-CAvFcju93a6Z1xPA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Decent food, decent price. Ordered the Dan Dan (egg) noodles, quite tasty but also quite oily. Would recommend for a staple cheap student meal but not more than that. Decent service.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOz1PE39GZeDjp_uU0TwU4rZ1zCXKBiVoQNdxni\u0026fid=0x0:0x97af90bfdba20390"],"When":"2021-1-28"},{"Name":"J Chow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX5nTjAm8gcoM8KEoMc5sPDIPLKdZEtk_2xDDFiiYwdxxyp1qQ7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tasty and relatively inexpensive. Unfortunately I misordered. Their spicy beef noodle soup does not have hand pulled noodles. It uses rice noodles! Get the hand pulled next time!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile\u0026image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOkPr0flQbuFkNy5blRTS4gtw1c4BAaOytWa_nW\u0026fid=0x0:0x97af90bfdba20390"],"When":"2019-3-13"},{"Name":"牛犇","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJjm733-p1EO9YisjFSmP81nw_wdJZywpGyNzzdUYijEmjJvQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This lanzhou noodle is pretty bad. It's kind of instant noodles. Doesn't match with the picture at all.  I won't be there any more.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jaden Chung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUM2ggNMzvyF3-mbTCuUBp5sV15NjtcwDNnBrTCqRD4nn9vAlRl=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"(Trying everything at UBC journal #1)\nOn my first stop, I went to Kung Fu Noodle in the international food court and ordered the Dandan noodles. Initially, the dish was quite tasty and the savoury peanut-y sauce coated the noodles very well. However, to my disappointment, I would find a piece of small plastic in my food, which made me dock this place one star. The wait for the food was also a little long compared to other places at the IFC. However, I would potentially eat here again as the food was quite tasty and relatively cheap (~13).\nRating: 6.5/10 (without plastic, 7.3/10)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"J Tsang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUzr6Y0twlmtUXm9KeDl3Yec3FqKKWpE7LlW49p3XyuhSVOFIAH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Food is decent here and prices good but man, the service is so inefficient and SLOW!  Longest wait of all the stalls in this food court, unreasonably long.  Don't order here if you're in any kind of a time schedule.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"James Selje","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURoXUkvPHUEdcJaDZ94eznUuD660xrVnD-m6ao5pBk4TAoEygk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Waiting time is a bit slow but their spicy beef noodle dish is delicious.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"RUI HONG","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ1yp8gOkQXQyev0kG3jcNVumkl-qssUud4UXK-ryZ8ZD7wkg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I’ve bought my meals here for 2 years, I just figured out that they have “secret menu” and that day I order a big plate chicken. The portion is huge and the flavor is outstanding.","Images":null,"When":""}]

This was dressed in a fragrant chilli oil sauce, and was decently spicy/numbing. (The kind that makes you sweat and blow your nose mid-meal). Generous portion of thicker hand-pulled noodles and sliced lamb, and only a handful of gratuitous veggies at the bottom. This is a heavier option for a meal so be warned. Decent value for $15+tax. Only wish it was tad less greasy and included more veggies. Service was super friendly!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsGHmIHxKdxVTdO5K1hvrNzisuObOdV8gOpEDr&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2024-9-6"},{"Name":"Josh J","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXe42PdxuYHUOJL_X8RN0pr9xXBVzrdppHzz1uqjoxioU06wUY=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered a Beef Fried Rice Noodle. The entire bowl had only a handful of beef (around 3-5 pieces). The rest is bean sprouts. Literally around 500g of bean sprouted on my bowl. And doused in so much oil I can't taste anything but the oil.

I get that there's cost cutting measures but this is just inexcusable for the price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNShl1CT87CReQzrVfSvBSP_m74OWBFYD5Au1Tf&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2024-8-7"},{"Name":"Serena Jiang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdrdumUkGSxjbtk1_LQZc0knhS2eGprfXet3quGlQUesHypA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"The food was lukewarm and you could see oil coagulating in the trays. I understand it’s made earlier in the day but shouldn’t fast food at least be served hot considering people are eating it right away? Also I’m clearly getting tiny portions of the items compared to the photos here and from the reviews saying “generous portions/ good portion for the price”. To be fair I could imagine the braised beef tasting really good for tray food if it’s hot, hence one more star than this experience deserves.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNl6gVMVsuDEnQrnqEc4lczMnKqKGZ-0QpTvEE9&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2024-5-5"},{"Name":"Iman Sh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWY_It5dFbhJ3ahD3y8wnnvsyYECBdVwU0ipYiueTLf-0IgvGbE=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered two dishes, one with two toppings and one with three toppings. The base was fried rice with vegetables, which was tasty. Our favorite topping was the sweet and sour chicken, followed by the spicy fried shrimp. I'm not a fan of beef brisket, so I didn't enjoy it as much, but it wasn't bad at all. The tofu and fried chicken were also good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPYn5ivfW57olI8tk1-SStvN0ONJf03iQ8hIsij&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2024-3-23"},{"Name":"Thanh To","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVd1WYJP1UmnIbSg76XorhMDMrCl48AkAncBIVkE7p0lcIIllbB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Not sure why all the hate but Sesame probably gives the most bang for your bucks on campus. That said, prices have increased within the last few months. Also, come near closing for a discount.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzwl9JXPv3noDGVsPFDwOkpgy-9dPOYukS4_lY&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2023-9-11"},{"Name":"Rhiannon Wallace","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAx5QcOsQKCDu6tdQ5r1AX6YB3HZHIwCoaxkohXBCloCBZAxbs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Food was prepared super quick so I’ll give them one star for service. Not likely to stop here for lunch again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNwDsKfzc3kuo7Bobehbl0uPU2QObRCrtyoMp7I&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2023-8-21"},{"Name":"E Chen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKy2o0HCNtv9vy3r48TF8rMzRuC3IjPPUXtIN5-DUX13g-Qqww=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Really wonder where do the good reviews came from- we tried 3 dishes and all tasted like fast food.

Lamb noodle taste like boiled noodles mix with sauces that’s all.

The menu photos look very tasty so that’s impressive, taste is no where near what the photos look like","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8D90SHV6CanI8GDvaEvc126_8yL3DphT7o50_&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2021-10-1"},{"Name":"Afindi Useng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURvlo3nZ4dDsYeBdJVxIo4OKsPCbGpPRUkFRo_W8UXjbvU9qFr=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I went in today and ordered their Mapo Tofu and was extremely disappointed by the food and service. The worst part was that when I went back to the store and asked them if they got the order wrong and if they could fix it they just turned me down and argued that this was what it's supposed to be.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMJfXtVta3AhH3AEpWaACERvuzzWr_SxMTKjoUT&fid=0x0:0xde85ee07a75a480f"],"When":"2021-9-26"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Rowan Tetrault","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWfO97gMjqDhcxLto7LhpXIwpHTc_aV_Za2PD-ik6ShIa9lAwtk0A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Unless you live in Place Vanier, it may seem inconvenient to come all the way to Gather for food, but when their best options are available it is 100% worth it.

One thing I noticed about the 3 UBC dining halls is that they try their best to be high quality, so when it took 5 minutes for my ordered poke bowl to be made I knew that it would be good. The fish tasted fresh and the bowl was stuffed with kimchi, edamame, and other goodies that I did not expect them to include.

Just because of this experience and the other high quality options Gather frequently has (including their solid shawarma and gyro wraps and vegan brownies) I seriously believe this could be the best first year dining hall on campus.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPMwUMSywIfBT8IVruFiiEXEKlWcFg9eiskGds&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2024-9-28"},{"Name":"Hugh Gao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVFlJmYlj82sx6sLKOje56IkZUG693ZnITvHtJUekoopvQlVKt9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"There’s a station here at Gather called “Simply Local” that makes some outstanding dishes.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM9pJkT3-BNBojmCwdrk9PX3Gn5zU2s_WhpLb6-&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2024-10-7"},{"Name":"Alexander Hunt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKntg94WsHup3cVgJBk3yO0jaRf4K-ndL2T0xGy94s_gBQtie8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Place Vanier's Gathering Student Residence Dinning Hall is one of the three dining halls available on the UBC campus. It is the farthest dining hall compared to the other two.

After entering the building, you will have to take a flight of stairs to get to the dining hall. The food available at Place Vanier comes from a variety of different cultures. Everyone will find something good to eat the dining hall. The dining hall can sit 200-300 people. It is a buffet style dining hall and you can get as much food you can eat.

There is a salad bar and custom sandwich making station. There is a  burgers, tacos, pork bun and pork belly ramen station. Food changes from time to time. It is best to check Nutrislice, the online menu app, to see what food the dining hall is serving before paying. The dining hall building has big windows overlooking the court yard of Place Vanier. You also have different kinds of seats like the Café style seats and also the long dining hall tables.

During regular hours like mornings from 8-9am, lunch from 12-1pm, and dinner from 7-9pm, you will find lots of people there. You can avoid the traffic by avoiding these common times or arriving earlier to skip the potential line-up for food.

The presentation of the dish is average. The portions are small. Food is placed on the counter which may get cold and unclean. Food quality tastes ok, but the servers are more concerned about getting as much food out to as many students and people as possible. During peak hours, the place becomes hectic.  Food also is warm, not hot after peak times. Staff there are friendly and kind.

Washrooms are downstairs, separate from the dining hall.

Parking is very close to the dining hall about a 5 minute walk. Near this dining hall, there are lots of nice trees to look at.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNkJTXAZhQtPzHpRvjlF4cdHyFgKSktppk9ET2t&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2024-2-23"},{"Name":"Raúl de León","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXR1w_Ji0Yz-Xp82r5o46luBx2_3UdjKeiMHOkVr4mcBNjLxloC=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I don't know why people give bad reviews, this place is amazing. Food is tasty, service is good, great choice of dishes, and for the quantity of food you can eat it's worth. I come here very often.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOSUe-AzPEDj9K7keJtauLlc84KoBtXeRrR1lB2&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2023-9-30"},{"Name":"Michelle Lam","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUrZc4FOCz7AcGuorZE4SGdMyBNzLpAyMERBSqnXndHoxWZ5T_e=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I really like the food here except for being repetitive.
I love Fresh Fare the most but they don’t change menu as often. I Iove the overnight oats, avocado toast and fajita bowl. A really good vegetarian station. Smoothie is my go to! Love the one with yoghurt, blueberries, chia seed, etc. Soup is pretty good too! They rotate all the time but I like their chicken soup, vegetables and legume curry, whatever bean soup, etc.

Gather has too much hate haha. It’s actually one of the healthiest and cheapest residence food among all the three.

I wish they have more cooked green vegetables. They always have potatoes and squash but they don’t have enough broccoli, spinach, green beans, etc.

Grill station is pretty good and they change menu around 2-4 weeks. Salmon burger is decent. I wish their chicken burger is cheaper.

Latino is also my favourite. The Havana bowl is pretty good but sometimes they don’t season the chicken or tofu enough.

Home cooking is also one of my favourite because they rotate the food daily. They have similar food every week. The vegetable lasagna with garlic bread is so good! Not a lot of cheese and love the sauce. Butter chicken is not really good imo.

Sandwich station is alright except they don’t have the press!!! Please we def need the press for sandwich especially for those who order with cheese.

Simply local is a lot of people’s favourite. Not too expensive unless you get a main with two sides (around 12-14?). They serve beef brisket, pork chop, chicken breast, salmon and a vegetarian day every week.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPMSCT6VsYqtYkDRF-j31F88f1xfA6I9Q7h3tsB&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2021-10-16"},{"Name":"Dana Sullivan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWQIw-0oOUNgoyniYugTscGkgpKJS8tpx4V0tAajn3ZGkNIfqEk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"They offer a great variety of food, including Latino, vegan, burgers, sushi-inspired, world (rotates often), baked goods, salads, and soups. Everything is fresh and there are some interesting things to try. Portions are usually pretty filling for me. As with other UBC dining halls/markets, prices run a little high. Also it's hard to find a time that every station is open - stations will often close unexpectedly for the day or even for a few hours during the day.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMqfjc_HqIif1hZmIstsralupMRNW7XFrdevVyw&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2018-12-4"},{"Name":"Luke Kuro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYgP_ll8ede6rokqjyo-gOuHJnPxjys9UFzHU35KFVwvMyuKs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Buffet, lunch for $16 per person
Best dine-in place in UBC with fair price.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNHAKj0GGdoJ6QYLEWd48pKfqiCkWAB268qMjiK&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2024-3-12"},{"Name":"Neil Sharma","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLwJoC3pQnZZnUx7vr-pCC8C_c6dpXLIiL2qDjojVFRSBIWWg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Only carbohydrates and fats, not much protein consistency. Desserts are good if you like sweets. Pic of cheese bagel attached!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNTgtbx3C5QnopesabURqL1khnsdnXVg1nJAG3d&fid=0x0:0xe5bca09347600efd"],"When":"2023-11-1"}]

[{"Name":"Nelli S","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUYqdeN-R5LF87KTDEqaw6sJisI0ncLfXvpqJx3EleF1LdBqzPr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great service, delicious food, very nice atmosphere. I recommend to come here on their Happy hours (2-6pm). Also we enjoyed Festival of Lights.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO4eeZkpUScusoGh05YtxXBhsxrART7364I5-BJ&fid=0x0:0xe3178a02fcde58a6"],"When":"2024-12-8"},{"Name":"Tuna Canoe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIxuMgPtlPZ-uE8yNHSTq_Z5MJ1hEv_H44UTamA4NFV6LAU3JU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"To avoid the impatient backlog of traffic coming off the busy Tsawwassen Ferry & Causeway, Take the 2nd exit ( turn right on 52nd street ) and take your very next right again . Here you will find a little gem called  ~ Pat Quinn’s Restaurant & Bar. ~ Just take an hour to relax and enjoy an amazing experience here while you let the traffic congestion subside .

I can write a whole bunch of amazing and good things, but this will be way too long !

The bottom line, amazing food , huge portions , great views, cool atmosphere. But honestly, the main reason we will return here again is because our service was an 11/10 ( our server Bryn ) You can have a meal pretty much anywhere , but we definitely will be back because of her amazing service today !

Thank you so much again Bryn !

Updated Oct.2nd lunch : with more pics : Salmon & Cod cakes , and Hawaiian pizza ( with Jalapeños) Outstanding service again !!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOfaecDlvFPPoRaFJDgZPHKOqJbBWt-bGwcXwVq&fid=0x0:0xe3178a02fcde58a6"],"When":"2024-8-16"},{"Name":"Shela Yuen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLxRFX65srqH3-KccY4AUhBn3sK5L-aeATFZiVVf12Fx1nVd4g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am here for the third time! Rigatoni bolognese and fries are exceptional. Great atmosphere, nice view. With happy hour’s pricing, this place has become a must-go every time I come to Tsawwassen.

And today I found another reason that this placw is a must go — Mr. Tom Kwan’s services! He truly made us felt very warm and welcomed. Despite the restaurant’s so busy and probably under-staffed due to BC day, he still served us with unmatched hospitality. We are truly thankful for Tom’s services. Will definitely come again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP-bcYoWbHS9EB_J9tZ205gW7KzP-UTkjxjMfsr&fid=0x0:0xe3178a02fcde58a6"],"When":"2024-8-5"},{"Name":"Dawn Mist","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyR-na2sQcGqnSW-JxTn27RMX1oocQ3hojpV86Eb8qwbPHRL0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Been here several times and it is begrudgingly inconsistent. One time we ordered a couple of the beef dips and they forget the dip part. Sometimes the pizza tastes like pizza, other times there is no sauce on it. Very up and down, very inconsistent. We keep giving it a shot hoping that consistency might come back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2-WG9SE8XYfMbJBNz_nnPXMCCVdouQOCJp-H5&fid=0x0:0xe3178a02fcde58a6"],"When":"2024-11-15"},{"Name":"Jagdeep Chahal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJaLw0I3vM9nfwmD3H8tXGPJeDG7bGdT8tRmfrHe4cLBPb2ag=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of my favourite restaurants. The food is always on point and the staff are always amazing. I was finally able to book reservations for Brunch with Santa and it did not disappoint. My nieces had the best time and created a wonderful memory for them. They’re already asking to come back next year and I think it might just become one of our Christmas traditions. There were no crazy wait times for the buffet and everything was always topped up.  Also, I loved how Santa and his elf came around to each table to chat with the families.  A great experience overall!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thedishdetective Lala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKD_tj6k6xpF8R8uVmPtHQuGBgjvefVOKaKmqeE1mkWnmvdyA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Pat Quinn’s Restaurant & Bar
Location: 5133 Spring Blvd #100, Tsawwassen, BC V4M 0A6

Clam Chowder
The clam chowder had a good portion size, though it was a bit runny for my taste. However, the seasoning was quite good. Overall, I’d give it a 7 out of 10.

Butternut Squash
The butternut squash was delicious, with excellent seasoning. I enjoyed it a lot and would rate it an 8 out of 10.

Crab Cake
The crab cake was well-seasoned, fried, and crispy. It was decent but didn’t stand out as much as other dishes. I’d give it a 6 out of 10.

Mussels
The mussels were a highlight of the meal. They were well-seasoned, had a good portion size, and tasted really good. I would rate them a 9 out of 10.

Steak
Unfortunately, the steak was disappointing. It was hard and chewy, despite ordering it rare. The only redeeming part of the dish was the gravy. I’d rate the steak a 3 out of 10.

Service
The service was good. The server was nice and attentive, earning a 7 out of 10.

Venue
The venue is really nice and cozy, providing a comfortable and pleasant dining atmosphere.

Price
The price was reasonable, earning a 3 out of 5.

Verdict
Overall, despite some hits and misses, I would come back for another visit.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMeCj6ISD-0mJyzQmc7SZNL2Tv9-9Pe9ea0Um9N&fid=0x0:0xe3178a02fcde58a6"],"When":"2024-6-5"},{"Name":"Susan Ninow - Realtor","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJLhR2xv519-zmTSY9obAY5M46DsiXjVum-r80rdag4lo3d0rCn=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Enjoyed an early evening with friends at Pat Quinn’s. The food and atmosphere is excellent. Loved the views of the golf course! Happy hour offers excellent value! The Happy Hour spring salad and burger is delicious!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMjRADCZiBMAlnAtraWZANwPbW7F1fGHHIla1Ke&fid=0x0:0xe3178a02fcde58a6"],"When":"2024-6-30"},{"Name":"Munro Stuff","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWj0Wcuk6ox5dfAeJ4fAaMbhX_F-nzzt3p5oc_f0hBd0NpbGSM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Had a good brunch here. The non-alcoholic green tea lemonade with mango was really tasty without being sweet. Excellent yam fries, perfectly cooked. The Tuna Buddha Bowl had all the right ingredients but the tuna needed a marinade and the bowl needed a better/more dressing. Good service and lovely festive decor.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Jerry Yao","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkwf2E1WF8z--h8mFLrUAWr1RNYrZKAAKQBGFCgReDiNF86w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Found fish bone in salmon dish. Plate is icy cold for main course. Spaghetti and rice becomes watery after touching the cold plate. Chef should be aware of this. Food portion is good, environment is fine, service is also good. But still lot of things to improve.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOsHPgsrCS8L-_GUdwwqmlGf3AzybnLpW34vUI3&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Thedishdetective Lala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKD_tj6k6xpF8R8uVmPtHQuGBgjvefVOKaKmqeE1mkWnmvdyA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"**Location:** 1602 4949 Canoe Pass Way, Tsawwassen

**Clam Chowder**
- **Rating:** 8/10
The clam chowder was impressive, with a rich, creamy texture that wasn't watery at all. There was a generous amount of clam, which added to the overall flavor and satisfaction.

**Calamari**
- **Rating:** 5/10
The calamari was fairly standard and didn't stand out much. While the portion size was generous, it was a bit too salty for my taste. It was well-fried but lacked any unique flavors or seasonings.

**Steak**
- **Rating:** 6.5/10
The steak was reasonably good for the price, offering a decent cut of meat. However, it could have benefited from more seasoning to enhance the flavor. The accompanying vegetables were slightly undercooked, which detracted from the overall dish.

**Price**
- **Rating:** 2/5
- **Notes:** The pricing was quite cheap for the quality of food served. While some dishes were enjoyable, the low cost was a pleasant surprise compared to the overall dining experience.

**Ambience**
The ambience of the restaurant was nice and cozy, creating a welcoming atmosphere. The decor was pleasant and added to a comfortable dining experience.

**Service**
The service was good. The staff was attentive and courteous, ensuring that we had everything we needed throughout our meal.

**Verdict:** Will come back again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwnUhv8otttaLvfhmouNIkPuhjci9JvsRZyzmG&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2024-5-17"},{"Name":"Teresa Wright","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL98sa5_1FmXtHLNNF3WDAOGgI03qDcyVGoMEnhGH4FWHfuSw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came here after I got off the ferry on Wednesday, October 16th. I was greeted by a very nice young woman. She suggested a couple of things for me, and in the end, I went with the two stones burger. It was juicy and piping hot served with crispy fries and house salad. I would eat here again! The server was super friendly and outgoing!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_zdFXA68q5boYFlJFuk_xJYZ1QV5b748rdXr5&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2024-10-17"},{"Name":"Greg Leo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWm8ssH7mLognVswOCUTCA_m_WUoavv1VB46ZtNXUUngffyGHMZ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Always pleasant..
Always delicious..
The 2Stones burger is da bomb..
Would luv it if they got Beck's and Guinness non alcohol beers in..hint hint
One of the only restaurants I eat in South Delta ..
Thanks for being an awesome place !","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Rebecca Kyriakou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXFRK8XemYLbguyv8cIkBYTm6iiXr_JMZgzXGoSkEs5YghyEVk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Just finished lunch Two Stones Grill here in Tsawwassen and what a good choice it was. The food was fabulous! Starter Calamari and then the prawns in butter and lemon pepper was Devine. My husband chose the Two Stones Burger. It was a rustic, hand made patty that was just right (his words😂). I would HIGHLY recommend anyone stopping in here for lunch or dinner. They have some amazing daily specials!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP28m2IHTtF2uaOMJDFTnietx2R6vjWUgpKlQEE&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2024-4-29"},{"Name":"Michael Scarn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLAUdj_jT_b5wqz1YfQq7yKNPPnDMs3mF_DB5Qfrce33dBwSQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We ordered the chicken souvlaki meal which was a part of their 7 items for $11 promotion and were thoroughly disappointed. Just some white rice and a single chicken skewer. It’s not worth any additional words - just look at the picture and decide if it’s for you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNo3WAjQ9KAuSEPuSSHHlFGTBmUxjEr-clvFYVW&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2024-11-25"},{"Name":"Bernie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPXTBFQGy4UZogf6r0hGxUGZ8fvtwePPN5iicbAtQksaWtpwOP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"After shopping at the Tsawwassen Mall, we try to find a new place for dinner and found the ‘Two Stone Grill’.  We got the Crispy Calamari, Chicken Souvlaki meal (with Caesar salad & pita bread) and the New York Steak & Prawns (with Caesar Salad). They have really good food choices, super delicious and reasonably priced.

Daily lunch specials are truly inviting.  A week later, I tried their Lunch Specials. We tried the Fettucini Alfredo, Chicken Tenders and Broccoli Soup with Caesar Salad and drinks for $12.00 each. It's all deliciously yummy and in big shareable servings. Aside from the regular menu choices, they offer good deals for Dinner 2 Course meals inclusive of drinks and ‘to go’ meals.

The dining place is small and has a cozy ambiance. Great place for couples on dates. I suggest making reservations because this place is mostly full.

Jessie, the serving staff is very friendly and attentive. Service is amazing. Parking is not a problem. They’re closed on Sunday.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO_93_g0m9ZBTznOj0OyGEucmUMSgUP5_lKQoSy&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2023-5-16"},{"Name":"Jesse","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJSDyGy576NjOpFot9rCBdIpO7u4qZP6Qzr6EXuEXmqpkbcdQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I am blown away !!! I just ordered a few orders of the spaghetti special’s and a couple of burgers and they were SO GOOD !!! I can’t believe how good these burgers are !! Tastes like a homemade patty not a cheap frozen one like everywhere else.  The bun was fresh and delicious!!! And the spaghetti! It is also delicious again tastes like a homemade sauce not the usually generic tasting one that every restaurant seems to use including Boston pizza.   This place is really really good.  Great prices and great food.   I will be back all te time now cheers guys great work !!!  Sorry burger didn’t lAst long enough for the picture.  It was too good !!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8eL8tDEHp5D4B7j-K8PMAOmEaaQgVt_leLh7v&fid=0x0:0xef2f97c42e16e3e5"],"When":"2024-2-14"}]

[{"Name":"Hamed","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjViJ9EznENDd1HeEqpUkYuqmZFdKwptQI-w0AYNvWdb_l07iQpU7w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The atmosphere was great. The management greeted us warmly. The waiters were very polite and friendly.

The pizza and pasta were both great. Pizza especially was full of toppings. Unlike the classic Italian style which is not as dense in toppings. We loved it though.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNzL21Em97yXFGck6U2k3_dGVBJQVpE1A6xaHfJ&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"Leasa Ferneyhough","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyIeO7VzLVo9O3Un3xr2ksgRw0ut6tXtLBY535nxO6cQHWOfU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our takeout meal of appetizers and entrees was so delicious. Perfectly cooked, fresh seafood. The bruschetta was to die for. It had a really lovely balsamic reduction on it that was flavourful, but still left room for the fresh tomato and feta to shine as well. Balanced flavours, seasoned perfectly. The team member who greeted us and brought us our order was friendly and quick. We received excellent service, even though it was Saturday night and the place was packed. I ate here 5 years ago on another trip to Delta and can honestly say the consistency of food quality and service was great both visits. A really great restaurant. Thank you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuif1-EHcFfV7oMquxibIylA8i46yjNmck7_Gt&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2024-10-1"},{"Name":"Emilia Muirragui","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVbrBdWMJwAdDmTKF2rqn3OE2f7BKVf4ff7Eui90G41UPNKe7l=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I absolutely love this place! We came across it randomly, as a "near you" recommendation by Google Maps. And let me tell you that the food was SPECTACULAR! I had a special menu item: a Salmon Risotto and it was absolutely delicious. My husband ordered a quesadillas from the happy hour menu and they were really good and very abundant. I loved the atmosphere of this place, fancy but still not so fancy that you actually have to plan to dress up for it, very cozy, and they even have blankets if you decide to sit outside on their patio. I cannot recommend it enough and I cannot wait to go back for more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOxjpG0lZT289xitiw9JXKe30lXckpwUutLhbPk&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2024-5-31"},{"Name":"prabhjot Sohi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLNCwEpx0kUHz8GSEDHGZH3WZ7euyF1v5CYXR_LA2y5mgm9pg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would highly recommend this place. The service and food both were great. Jackson was really helpful, polite and his services were amazing.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPHVObrledjY4PSr4f5orPixingObDYWX0xCmwc&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2024-11-16"},{"Name":"Charn Thandhi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUAuCLfNf1I-ocypWvJIt2QP7eekFSmny-FkhPG2ukh8w4IUMbV=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time visiting this place with my wife and our good friends and I loved it. Never tried a Mediterranean pizza (not shown here) and I loved it as well as this Chicken Romano which I split with my wife. The food was delicious and I would absolutely recommend this place 👍👌","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipME9oPHhiivSjx3ceSanWL86eVgfBPboigrqx1R&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2024-8-6"},{"Name":"Mohammadreza Behnejad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbfFjgusvHBDGevsLnSFlRH6CqkrxaSYgN1dtBgif3eqTdhnw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Very good vibe in this place. Staff were professional and nice.

Food tastes delicious. They offer two size of portions. Larger size is $3-4 extra and can be shared for two.

A group of 10 people non of us could finish the full portion dish.

It took almost an hour to serve the food. To be fair maybe it was because of our larger table.

Cajun chicken Alfredo linguine and Lasagna was absolutely delicious.

Overall very satisfied with taste and quality.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8nLXgqUlXLNwCwtiC-W9j_VPh_bNEUELF_Nw&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2023-5-17"},{"Name":"kayla Sabbe","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWpSiKbA3LurEcnUJo1uQLIuFZ7jgMo04Ijp9XqL_9LhSPx0Kg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"My husband and I dined here for the first time. We had lunch on the patio which was incredibly clean and comfortable. They offer blankets on the seats if it's cold out which was a very nice touch. It's hard to find a place to eat where the service is 10/10 all around nowadays but our server was so attentive, incredibly kind and just all around a pleasure. She was so good I called Mario's after we left just to let the manager know how she did. I wish I had her name but I hope she got kudos because a lot of younger servers nowadays just don't care much.

The food was also a 10/10.. as a vegetarian I got so many options to choose from as the server went out of her way to explain that I could get almost anything on the menu without meat. The goat cheese salad is a MUST try and the meat lasagna was so hearty, my husband loved it.

We thought this place was fancy so maybe the portions would be small and prices high for quality over quantity but no... you get quantity and quality for a good price. Everything about this place was so inviting, we will be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOAqVNqpPDLIkzghkw1-AudsPMk7H60y565KsPG&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2023-9-3"},{"Name":"Luan Reisdoerfer Cardoso","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXJy4d20z2cS8v7rChMGw3z6muiCCzuI588LnB8lkU6JnQBfH_g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing experience! We were looking for a new restaurant to try, and we couldn't have chosen a better one. Attentive service, comfortable patio, and mouth-watering food! I couldn't recommend it more. We are definitely going to return.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPbaFqcQr2taez51BVtJ5aSZBSMINB8VTL5eDWh&fid=0x0:0x4a25ec699118faf3"],"When":"2024-2-27"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Albert Luk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVaD3o96lx5KFqGPVNTfbIw-nZHFFA950dd8GZz9qbGbOe0Sjog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Don’t bring your date here: impossible to have a quiet conversation. Music is good though too loud. We made reservations but they placed us in the middle next to a boisterous table. Food: meh. Went with tapas and they were all bland. Server missed the wine order. Dismal experience.  Tacos: just ok, you’re better off going to some place else. Sliders: dry. Cauliflower: ok. Brussels sprouts: average.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM1r7Wwqiy86f9jgEI-tE16xg6t64ucQTH9-VyO&fid=0x0:0x70b2c89c4b724af6"],"When":"2024-8-17"},{"Name":"Tricia S.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUBIPgdHNtXGMVDBPAiyBZPz5RlbPOO-0QbSlZMCorEUFy6yRE=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"As long-time residents of the South Delta community, my now-husband and I have always valued supporting our local businesses. When planning and hosting our wedding, we sought venues that would not only provide exceptional service but also reflect the warmth and spirit of our hometown. Mario's Kitchen and its neighboring restaurant, Gracie's Next Door, stood out as the perfect choices for our post-ceremony cocktail reception.

Mario's Kitchen has been a staple location for our family dinners and events over the years, and this time, we decided to host at Gracie's Next Door. The outcome was nothing short of spectacular. From the outset, the management and staff demonstrated remarkable dedication and professionalism.

The team at Gracie's Next Door delivered excellent service throughout our event. They were attentive, ensuring that tabs were accurately started for the correct guests and taking the time to remember each guest's name and preferences. The food was absolutely outstanding, with our guests continually commenting on how delicious and plentiful everything was. The impressive spread truly elevated the experience and left everyone delighted.

We were truly amazed by the turnout and the seamless execution of our reception. The hard work and commitment of the staff ensured that our day was flawless and unforgettable. A special thank you to Darren and the entire team at Mario's Kitchen and Gracie's Next Door for their exceptional service and support.

We wholeheartedly recommend Mario's Kitchen and Gracie's Next Door to both locals and visitors in South Delta. These establishments are key spots to wine and dine, offering not only delicious cuisine but also a welcoming and professional environment that makes every occasion special.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMZp_Ndokgi_04wHy3-0IyRHEL344DEmbdSzVAK&fid=0x0:0x70b2c89c4b724af6"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Keith Adler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV-w0ymVj8anzOJoTo6l50yzn_DFPba_nWtAvCmch_RV1kWDnFy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Best meal I had in Canada, from several trips. Lots of good options and clear allergen markings. Fantastic service","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPwCuN7xLwxfHJ3vDUHNwcvc1BcpeN1b_y0-9r7&fid=0x0:0x70b2c89c4b724af6"],"When":"2024-10-23"},{"Name":"Dana O'Higgins","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIdr3pjwz6o3aaIhH0k9AWopcCiN5GSus8Q2_EdBH5NrnP6zQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great spot! The outdoor patios have numerous warming devices so you can sit out and have fresh air and dine even in the winter.

Excellent menu, so many gluten free options, and lots of authentic feeling Mexican items.

I had the roast lamb, it was quite good, topped with and interesting puree and served with nicely brazen potatoes and cauliflower.

Tortilla soup was really good, tostada's and coconut prawns were also really good!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Laline De Guia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ9wtiqDL7jFuGd32VGjqy4EYfl8BZ79PuR3ETkSSOu6bVNLw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Came in here last night and the place was packed but they were able to squeeze us in (a group of 7). My 7-year-old niece, who is usually the pickiest of picky eaters, ate like she'd just spent 39 days on Survivor and was rewarded with a feast — just a long way to say the food was fantastic! Our server, Shelby, was an absolute delight. Overall, it was a wonderful experience :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Melanie E","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUR0bJcxqNkJt-i1wxCH3EaQXevncA86panZszfT__NAs_0KWRp=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The rating is based on a dine-in dinner experience.

Ambience: 5/5 - A great place to dine with friends and family for special occasions or just because…
Service: 5/5 – our server, Bailey came to check on us often
Food: 5/5 – ordered the halibut burger wrapped in lettuce rather than a brioche bun. It came with potato wedges. The fish was cooked to perfection & didn’t taste dry. The other dish was the seafood linguine with plenty of prawns, scallops & mussels in tomato sauce. We finished the meal off with crème crème brulee. I recommend all 3 dishes. There’s an extensive taco menu. Great choices for vegans and vegetarians.
Value: 5/5 – reasonably priced compared to city prices
Parking: 5/5 – complimentary parking in front

If you’re ever in the neighbourhood in need of a good meal especially before or after a ferry ride, this is the place to go! Can’t wait to come back to try their tacos.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOdVwfN3Ye-oShaogEqjgWSQLCTrViu_VIJjwL-&fid=0x0:0x70b2c89c4b724af6"],"When":"2023-9-22"},{"Name":"Sukhraj Hothi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWxQjM5nJbgElJc2hyhhoXQyiMBiFOcfOQTg0d9N8DVTMBMUnkcEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came here for a cozy brunch on a rainy Sunday; they got heaters and even blankets on the chairs!

The food was great, but I really couldn’t give it 5/5, service was just subpar. Maybe it was just a quiet morning for the place but overall, good food :)

Would come again,","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPeDXW4RyoiTdbRoI9lwaa4Hm7O8_VUEJ_oRoDa&fid=0x0:0x70b2c89c4b724af6"],"When":"2022-7-3"},{"Name":"Jack Canon","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjiIxAtpA98tHCikn081BC4pndLFCoXumRILc8Dh6dhMHh3qy9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"January 12th 2024 We had a wedding dinner planned for 20 with the wedding ceremony to take place on the beach in Tsawassen. Unfortunately it was -13°c and a wind of 60KM so at 9am I contacted Michaela and asked if there was any way we could do it at the restaurant. She said yes and Wow it worked out amazing everything was perfect right down to we moved inside they made it just so perfect. And our server Annabel I can't believe how amazing she was handling 20 guests everyone made great comments on the server and Great Food.
I truly cannot thank the whole team at Grace's for making our day perfect from just a simple I Do to a 1st Class wedding Thank You from the bottom of my Heart ❤️  Richard and Tina Glasner","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPF6u2phCG3uyp1FP8NG_R2B5DoyZ5lET_VW9xT&fid=0x0:0x70b2c89c4b724af6"],"When":"2024-1-14"}]
