[{"Name":"Happy Sunny","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIhrtA612fP6soH2c7PBaInHGNvnte3YNRS_qAs35pTYrJn3A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We only visited for happy hour and enjoyed the lovely view and super friendly service. Arriving after lunch, we weren't very hungry, so we ordered lattes and a cocktail. The sandwich was a bit plain, but the sweet potato fries and potato skins were quite good. Overall, it was a pleasant time spent with family, enhanced by the beautiful view.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMsUqJP9M4IhwuOhrC5NVjTFn6NMBevEjIjtn-C&fid=0x0:0xecd6f6fa8e77ba07"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"richard chan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIf1neCZqBnJLrk0cTe43Vpuwux4gjmUzrrV78_wxQmqDskDw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I've been golfing the Tsawwassen golf course for years, even when it was an executive course. I liked it then but I like it even more since they changed it to a par 70 full course. Plus, they have custom-built houses and condos lining the fairways. The course has a nice layout, and they kept the first long par 5 hole from the old executive. It has a great mix of long and short doglegs and water features. The drainage on rainy days I thought is very good and it's in sunny Tsawwassen. So the weather is always great for playing. There's a small shack that serves food and drinks on the walk to the 11th tee box. It has a driving range and putting green for practice. The big clubhouse is full service and you can eat at the Pat Quinn Restaurant after your round. I totally love this course.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOK_EIcl4_dbtVeAPaUDMaY9husMqZ1wjr3IJox&fid=0x0:0xecd6f6fa8e77ba07"],"When":"2023-5-31"},{"Name":"Tamara Yarwood","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlcz2XuMmO5RLvD55VGgxmWy3HrLNczK76Ymgkxx6DGIgAeu4r=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We had our wedding at Tsawwassen Springs this past weekend and it was amazing! Lauren (the event coordinator) made sure everything went smoothly leading up to the day and went above and beyond on the day of! The chef was incredible! Everything was perfectly cooked and the baron of beef was juicy and tasty. He even made some special changes for our menu that were wonderful and spicy! I highly recommend the venue to anyone considering it for their wedding.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Mason Chou","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWhfNjZOP0h9QNFuqZppF2wkFAzQrgPn9irCcSF1nSDu0IvRtc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I recently played a round of golf at tsawwassen springs , and I have to say it was one of the most frustrating experiences I've had on a golf course. The pace of play was absolutely atrocious. It felt like we were moving at a snail's pace, and to make matters worse, the group behind us kept yelling at us to pick up the pace.

We tried to call the pro shop to address the situation and seek assistance, but no one answered the phone. I called three times, and each time I was met with silence. It was incredibly disappointing not to have any support or communication from the staff during such a frustrating round.

Overall, the lack of pace and the inability to get help from the pro shop ruined what should have been an enjoyable day on the course. I hope the management can address these issues for future guests. I certainly won't be returning anytime soon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Zaedyn","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWkD41PAsaR9K6IrqNQV5LAnCayNPuxcucgCCFcaHjyVPQql08=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Beautiful course, but when i went on from about 4-6, there was way too many mosquitos. Got 11 bites, and the mosquitos will follow you out of the cart and bite while you're trying to hit the ball so beware!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jason Kovacs","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXz29KIiEWuicCCRIXs6efgv2oy4z0w-d2WrZYZUMcC7Ge03Uk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great golf course that has only gotten better over the years! I was a Junior member back in the 90’s so I love coming back here when I can. The new pro shop and facilities are second to none.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOTa4OeoFEEH1DmBuJVJD_5qPJ8UL0PTmsGluk&fid=0x0:0xecd6f6fa8e77ba07"],"When":"2020-11-9"},{"Name":"Joseph Kudzin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLbXgpxz7F7dVM_TMXxcfZkeiADBqBD8Z8aYiqIXxtIFBkKMQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Tsawwassen Springs is not an easy Executive Golf Course. The Par 70 Course, provides a challenge for all levels of golfer.  Water, sand traps,  and high rough on some holes make precision tee shots a must.  A driver is not the club of choice on many of the Par 4 holes.  The smart play is to have the ball on the fairway for your approach shot.  Once on the green, you will find undulating surfaces that make 3 putts quite routine if you're not on your game. The Course is, however, fair and makes for a fun walk in the park. Enjoy!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Patrick Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWVCacCdOHJrDHjBmksff_WcgsSKXVHIV0dSGZpna2hTTSSTLVb=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Had a tee time at 4pm......and they ran out of pull carts. Nothing like a complimentary power cart(wishful thinking) I know. They said there will be some at the turn.  6pm came......still no pull carts. Whoever is in charge of purchasing.......please order more. This is the only course I've been to that has no pull carts.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Stephanie Maber","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8DGahQWQUa0E7cP6I5VrKcm-LE2NJiKP7PuCPCO_GcV8y7op3Ng=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"I used to get Freshii all the time and loved how big their salads are. Maybe it's just this location, as it's my first time at it, but for $13 I have never had such a small salad.

The salad base is $8.99 and then an additional $3.79 for chicken. As you can see from the photos there was hardly any chicken. And the bowl was not even full. When she handed it to me I thought it was a joke. It's empty. I actually asked for more dressing as it was invisible.

To top it off, they didn't even have lids so I had to drive home trying not to spill my little salad all over.

The girl working was lovely but I won't be back. Not worth the money. I'll go to subway next door who make the same kind of salad.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7DCp2vWHD4CJqyrvbvydQUnbO5DkTIPn1BVxs&fid=0x0:0x5d8d834085e8c4ec"],"When":"2023-4-4"},{"Name":"hesam bahremand","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWaf9uwWVj1F8UIlbqdk6V0gJ7Z8TmfSp3PUAwWhgOCv0Q07lVv=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Amazing delicious foods. I absolutely love their custom-built burritos with steak. Also, the bowls, wraps, and smoothies are sooo good. The staff are very nice, friendly and professional. It's also new and very clean. I'd definitely recommend it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMPYA5_kP6VPoFyxf5cw7kecyCs_ZMuAZ4tzK_H&fid=0x0:0x5d8d834085e8c4ec"],"When":"2019-9-30"},{"Name":"Lucy Yep.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyWEm1iVA5BhD52EO30x5805b5fs28qVCdlDvtJbrD1_d2ndv1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The manager is a very kind and friendly guy his customer service is incredible. The soups combo with a pocket are perfect for lunch and it is big enough for the price. The squash soup is amazing, must try it! The ginger shots are good too. Bowls are always recommended. Juices are availbleas well. The place is always clean. Close early on Fridays.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPUAYx0KxeWwDk_ri-fEkcD2VZOzKk1TZvwSZMR&fid=0x0:0x5d8d834085e8c4ec"],"When":"2022-3-4"},{"Name":"NJM","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKBkR932MbCAjGkzPVGYDorKNxOypr_oVD5Ao1M33EKI23cq_U=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Want to pay $9 for syrup drink that just loaded with chemicals and no real food come here... They try to say their all natural and healthy but just selling over priced syrup drinks watch them make it little to no real food is added... never again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bell Ini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIpRQhpgiMNwMiv-rrcHn_mSsRr-Y6iJ71DS78ZQ65Li5JoQw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Thought we would try out their new Freshii Beyond Chilli. Quite disappointed. The portions were small for the price. Rice on the bottom was dry and hard. Their so called beyond protein  was diced up.hard dry pieces overpowered by the rice and hot spices. We would like to know where the rest of our chili was. The smoothies were watered down
Again, half size cups at full cup prices. Will not be back.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOR8_YAxw87AqVQIKB7E5ejgqZpfj722G4qfU6B&fid=0x0:0x5d8d834085e8c4ec"],"When":"2019-11-17"},{"Name":"Lydia Elder","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXK4bFpSYWG4_r0XgZnnQPB1AU3Pu_Gldz-QG608aTBr8uNUB6K=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The staff here are lovely. So friendly, prompt & kind. The food is tasty, fresh (as the name implies!) and healthy. I always end up ordering the same thing (Oaxaca bowl w tofu) because it’s soooo good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Giordi Giacomelli","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocInSIkWNDV-4XEk3bR52dzgFj5TqktS4LFGMxFC37_WzshzJA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The man who served me had such a nice smile and was one of the friendliest workers I have ever encountered. Such a pleasant surprise! The food was also great and everything was sparkling clean. I'll be back!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jasmine Davis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdgu4G8_G1Grr_RmxDp0FIl47we0IfE3SZ35mQP1UtAFj7C-A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was such a great place to stop for a quick dinner! The food was delcious, tasty and OH SO FRESH. and their smoothies are to die for.

The owner and other workers here are so lovely and make the experience one to remember.

Thank you for your hard work, it was an awesome dinning experience, and I left feeling super happy and welcomed.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"xxxhearteaterxxx Meow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI6V2Wm_XqUa_aUk33-GPqWYZq7L24ZQP_nhY_9mbefGcMyLg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"For a pizza that I ordered that was supposed to be 5 cheese with Alfredo sauce, and extra cheese, it’s clear that mozzarella wasn’t even put on the pizza. Zero “cheese pull” factor and because of that, the Alfredo overpowered the whole thing. They didn’t even add cheese close to the crust either. Super disappointed. Won’t be ordering from here again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGVd5s-06Fr3JDo-bYWWNiziS7uiGN7g2hEorOk1Vp-qtDK_-cTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"I've had several bad customer service experiences here, once I was reprimanded for placing a small pickup order half an hour before closing and the other time an employee ignored us while we waited 15 whole minutes just to find out our order was there the whole time--she seemed very annoyed when we tried to grab her attention.
Quality wise it's ok but a little bland. You'd be better off getting pizza elsewhere by people who don't hate serving customers.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alex Grundy","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUh3zxS9QxZsRTtIzXiRV89XaemSZbcHJl9FgW2ISwM3Rp53ecL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I had order a few times with very little problem until yesterday.

I ordered two pizzas and an order of wings. Arrived a few minutes early. Waiting at the door and I see a mouse scurry from under the drink cooler back into the kitchen. Right then I should have just left, but I stupidly decide to continue- justifying it with the pizza ingredients are kept in the fridge and it’s fresh out of the ovens.

Get the pizzas and wings home, opened up. The pizza tastes fine. Grab a wing and suddenly feel like my thumb has been cut. Look down and there is some kind of shard of metal mixed in with the wings. Almost like from a dish washing brush but much stiffer. Okay. Well not ideal, but these kinds of things happen, right?

I call the number provided in my online receipt and after it rang through it routes me to corporate, explain the issue and they say it has to be done at the store level, transfer me. Rings through again and send me back to corporate. Explain the issue again and she goes to transfer me (again). I explain we have done that already. The next thing…... It was as if the phone was set on a table and left. Quiet. But I could faintly hear people in the background. I say “hello?hello?” But nothing. 15 seconds later I’m hung up on. Call back the store. Someone answers and says I need to call back at 6pm to speak to a manager. I call at 6:12pm. Manager isn’t in today, he is at Ladner- call there. So I do. He takes down my number and says he will call at 4pm the following day. Guess what? Doesn’t call.

These guys just don’t care at all about serving good food or you having a good experience. Money in the bank account, and they are stuck dealing with customers. Oh and the mouse issue. Yes, I reported to the heath inspection authorities.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Parm Sandhu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ9WRZGfqIdhPQjjwt2OgSs0i3tsZ82VEOIxhGl7h1UyIbS3g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The worst customer experience.  I called to place and order and first I got put on hold for about 4 minutes.  Then when the international student came back on the phone she couldn't take down my address correct.  I asked her to repeat it back to me and it was wrong.  I corrected her and asked her to repeat it back to me again and it was wrong.  I gave up and hung up the phone.  The food is garbage, it’s not Pizza Hut level.  Somebody please help this place or shut it down!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Richard Glasner","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlFSX_UUx6rW0lix6i7dkX9lVOSyBZB-F5xxqlskw_ZqxWVSPR=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great Definitely better than the Ladner location .","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shawn Hollywood","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJgEeOwuitaJvOzIZfynjqWUznHDHIVGoyFK-UPcXzT7ALV5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Decided to try this again after 6 months to see if anything has changed. CLEARLY, the owner doesn't care. Hard to believe, but it is WORSE. A triple crown pizza had not even enough meat to cover 1 piece per slice. They used, at best, 1 medium mushroom, sliced so thin, throughout the whole pizza. There were MAYBE 6 cubes of green pepper on the whole pizza. It's not like the chef couldn't tell either, as there was barely any cheese whatsoever onthe pizza. It was essentially undercooked dough.
Do yourself a favor, go to your local grocery store and buy a frozen pizza. It will be 100X better than this garbage. How this place is still open, is beyond me. They should be in jail for robbing their customers. This is anything but pizza. Even the raccoons that pillage your garbage wouldn't eat this.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Chris Murray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUvm-9fmZsNh3XhAST_u28ot_ESL2KvdrqyhUNJBCGbZ0fuKE-I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Gross cold pizza, more disgusting than pizza hut normally is. I don't recommend eating here. 4/5 of those in my house at the pizza and we all feel unwell today.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ruth Kaune","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKyjydWNOPwrxUrbmb-PeUkwOxJk8sTrxbRZyG8NLcztWTztw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Food wasn't ready on time. I used up my whole lunch break just to pick it up. When I got back to work, I discovered that they had given me those breaded boneless bites instead of the traditional wings. There was a dead mouse in front of the counter on the floor...","Images":null,"When":""}]

Super awesome pet friendly hotel will recommend to everyone!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Linda Herbert","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIHgCS_1LSidF8f9bp4SdCu68KTwEApuFyPY8wGxKI9VfKVgw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The best value for the money we have experienced in a very long time. Exquisite design of rooms in terms of lighting, materials, finish details. Outstanding breakfast included. Genuinely friendly, professional staff. Room immaculate. VERY quiet considering location on a busy arterial.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Georgina Langley","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIo-mgele4USmB0pPvdtl01J5bPGr8YKu2HlPN0z5E2MHfPXA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Hi, My vehicle ended up with a dead battery upon my checking out. Kevin and his colleague noticed me with the hood up and asked if I needed help. Don't know what I would have done without their assistance. Incredibly kind. This commitment to customer service and assistance is exceptional and so very much appreciated. I still made the ferry! Front desk and housekeeping staff are also wonderful.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Virginia N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QewvQXK08PhtQgCu1fT7TcdWcgcaXdOmFk48xW5xlmLo-Eqy0UOp2YqveGvl0etYz5BzA=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"For the third time, this is the best lodging I've ever stayed at. Their fitness room is better than many full-scale gyms. Maybe they provide class opportunities when not full of guests. Although there were meetings during my stay, there was no crowding. Breakfasts can be spectacular in Europe and South America, but seldom in Canada and the US. However, this hotel manages to provide something different each day, and that is one of the reasons I stay here, even though another establishment, of which I'm a member, is only a kilometer farther, but has the typical US-style breakfast. Finally, they always have more than one staff member available.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shelley H.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIogU86uNkZ48U2hpeuIRUpbvqikDHBU8IqJyL81wrpz1uJSA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Family Stay! Just checked out and our stay was fantastic 5/5. Comfortable, fresh and a welcoming. Breakfast was included and lots to choose from & our room had everything we needed. Thank you to all the staff for making our stay comfortable. We will be back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Natalie C","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/local-reviews/AJMZ0QeNj0UTN0yIrCGyJ0JhWwDODOg5QjAH0gdfB9Ji-oFl0zWFI-YVmhNAr-FGLycdpIjFmw=s120-c-br100","Rating":0,"Description":"What a magnificent hotel, the staff were all so welcoming, helpful and kind. We stayed in one of the family suites after an extremely long travel day and it sure was appreciated. The manager was nice enough to offer us the family suite instead of 2 separate rooms, what a kind way to lift our spirits. |Convenient for all of us and our pets while we moved from out of province, it was nice to have a room that felt like home, even if for a short time. |Having Brown’s Social House next door meant that we could settle in and not wander far at all for dinner. Breakfast in the morning was convenient and delicious. The beds and furniture comfortable and the bathtub was exactly what I didn’t know I needed after that long journey. |Our family had the first relaxing night in quite some time, we would definitely stay again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Wayne Antonishin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXB6uOugfLUMvjrshMlE1r6TvZdus5dG5khiu5U8x-kgakgA4h_=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Booked a king bed suite, and took the upgrade option to a suite with jetted tub. Worth the extra $36.00!!
Room was beautifully appointed with furnishings, including the wall art.
The beach, coastal, relaxed vibe was palpable.
Bed and pillows were very luxurious. Just sink in and rest after a good hot soak.
Would recommend to anyone.","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Ray","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXGVd5s-06Fr3JDo-bYWWNiziS7uiGN7g2hEorOk1Vp-qtDK_-cTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"Personally, not a fan of their regular menu items. They are quite salty and lacking fresh flavors to contrast the grease. This may scratch some people's cravings, though, as this is just my personal preference. Their curly fries are a classic, though, and always hot and crispy!

Every now and then, though, they will make limited time items that are great. Their pulled chicken sriracha sandwich and triple cheese turkey BLT sandwich are absolutely delicious. The sandwiches were so saucy and cheesy.

The strawberry milkshake is really thick and tastes like gummies.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXUQRgUcDt8NQs7dtgX0SeAAfkmqjijPlKtj5n&fid=0x0:0x95a4e6b532ee2163"],"When":"2024-5-23"},{"Name":"justin mckillop","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXycL53shbjuiaMD6urzpkXK-Gz6EEnmXV8W8247HHolXRLn9Od=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place was nice & clean. Friendly staff, good food! Very spacious. Lots of seating. Public washrooms available.  Highchair available for conveniency. Kids menu for the little ones. Good variety of food items to choose from. Lots of parking. A little tricky to get into the parking lot if you're not familiar with the area. Would go here more often if it was closer. Sucks there's only 2 locations to choose from!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPICWDwtVvykz1zRHAYGHg16tPNwpYp_mjt8M_q&fid=0x0:0x95a4e6b532ee2163"],"When":"2024-3-24"},{"Name":"Jen H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU4ziiKSXqfIKf0bikiIoBftFD2DejYRf_RBnE0G-0IBOO3x2vx=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"This location sold Gift Cards last winter, I received one as a gift. For the last 6 months I have not been able to redeem the card as they “don’t have a Gift Card Machine”. At first they said the issue would be fixed shortly. But months later, they have no idea if or when the issue will be resolved. So, they stole from their customers. They took our money in exchange for Gift Cards and now they refuse to allow us to redeem them. I’ve talked with the manager, I’ve asked if they can at least give us our money back or food coupons to compensate us, but nope. They took our money and they are content to not be responsible for their end of the deal. I’ve written in to Customer Service and I have called them. No one from this location or Franchise cares to deal with this illegal situation. This is totally unacceptable!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Dylan H","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUewRUS3Ydq2RJWFjKxTIaCd2qba4AaBYAfKLd_MEk6mfo-j8cy=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is my first time going to Arby’s and I’m not sure what I was expecting. The mozzarella sticks and 3 cheese sub were decent, not a fan of the sandwiches. Milkshake was great.

The staff were friendly and the location was quiet except for the drink machine making some strange noises.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jon Lo (VancityLolz)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyHXIvO6zjUGBm2q5mj88BnbYXYXFce_0_r9hk7c_P-UzKlHQRTg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Got the double roast beef sandwich and curly fries and chicken nuggets with crinkle fries. It’s pricey without a coupon but Arby’s is hard to find these days and the amount of meat you get really fills you up. Chicken is good quality as well.

Store is relatively clean, washroom so clean. At 1pm on a Sunday it was just full enough without feeling too busy.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJ6xOzhiQlvoD92VtZGMLgbaKmgQ2xPAT9ESld&fid=0x0:0x95a4e6b532ee2163"],"When":"2023-7-10"},{"Name":"Mohammadreza Behnejad","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXbfFjgusvHBDGevsLnSFlRH6CqkrxaSYgN1dtBgif3eqTdhnw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Absolutely delicious sandwich,
I wish they had more branches in lower mainland.
The store is clean and not too busy during the day.
Staff are nice.
Prices are decent and worth the taste.
Fries 🍟 was also good","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPDfNY0IA8X2xrnzl5V9Kay4y69ybugVG6esv8&fid=0x0:0x95a4e6b532ee2163"],"When":"2022-11-30"},{"Name":"Edgar Ignacio","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7oexz4qXoBKr6ujKuYxwMvlf16ckv-ovFMKFmC4nzUqeMSoelFA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba7-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Large burgers which are very tasty and their prices are affordable for the big portion that you get. Food are not greasy which is common for fastfoods like this. When you think of burgers and fries you came to the right place.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMDEKwST779TSuXVONDMROb4jofSC-SqFqlPhA-&fid=0x0:0x95a4e6b532ee2163"],"When":"2023-8-6"},{"Name":"Elephant Bea","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVmbTkWbvkzq9BEURa4cDUNDp_dqnBpyYXDtKQjP6X4hyrXm3Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Super friendly staff and clean washroom; unfortunately, the classic  burger is not my thing, I wish some lectures, tomato, and pickle to make it more balance. The bun has unique texture, very impressed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9mgUjB41TWyhMZChLwL0QVz_ib168dGto9ML8&fid=0x0:0x95a4e6b532ee2163"],"When":"2023-12-16"}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Lucy Yep.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWyWEm1iVA5BhD52EO30x5805b5fs28qVCdlDvtJbrD1_d2ndv1=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Four Winds is a new dining spot in Tsawwassen that offers an a good selection of food and drinks. One of their standout options is the beer flight, which provides an opportunity to sample various unique flavors. While I found some of the dishes a bit on the oily side, the overall taste was good. The cod burger was difficult to eat as the fish was super soft.

If you’re looking to avoid long wait times, making a reservation is highly recommended. The booking process is straightforward, and it even allows for specific requests like special occasions. However, while they do ask if you're celebrating something special, the service doesn’t come with perks like complimentary desserts, which could feel like a missed opportunity for adding a more personalized touch.

The all humans bathroom is very uncomfortable experience.

The patio is a great dining option on sunny days, adding to the vibrant ambiance.

Inside the place is too loud and it is difficult to enjoy a conversation.

Additionally, the customer service is outstanding; the staff is attentive just no need to ask if everything was ok so many times. In general they are very friendly which enhances the dining experience and makes you feel welcome.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPpfUVGMRRIqTa7WNaHKRsavvADl_-5U78K69Ex&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-11-11"},{"Name":"Andrew Giassa","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKs2M8Lm_fO5YMx6QeBO4bPk3OR_tJ-4_oCO6-v2DtArGT_4g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Went to Four Winds post Boundary Bay Marathon for some celebration drinks and food! I have been to the Annacis Island location in the past, which I really enjoyed, however first time at the Beach House! I love the open space, high ceilings, decor, and ambiance! Had a big selection of food at the table, which was shared! Everything was so delicious, my favourite being the chowder (special) and Brewmaster burger! The s'mores dessert was so tasty too! As always, excellent beer with my favourite being the dark lager! Our server Izzy was super friendly and efficient, and that goes for the other staff too! Very wonderful experience! I would recommend to friends/family and will be returning!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO8p0Zs4-6am4DCganVb2SW9dpfeso-G-Cmqmq5&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-11-4"},{"Name":"Erica Bearss","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUDaS88i8UI0EGR8dmybERXtdUX7zrkVtQV_GqB74oaYyXXVe_JrA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This was our first time at Four Winds Beach House and Brewery. The experience exceeded expectations. The atmosphere was perfect and the patio was an ideal complement to the gorgeous weather. Loved the open concept inside and out. Our server, Annalise, was phenomenal and made our experience one we will never forget. The butter on the pull apart bread set the stage for even better mains. Order the Smores Bar—it will blow your mind. We paired dessert with an espresso martini and a rum spiked root beer float for a flavour combination that was truly world class. We will be back as often as we can.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7XFCpeGcMo0HrzdbLJLDO44OXSVCOF7Aifuw5&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Bobby Bedi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVhxgbY0n0zWF3qsYcFT7w4K-aoSZ7dS8epGuHDyXmvvSfvyb9f5Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐
Four Winds Beach House and Brewery is a gem in Tsawwassen! They offer some of the finest beers in Western Canada, and the food is equally impressive—truly top-notch quality. The ambiance is sophisticated yet welcoming, and the outdoor patio is perfect on sunny days, making it a fantastic spot to relax and enjoy. Prices are great for the high-end experience they provide. You really have to come and see it to believe it—hands down the best brewery in Western Canada!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMwUaRnKAGM9QK_5XLAJ-fGDM1NkgchA7pWW7p6&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-10-3"},{"Name":"Linda Hansbauer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbhYntSwrf3fPiWmrNihB_RxxZEX6epZ6NkhTpeBuOWgHv5aaF=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I  am a visitor from Australia 🇦🇺 🪃  and we decided to check out the recently opened establishment. Ambience nice - decor very pleasing to the eye. We only had drinks, and the kids had some truffle chips.  Water or sparkling water was offered - nice touch.  The beer we decided to have very tasty -  the consistency of pouring a beer - was not 300 ml as stated on the menu - every glass was different levels - judge for yourself.
I am sure after a couple of weeks all the new  staff will have all the training necessary,  to work in such a
nice and new upcoming restaurant. After writing this - I checked other reviews - customers made the same comments about the beer pouring. Overall, the place looks inviting - it is going to be very cosy, with the beautiful  fireplace - when the weather gets cold - so all the best to the staff and management.
My family will be back - the kids loved the sheets of drawing options, and it kept them entertained. Thank you!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNksgD8VwxT63_D7k_XOsuyx1M3e0q1z7p8A9kf&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"Em","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXwT6tEzL3WJcfKi-6wpRMOJI1G-6s5wZxB5kN0OUIQi9PuSdOk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"First time being here and it was excellent. The vibe was great, the service was immaculate and the food was delicious. We got some drinks, sourdough bread and oysters to start. Had the beach house burger and the brewmaster for dinner and tried the lavender cheesecake for dessert. All of it was  10/10. Had the pleasure of interacting with a Robert, Jesse, Etem and Barry. Excellent customer service will be back for sure. Definitely check this place out!  No TV’s, perfect for date night or a night out with friends. Four winds gives you more of an intimate vibe. Loved it! Oh and try the lemon aioli with your fries.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPBudFkkb_9hwfkCOrxdzZ13m2_elE8gA8LmMkI&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-12-4"},{"Name":"Ofri Livneh","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX16STGcz1WkHjUy4qq_7S8xXO7R5LIxtHEuX0qTlmdW8ybL5ZH=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is outstanding! Food, atmosphere, service and everything in between.
What a great combination of flavours that explodes in the mouth.🎉
Service is fantastic and the chef should definitely be rewarded for his creativity and work of art!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipODEYHDHLukdB22ja-dOmF6mSvd2qNrK6JEyFDF&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-11-20"},{"Name":"Jeff and Cat Chang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUuaO4qWxQoHYN_xctVA-vkdLQu4qoKrOrAaxWLOEhghP9fOzs=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Checked this place out all the way from Vancouver and it was defintiely worth the trip out! For a brewery, we were surprised by how good the cocktails were. We had their version of a Paper Plane and a Negroni, both with a fun beer element to them.

The food is the real standout though. I didn't get a chance to take a photo of the bread roll and fancy butter, but it was literally to die for. I would have ordered just the bread.

We had the chicken piccata which was like a schnitzel but chicken, it was flavourful and crispy. The sald of golden beets and stone fruit was really nice as well, peach with basil? What a combo. If it's cold outside we'd recommend asking for a spot in the main dining room area. It's so cool and has an amazing fireplace.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN8RbS-FPABUCkTrEne9_OeoVJD5V8oXHqjWjDv&fid=0x0:0xafb9ff01afcb06e7"],"When":"2024-9-17"}]

[{"Name":"Azeen Khehra","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbM4K_boQ6PMOv25M1oqKSMGP8lxPEx1Yl6h3dWkGtJQA0Vw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst Service By Komalpreet..
Firstly i asked for Flatbread pizza n she said we can’t make it n then i ordered 3 bagels and she burnt them all n when i asked for atleast 1 new bagel she started arguing like this is not your store..
If u have authority to remake the stuff then why u can’t just make it without arguing..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPKU7qMUy3CG5W4k5w38TYqusFfu-hqi71YMe-&fid=0x0:0x6a3e2578d4976537"],"When":"2024-11-3"},{"Name":"Joan Crawford","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLLEB6f0HvP3lLgbpMMDeVhv3jySnL9qESYJriLzyQB-uGSBw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"l had the worst experience and last experience at this TH.   The drive through young woman charged me over $7 for steeped tea and a croissant with plain cream cheese.  I asked her why it was such a high price today???   She didn't answer just started to give me my tea and then a water bottle.  I had not ordered a water bottle.  She said l did. I had ordered a cup of water.   She gave me back my money and then got another order to deal with.  I drove away without my sandwich.  I came back and went inside and told the girl at the til.  She said she saw me get my money for my sandwich back from the drive through girl.  I had to argue with her that was for the water bottle l did not order.  .  Then she kept backing up her co worker.   The girl at the drive through forgot to HAND me my sandwich after she had to refund that water bottle.  Holy talk about two rude young women.
I think the two men who run the driveway through are very rude but they are great compared to these two young women.   I also think some of the drive through staff talk way to fast.   It seems like a competition to them to get everyone in and out fast.  This person. At the window was talking way to fast too.  Good grief.  Slow down.

Train your staff better!!!!!

I have heard many people upset about the staff in this particular place.  You are loosing customers.  There are no long line ups at this TH like at Starbucks on Canoe Dr.  Maybe a short rush at lunch sometimes but not really compared to other TH.

They need to learn some skills for dealing with the public.
I will never go back to this place.

This article does not include the few wonderful polite ones they have there.  You know who you are.    Get a job somewhere else quick.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Bradley Dougherty","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJqgGwHhnGDE0p20s1bs7ju-N01GgzCaA_vBAarBf3FDMzl3w=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Never had a problem here up until today, actually have always raved about how fast and accurate this particular location usually is.

HOWEVER!
Lately service has been lacking, as has friendliness, which is evident by the negative reviews as of late.

On a more serious note.
Today, there was a very long line, and as I was sitting there watching and waiting for my turn at the drive thru window (I was next), I watched as one of the Tim Hortons staff members threw garbage out the window onto the ground.
I clearly watched this happen, and it was absolutely intentional, there was no way it was an accident.
When I got to the window a few seconds later, I told him I saw that, and I received every excuse possible.
I just want to make it extremely clear, that there is absolutely no excuse for this. And that this is absolutely despicable behaviour and does not represent the value and culture of Tim Hortons.
If I ever see this happen again, I will be making plenty of phone calls
1. To corporate and reporting the franchise
2. To Bilaw and filing a complaint
3. To Tsawwassen Mills as they will fine the location

Honestly, shocked that I witnessed that this morning. And I expect some sort of conversation to happen within your staff.

This happened Thursday Dec 19 at approx 12:15pm","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Harshpreet kaur","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI5Cj17k5VGtavNvEKNXlsO0TNgLjgRGfjoOu0k0yqqzuXFYA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I usually have a decent experience at Tim Hortons, but today was exceptionally frustrating. We ordered a bagel through the drive-thru and politely asked the staff member, SUKHMAN to cut it in half, as we’ve done countless times before. Shockingly, she refused, stating they couldn’t do it. When we mentioned that this has never been an issue in the past, she remained rude and unhelpful.

Customer service is crucial, and being treated with disrespect is unacceptable. I hope management takes note and ensures that all staff members are trained to be courteous and accommodating. This experience has made me reconsider returning to this location.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Prikshit Rana","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLq5VJ7JI4qmRlPo86l2o2-zO_2DcOzTGR_PrhvjdeVPjLqTZw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst experience ever, the staff is rude and untrained. Firstly, they took the wrong order, Secondly, they kept the order on the counter and didn't even call for it. When we asked if it was our order, they had no clue the guy who took the order literally said to his coworker "I have no idea whose order is this". We were confused too, because we ordered Oreo ice cap and it was a normal ice cap. But, later he confirmed it was our order. But when we went to call out for the wrong order, it's hard to get hold of them, they act so busy when there are hardly 1 customers and they are 6-7 servers. Then the person insisted, we have ordered the normal ice cap ( trying to say, we were wrong), but changed the order later and took too long, almost cleared all orders before our's. No wonders why the store hardly had any customer.

Lastly when we asked to talk to manager, he was the same guy who took our order. Even we were speechless, if the manager doesn't know what he is doing, I can imagine the team. In customer service Half of the battle i lost, when you have a uninterested face while talking to customer, and these guys was uninterested to take the order and deliver the right one.

All the staff including the manager are so busy when there is no rush, I don't understand how?, when I was calling a guy, literally standing next to the counter, he ignored as if he didn't listen, after 4 loud calls. Guys if you want customer to wait despite listening to customers call, please ask the customer to wait, don't straight away ignore. All the faces were full of disappointment and feel like they don't wanna work. I have been to such busy Tim's where they have 50 orders at a time, still they smile, and treat customers the way they should be treated. At least call for the order when it's ready. Uninterested faces while taking orders, rude looks when someone is calling out for wrong order, will not make your life easy, it will piss off the other person, ruin their mood and endup in a bad review.

And when I saw the reviews of this place, no wonders there were a lot of people not happy with the service. TH Management please look at it, you are losing customers. If the staff don't wanna work, please change them, because looking at the reviews I am sure they don't wanna improve themselves.

I am not visiting this Tim's again, but this is concerning for Tim Hortons management, so many complaints from one particular branch. Please act now do not wait for a major mess in the future.

P.S:- Kudos to Tim's King George SkyTrain station, one of the best Tim's, they seamlessly handle such a huge rush at all times and most importantly with a smile.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"James Quiros","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVKBj9KhrHnpMxkWmoQzGoAbAt71NnBp7_tWZzxU2BlPDYiaYF8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I went last night about 5 minutes to closing time and was told they were already closed?! Then i read the reviews on this location about how incompetent the staff is, needless to say i will NEVER go back there and will advise everyone to read the reviews for this location so they can save themselves the trouble of going  to a Tims where the staff clearly doesnt care about the clients.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Abu Osman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUNYQrpSAPmNBexWcQ-TK_wz6eRdBlO1nmK8dr1rofYisDgjlNB=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Watch out your bill always they will charge you extra and when you cache it they will claim it's donations by Tim Horton out of ourcontrol & I didn't get how dare charged without your permission.? 😤
And the worst they cancel your orders if you don't except it.!!?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Francesca","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLSsNoBEHmQ0RfDPJstcswSnNys4JvxuLG7zyvkRIgS0XbOLrk=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Worst customer service ever. [{"Name":"Jeremy Hannaford","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVJh4gJaa4fTCJIngBRIGMrmmqMdx4ZxIh5c_eHCdtOqz7VOAFhyQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Pretty swell coffee place. Great atmosphere and decor. Also has a ton of community related items on the wall, including art pieces for sale and animal adoption info.
Oh and the coffee and croissants were pretty darn good!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN3ETX0nuNAe2YJf1ow_IB754lGRdwYAQK8Lfdw&fid=0x0:0x25ec062c21bbff3f"],"When":"2024-7-3"},{"Name":"A M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUeebfnK5XN9sLBosxHSVgANpfNEAx82Msa9wpAjERgqubi84yG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The coffee here is amazing — rich and perfectly brewed. And the croissants? Hands down the best I’ve ever had, and trust me, I’ve tried a lot of them! Flaky, buttery, and fresh. The service was friendly and attentive, and the space is so spacious and inviting. I’ll definitely be coming back for more!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"EV NA","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKkrFEYUDX56vJrEozPX61XeE38WxjNbtQFPsVaCY2-cAwrUA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The demands of such cafe owners really upset me, hence giving this place one star:
- really needed something sweet after a long flight/day and I came across this place and thought 'great, I will have a nice cake'.  Not only was the Mango cake very dry and tasteless but it was priced around 6 dollars!!!!!  What a con!!!
- to add insult to injury, the thin guy with glasses reading a book decided to push his paying device asking me to tip him for moving his behind from the cake stand to the paying point looking at me like a vulture.  I felt so intimidated and I felt like saying 'no, I do not think you deserve a tip for doing your job while the rest of us work for peanuts too' but I was too sick and tired for that, so I just tipped him to eat a bit of that awful, dry cake with some mango concoction on top and lots of dry dough in the middle.  How old was that cake, I wonder: most surely a few days.  So yes, I would give 0 stars if I could.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOh3nDxk9HsJ0FPFmLrxIlO7m4y9ASGK9F4R_1G&fid=0x0:0x25ec062c21bbff3f"],"When":"2024-7-8"},{"Name":"xs2 Guds","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUXL1MtZr55okeMBEgHO08piUEZFinJ_btlIvM0JYQi_q_K-RRt=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Love the ambience, lovely place. Hidden gem. One of the best coffee shops in Vancouver area. Baked goods are really good. A perfect spot to relax. Ample seating & easy to get a nice spot.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNccm9XXcPaeZuTGJKoaErA9pqUO4VNtjT6Ze-C&fid=0x0:0x25ec062c21bbff3f"],"When":"2024-5-26"},{"Name":"Felix Mann","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjURZHNzaXnL1eYNqk8_OZ0MlZR_GVqIuKwaqUOLUCixCtcS6tjNvg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very cute family-run business. The atmosphere is great for after school studying and the mix of staple café drinks with a cycling list of unique refreshers keeps the menu exciting. I especially loved the multiple community-oriented bulletin boards, including a board for local artists and a different board showcasing animals currently up for adoption from a local shelter. The food and drink were fantastic, I had the sunset refresher and a scone and my partner the mocha. Both drinks were fantastic. user_reviews: [{"Name":"Telemark1107","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJUpVy0BwbUBm1hRVoKm9qdT6KU-oGzmNFiKfvYbAQdr6ujhA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Have had meals from this restaurant many times over the years. Portion of noodles appeared to be fine but then watched as the server picked through the broccoli, piece by piece and green beans the same - no scooping. The guy serving me was obviously hating his life. He was very blunt and looked angry the entire time. I bought a 3 item meal for just under $15.00 and he put a very small portion of chow mein and 3 very small portions of the items I ordered. The vegetables looked great behind the counter but his little scoop he gave me was just cabbage. He avoided the good stuff. The lemon chicken didn’t taste of lemon at all and was very hard and crunchy. The lady that took payment was in a better mood. I showed her my tiny meal and said that the portion size is small and doesn’t reflect the price. She said oh and clearly didn’t care. The lady in front of me got a 2 item and had a very small portion as well. I wouldn’t be surprised if I get food poisoning. If this is how they run the front of their business, imagine how they run the back! I hope the dude behind the counter finds some happiness in his life because he’s nothing short of a miserable, rude little man. Cheap cheap cheap!!!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kenny A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIszkS3SPMCAMG_Zt7q84-znT660uc0lWm6BjOs10PChRby8w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I should have checked the reviews on this place first.\nDishonest service. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Alex Thornton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIqxhEuh7iMg1REQztI_a_NmEsojkE3hjn3QZVAdAdUeR_q5g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Willing to remove the review if not the correct place. In memory, this has always been the Centennial Beach Cafe/"the only place to get food and ice cream". There are however multiple listings across different websites, which show the same photo and menu but have a different name and disconnected phones. This phone number exists, connection is very poor. Unable to report food poisoning, and inquire if cross contamination is contributing.

Food taste: decent. It was acceptable chicken strips and fries, difficult but possible to mess up. Decent price (~$10) and quick service (midday midweek).","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Martin Urban","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXml4QRvTUaJIyaJ-ZUsBBE6AKLU5lKvyna3vp5WxSaWzOYBzM=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Whoever is managing this establishment needs to have a serious look at their operation. Understaffed. Very long wait time. Food could barely be called food. Chicken nuggets overcooked on outside and mushy inside. Guessing oil was too hot? Burger meat was so cheap.. then poorly cooked.. grey, cold and mushy. Fries.. which I cannot believe could be messed up, were raw in some.. cold and soggy. You could hear the poor staff slamming the microwave over and over trying to get orders out and keep the mush warm. Waiting for order you could hear server constantly tell customers they were out of everything. Bought food for children but after trying my own then inspecting theirs I couldn't in any right mind let them eat it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Lance Kersey","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWR3WRn7HK2MQheFyDOVZykp-TWmPuOU3RYPYGWUvPDx5hFgCiG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"They had sandwiches on the menu with grill marks, I thought they were paninis. What I got was a sandwich grilled just long enough to leave marks, but the ingredients inside were cold and cheese unmelted. The ham was a single 1/4" thick slice instead of sliced thin like normal. Like how do you screw up a ham and cheese panini so badly?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sherryl Jane","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocITtNJZ4YTk6ZBZiEJOQnw31bf9k2QsOEpFwY_Oya8-rbrYWg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Was told the kitchen service was closed by management just as I got to the front of the line to order. Only drinks and ice cream available. Pretty frustrating since I heard the lady right before me give a full order complete with fish and chips, drinks and burgers.  This was on a sunny weekend in the summer at about 1pm - so lunch rush. Kitchen was to remain closed for up to an hour because they had "too many orders to go through".

I see another reviewer posted 5 hrs ago about being told wraps all of a sudden not being available (p.s. they were available until I got to the front of the line).

Little ones did not have their picnic and had to leave the beach to get food.  There was no way we were driving in and out for food to deal with finding parking and setting up on the beach again.

Ownership needs to address this as they lost quite a bit of business with such poor planning. Who closes their kitchen in the middle of a lunch rush?","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"H N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUTZ8cYDAqXtEuYt1yP_KsOvkuqkfDpZ-PQ6vd6BeFrSLl_lJSAPQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Prices could be better, but because of its prime location, it's a popular spot for beachgoers to grab a quick bite or a cold drink. There's also an indoor seating area.

My iced coffee ($3.55 plus tax) was a little acidic but hit the spot on a hot day. Loved how it came with a paper straw :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Alina P.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIlpcCKdtSIxZ4i-IvD0ozIIbEce-uA8ASaPlBoDa09u5pUD0w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Terrible customer service and dishonest employees. I asked for chicken wrap, but girl replied that they don’t do wraps at all today. But that was untruth because my friend ordered the same wrap 10 mins ago. [{"Name":"Jessica","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJnnZqxktJrDaNsm7KOZh9NgHj2A7QIL8-M179TSd8zvm2hRQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered an egg salad sandwich terrible. The egg salad has no flavor, and the bread; even with toasting, was stale.
This is my 3rd time in 3 years trying to give this place another chance. Everytime I am majorly disappointed.

They need to add a panini press and more condiments- if it's a sandwich place. They also had an issue adding hot sauce to my sandwich, offering to give it to me on the side to add. Who wants to take apart a sandwich to add sauce 🙄.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amal Behih","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK6Ua82EfMANkZjk6NcXHFV2UdnXyhPtMdovcevFXGw_z6Ltw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolutely terrible service. Server was snappy while we were trying to decide what to order. I asked if what I was about to order is sandwich or not and she snapped « tell me A or B » when we opened the container of food all the condiment packets were sitting on the eggs contaminating the food since we saw the condiments were retrieved from the counter, what’s the point of wearing gloves you might as well spit on the food.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tarek Belghith","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlygJfGwFrU1uyatLdJMdTVBLhomUupKh6cH2lcum6HMK58UEYyg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"This is a snack place that you can go to during the (sometimes long) wait for the ferry in Tsawassen terminal. This sky way gourmet has some areas of improvement, however, the food court is clean and well maintained, free public washrooms are also available for all genders, and the announcements are made on time to go back to the cars whenever needed.
Reviewed by Tarek Belghith from RZ Network Inc Ottawa Ontario Canada.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Krista Eglin","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJufJ-XxV5-otgzJI9kHMyl39PzkpjmuAYI0S0l0CvwIOynHw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Bread was typical grocery store bread, they don't ask what you want on the sandwich and seem upset when you specify what you would like. Terribly over salted. You could purchase all the ingredients for the price of one sandwich. Would not visit again .","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"John Baril","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX-KbecDjSyxFjz-Gk-B9uwtt5D6BouiBi-D5loK0kQp-i_MMc=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Service was extremely rude and slow. Had to run to get to ferry. Food was terrible. Toast was soggy.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Olivia Delisle","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXHQnBB03VSlx8ylxVp5cBw02z696Kghv8LMGoih7-n458lllxf=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"THE BEST SANDWICH I’VE EVER HAD! I had the vegetarian sandwich and it was absolutely amazing, seriously I think i’ll drive down to the ferry terminal just to get this sandwich again. It was so good. Amazing job.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thomas Fraser","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX_MTZjKM3wQcAFvXL7bqoT7ebDl65pypZ4BQzwzJbTo4C5jxu9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Their grilled cheese sandwich is two cheap slices of slightly warm bread witg a slice of cheap cheese. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Jaime Schwalb","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL0k_RsxKo5a-kB3AorfktSrxvR9V3MF4fXl8QS5RhuobvPkA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolute abomination!
Mac and cheese was basically a frozen meal. Saddest excuse of a smoke meat sandwich. Chili was "meh" and the hot dogs...... The hot dog were something else. Revolting to look at and in no way, were they "cooked".
Currently working on a time machine, To stop myself from even considering eating there ..","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM4slGHVnSwlxHIWc86BTP5pq5Mj-rKbXsO-kL5&fid=0x0:0x7ec8345a36365c41"],"When":"2024-8-29"},{"Name":"Kate O'Connell","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLrHDOrpvH995ukRPqXoWR_CL4zLkAAlPcQa6cXAPUWKz0i8Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Terrible doesn't accurately describe it. The soft pretzel tasted very doughy and underdone (and they forgot my dip). The pulled pork sandwich was bland and (how my friend described it when I sent a photo to her) "looks like sadness". Nothing even resembling barbecue here.

If you're trying to decide between eating on the ferry or eating here, just eat on the ferry. It's worth the price to just wait rather than go here.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNywchDRVzg9TkpdoBfq52EB5VXLHXZ9Lejc68m&fid=0x0:0x7ec8345a36365c41"],"When":"2023-10-15"},{"Name":"Sean M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLuH1YhaCzOLpfxjElEa100PBM4PuZHQFbC8ShAMdWflMTU9A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered a hot dog, for something quick grab and go. The hotdog was cold the pizza sauce was cold. The dog itself was full of hard bits, hard to imagine how someone could get a hotdog wrong but they did. 0/10 would advise against going here","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"james hong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIuUy2OG4Bplbxj_Ym7mbYDtZs9FWrEHXAQ_lSJQm4W1YCgQg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Not even close to what we call A sandwich. Bread smells. Yellow yacky mustard all over. Spoonful amount of meat. What a pity amount of saukercraft and it was not even close to be eatable. This is not a place to eat. The best choice in this complex would be surely Starbucks at the end....I wish I could find it sooner.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Scott Osselton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKjonqtCZN6XwoFo8pronPjlTmfjuoCUhY_FzwegLVDFdKsHw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I'd rather go hungry then eat here again. To start there was confusion over what a chili cheese dog was. My wife ordered a smoked meat sandwich that was mainly cold. The wings we got was not even tossed in sauce and just drissaled.  Waited 30 minutes for wings and received disapoinment. Save your money you'll be better off hungry.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMLJS0sBTxeXzVR2GpeHVbO_JWm9IZxwAbnIncf&fid=0x0:0x7ec8345a36365c41"],"When":"2023-8-14"},{"Name":"Dez Robin Mudryk","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV_cPTWAlnaqJ5O1sMeAmtFRpKiRe3sj-ufWHOeANNNwNqamRPG3Q=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"The absolute grossest beef dip I’ve ever had the unfortune of eating. 🤢. The bun was soggy. The meat tasted like soaked cardboard and the dip… the dip was salt water. So bad. Skip at all costs.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sharen Fraser","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUBfu-TQambQsa34adUgRSfH7DJgBxECc8sqPj3Lh_tuq_2c4Ly=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Absolutely inedible hard as a rock old,and I mean ancient old cooked many days or weeks ago and then microwaved.  Shameful.  Gross food way overpriced and you get not to see the food inside the container before they hit you with the huge bill and the person stands over you watching as you have the tip screen before you can pay.   Expensive and total garbage I would not feed an animal.  Seriously I had no idea that chicken wings could be that hardened!!   You would need an ice pik to eat these.  What a total waste of money.  Food safe needs to make a pop in visit at this joint.  Gawd awful!!!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPU2lqvHvWF2wmfVvBYU7jyckbQG8Nhrc4pUUzB&fid=0x0:0x7ec8345a36365c41"],"When":"2021-10-29"},{"Name":"Jeff CW Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU8bpPZBvR1j3TlvpPVyXUanNDJtYUNWxzSDHhUL8e4emrpLcCl3w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Chili was very mid, with more beans than meat and kinda watery for chili. But considering it is one of the cheaper options (that being said a small ball still cost $6) I might still get it next time if I absolutely must.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Susan Ninow","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXvpaRTEsl5529afMOwnBLq388-585p02laQsfHHAaEAmlKrIjM6w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I enjoyed an excellent Vietmese lunch. I ordered the  #39 Grilled lemongrass chicken, grilled shrimp skewer & deep fried spring roll on vermicelli. The server was warm and friendly. It was a nice quiet break from the shopping at Tswassen Mills.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO72GY8-dhldxyawhYUZGrTC2AacHuMfoBl_ead&fid=0x0:0x556fbf4d6a36e4d1"],"When":"2024-11-30"},{"Name":"Manigill Artistry","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJK9NIda3oChxEGR3J-3v3ycBS2zLnkW6R17UPv48bu28LosA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I would love to share my positive experience at Simply Pho in tsawwassen. The customer service was excellent!! (Which I feel is a rare thing to find these days)
They got my order wrong (which is fine accidents happen). I called to let them know. She apologized and right away offered to remake it. I wasn’t able to come back the same night. She said that was not a problem and that I could come back anytime and they will make sure it’s made just like I wanted. She was so sweet that she wrote down the exact order in a book with my name in it. I went there the next day, told them my name and they quickly made it. I personally I talked to the day before (I think the owner) was in the back. She came up to me handed me the order and kindly apologized again.
I was so impressed by their costumer service and professionalism.
Would totally recommend. The food is delicious and the staff/owner are amazing people!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Peter Cross","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUHmBXMXmX9-43PxxMc-vQWx8OaX3r8ByLsfhp1pyyCEQpdxmTkCA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It is a great spot for a quick meal away from the mall.  Great service, casual atmosphere.  Enjoyed our food.  We came looking for simple food and we enjoyed what we had.  The Pho was decent the Bahn Mi was excellent.  Wonton soup was decent.  Good lunch.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMO8W9YhrgF4L7XuTprORno7l_54tt6KkUiIa66&fid=0x0:0x556fbf4d6a36e4d1"],"When":"2024-3-30"},{"Name":"Albert Tseng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXd8up1SL2_CgEKQqYkLsRy_rqI3XAZq1E2pyXoHzBM5ViX_L0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We came at a raining day; not too busy; yet the service is great and the rice noodle I ordered is perfect; can’t say more; if you are a pho lover; do find time to visit","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipP4kaq8oBcsZ_a8052fIkrTwR3hGhcFGZH24n7x&fid=0x0:0x556fbf4d6a36e4d1"],"When":"2024-10-2"},{"Name":"Brian Shaler","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVanm_SU1M6cSuCRW78pg1T2oWnXPERDUCzn8bF70zKPszCwZw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The food choices in the area lack inspiration to say the least as most are your typical fast food. Don’t even get me started on the pathetic mall food court. This is one of the better options in the area if you want a step up. Is it an amazing bowl of pho? Nah…. But it’s better than decent and the restaurant feels clean and fresh.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNmQG6x9xFzjXQBEILpb_obOw4NS3XE1lrgqnwa&fid=0x0:0x556fbf4d6a36e4d1"],"When":"2023-5-1"},{"Name":"Vinculis","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjQ_62BAyqo-Ft14RaNkBZoMPoW-RyhYZgEg5uKOF95TtvT7_I=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We ordered a #3, two #59 (mine with no onion or sprouts), an order of chicken wings and an order of the fried squid. All of the noodle dishes were delicious! The bun bo hue had nice flavour and they gave us extra chili oil since we like it spicyyy. The wings and squid were fried fresh! Crispiness on the wings were in point. Definitely recommend a squeeze of lime on both the squid and the wings!

The staff were all super attentive and kind. It was very busy in there today but the staff were all in great moods and constantly checked in on how we felt about the food. We didn't feel rushed and our tea cups were always full! Definitely my recommendation if you're looking for pho in Ladner/Tsawwassen!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7w6NJBs913rqpsH_8yM_Nt3SH1JTT0YdnWZV7&fid=0x0:0x556fbf4d6a36e4d1"],"When":"2023-12-27"},{"Name":"Da Wanderer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW6gUX2zsQKdIE8uVzYWBnKKtvYQAJfEKJppzMJqd4hE4TuUun8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"A lot of people walked in during the time we dined in for lunch so I thought this must be a popular place in the area. It is clean and the atmosphere is so so. The servers are pleasant and efficient but the House special pho is very basic. I could name a few more pho places who serves a lot better.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMA7XkozF61B3APzpNc93kJT9ClS5c_Rcu-AeRG&fid=0x0:0x556fbf4d6a36e4d1"],"When":"2023-4-1"},{"Name":"Alexander Hunt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKntg94WsHup3cVgJBk3yO0jaRf4K-ndL2T0xGy94s_gBQtie8=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Came here with my family earlier on in the year so this review is long overdue; however, I still want to share my opinion. We ordered the noodle soup (Number 2/ 3). It was good. The restaurant was clean and tidy. We also ordered the spring roll.

I was actually surprised by the amount of soup in the noodle soup as I was expecting the dish to be primarily made out of noodles, beef slices and beef balls. Let the other Google users know if that has changed in the last couple of months when you dine or takeout for this restaurant.

Please refer below for pictures of the menu and restaurant dining atmosphere.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOP6gNRAhOqOYnJI3kjt3CjIjIsFUFonSW8ZNj6&fid=0x0:0x556fbf4d6a36e4d1"],"When":"2022-9-3"}]

(Oct 22/23). Food is great and you get lots:) I recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMYUsXJ-fg9x7_JbgTguhnbWiViJ9SxONaO_0gi&fid=0x0:0xc8bfcf8c24614d1a"],"When":"2023-10-22"},{"Name":"Hwa D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwQyjGi41SNIX6tVkw-8BfQdSHpbL_wDTFcZShwlM2dHZ3e1AW_w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I eat here occasionally because it's tasty~~ But personally, it's too sweet for me.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNN010DLw3XjG7-vZqND-EbvlBGXAHPeEGJ6oiZ&fid=0x0:0xc8bfcf8c24614d1a"],"When":"2024-2-5"},{"Name":"Birdie Num Nums","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJBzLW4KUsOcs0EFkZlh9-ZoYKK_5ax9JIIIF84dPwTxMMqmw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We shared a combo 3 with green beans (yummy and still slightly crisp) noodles (delicious with a hint of peanut) and sweet and sour pork, and sesame chicken. Both were awesome.

Maybe it was because the food court was slammed that the food was so tasty and fresh, they were busy and replaced dishes quickly.

It was better than any Chinese I’ve had in a while. Surprised it came from a food court but we really enjoyed it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ela Ipek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJm-1cHw3nOfaCpM_WpaMt2IcR1W53GRbOoqKHc7-xkANpKUxn8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Terrible experience. My mother was asking to put a little bit of noodles for my brother and they kept putting a lot. When they finally put a little bit we got some chicken (5 pieces) in there too. We got a different box filled with 2 spring rolls, some chicken and zucchini (5 pieces each). We started to pay and they charged us $22 for barely any food. We asked if they were going to weight it and they said no because it was considered a "combo". It's too expensive, if we had known we would've gotten more food. They were really quiet and didn't really explain it to us. The food wasn't even so tasty, the noodles tasted dry and there was too much sauce on the chicken. The zucchini didn't taste like zucchini should. I don't recommend this place. My family and I won't be coming back.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Farid Entezari","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV35QQyx2JmA30yOGa4kCXMTDZjBP0mMYjKzM0CL9HNh-FF7LAEEA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Quality of food was good, portion size was good as well.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOltecLold9xiTtGmjKpK_PuvJeaehJnuoFuBGF&fid=0x0:0xc8bfcf8c24614d1a"],"When":"2022-9-30"},{"Name":"sukhman grewal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWNvHULuxj_iLYG6TluNaAZkLFapvcAwmjorG_J5YWdKzT8bsCf=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I loved it! The food tastes amazing and the serving temperature was just on point. Often these fast-service restaurants like this have quality issues. I believe the food they were serving at the time was freshly cooked. I will go back there to give it another go. Hope to see the same standards. Thanks","Images":null,"When":""}]

user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Kurian OS","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUnUTamkSGE3-Q4iHVZFM9fycV45rWXYQjM7X987X_yn0jZVSPw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"It's a complete package, dog friendly walk areas, beach access, large parking lot, playground etc. One of the best place to get away from your daily life. You can be in nature and see some beautiful landscapes, birds and more.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPjiel5R_5mIk0GGWrfpfqEYY_0nYb3tJ-GCf7M&fid=0x0:0x2f7ee82454021306"],"When":"2024-10-6"},{"Name":"Yvonne Z","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVybMmry85nn_H35l1ugI7xCGuq9SVSSMJDIVRlE0Zifow3sJU=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"It's a great place to take the kids out to play in the water and Barbie Q.
you can walk them all day long but you have to watch the tide come in and go out and if you catch the tide you have to walk a long, long way to see the sea and the other thing is that the place where you can put the tent up is probably sand so it's best to put a layer of somethingor, Otherwise the bottom of the tent will be covered with dirt.
there's only one place on this big beach where people line up to wash their feet and sand and that's very, very, very bad and needs to be improved.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPu2EfBabMzhJT6KOO0UtaIoYdHobCa6CUgQGhE&fid=0x0:0x2f7ee82454021306"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"Wendy Threlfall","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVjepg-as1v4ScYNbFyg7v6gGrkHrfp8I0gAfu8HJ5w5rucuNRTSg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fantastic beach, actual sand and beach picnic area, allows smoking in designated places and is also alcohol friendly in the picnic area. Beautiful playground.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMbXL8qnPRCrBaM9UmmT-9voXY1z2105pm621dy&fid=0x0:0x2f7ee82454021306"],"When":"2024-8-20"},{"Name":"Vancouver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWH0VcKAVTe7ZDh01hlHgR0aElCSuLJDgRSdfNkG4TKG7360ZlL=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful place to visit with family , lots of spots for BBQ and amazing kid’s playground with expansive water view. Few walking trails around and many different birds.
Clean washrooms. Parking and small cafe with food options and different drinks.

Sometimes you can meet weird noisy families who don’t respect others.

You can reserve covered bbq tables on their websites for your occasion.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOKyPXxfv_2LaOrqLmyDdrXz-sHNcYL1k2f1rmr&fid=0x0:0x2f7ee82454021306"],"When":"2024-4-7"},{"Name":"Pussy Consumer","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUewOOrsCm94fscCqIi4Kv3TGQR-OueZ2MuFLVX5R90jCZoX3Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful beach! It was so stunningly blue and water was clear as well. Their washroom is clean and quite nice! They also has a playground for kids too. Would totally go again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNgv2p34PmXuGW3oiDhLnLsQzUC8QVVT3cXRZwd&fid=0x0:0x2f7ee82454021306"],"When":"2024-5-12"},{"Name":"p daelo","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU44ZxV7G7QJ7bIUJourYqF5kTEsCHsDY0hr5HkCQR0_rn58rUY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Wonderful beach. The tide goes out quite far. At times, the beach can be quite windy. Great mix of rocky beach and sandy beach. Food options and bathroom present","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNMFSXB-CyohJVDyS3Tq-zL5ksDGfpQAjayVhkR&fid=0x0:0x2f7ee82454021306"],"When":"2024-7-15"},{"Name":"Sangeeth","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWOxDTI55299-17xHczbV49Haf4_WAoEcbKkLa_T9lAaE1M6YHr6w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful, clean, safe, and well-structured beach. Located in a very calm place, this beautiful beach is very clean and huge. You can walk for a long time as it is not very shallow. There are plenty of places to take your family for a day out, picnic, or camping. There are also plenty of places to rest. A huge kids' play area is available, so kids will never want to leave. Clean washrooms with changing rooms are another highlight. Additionally, there is an open wash area. There are plenty of rest areas for group or team outings. An in-house canteen is available, and you can order and get food delivered from various delivery partners. Plenty of parking areas are available. Overall, it's a great place for a family outing, especially with kids. Lifeguards patrol almost all the time, so safety is top-notch. Make sure when you leave, you take only photos and memories, and ensure you clean the surroundings. Highly recommend, but please avoid during the weekend and school holidays.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOePPjS_XFqFSKlODetpGCH1D4w0sxVtjK8Rc0l&fid=0x0:0x2f7ee82454021306"],"When":"2024-6-14"},{"Name":"Mike Hudson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLCJ0oUprvyqfikYTSaBYyxVDF0T8Dug5NVMSvp_81r3o1i3A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This an absolutely awesome park, beach and eating space..what a great use of this area.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOrIqfn58CkFSr_6NpHyc1bMaO294y6mL9VpIkS&fid=0x0:0x2f7ee82454021306"],"When":"2024-10-9"}]

[{"Name":"Lygia Misquitta","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVXN3CUbzt47zfh4dameFA6V05sbmmVOgatGglaH24z_uJvtyeXkQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Buenos Dias Cafe is a hidden gem located in KinVillage Community Centre in Tsawwassen. Chef Adrian is a magician at his craft and he Cooks wonderful gourmet meals for reasonable prices.
Muffins and Almond croissants are baked fresh in house daily.
The Kombucha here is exceptional.
Specials and Soup changes weekly.
The Fish n Chips is a customer favorite and Curry Fridays are busy, so if you are a curry lover  please pre order.
You will love the food here. Very authentic. Absolutely great quality and presentation. Chef Adrian also does all kinds of Caterings from small gatherings, celebrations of Life, weddings. Buenos Dias Cafe got voted Best Caterer by peoples choice Awards in Delta.
The Cafe is only open Mon- Fri from 8am -2pm.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNBl3hHoCPHEwKixI0_a31p7AVGyi5WTBdcLy_-&fid=0x0:0x229670dd9344c12e"],"When":"2023-4-17"},{"Name":"Becky Lee","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLs8PLbMvH6iUPlyNF1_71YGyZOKFVKo9JmWQrggiF2sxpUXURN=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"such a hidden gem! chef adrian's food is so good, especially the unique weekly friday specials. today's friday special is keema ghotala which was super tasty.
