[{"Name":"Juliana Porto","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU1NsObHvzim5fX9Olc5MHUf_dYmQIrIKDlOq_BaNnHFW_TVHXh=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Dani Pani is absolutely amazing! The food is always delicious, and their service is top-notch. Recently, I had a small issue with the packaging of my order and shared my feedback. Their response blew me away—they were so kind, professional, and truly committed to improving. They immediately took steps to address my concerns and even went above and beyond to make things right.

This place has consistently delivered exceptional food and outstanding service, and they’ve truly earned my loyalty. I highly recommend this restaurant to everyone! You won’t be disappointed. :)","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Amanda Tuczek","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJej_EcaTFfvf2bdZNoRSkjtMwubDn3JzZEj8GnYeKvt_ndmHP8=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited Dani Pani, and I was blown away by the experience! From the moment I walked in, the atmosphere was warm and inviting. The staff was incredibly friendly and made us feel right at home. The food was absolutely delicious—each dish was bursting with flavor, and you could tell everything was made with fresh ingredients and authentic spices. I especially loved the coconut chicken, which was cooked to perfection. The portion sizes were generous, and the service was quick and attentive. If you're a fan of Indian cuisine, this place is a must-visit. Can't wait to come back for another amazing meal!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Thedishdetective Lala","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKD_tj6k6xpF8R8uVmPtHQuGBgjvefVOKaKmqeE1mkWnmvdyA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Dana Pani Indian Cuisine Review

•	Location: 805 Boyd St J120, New Westminster, BC V3M 5X2, located in SmartCentres Queensborough Landing.

Service: The service was commendable, with attentive staff ensuring a pleasant dining experience. It deserves an 8 out of 10.

Overview: Dana Pani Indian Cuisine stands out as one of our favorite Indian restaurants and a hidden gem in the area. We visited for a quick bite and were thoroughly impressed by the quality and flavor of the dishes.

Food:

•	Appetizer: We started with a large portion of vegetable pakora. These were excellently prepared, with a perfect fry and a well-balanced seasoning blend. The appetizer sets a promising tone for the meal and merits an 8 out of 10.

•	Main Course: We opted for the Tiffin Thali, a diverse and satisfying selection that included both vegetarian and non-vegetarian items, rice, naan, and raita.

•	Palak Paneer: This dish, a staple of North Indian cuisine, features paneer (Indian cottage cheese) in a rich, flavorful spinach-based sauce. The spinach is blanched and pureed to a smooth consistency, then sautéed with onions, garlic, ginger, and tomatoes, along with a medley of spices. It was expertly prepared and rates an 8 out of 10.

•	Chicken Tikka Masala: Known for its vibrant orange color and rich, creamy, spiced tomato-based sauce, this dish did not disappoint. The balance of flavors and the aromatic quality of the sauce were excellent. It earns an 8 out of 10.

•	Chana Masala: This dish features chickpeas cooked in a spicy and tangy tomato-onion gravy. It is a staple in Indian cuisine, celebrated for its rich flavors and aromatic spices. While tasty, it lacked the depth of flavor found in the other dishes and receives a 7 out of 10.

•	Butter Chicken: A personal favorite, this dish featured a creamy, luscious sauce with tender, delicious chicken. It stood out as the highlight of the meal and deserves a 9 out of 10.

Ambiance: The ambiance is modest but comfortable. While the space is small, it is adequately maintained and provides a cozy setting for dining.

Price: The pricing is very affordable, making it an excellent option for those seeking quality Indian cuisine without breaking the bank.
2/5

Verdict: Dana Pani Indian Cuisine is truly a hidden gem and one of the best Indian restaurants in the area. The variety and quality of the food are outstanding, and the affordability adds to its appeal. For those who enjoy spicy food, it’s worth noting that while the dishes are flavorful, they cater to various spice preferences, offering non-spicy, medium, and very hot options. Overall, it’s a restaurant we will certainly return to and highly recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO5yhzePV_P4zOnZyLnxZOBpAWD7VNYor1BubP0&fid=0x0:0xe029e562e7fb717a"],"When":"2024-6-27"},{"Name":"Chris Lochhead","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJuiipc_xz9ET6nJtGoC_1SL7eafro7oB6Q-WiHyZ8PyZyITQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This place is a hidden New Westminster gem.  All the tasty curries you’d expect from an Indian restaurant but their cooks have an extra touch at this spot.  The naan bread (especially if you are dining in) is the absolute best in the entire lower mainland….just the right amount of crisp on the outside.  Try their Tali combo for lunch, which is a serving of two curries of your choice with rice and naan but sized for a single person…yum!  Pay a little more and make it three curries!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPl_W-FowSvJSeQc2xstWZl9ce2nbCFVentarXb&fid=0x0:0xe029e562e7fb717a"],"When":"2024-11-8"},{"Name":"Linh Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbP3plInkqXVOA2XJc8czoQ80aWBGnT8WS-yMiUPgvNShtt-y90A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The restaurant seemed humble but the food was tasty. My goat curry was so delicious while my husband loved his butter chicken so much. They're also very generous with the quantity of meat and rice in the portion. I especially love their garlic naan, so buttery!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPJvUT8qqNQ-oJm5478Swlqw48bEmAmAjgDyUkL&fid=0x0:0xe029e562e7fb717a"],"When":"2024-3-20"},{"Name":"Hanna Sampson","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXUI13FeBwcP-10PKakA44vzfLYMGFIcjAI-w79aF7DmVwltrQq5w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Delicious food and at a VERY reasonable price! Large portions of rice and Naan. Great combo meals for under $15. Will absolutely be back:)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMXZEQv_O91GPXrUyC3sQXmSV7-xM-936viMKEF&fid=0x0:0xe029e562e7fb717a"],"When":"2024-8-2"},{"Name":"nikhil naidu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJRSq7g-emI6rOuulL4_ub-YDKRfMFNnoqEuJalAXx7FvkTog=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Rare find in Queensborough area. Nice and cozy restaurant. The owner and the staff are very friendly and service is 10/10. Food quality is always fresh and delicious. My hot favorites are Fish Pakora and Grilled fish and in main course Mutton Curry. Their Indo-Chinese food is also great.

[{"Name":"Joe W.","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWr5W9mdlAV3O23BOO4Bd8Ea19vBOm9lh8GncQo9V3SBCJlUG7Jow=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Do not come here unless you have plenty of time to spare.  The food was decent but you can hardly find anyone when you need them.  There were only 3 tables on the dining side but at least 3 occasions we had to walk into the back area to find a staff ourselves.  There was simply nobody around out there.  They are either seriously understaffed or the staff just weren't paying attention to the customers' need.  Either way, management needs to work on their service level.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Susan Hill","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWV5D3pd1-7f1WRg6mfB7OdEUHbR8vKhmA1KworYfcg3p7kPpUu=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"To be clear, this was the very first time I have been back at Boston Pizza in over a year as their prices keep going up and the food hasn’t certainly gotten any better.  The service last few times wasn’t great either.

So I waited a while to order. I ordered a margarita and some prawn fettuccine and waited and waited and waited. Finally, the majority came to the table and told me that as their blender was broken I should order something else to drink so I asked for a margarita on the rocks

After waiting a long time again, I was told by the same individual that they couldn’t make that either and I should ask for something else again
I asked for them to surprise me with something lime flavored

Eventually, my waitress showed up and apologized and told me that the blender wasn’t working. I told her that I had asked the bartender to surprise me, but since that wasn’t coming anytime soon, it seemed I just wanted to cancel it.

Shortly after this, she brought me food. After a few bites I realized my spicy prawn fettuccine had no prawns and was not spicy either. She had brought me the wrong food.

This officially confirmed that I will not be coming back to Boston Pizza probably at any location due to their overly high prices for Italian food, which is some of the cheapest food to make on the planet","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Erica EDMAN","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWtbgYq8CYPacpxIsi-vVF8k4WDkLqimMZbC08jZPNycTuc4Mo=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Boston Pizza, as a corporate brand, is not only a place where we can enjoy delicious meals but also a venue that supports sports and has a global reach. It’s a comfortable space to relax, eat, and have fun, thanks to its excellent employees and the amazing flavors they serve. When you combine all of this, everything comes together perfectly. That’s why I highly recommend it—you should definitely try it!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"E A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ2tr69zditFgb4vd9PKKPg-4vyS0N5C24WXnk5zPZlDs-IhA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"All our food was delicious, portions are huge, restaurant and bathrooms are very clean, and our server Parul was very sweet and kind, attentive, always smiling, and didn’t forget anything we asked for. We had an international guest with us and she loved it, great experience!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOJ1OrgD7yv88cJlOFM0_lUDSi5otOBXam9J_vZ&fid=0x0:0xf56f0ca3eefb9c0"],"When":"2024-8-30"},{"Name":"Jack SUNSET","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV4IWe2Is123c_lBB-O0he2VLMZyE3yBWLFtFUOkDMxLedOdeU=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"“This is a perfect place to go with your family for a meal. The atmosphere is very romantic in the evenings, and you have the chance to watch your favorite sports on big-screen TVs. The staff is incredibly polite, and the food is delicious. I highly recommend it, and I insist you give it a try. Thank you!”","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Clement Tsang","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVlnMDAP3bpkDDKvV1biwN8gKMqY9QPN2tRRszD8X2osjIyB-xd=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Unbelievable.... absolutely horrendous. My most worst dining out experience in all my decades.

Arrive here at 5:53pm with my pregnant wife for Valentines day dinner because she wanted the heart shaped pizza. Ordered by 6:05 and left us with waters, this would be the last time our server came to our table. 3 tables near us as we witnessed sat down after us, ordered and got their food. Around 6:45 I walked up to the heat lamps and asked for service and demanded we get service. They came with the food we ordered! Yay? Nay.... it was cold and dried. Absolute garbage but still no server to be seen. I grabbed all my plates of food and brought it back to the heat lamps and told them it's all dried and cold.

Around 7pm somebody, I believe was a line cook or dishwasher, helped bring some food out. 1 out of 3 items served. We started eating it. At this point I realized under one of the pizzas was something that looks like a mostly eaten garlic bread!!!!!!!!!!!!!! Disgusting.

A food runner came by with our 2 other plates while the table next to us finished their meal and I told her about it. She said she will bring it to her manager and did not come back since.

While eating the other 2 plates we noticed smaller things we could live without complaining to them. Bunched up calamari, unmixed and smaller portion of the Jambalaya, a random pasta that looked like a kids pasta in the Jambalaya.

Still no sign of the server. Another food runner came by at the end and said our meal was taken care of and apologized for everything.

I used to frequent another Boston Pizza location that was closed down. I'm not coming back ever.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO3otXGw4aI1aOeypbrytEoOSDZFwT1Ov-kfcOq&fid=0x0:0xf56f0ca3eefb9c0"],"When":"2023-2-15"},{"Name":"James Coles-Nash","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUkJrmtjWT371XtK4SkdD-gc4742YrtKT1KSibl27VRSYpTt9Yi=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Sooo bloody slooooow, took 10 minutes to get seated in an empty restaurant, 30 to get our order in, 30 to wait for food, and another 15 to get our bloody bill! Did I mention they were empty? Two waitresses running around like headless chickens. The food was pretty obviously prepared in a warehouse somewhere frozen and then re heated, I swear the chicken soup was canned Campbell's reheated multiple times. I will never come back to this restaurant.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOXA_fURXHer7FBkbuFw6LvlQ2wgnQGKmqY7Wlq&fid=0x0:0xf56f0ca3eefb9c0"],"When":"2023-5-6"},{"Name":"Amy Wong","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW1Fqng1TSwXq9T24MRYmHHHX9f4qHb56PSWtHso-CGga0uBLtUFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Generally good, quieter dining experience. Normally great service, but would not honour sign found on Westminster highway advertising 10% off on pick-up orders. Was told that nothing was known about it. Would recommend that the sign is removed to avoid confusion","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMmY_StewA_w-zvuy80_gS44FJRj6e1eMVDwjpS&fid=0x0:0xf56f0ca3eefb9c0"],"When":"2024-6-1"}]

[{"Name":"Vanika Vanika","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWi-xsR_M07Zdm4atI_oW8JYZDaYaRBghyEWsVUcQkN2g6ZAAI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had been looking for perfect Indian street noodles and now I have found my people! They have the yummiest noodles with ample quantity at a budget price. The butter chicken is cooked to perfection. Portion size is huge. My server Malika was such a sweet girl too!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPAapOXuOktPyCEPfk6J82BO7rDdy2DxyM9nHVE&fid=0x0:0xf0212ded0051493f"],"When":"2024-9-15"},{"Name":"Parth Thakkar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJvPHMh0QVw0t-KmiqqZNyaMJ-6bNHKj4kGOSpy1qIl_Mi6qo6Y=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Town’s go to Indio-Chinese spot.
Must have’s: Honey Garlic Cauliflower, Veg Manchurian & Schezwan Fried Rice.

Utterly delicious, large portions & value for the money.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPn9a39iO3B3lUqJdHeKjQvaTQZ64P0aKCBK-2L&fid=0x0:0xf0212ded0051493f"],"When":"2024-12-5"},{"Name":"Dr. Naresh.R. Thumati","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXZe9i5l3lcphUrpMV7UIgJLbGmYTbI6xZPxyGLcsocFMCumCPI=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"While passing through this restaurant, I noticed this lunch special Thaali board with special price. I couldn't resist mys self to try this Thaali. I am big fan of Indian Thalis.

They said, You can choose any Curry from their menu for Thaali, which surprised me (that means they make  fresh curry for only for your Thali). I have chosen non-veg Thali (13.49$) option which comes with one veg and one chicken Curry (no lamb and shrimp included in Thali), one plain naan, Rice and Raita. I have selected Karahi Paneer (veg Curry)  and Chicken tikka Masala ( non-veg Curry). The ambience is good, very clean and good service. The food is not at it's best but I can say it's worth for the given price. It is far better than eating junk food by paying 20$ on your work day lunch. The paneer Currey is 4 out of 5, but they should work on chicken tikka masala. I didn't find any taste in it. But the quality of food is good. The naan is very plain, they should offer Garlic naan to make the Thaali more tasty. Rice is of good quality they have used. Raita is fresh. Overall I am not disappointed,  although I expected a better Chicken tikka masala which is a basic chicken curry in any Indian place and it shouldn't go wrong.

Overall I appreciate this restaurant team for their efforts to offer Thali at such low price yet quoty food. You don't even get a burger or sandwich from McD  for that price in these inflation days. Also, the girl at front was friendly and did good job.

I wanted to try Chana bathura next time.

Thank you.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN0XMLgOx4y_8kqS_FWesvvQNTC3Funx6F9Rev4&fid=0x0:0xf0212ded0051493f"],"When":"2024-6-13"},{"Name":"Sathiyaseelan Suhashini","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWGCDhZwAvUF3Q8iMEpEx8TQCvKbwiXzYFJN0uOrenEt7v0wxGX=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Loved the sweets which are delicious. Trying many north indian sweets for the first time and loving the quality of it in this place.

Tried Channa Bhatura aka Poori with Chickpeas curry that comes with cream and freshly cut onions. It was for $ 6. 95 during lunch hours.

Loved its freshness and will be back soon !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNoW9zMNweUNmDh1j3IGE_fstOFiSqYmG8GdWnr&fid=0x0:0xf0212ded0051493f"],"When":"2024-11-4"},{"Name":"Linh Tran","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUbP3plInkqXVOA2XJc8czoQ80aWBGnT8WS-yMiUPgvNShtt-y90A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I love it! Their lamb kebab, goat curry, butter chicken, garlic naans, chai tea, mango lassi and desserts are all good. My new go-to place for Indian food. The owner is very nice, price is great, and there's a big parking lot in the rear. Will come back very soon to try the rest of the menu :D","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMhyKhEftWleTJIUYYOQni0QkFhMsNfBJwa28jF&fid=0x0:0xf0212ded0051493f"],"When":"2024-4-2"},{"Name":"Jashan","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUT2DsBWm66GpZrhJ3gqnHsIa7xRHnVnNHTZoadqXPgkapvqB4=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Today, I visited this place , I tried Amritsari kulcha & veg Thali , food was awesome…… thanks for making my day ❤️","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOYf6l-DGt9DsQFbMv7ez7tztfDE27OFikOd_Nv&fid=0x0:0xf0212ded0051493f"],"When":"2024-11-2"},{"Name":"Leah Sargent","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVkbXH-OQ_7sFeemekssqTaoKEfoLwz8C9cJi6AwQRDmbir2ZKS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Great gluten free, dairy free options and the food was DELICIOUS. My favourite Indian since moving to Canada (11 years ago from England) superb flavour, not too fatty and good portion sizes (good amount of leftovers). Highly recommend! (Coconut chicken curry was my fav)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNcXdxQ5XM8NViO2HOwLWpTGrxkBasYP-WEHHPU&fid=0x0:0xf0212ded0051493f"],"When":"2024-4-1"},{"Name":"Michael A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3NxtyRfPp-9ZhswWx21Mo8fQSmRiHA8ouIN6Y3mcVxWJESOSnfg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ok, so every now and then you stumble across a hole in the wall restaurant that you have to think really, why didn’t I know about this place before! Well, this is one of them! Amazing Indian food, at great price and it’s just so good we have made it our go to place for Indian cuisine moving forward. If you wish to try great Indian food , there is no other place to come!  The decor is simple and clean and comfy, but nothing fancy. Don’t be fooled by the decor, the food is insanely good! OMG ! For those lucky enough to read this, go now and order it before the queues become insane !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPPKu5qrAFWM6d0rrweLwa0xObRGjgP5kOmdJOL&fid=0x0:0xf0212ded0051493f"],"When":"2023-12-3"}]

[{"Name":"Jack Yuen","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJhRPpXHdrFGpSfFPj2Llvg9rACCkMWbpnKawexr7OBRxKhKQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I will say it is a great value dinner. You can get everything a taste without order a big portion of same thing. Pasta is good but my steak is simply so-so and the taste is too plain. Service is definite an issue and I keep waiting for my table and no one is calling my name. Once I am in restaurant, there was  lots of table available. Server seemed so busy and one server need to serve so many tables and no time to clean up dirty table","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPKKsQslLqMrQfo7kXBQXunSMtYWSe6Fp3bWQ8X&fid=0x0:0xb8605b6977443e66"],"When":"2024-9-16"},{"Name":"Francis Wu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUachXJf0WTzrHMSnePZ9iHmUBp8eKFhZg_hqN3cQx4lsTYkO0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"A good place to go for a family meal or hosting a big party. Nice ambience with traditional family restaurant style decor.

Suggest to upgrade to clam chowder because it is much better than the minestrone. I had the Caesar salad with grilled chicken, which is alright. Would definitely recommend the spumoni ice cream too!

Lots of parking, and you can overflow to the bowling alley side too. It does get busy because it's next to the theatre, ice centre and Watermania.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMWNb8S5c4Z9Qa1T50KzjPYePOjz9dC-fQJCw3w&fid=0x0:0xb8605b6977443e66"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"Pradeep Grason","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUJFuPvAS8F6Cdnotp3L8p878gNVWsETZdDnJ2Dh2Pp5wBixMeC=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I recently visited The Old Spaghetti Factory, and it was an amazing experience! The fresh bread, French onion soup, and spaghetti with meatballs were simply delicious. The sauce tasted incredibly fresh, and everything I ordered was perfect. I loved every bite and will definitely be returning!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN2z3o8U7YxfnsbmvpMsjcL8NmFoVIrGdr32zfZ&fid=0x0:0xb8605b6977443e66"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Jessica Yu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVbKN7JTB8-geSMCvSN4JUMFRJdzyUw9Zem00rFXxig6jms97b4=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Overall Summary: great ambience, good food, and excellent service. Would come again!

Service: Excellent service! The waiters were very accommodating and friendly to us.

Atmosphere: The area was dimly lit, and had a calming and relaxing atmosphere. A great place to hang out with friends, family, or a significant family.

Food: Food is really good! I ordered the seafood linguine marinara, and my friends got the Alfredo pasta, Bam Bam shrimp, Cranberry Goat Cheese Spinach Salad, and more! I highly recommend the linguine pasta, and my friends seemed to all enjoy their food.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMISW3xSGOdgH4W6-95zjA9rbz_-OTG-0S8Qty8&fid=0x0:0xb8605b6977443e66"],"When":"2024-10-5"},{"Name":"Alice Young","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ6kmLBm-l0fKYauhLrXU_hg4awzQzHj653e_nW7zJbuIVhTA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"This is my first time to try this restaurant.
Our server "harleen" is fast and friendly with big smile all the time.

I love their mussels, I cannot stop eating it, I finished 1 whole dish by myself within 5 minutes and
i ordered second dish for my hubby.

My hubby likes their French onions soup and lasagna. A lot of cheese inside.

But we don't like their calamari, taste like .. they used dated oil to cook it.

We will go there again to try
Different things next month.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNLqNchuWUU9iy30MY47scbEcR-AehhAJMqr-UD&fid=0x0:0xb8605b6977443e66"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Rachel Keery","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW7HrRs2lYWD-a0OMwYD8hcg13jIWjm47WrdDcC3B391YGfNtPv3A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Chicken parmigiana was really tasty. Cheap cocktails.
The mushroom pasta wasn’t the best not enough mushrooms 🥲.
Plan a little extra time, had a reservation but waited about 10 minutes longer and another wait for the food and bill.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO5uO_9NkeKWj8jxhIfNb1aDK3y4ZqTAZomEHa2&fid=0x0:0xb8605b6977443e66"],"When":"2024-9-1"},{"Name":"SakuraPop","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2Ydh_zMaRhCOGSDaDReRXTHAfQoioR2bjEOTTAd92-Gh4fTq9=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"The pastas I recommend are lasagna or spaghetti and meatballs. The winning dish is uncommonly mentioned amongst the reviews, which is their New York Steak. Better or as good as steak houses.

Service is top notch. My server was attentive to our needs and quick to make things happen.

Would definitely come again. You cannot beat this package menu.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPN7SOT14A5F-k_ZiL_Fw5vlSCLpF3gdvubC7_x&fid=0x0:0xb8605b6977443e66"],"When":"2024-7-30"},{"Name":"Hiro","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKTugIRaO0gkYAy_ExJDXCZFxJqHjBnPyDVYLBYjjBCRdT652sY=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"We visited there when they were not busy in the late afternoon. I saw many tables that were not cleaned. We had to wait for a while to get our table. We ordered some pasta and kids meals which were good deal for a family. We were a bit disappointed because the waitress brought us dirty silverware and sharing plates. The waitress was busy, so we had to wipe them ourselves. Another disappointment was that my kids got very watery orange juice. I guess it’s been in a dispenser with lots of ice cube. Their food was OK, but not so good as it used to be.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOt6lArGjvFtYPYTvoX4HpTs4UUn4z6FioFB7ny&fid=0x0:0xb8605b6977443e66"],"When":"2024-6-20"}]

title: Duncanby Lodge
about: null
user_reviews:
[{"Name":"George Roper","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI6HV6-dKzL-CIFbb7RMTy-u27XviHTwUwZ5wStymxEB1_xFg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"The happiest place on earth. Sid and his crew are the best. They see to your every need and aim to make your trip the most spectacular fishing adventure you have ever had. From the fine dining and accommodations to the boats and dock staff that make your trip enjoyable. Fishing from the boats with fine gear and great guides helps make your experience great. The staff at Duncanby Lodge are truly a family. I would recommend visiting them if you are up for some great fishing and even better food. Thanks again to the staff at Duncanby Lodge and the ladies working at the office in Richmond. You have truly impressed me and I WILL be back soon.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Paul Schram","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIeU5AEHkZdn2pOXCR_HR37nrRiUISfWwtr0lclnLe3fd-ZNg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"This review of Duncanby Lodge is somewhat dated, as I have not fished with them since 2008.  However, last night as my son and I returned from our 12th salmon fishing trip to the BC coast, (which we have been doing since he was eight years old), I began thinking about all of lodges that we have stayed at over the past decade or so.  During that time we have fished at 9 different BC salmon lodges.  I realized that out of all of the fishing lodges that we have stayed at, Duncanby Lodge has remained, in our minds, the best overall fishing lodge that we have ever stayed at. Their accommodations have been the best, their meal plans were fantastic, their boats and equipment is great, their owner and staff were more then dedicated to helping to ensure that their guests catch fish, and everyone at the lodge treats you like family.  Although my boy and I did not catch many fish at Duncanby on that trip, that was not because the fish were not there.  It was only because of our inexperience at that time, with fishing for salmon.  However, even though we had not paid for a guide, the owner cared enough to have a guide take us out one afternoon, giving my son his first opportunity to catch bottom fish. The people at Duncanby simply cared about us, and took the time to ensure that we had a great trip.  I have watched their web site over the years, and it is obvious that they are still treating their guests just as great.  This is evidenced in the fact that they are always booked for a year in advance.   The only reason that we have never been back is because I can’t plan so far in advance. Ultimately, I wanted to write this review to let others know that with all of the experience that we have gained at eight other salmon fishing lodges over the years, Duncanby has been the best one of them all.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNr7SCYQwGO5kH7vqsS5cMGYSHRO1V1McugvtuL&fid=0x0:0x6621c68d52a349fb"],"When":"2018-7-23"},{"Name":"whatthefuk4","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjU6LEi31F-If0ZN1nUlwh1yJvDZQpCsFPxdXQdaeAHMr0ETGp4j=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"One of the most serene places on Earth. Unmatched quality service and fishing experience. The rooms are clean and well equipped for a comfortable stay.Plane access only but don't worry you'll eat like a king. The food at the kitchen is 5 star. A must experience.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMCcrpASFimXJQwVSV_uLsV0Beb28FfAm2Z3Kko&fid=0x0:0x6621c68d52a349fb"],"When":"2023-4-14"},{"Name":"Wes Masztalar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWzxAR04JD5myrSxMdmTM9LgWsU9bXW5yoQwyNPsZ-Pkcm-dpl3=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Duncanby isn't only a location, its an experience.
The passion and movement behind the recovery and preservation of our coastal fish and habitats that Duncanby shares and exercises is contagious and extremely admirable.  You're inspired to enjoy the sport of fishing, but just as inspired to become apart of the movement towards returning and bringing more large fish back into our inlets and oceans; With their prize/acknowledgment system its hard not to want to be apart of it. I've left with a completely different outlook and respect towards fishing and the outdoors, and i've fallen inlove again.
The staff was so kind, and its obvious and refreshing to see how much they care for one another.  I felt like I landed at a family cabin and before I knew it, they had me feeling like family aswell.
The food was amazing, the kitchen flexibility is amazing, the drinks, options and just everything is so great!
With sport fishing can come a hussle. Duncanby does an amazing job at reminding you you're on vacation with how enjoyable, flexible and comfortable everything about it is..
I will forever be saving my pennies for as many Duncanby experiences as I can squeeze into this life time.. Until then!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Debbie Mode","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKTT9hVsxoG9YzphUl8E7fUaXM8b0IVH8MOdoBu2AMdKYqmbQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Beautiful location, excellent accommodations, delicious food, well constructed and maintained boats - however the best is the amazing staff that does so much to make sure each guest is taken care of and having a terrific time. We have been to River's Inlet more than 10 times over a 20 year period - this visit, our first at Duncanby, was the best!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Christopher Sparling","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLk2sYB_UGkmq4-9SB_jBOrWGA2Z-VCEDdJMXZJ9OE_wYghCg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"A first class operation in all respects. The entire team operates as 'one', with the genuine goal of making your experience the best it can be. The scenery, the fishing, the food and the accommodations are only surpassed by the level of customer service that Sid and his well trained staff provide. 5 Stars in my book.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"DARRIN LITTLE","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKvmmK2HXVBzM2KGDMiKIu-WgoFOZMPSc7v1j8du3ME49-7gg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"If you have an ambision to catch epic fish, abord the best boats while enjoying fine dining and absoult cabin comfort. It is heaven on earth.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ryan Burghardt","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKCxPYBJoN5m1GyOZ1Qddl_KhaLSR9nfHrctJs8Oz9Un0EZ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Can’t say enough good things about this place. [{"Name":"SAT DK","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXlFQNTii-i8DW-hoxyXeyJh4yNTEVBytvZpP_YLerrLZONIaD7=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Blue Duck Café is an absolute gem! I recently stopped by and was blown away by the combination of fantastic food, cozy atmosphere, and wonderful service. The moment I walked in, I felt welcomed by the warm and inviting décor. It’s the perfect spot whether you’re looking for a quiet coffee break or a full meal with friends.

The menu offers a great variety of options, and everything I tried was delicious. The ingredients were fresh, and the flavors were well-balanced. Whether you're there for breakfast, lunch, or just a snack, Blue Duck Café does not disappoint. The coffee is top-notch too—smooth, rich, and exactly what you need to start your day or power through your afternoon.

The staff are incredibly friendly and attentive. They made sure everything was just right without being overbearing, and they were quick to offer recommendations when asked. It’s clear that they genuinely care about providing a great experience for their customers.

The prices are reasonable, especially considering the quality of the food and service. It’s a great value for such a lovely experience. The café has a laid-back, yet trendy vibe, which makes it a great spot to meet up with friends or get some work done.

Overall, I can’t recommend Blue Duck Café enough! It’s a must-visit if you’re in the area and looking for a place with excellent food, great coffee, and a relaxed atmosphere. I’ll definitely be coming back again and again.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Tao Pollock","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIWejx4bkJFDa-jJ_bwiaDyRN1cQeZDqc-3eU0thw-iEPAX5A=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Very nice vibes, feels like you are having a home cooked meal and the food is very good and fresh. Fresh salad rolls mostly lettuce. Deep fried spring roll was small and oily. Ordered the beef soup. Was very fishy. Ordered the meat ball soup. Broth was bland. Soap dispenser was open. Saw inside. Was so gross","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPiREdledvzRZ6pZA44xuigfvKlBWsdw-LOXVQe&fid=0x0:0xe47f1d0de4e8346c"],"When":"2024-8-25"},{"Name":"David 04 Make the World a Better Place","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXXmkrAyRsAwad4uDl0EKEwpsCVMLq51IOxmbley55h_iwJzGo=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"David's Overall Recommendation
★☆☆☆☆

Comment:
It's disappointing for the price.
Unsanitary and disappointed by the price and food portion
If you really want to eat Vietnamese rice noodles and can't move a step, then eat it here

Basic
● Taste ★★☆☆☆
● Price ★☆☆☆☆
● Kindness ★★☆☆☆
● Comfort ★★☆☆☆
● Cleanliness ★☆☆☆☆

Lately, restaurants are struggling with rising rental costs, food ingredient prices, and wages.

However, this is about noodle cuisine. Additionally, this place operates as an express service. Considering the price and the quantity of food, it is quite disappointing.

Another issue is the lack of hygiene. The tables were not clean. Placing chopsticks haphazardly means someone might end up eating their food with the end someone else has touched with their hands. The hygiene in the bathroom was... let's just say I turned around and walked out after one glance at the entrance.

Only good thing was free parking lots.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMt0c9eN1Q4tDb7luk0xZ4yrSDvVcyKPr3Fp00&fid=0x0:0xe47f1d0de4e8346c"],"When":"2024-3-23"},{"Name":"Bernie","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVPXTBFQGy4UZogf6r0hGxUGZ8fvtwePPN5iicbAtQksaWtpwOP=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Got the Well-Done Beef Noodle Soup and Vietnamese spring rolls. Taste is decent for the price with free tea in a teapot. Service is good, place is pretty dark.  Credit card is not accepted, only cash or debit card.  Parking is free.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM7YzTyjYqMFawW6aLQ6Uv8F7PjIwN3S0L6flbX&fid=0x0:0xe47f1d0de4e8346c"],"When":"2023-7-31"},{"Name":"Andrew Swain","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUb-SWtBl9eu5uGco3miNiplRLbF2Abz6kUTJ0z6yGFb0ftahP0=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Fast and tasty. Only tried the pho but it was just a few minutes between ordering and receiving. Loaded it up with chili oil that each table has, really enjoyed it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOCX0MsH95zoDP-bpAItuQJPEg5byNdXcNFdQZ2&fid=0x0:0xe47f1d0de4e8346c"],"When":"2024-9-2"},{"Name":"Christina D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKdbzCgX2mAlkgoRDRpQdmyhvqkcWi1Q4oMSB2c7X4rmlkfGg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I was expecting to get disappointed by the amount of negative reviews of this restaurant but I’m actually impressed.

I have reviewed about 40 pho restaurants in Vancouver (check profile if you don’t believe me). And I must say, this restaurant deserves a much better rating.

Then I read the negative reviews. Dang, some are actually restaurant mistakes. But majority of the bad reviews are people who have never eaten at a pho restaurant. Seriously, if you’ve been at pho restaurant, you know they leave a container of chopsticks, napkins and soup spoons on each table so the patrons can use.

I keep reading the word hygiene on the negative reviews and this place seems a lot better than many Vancouver restaurants. Tables are clean, chopsticks, spoons, dishes all clean. And on top of that, the bean sprouts were extremely fresh and crisp.

We ordered pho. The broth is light yet flavourful. A bit low on the salt side which is a major plus for me. I add extra sriracha as my ‘salt’.

The pho is great. Good portion and good size and great value.

I would definitely eat here again next time I go to the Walmart nearby.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNyqrZ5fSXmt3LcLT5iJct9eon0w5IvhVXsgrsZ&fid=0x0:0xe47f1d0de4e8346c"],"When":"2024-8-22"},{"Name":"miss__shanny","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHr6yU1FW2ClY90UTMc-TusIMZMyTtqSbw9mn_nM6-5ZQcmDVr=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Food is phenomenal. Caution is great. Customer service excellent. Overall five star 100%. I would definitely come back. I forgot to take a befor photo it's just so good haha","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNtJ5NWopjqcKwXsiyXzXGXnqCZj0MObI2rvnzM&fid=0x0:0xe47f1d0de4e8346c"],"When":"2024-8-20"},{"Name":"What I think","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV29HaeFsNWkgPsI3q8cTp7ndAScxs2BDU3d8hn3sRLiNB2zus=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Pho Express Angkor Queensborough

Vietnamese
Free parking lot at Queensborough outlet mall
Family friendly
Food average
Service not bad

Although we’ve been living close by for over a decade now, we don’t come often because we find their Pho and other dishes mediocre at best. They have a small selection of Thai dishes which to be fair, we haven’t the courage to try. Anyway, this visit was mainly due to a short lunch break.

#9 Pork banh mi
Very little meat. More like picked carrot sandwich instead. And they are too sweet. So the sandwich tasted odd.

#45 Lemon grass chicken and pork chop rice.
Wasn’t expecting some sort of gravy covering the chops (wasn’t like that before) while everywhere serve charred meat. Little amount of rice (thin layer sprend out). Where is my chicken? It's half the size of the bun... The chunk on the top bun is just skin, which was burnt and rolled up, tasted awful.  What chicken was there was also overcooked and dry AF.  Literally one bite gets onion...

I've had this sandwich at probably a dozen nandos locations, this isn't how these sandwiches should look or taste
(I ordered no tomato)","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN7iaT7sCtSH53pisl4PAxw78mbKpiGVfLVZefk&fid=0x0:0x2bd29f8bf31b3a3b"],"When":"2024-10-25"},{"Name":"S A","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWJOMOiZKMkVhzEB7ZORr37dwap2afh8DAG6IHDyoctwDav8XVN=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We went for lunch today around 1-2 and it was quite busy but not crowded!

As the  space is quite big enough, it didn’t seem crowded and the aesthetics are really good and I couldn’t stop myself from clicking pictures!

There was a guy who helped us today and he is very warm and welcoming, I didn’t ask for his name unfortunately but I would give 5/5 for his exceptional service!

The food is delicious, this is my second time visiting Nando’s but at diff location!

We ordered half chicken with mango and lime sauce - 4/5
Golden Cauliflower - 2.5/5
Spiced rice - 3/5
Peri peri fries - 4.5/5 I love peri peri flavour and the sauce from Nando’s!
One leg and thigh with hot sauce - 5/5
Kisses for dessert - 2.5/5
Custard tarts - 2.5/5
Rainbow rice bowl - 4/5

We had a coupon so we have used it and overall it’s a good experience !","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPkVTg_aBdU4RDzEBaLbD2PFU7vJOkpubE_NxlJ&fid=0x0:0x2bd29f8bf31b3a3b"],"When":"2024-2-19"},{"Name":"loz designz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjW2Kh3OktqywzqCfM31W6GrKd8Vhm8o4t-rvOWhx5Nqw1jSDv1m=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I ate for the first time at Nando's in Queensborough. I really enjoyed the lemon and herb flavour of my chicken, and the Brussels sprouts were good. We enjoyed our meals (perfectly cooked!) and the staff were all very pleasant and welcoming too. It was a bit chilly in the restaurant, but other than that we were comfortable. I'll return!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"S K (OxtailGravy)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIINjUguJePPet75HTnX-unbS8rsk4LQ_Ku9eCz7eh0Wy--ZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Consistently provides quality tasteful chicken with great customer service in a clean and organized restaurant. This is my go to lunch spot in New Westminster.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOhQ-ZDz0797RHcEvNWO4uhqqyn3rPZpePuNwec&fid=0x0:0x2bd29f8bf31b3a3b"],"When":"2024-8-23"},{"Name":"NDS Investments","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVikPs6WOuTzc-E92-sZ1BLaCA6XPNBLrLbmLXnMK-Mmkbrg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Our family only has done takeout at this location several times, not one issue to date.

We usually order either the Family platter or Jumbo chicken platter...few pics are attached.

Parking - plenty
Staff - attentive and wonderful
Food quality - always has been great
Portions - decent for chicken...as per sides, don't really like having to pay a fee for the rice to family portion.  The one the platters come with is not enough for a family.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPVDqj9a7lITay0mWYmdWLZdYT2jxXLbTXEVOT8&fid=0x0:0x2bd29f8bf31b3a3b"],"When":"2022-5-22"},{"Name":"Paighton D","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJ3GQ1Hbfm1JHNEW83IOMXR9Az4y_1JBjQ4ckoTy247wLX8Bw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Came here for a lunch meal. At nandos I always order the chicken sandwich. I have never had a piece of chicken this small..... I kid u not it was mostly all bun & a couple bites of chicken. I called and she said all pieces of chicken are small for the sandwich and this is how they come now.
Well that's the last time I ever buy or eat there chicken sandwich. I want an actual proper portion of CHICKEN in the chicken sandwich.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNpQkAJhWM61WTTuFdPLZbvkpnAffBmN1XT-IzO&fid=0x0:0x2bd29f8bf31b3a3b"],"When":"2023-11-29"},{"Name":"Curtis L","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWAXt2v13n7vgj7rJxv4X0f2PEgr_YXo4pwByRm1iYv5N-kpVs=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered a peri-peri bowl and I got the bowl with the chicken and when I got the bowl the piece of chicken I ordered was a big as maybe 3 chicken nuggets combined! Keep in mind the bowl was $17. The service was the only decent thing in this restaurant as the food came out quick. The atmosphere was pretty bad as there were only two other groups in the restaurant, there was also dirty dishes on some of the tables. Overall I am disappointed mainly in the portioning of the food.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ariel Freebs","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLfNiZqYOh-Wg0pABIvhLNcpv8WWvwTVJ3bMyXrEVUERQ6geA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered a Chicken Peri peri bowl with this Nandos. I was served VERY raw chicken it was pink in every strip. When we brought it back to the counter, the manager was anything but nice to us. She gave us an extreme attitude back to me when asking for a refund and didn't seem to care at all that the kitchen just gave out pink chicken.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMW1IVLXUxEkR8NvX2k8KCSULO-kYPvTWnOVl39&fid=0x0:0x2bd29f8bf31b3a3b"],"When":"2023-10-19"}]

[{"Name":"Mucahit Mert Alagoz","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUlZFzlr8OmJ6ReNSeqILjiXkPYOR-Wi6HlJhjaTTE_xGsRl7kohA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"The food is generally average, and they don't provide lemon with the salad. It has nothing to do with Greek cuisine, as the staff are Indian (so they don’t really know this culture, the dishes are Greek in name only). We didn’t want any drinks and just asked for a glass of water, but they didn’t understand and sold us a cola instead. Overall, it's a place where you can fill your stomach, and the cleanliness of the restaurant is good.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOWzp1DQVtYVNAjsbP1pz-apYjfAhZsgqbY43q-&fid=0x0:0x5c6989b643083b68"],"When":"2024-9-29"},{"Name":"Terra R","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJbAEv00VRUG0URFP2yUGRpRj5JfETxNf8hiWwPaPGiYnkd2g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"How old was that chicken you just gave me? It was as hard as a rock, I couldn't even bite through it. The pita was hard and crumbly, and why does it taste like Indian food? I threw the whole thing in the trash. Funny part it was so bad the trash threw it back at me.
I will never be back and I will recommend not going here. It's too bad there's not a lot here in Queensborough, you think they'd do better. Maybe care .

You've gone way down hill.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Kelly","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV7ZgTTMvehublJriEZdNACLnkg32LznpVyUa1Mj9jQF9k2XMaG=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Crispy like bacon! How is a Gyro hard, dry and crispy?
I know! They use old meat that's probably sitting out in the open and air drying out after it's been cooked over and over again.

I've never had a Gyro that wasn't soft, juicy and tender until today.

Bought two gyros and after the first one I dissect the 2nd one and see what was going on. You can clearly see this meat needs to be rehydrated

Would not recommend.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPXBKQmbrDMOeG83872uhXxFhuYApxEfcaQ6y5o&fid=0x0:0x5c6989b643083b68"],"When":"2024-3-24"},{"Name":"Navid Hasani","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI5WO6imytoWgyOyLzu4LNEg_FRiwD5M4mREaxYhei_qeUIxg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"We found a piece of scrubber! in our food, I immediately took the dish to the lady taking order to show it to her. I asked her to give us a new dish, she was planning to return the same dish! but after she saw my look! she decided to not do that! then she gave us a new dish but this time she reduced the amount of salad she gave us. When I said why is this like this, she said that is our usual amount we are allowed to give! So rude!
If you go here expect to see scubber in your food!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Claude Lemay","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUwd-Gb5EQVIF5eogSnHf9qj_Q2dRQGp-W-29ljr-HvQACgOiC7GQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"We had the mega platter with chicken, falafel bites and greek salad. The food was very good, service was fast but charged $2.50 + tax for a paper bag.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Ashleen Mudaliar","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjX8Atk-I-uQ2qsr33K3XqhPu2V2VKUCe37PTEiaCe_5O5FSEpmX=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Me and my friend popped in for an after work dinner and we were left beyond disappointed. My friend had ordered a caeser salad but got a Greek salad despite being mildly allergic. We talked to the cashier and she told us “no you didn’t. you ordered a Greek salad” but like why would she order a Greek salad when she’s allergic! The cashier tried to gaslight us into thinking that my friend ordered a Greek salad. Terrible experience. They don’t take allergies serious here","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPLTiYjzluzUZKTekJ7dCFYExqhiVhj00BrmxEH&fid=0x0:0x5c6989b643083b68"],"When":"2022-6-27"},{"Name":"Alireza Dashti","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXzlkHHbKU8GSv1EXNB24_ronGNtm71oBmwPKHxkgGsQ1J5JqI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I visited this restaurant two days ago and ordered a souvlaki and a moussaka. Unfortunately, the quality of the vegetables was poor, and the meat tasted like it wasn’t fresh. After eating, I felt nauseous. I called the restaurant twice and spoke with the staff, but they were unable to connect me with the manager or transfer my call to management. The restaurant’s environment also didn’t seem clean, and overall, the food quality was disappointing.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shayne Farah","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWv9NVrA6YcenSmR6yk-m-H3BPln3OnkNcfuusJQN_BU_anyDQTuA=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"My favorite, calamari with Greek salad.  Salad is yummy,  fresh,  fries are great. But the only problem I thought was they cut the calamari so thin.  So I think, when they buy the frozen calamari, they cut it on half. Like seriously the calamari is thin like paper and full of batter.  Service us amazing,  the in-house sauces are amazing especially the chillie sauce, just the calamari bit.i stopped going here, I go to the metro town opa instead,  or the tsawwassen.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"Larry LaRose","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXppqlLBfylyuqrBhgeVpR5HGRMyNCMuGdQGyTi4df8Serhxj2xPg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had a fantastic experience at the restaurant in Starlight Casino. Although finding the main entrance was a bit tricky, the moment I walked in, Terry the bartender warmly greeted me and offered a menu. Since I didn’t have my glasses, he kindly helped me choose a meal. I requested a chicken burger on a whole wheat bun, which wasn’t on the menu, but Terry accommodated my request without hesitation. The meal was excellent and served promptly. Terry checked in on me several times, adding to the positive experience. I highly recommend this place for a great lunch!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPQSY4I0Cv6hfBblrIAanYSr1or9UY91RE6pvLv&fid=0x0:0x20a80f1560b67cf5"],"When":"2024-7-18"},{"Name":"Shirley Ann Harris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLTufZ1O7YNqmevegFQNEbK68BixarB9ooeJyWD92O9OkSBiQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"I went to the Starlight casino with some friends for the first time in years. The band famous players was on that night. I wish I had the words to describe how amazing they are! From their talented voices to the theatrics and drama on stage , it was incredible. The chemistry between the two lead singers kept all of us engaged. The dance floor was full at all times. If you want a good night out with some good music, I would strongly recommend the Starlight lounge when famous players is scheduled.
Unfortunately, I wish I could say the same for the service and the food. I had the South Beach salad . My avocado was brown on places and I asked for Caesar dressing and I got mayonnaise. One. I spoke to the waitress. Said she would bring me ranch. The waitress was very sweet but not very good at her job! She would take one order, walk away, do that, and then come back and dig another order as opposed to taking all of our orders and requests at the same time. She would bring us our food but not come back and ask us if we needed anything and we would have to literally wave her down. At times people waited in extremely long time to have coffee, refilled or even another drink order. Because the band was so amazing. I will go back to the Starlight lounge. Probably not to eat!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipMuxVAVKWcz16jTNjmBEUTUSbTReqDKxeWQwJRk&fid=0x0:0x20a80f1560b67cf5"],"When":"2024-9-22"},{"Name":"Mike Liu","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS3TomIjeVsXZOdRPO53t7f3UGdwg-yRZRaS5bbXh_A7qbV4E=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"1.  The facility, services, and foods at Starlight Casino in New Westminster BC are inferior and way below bar.
2.	Services have reduced at Starlight Casino in New Westminster BC  drastically over the past six months. Three of the five small coffee machines have been removed for good. Only the two near the washroom at the far end remains, often broken. IT IS INSULTING TO the patrons when the Starlight Casino in New Westminster management CLAIM MORE SERVICES and were "excited" when they REDUCING them FROM 5 TO 2.
3.The swiping incentive is useless these days  The rewards have reduced to a few silly credits are insulting . You might as well remove and dump the swiping machines.
4.	Buffet is practically closed - some snacks remain. Buffet used to be a very popular and well-liked place to eat and drink. But since the price has doubled, services reduced and poor foods, Starlight casino practically “killed” the popular venue.
5.	 Most popular slot machines have been removed for good and more card tables added. Less and less patrons could be seen at the Starlight Casino these days. My friends and myself now rather go to River Rock Casino.
6.	In sum, the management of Starlight Casino in New Westminster BC should be reviewed and replaced. We do not want to see it closed which will happen if the present management continues their unpopular, unfriendly and ridiculous services.
7.	I am so unhappy that I did not even bother to check my typos and grammatical mistakes as that would just waste more of my time.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNReVZP-w6JDEcHhpnXDFAf0jy6f1qVIOjodzw&fid=0x0:0x20a80f1560b67cf5"],"When":"2024-7-15"},{"Name":"Frank Li","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUqU7w4lL0DBsy1BjK_cj8vbNltIdZkHHYfmHo3u05AoSN2BGW5=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I came here for lunch on Sunday. It's a reasonable price for $22.

The dining options are top-notch, with several restaurants to choose from. I particularly enjoyed the food at MATCH Eatery & Public House and the elegant dining experience at ATLAS Steak + Fish. The service was excellent, and the staff were friendly and attentive.

This pizza place is literally 100/10.

⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️⭐️
Delicious Pizza and Friendly Service:)

I had the pleasure of enjoying both the Hawaiian and veggie pizzas, and they were simply amazing. The Hawaiian was a perfect balance of sweet and savoury, with juicy pineapple and flavourful ham, while the veggie pizza was loaded with fresh, crisp toppings. The crust on both was just right—crispy on the outside and soft on the inside.

What made the experience even better was the fantastic service. The staff was incredibly friendly, welcoming, and attentive. It’s not just the pizza that will have me coming back, but the warm, professional service too. Pizza tastes frozen and reheated too. Used to go there once in a while but I forgot how terrible it was. Definitely not going back. Just go to Queensborough Pizza, it's so much better and it's really good.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Vishal Goyal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXi4u-i5CXrp6ymv6Vl8g03bSSYZcGDX8NEXmd3LzvtkRh_tF3OZQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Title: A Slice of Heaven: New West Pizza Delights

New West Pizza in New Westminster is a culinary gem that has quickly become my go-to spot for a satisfying slice. From the moment you step inside, the inviting aroma of freshly baked dough and savory toppings greets you, setting the stage for a memorable dining experience.

The menu boasts a wide array of options, from classic pepperoni to inventive gourmet creations, ensuring there's something to please every palate. What sets New West Pizza apart, however, is the quality of their ingredients. Each bite bursts with flavor, thanks to the use of fresh, locally sourced produce and premium meats.

Not only is the pizza top-notch, but the service is also exceptional. The staff is friendly, attentive, and always eager to accommodate special requests. Whether you're dining in or opting for delivery, you can expect prompt and courteous service every time.

The cozy ambiance of the restaurant adds to the overall charm, making it the perfect spot for a casual meal with friends or a cozy date night. And with generous portion sizes at reasonable prices, you'll leave feeling satisfied without breaking the bank.

In conclusion, New West Pizza in New Westminster is a must-visit for any pizza lover. Delicious food, friendly service, and a welcoming atmosphere combine to create an unforgettable dining experience. I can't wait to return for another slice of heaven!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Stephanie Krushinsky","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjV3fmFXutFrt3LbgshWkzotw65tphKrSFQ47wyAISm4tROsygMMhg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Pizza was amazing..wings were just..wings no drumettes.Deep fryer oil needs to be changed as it makes wings taste like old oil.. would not order the wings again.9$ for not very great tasting wings and no drumettes? Also..white sauce costs extra? I thought that usually this was something you could order anywhere. Without an extra cost.. I would order some pizza again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipM74eeyxBSYkndHt_ogpZwGzTX7ciOQ9al0Gket&fid=0x0:0x4ba2a276347e36ab"],"When":"2022-1-23"}]

The berry swirl smoothie was a delight, I enjoyed the added cream inside.

The burgers here are good as always, I quite liked the buddy burger compared to Nashville chicken and mozzarella mushroom burger.

Extremely quick and decently friendly service. Seating is okay with large windows for viewing.

Would visit again!","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPRjr03yiSqP8XyJ2lMLBbmfteJzvx74p4UcAde&fid=0x0:0x4ea0d3e7707140fa"],"When":"2024-11-24"},{"Name":"Utried Butusuck","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJmsncilF6iYB8hfC-Ud6milrQS2Xty835DofvfiHWoyXNdWg=s120-c-rp-mo-ba2-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered a mozza combo for over $18. user_reviews:
[{"Name":"Michael Creighton","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJk9v3KOInw3tMbXIV2jeJFl29A3jxYvN7Rw90FoHk3Hp3FNw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I cannot express enough how phenomenal Lola from Triumph Entertainment has been for our events. Her dedication and expertise have truly elevated our experiences every single time. From start to finish, Lola exudes grace, professionalism, charisma, and humor, making every interaction with her an absolute pleasure.

Lola's attention to detail is impeccable. She ensures that every aspect of the event is meticulously planned and executed flawlessly. Her ability to handle unexpected challenges with ease and a positive attitude sets her apart as a true professional in her field.

What truly sets Lola apart is her genuine passion for what she does. It's evident in the way she goes above and beyond to exceed our expectations. She takes the time to understand our needs and preferences, tailoring each event to perfection.

Lola has become our go-to person for all our events, and for good reason. Her creativity and innovative ideas always bring a unique touch that leaves a lasting impression on our guests. Lola has an amazing voice herself and will occasionally treat us with a song or two throughout the evening as well.

In summary, Lola is a remarkable event coordinator who consistently delivers exceptional results. We look forward to working with her on many more successful events in the future. Highly recommended!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gracenote Vancouver","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjWBRI04L4cNmQM4S5GKlu-AO5bP1C7lBbnapr1uFKFyIX9npScJ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"We hired Lola to host karaoke at our fundraising event and she was wonderful! She was energetic and kept the vibe going. Planning for the event was clear and prompt. We will absolutely hire Triumph Entertainment again!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Hélène Dez","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUOsCz4i0r4t8ddILFqi0Pph6_h1LfLBNlKuPBwvjFpkBO5zRTS=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I have been to a bunch of karaoke nights with Lola and she's just excellent.
Professional, knows her business and have good communication skills.
She sometimes has to deal with very difficult clients and doesn't loose her professionalism.
She also has an amazing voice and knows how to make the crowds sing along.
100% recommend her.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Simon Paris","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVDBxFBebS9zI7D7qW2YQlmzcNG73JHXuWA17EjEAA1QVc-ht0=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I had such a great time thanks to Lola. She was really nice and reassuring, only good vibes throughout the night ! The list of songs is endless, she even had a really fair number of French songs which was a really nice gesture for a French speaking public !

I was told she had a great voice so I asked her to sing just one song and OMG she lit up the whole room. Every one got up, danced and sang along - it was AMAZING 🔥 🔥 🔥

I’ll definitely be back for more, thanks again","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Andrew Naicker","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocI-uOUrgMePx5JbwSbGrE5m_xde9gorm4tQ1WwIjOS04lMmFQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I started going to Triumph's Karaoke events around 2 years ago and  they are amazing. The hosts are all very professional and great hype people. I am pretty socially shy but the atmosphere they made gives me a great night each time I go around.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Gayan Monachino","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJVncUda5rffGJ3Iv1ai9M9JIywMYpLGf2ftAoJbEVEeM6KoQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"AVOID ABSOLUTELY!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! I do not recommend Lola's services at all.She's not professional and she just wants to take your money. I took 2 months in advance to prepare a karaoke because it will be big event with 80 people and she asked me $500 for the full service just for 4 hours. once paid Lola the deposited ($250) Lola doesn't no longer answered my emails or my phone calls. 2 days before the event Lola tells me that they don't have speakers. How does a (professional) karaoke company doesn't have speakers? (I had to rent the speakers myself) the same day I sent her a message to be sure that she had all the equipment (brig screen, projectors, microphones, etc.) given the lack of professionalism, I had anticipated and rented my own equipment and guess What .. I was right !!!!!same day she had no projectors, and the screen was a screen tv (small). I never seen a lack of professionalism like this before! don't go through them ! it's A SCAM","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Jeff Meagher","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLRrSeP84RVq8hIEDbvOXcDz-aBXRJa7Zp3YF_Y8vNb9VYNQA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"You’re always going to get a great show with properly mixed sound and a huge library of songs. All of the staff are very kind and professional. If I could rate higher than 5 stars, I would.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sophie N","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVHDslCfCMzHyuEzgj5qXRKt6SsEkiOUiykIa1LLNJL4Dh6c7dBxQ=s120-c-rp-mo-ba6-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Really fun night with karaoke handled by Lola, she has an amazing voice and it was nice having her singing a couple of songs.","Images":null,"When":""}]

[{"Name":"M R (cndn_hippo)","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUSUGlOqsxZsnICDm9_y90peAIJ-FMhmEr94lfGziKuJOuHJ6qt2A=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Desi pizza is where it's at for Canadian pizza. IYKYK. Queensborough is no exception.  Delicious pizza with cheese and toppings right to the edge. Perfectly baked crust. Lovely staff. Decent prices for an independent pizza place.
We live in Coquitlam, so it's not somewhere we'd be going to a lot, but we'll definitely go back! Eagerly.

Skip the cheesy garlic bread.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNqwZVhYJ758SderpRL_bjKXAUJkdHZYx3NL1FX&fid=0x0:0xa7f85bb1a2bb89bf"],"When":"2024-9-8"},{"Name":"Keith Harasymiw","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJX6b2Eka9tYe9Jslf-NXuefSERW3K-SSnb2OoIjz8bje3o2w=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Needed 4 pizzas ready for 1120am, called the night before to order. Pizzas were ready for us and were delicious, so good, they were not shy on the toppings which was great, perfect pizzas, we desteoyed them all. And the price was just right. Thanks again and we will be ordering again for sure.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOBmvbwBv74dWgOumLTGeGF9V9QKWiBi_JdWJ4C&fid=0x0:0xa7f85bb1a2bb89bf"],"When":"2022-4-14"},{"Name":"Bat Girl","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjXsHrMF1U97M_AI9bk2xNb41tFGVAPF-s0krNV-O3nZrEGmgtwk=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"Ordered their special, and cheese pizza for a late night snack and their pizzas did not disappoint. The ingredients seem fresh and it was a very thoughtful touch for them to have wax paper underneath the pizza so the pizza does not stick to the cardboard. Their dough is thin compared to other pizza places so there no big crust which is fine with me. The toppings are generous which I do prefer over having more crust. I would order their pizzas again.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_eWl6lgzp0VpTiYrPTeRhG5D6e7cjwEwrEdn4&fid=0x0:0xa7f85bb1a2bb89bf"],"When":"2020-10-19"},{"Name":"Felix Cheung","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJIsEF2zYuOa8K13gofBZbzH3T6HqZa4rfVgyGQ90HEXqQB4g=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Just in general not bad
But ordering whole pizzas to go is better than ordering by slices cuz this is the first time i don't see reheating the pizzas for u","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Shyamin Rahiman","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocK21PNgD59kzmiKAc5juE6SoPuB5xyaxXu7BiXCZm8PMJ93aQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Ordered 2 large pizza one veggie and other one with shrimp. Shrimp smelled so bad that my whole house stinks. I’m sure the shrimp was bad when called them…didn’t care only gave 50% of for my next order pizza. Totally disappointed!","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Priyanka Ahluwalia","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVGh6qf5PEz8UqUvKYrwokKEc848dxK7A3gihg2iVX_JlVutwpD=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Amazing!!! We asked for extra sauce and they delivered!!!

UPDATE: MARCH 13th 2024: was going to place an order like usual. We order from here very regularly and asked for the sauce (hot sauce and ranch) on top LIKE ALWAYS. The lady on the phone says she will charge me 2$. If we were to go pickup this order it would’ve be free. So just because it is being delivered they are charging for sauce. AGAIN: if i were to pick it up and open the box to put the sauce on myself = no charge. But if the lady puts it on before she hands it to the delivery guy= 2$. Im sorry what?!?!? So sad considering we’ve been coming here for 5 YEARS.

The photo below was from when they DELIVERED it with SAUCE NO CHARGE.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipN_FPDvUS8FlY4HFVbLYBieOtXMKX6AzpWmsbsf&fid=0x0:0xa7f85bb1a2bb89bf"],"When":"2023-12-12"},{"Name":"Ujwal Baweja","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocLja_obqYgWPyMF_SfnGf4p6q17DMkaRaL_xd830V41TiV0vQ=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I ordered two toppings pizza n they put the ratio of 90 % qty. of Capsicum n 10 % qty. of corn. Now, it's not eatable and they have denied to replace it.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Melissa M","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKldiqvGpvedqDiOB2OkW4CrIvjsobrWaTUOXxMspvKJNHw2g=s120-c-rp-mo-ba4-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"THIS RESTAURANT SERVED ME RAW CHICKEN. I ordered the Ceasar salad and when I went to bite into it I realized that the chicken was completely Raw! So I called To tell them and the woman who told me her name was Kieran (not sure of spelling) told me that they don't cook their chicken there and that it tastes better raw and that people don't get sick from eating raw chicken. She actually said that. No apologies, no offering to make it right. I asked for the owners contact information and she told me that he won't care about this and that he shouldn't be bothered with this issue. Then she told me that she will give me my money back but that they will never take an order from me again. I am so so disgusted by not only being served raw chicken and being told its fine, but the horrible customer service I received when I brought this to their attention. I order from there all the time, I can't even believe this is how they would treat a customer. Serving raw meat is never okay.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO2Ss3cMCES2OSPTdBsBzhYHhyKkeSWpS169wRC&fid=0x0:0xa7f85bb1a2bb89bf"],"When":"2021-8-8"}]

[{"Name":"Andrew Racanelli","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocKy1AT91OXGCY7xFvO4GNNrOOe8vIv7zLjO19ZbW5ccZHmm7XI=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"Wow where do I begin. DO NOT PLAY HERE! This course is dilapidated, unkempt and the front desk staff are apparently instructed to enforce a “no refund” policy even if the guest does not end up playing.

In the middle of summer, you are hitting off turf mats. The greens are in absolutely ABYSMAL shape, and the fairways (if you want to call them that) are essentially the equivalent of everyone in deltas front lawn that has been recently mowed…by a Ryobi special.

The owner (offshore individual) has clearly neglected this asset and does not care for the customer experience or putting in any effort to improve this facility.

Lastly, the price of $81 (2x green fees and 2x push carts), is TERRIBLE!  If it was $15 per person, I could forgive the conditions, layout, lack of customer service, and general experience. But for $67 (2x green fees/ 2x push carts) you can play a PRISTINE 9 hole course in west Vancouver.

This facility is an embarrassment and the owners should be ashamed.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipOqFhpFpLRJjaQ-1eM3IsjzAC5gjvpkkjMCUyEB&fid=0x0:0x815b9762f2a9ed6b"],"When":"2024-7-28"},{"Name":"Manisha Gosal","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocJc1brba4GGF7XlnZeA-4dZ29bxsM2b2YrK6-ab1PbqqZC9Ow=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"If I could give this place a zero I would. Rentals are held together with glue and tape and then they charge you $50.00 if you break it..  if you try to even tell them what happened they claim to tell you that you don’t know how to play golf. I don’t recommend this run down golf course don’t waste your money spend it somewhere else.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Briany Tai","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUaDpQzEuNStDRBr5hOYPbjSHf_qOdJOhQC38WblA_bsCmoKHOz=s120-c-rp-mo-ba5-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Taking my golf lessons here from Jason. Don’t know what to expect/ compare really. The coach is nice and skillful. I know they just finished their clubhouse. You can have functions here, ie weddings or gatherings. With covid lifting, this is a hidden gem that less people knows about.

We were going to held event here and their pricing is very reasonable.

Their main club house is renovating to be a 9000sqft, very excited to see how it turns out.

The driving range is also needs a little upgrade.

Overall, it is the cheapest driving range around.

Tho I have to mention, that you need to purchase your on tee if you want to practice your wood. Otherwise they charge you for it.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipO9yPuFKRmQ6q6RVQzbd4ntqkRcuYDCja69wj9I&fid=0x0:0x815b9762f2a9ed6b"],"When":"2021-7-3"},{"Name":"Kevin Zheng","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIhVkAlo0agsAGireLzNQAd01lTSCP2p5_SOkSs4PkKPcg9Kw=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":2,"Description":"Driving range balls are in terrible shape, a few of mine straight up had chunks of the ball missing.

Driving range mats need replacement, there’s holes in them.

Pro shop lady was pretty unhelpful. Was looking for a driver adjustment wrench to tighten my driver shaft and she had no clue what I was even talking about lol.","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Sachin Raturi","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIGm0n0z8oCzWMY7EtBjZ2Z3EQfpbVsjGY6bk8a36sU-TUuAg=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":1,"Description":"I used the company’s clubs. Shortly after starting, the hitting end of the club came off after just a few hits, without any contact with the mat or floor(just hitting ball).

Upon inspection, it appeared that the base of the club was poorly superglued. This issue was clearly not our fault, and it was unfair of the employee to charge us for the damage. The club was either low quality or was superglued on…

Before writing this review, I emailed them. A week later still no reply","Images":null,"When":""},{"Name":"Danielle Doucet","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocIkO5PuiSgvrZQy85dIw8vr6UPvakDN4BEfwYY3ldNLLOj77Q=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":4,"Description":"Great little par 3 course to play. I'm a beginner and they have decent membership pricing for driving range keys. Club rentals, cart rentals and ample parking.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipPTCj-LSeVL904PmUbOjyVt8PqSSnE0xlduk0xR&fid=0x0:0x815b9762f2a9ed6b"],"When":"2019-6-26"},{"Name":"Hermes Banico","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUS1RuiZyaxl61OYoSH3Fs5QN5gl8Cf1kNkhLvw73JA__YSzQpw=s120-c-rp-mo-ba3-br100","Rating":5,"Description":"I played the course a 2nd time this year on Sat Apr 17th. It was a nice, hot, sunny day. The greens were surprisingly lightning fast. You have to change the way you attack the greens. Its hard aiming to land your ball on the greens because they are very firm, fast and tiny. It was definitely nice seeing these fast greens on a Par 3 course.

There were definitely a lot of new younger golfers, new to the game playing here. Course is wide open. A few water hazards but other than that, you won't lose a ball here hopefully.

That house on the back 9 is a treat to play around.","Images":["www.google.com/local/imagery/report/?cb_client=maps_sv.tactile&image_key=!1e10!2sAF1QipNFF3F01xG-hedsfTDGW5pigDtsQCu-zu61DHwE&fid=0x0:0x815b9762f2a9ed6b"],"When":"2021-2-1"},{"Name":"Lewis Ward","ProfilePicture":"https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a/ACg8ocL1l0CVE2AAjTmNTsY1nRXyMZE44cJNrQz6TntbYifLt8nwuA=s120-c-rp-mo-br100","Rating":3,"Description":"driving range was in okay condition, but was very empty so it was peaceful","Images":null,"When":""}]
